\begin_layout Standard
Those who rest not their hope on their meeting with Us, but are pleased
 and satisfied with the life of the present, and those who heed not Our
 Signs,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Their abode is the Fire, because of the (evil) they earned.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who believe, and work righteousness,- their Lord will guide them because
 of their faith: beneath them will flow rivers in gardens of bliss.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(This will be) their cry therein: "Glory to Thee, O Allah!" And "Peace"
 will be their greeting therein! and the close of their cry will be: "Praise
 be to Allah, the Cherisher and Sustainer of the worlds!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If Allah were to hasten for men the ill (they have earned) as they would
 fain hasten on the good,- then would their respite be settled at once.
 But We leave those who rest not their hope on their meeting with Us, in
 their trespasses, wandering in distraction to and fro.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When trouble toucheth a man, He crieth unto Us (in all postures)- lying
 down on his side, or sitting, or standing.
 But when We have solved his trouble, he passeth on his way as if he had
 never cried to Us for a trouble that touched him! thus do the deeds of
 transgressors seem fair in their eyes!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Generations before you We destroyed when they did wrong: their messengers
 came to them with clear-signs, but they would not believe! thus do We requite
