 garden; they will abide therein (for aye)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those who have earned evil will have a reward of like evil: ignominy
 will cover their (faces): No defender will they have from (the wrath of)
 Allah: Their faces will be covered, as it were, with pieces from the depth
 of the darkness of night: they are companions of the Fire: they will abide
 therein (for aye)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One day shall We gather them all together.
 Then shall We say to those who joined gods (with Us): "To your place! ye
 and those ye joined as 'partners' We shall separate them, and their "Partners"
 shall say: "It was not us that ye worshipped!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Enough is Allah for a witness between us and you: we certainly knew nothing
 of your worship of us!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There will every soul prove (the fruits of) the deeds it sent before: they
 will be brought back to Allah their rightful Lord, and their invented falsehood
s will leave them in the lurch.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Who is it that sustains you (in life) from the sky and from the earth?
 or who is it that has power over hearing and sight? And who is it that
 brings out the living from the dead and the dead from the living? and who
 is it that rules and regulates all affairs?" They will soon say, "Allah".
 Say, "will ye not then show piety (to Him)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such is Allah, your real Cherisher and Sustainer: apart from truth, what
 (remains) but error? How then are ye turned away?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus is the word of thy Lord proved true against those who rebel: Verily
 they will not believe.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Of your 'partners', can any originate creation and repeat it?" Say:
 "It is Allah Who originates creation and repeats it: then how are ye deluded
 away (from the truth)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Of your 'partners' is there any that can give any guidance towards
 truth?" Say: "It is Allah Who gives guidance towards truth, is then He
 Who gives guidance to truth more worthy to be followed, or he who finds
 not guidance (himself) unless he is guided? what then is the matter with
 you? How judge ye?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But most of them follow nothing but fancy: truly fancy can be of no avail
 against truth.
 Verily Allah is well aware of all that they do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This Qur'an is not such as can be produced by other than Allah; on the contrary
 it is a confirmation of (revelations) that went before it, and a fuller
 explanation of the Book - wherein there is no doubt - from the Lord of
 the worlds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or do they say, "He forged it"? say: "Bring then a Sura like unto it, and
 call (to your aid) anyone you can besides Allah, if it be ye speak the
 truth!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, they charge with falsehood that whose knowledge they cannot compass,
 even before the elucidation thereof hath reached them: thus did those before
 them make charges of falsehood: but see what was the end of those who did
 wrong!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Of them there are some who believe therein, and some who do not: and thy
 Lord knoweth best those who are out for mischief.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If they charge thee with falsehood, say: "My work to me, and yours to you!
 ye are free from responsibility for what I do, and I for what ye do!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Among them are some who (pretend to) listen to thee: But canst thou make
 the deaf to hear,- even though they are without understanding?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And among them are some who look at thee: but canst thou guide the blind,-
 even though they will not see?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily Allah will not deal unjustly with man in aught: It is man that wrongs
 his own soul.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One day He will gather them together: (It will be) as if they had tarried
 but an hour of a day: they will recognise each other: assuredly those will
 be lost who denied the meeting with Allah and refused to receive true guidance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whether We show thee (realised in thy life-time) some part of what We promise
 them,- or We take thy soul (to Our Mercy) (Before that),- in any case,
 to Us is their return: ultimately Allah is witness, to all that they do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To every people (was sent) a messenger: when their messenger comes (before
 them), the matter will be judged between them with justice, and they will
 not be wronged.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They say: "When will this promise come to pass,- if ye speak the truth?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "I have no power over any harm or profit to myself except as Allah
 willeth.
 To every people is a term appointed: when their term is reached, not an
 hour can they cause delay, nor (an hour) can they advance (it in anticipation)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Do ye see,- if His punishment should come to you by night or by day,-
 what portion of it would the sinners wish to hasten?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Would ye then believe in it at last, when it actually cometh to pass? (It
 will then be said): 'Ah! now? and ye wanted (aforetime) to hasten it on!'
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"At length will be said to the wrong-doers: 'Taste ye the enduring punishment!
 ye get but the recompense of what ye earned!'"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They seek to be informed by thee: "Is that true?" Say: "Aye! by my Lord!
 it is the very truth! and ye cannot frustrate it!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Every soul that hath sinned, if it possessed all that is on earth, would
 fain give it in ransom: They would declare (their) repentance when they
 see the penalty: but the judgment between them will be with justice, and
 no wrong will be done unto them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is it not (the case) that to Allah belongeth whatever is in the heavens
 and on earth? Is it not (the case) that Allah's promise is assuredly true?
 Yet most of them understand not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who giveth life and who taketh it, and to Him shall ye all be brought
 back.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O mankind! there hath come to you a direction from your Lord and a healing
 for the (diseases) in your hearts,- and for those who believe, a guidance
 and a Mercy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "In the bounty of Allah.
 And in His Mercy,- in that let them rejoice": that is better than the (wealth)
 they hoard.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "See ye what things Allah hath sent down to you for sustenance? Yet
 ye hold forbidden some things thereof and (some things) lawful." Say: "Hath
 Allah indeed permitted you, or do ye invent (things) to attribute to Allah?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And what think those who invent lies against Allah, of the Day of Judgment?
 Verily Allah is full of bounty to mankind, but most of them are ungrateful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In whatever business thou mayest be, and whatever portion thou mayest be
