 Then see what was the end of those who were warned (but heeded not)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then after him We sent (many) messengers to their peoples: they brought
 them Clear Signs, but they would not believe what they had already rejected
 beforehand.
 Thus do We seal the hearts of the transgressors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then after them sent We Moses and Aaron to Pharaoh and his chiefs with Our
 Signs.
 But they were arrogant: they were a people in sin.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the Truth did come to them from Us, they said: "This is indeed evident
 sorcery!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Said Moses: "Say ye (this) about the truth when it hath (actually) reached
 you? Is sorcery (like) this? But sorcerers will not prosper."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "Hast thou come to us to turn us away from the ways we found
 our fathers following,- in order that thou and thy brother may have greatness
 in the land? But not we shall believe in you!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Said Pharaoh: "Bring me every sorcerer well versed."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the sorcerers came, Moses said to them: "Throw ye what ye (wish) to
 throw!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When they had had their throw, Moses said: "What ye have brought is sorcery:
 Allah will surely make it of no effect: for Allah prospereth not the work
 of those who make mischief.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And Allah by His words doth prove and establish His truth, however much
 the sinners may hate it!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But none believed in Moses except some children of his people, because of
 the fear of Pharaoh and his chiefs, lest they should persecute them; and
 certainly Pharaoh was mighty on the earth and one who transgressed all
 bounds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moses said: "O my people! If ye do (really) believe in Allah, then in Him
 put your trust if ye submit (your will to His)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "In Allah do we put out trust.
 Our Lord! make us not a trial for those who practise oppression;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And deliver us by Thy Mercy from those who reject (Thee)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We inspired Moses and his brother with this Message: "Provide dwellings
 for your people in Egypt, make your dwellings into places of worship, and
 establish regular prayers: and give glad tidings to those who believe!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moses prayed: "Our Lord! Thou hast indeed bestowed on Pharaoh and his chiefs
 splendour and wealth in the life of the present, and so, Our Lord, they
 mislead (men) from Thy Path.
 Deface, our Lord, the features of their wealth, and send hardness to their
 hearts, so they will not believe until they see the grievous penalty."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah said: "Accepted is your prayer (O Moses and Aaron)! So stand ye straight,
 and follow not the path of those who know not."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We took the Children of Israel across the sea: Pharaoh and his hosts followed
 them in insolence and spite.
 At length, when overwhelmed with the flood, he said: "I believe that there
 is no god except Him Whom the Children of Israel believe in: I am of those
 who submit (to Allah in Islam)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It was said to him): "Ah now!- But a little while before, wast thou in
 rebellion!- and thou didst mischief (and violence)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"This day shall We save thee in the body, that thou mayest be a sign to
 those who come after thee! but verily, many among mankind are heedless
 of Our Signs!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We settled the Children of Israel in a beautiful dwelling-place, and provided
 for them sustenance of the best: it was after knowledge had been granted
 to them, that they fell into schisms.
 Verily Allah will judge between them as to the schisms amongst them, on
 the Day of Judgment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If thou wert in doubt as to what We have revealed unto thee, then ask those
 who have been reading the Book from before thee: the Truth hath indeed
 come to thee from thy Lord: so be in no wise of those in doubt.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor be of those who reject the signs of Allah, or thou shalt be of those
 who perish.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those against whom the word of thy Lord hath been verified would not believe-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Even if every Sign was brought unto them,- until they see (for themselves)
 the penalty grievous.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Why was there not a single township (among those We warned), which believed,-
 so its faith should have profited it,- except the people of Jonah? When
 they believed, We removed from them the penalty of ignominy in the life
 of the present, and permitted them to enjoy (their life) for a while.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If it had been thy Lord's will, they would all have believed,- all who are
 on earth! wilt thou then compel mankind, against their will, to believe!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No soul can believe, except by the will of Allah, and He will place doubt
 (or obscurity) on those who will not understand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Behold all that is in the heavens and on earth"; but neither Signs
 nor Warners profit those who believe not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they then expect (any thing) but (what happened in) the days of the men
 who passed away before them? Say: "Wait ye then: for I, too, will wait
 with you."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the end We deliver Our messengers and those who believe: Thus is it fitting
 on Our part that We should deliver those who believe!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "O ye men! If ye are in doubt as to my religion, (behold!) I worship
 not what ye worship, other than Allah! But I worship Allah - Who will take
 your souls (at death): I am commanded to be (in the ranks) of the Believers,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And further (thus): 'set thy face towards religion with true piety, and
 never in any wise be of the Unbelievers;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"'Nor call on any, other than Allah;- Such will neither profit thee nor
 hurt thee: if thou dost, behold! thou shalt certainly be of those who do
 wrong.'"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If Allah do touch thee with hurt, there is none can remove it but He: if
 He do design some benefit for thee, there is none can keep back His favour:
 He causeth it to reach whomsoever of His servants He pleaseth.
 And He is the Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "O ye men! Now Truth hath reached you from your Lord! those who receive
 guidance, do so for the good of their own souls; those who stray, do so
 to their own loss: and I am not (set) over you to arrange your affairs."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Follow thou the inspiration sent unto thee, and be patient and constant,
 till Allah do decide: for He is the best to decide.
\end_layout

