\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Remember! Moses said to his people: "Call to mind the favour of Allah to
 you when He delivered you from the people of Pharaoh: they set you hard
 tasks and punishments, slaughtered your sons, and let your women-folk live:
 therein was a tremendous trial from your Lord."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And remember! your Lord caused to be declared (publicly): "If ye are grateful,
 I will add more (favours) unto you; But if ye show ingratitude, truly My
 punishment is terrible indeed."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Moses said: "If ye show ingratitude, ye and all on earth together, yet
 is Allah free of all wants, worthy of all praise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Has not the story reached you, (O people!), of those who (went) before you?
 - of the people of Noah, and 'Ad, and Thamud? - And of those who (came)
 after them? None knows them but Allah.
 To them came messengers with Clear (Signs); but they put their hands up
 to their mouths, and said: "We do deny (the mission) on which ye have been
 sent, and we are really in suspicious (disquieting) doubt as to that to
 which ye invite us."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Their messengers said: "Is there a doubt about Allah, The Creator of the
 heavens and the earth? It is He Who invites you, in order that He may forgive
 you your sins and give you respite for a term appointed!" They said: "Ah!
 ye are no more than human, like ourselves! Ye wish to turn us away from
 the (gods) our fathers used to worship: then bring us some clear authority."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Their messengers said to them: "True, we are human like yourselves, but
 Allah doth grant His grace to such of his servants as He pleases.
 It is not for us to bring you an authority except as Allah permits.
 And on Allah let all men of faith put their trust.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"No reason have we why we should not put our trust on Allah.
 Indeed He Has guided us to the Ways we (follow).
 We shall certainly bear with patience all the hurt you may cause us.
 For those who put their trust should put their trust on Allah."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Unbelievers said to their messengers: "Be sure we shall drive you
 out of our land, or ye shall return to our religion." But their Lord inspired
 (this Message) to them: "Verily We shall cause the wrong-doers to perish!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And verily We shall cause you to abide in the land, and succeed them.
 This for such as fear the Time when they shall stand before My tribunal,-
 such as fear the punishment denounced."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But they sought victory and decision (there and then), and frustration was
 the lot of every powerful obstinate transgressor.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In front of such a one is Hell, and he is given, for drink, boiling fetid
 water.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In gulps will he sip it, but never will he be near swallowing it down his
 throat: death will come to him from every quarter, yet will he not die:
 and in front of him will be a chastisement unrelenting.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The parable of those who reject their Lord is that their works are as ashes,
 on which the wind blows furiously on a tempestuous day: No power have they
 over aught that they have earned: that is the straying far, far (from the
 goal).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou not that Allah created the heavens and the earth in Truth? If
 He so will, He can remove you and put (in your place) a new creation?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor is that for Allah any great matter.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will all be marshalled before Allah together: then will the weak say
 to those who were arrogant, "For us, we but followed you; can ye then avail
 us to all against the wrath of Allah?" They will reply, "If we had received
 the Guidance of Allah, we should have given it to you: to us it makes no
 difference (now) whether we rage, or bear (these torments) with patience:
 for ourselves there is no way of escape."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Satan will say when the matter is decided: "It was Allah Who gave you
 a promise of Truth: I too promised, but I failed in my promise to you.
 I had no authority over you except to call you but ye listened to me: then
 reproach not me, but reproach your own souls.
 I cannot listen to your cries, nor can ye listen to mine.
 I reject your former act in associating me with Allah.
 For wrong-doers there must be a grievous penalty."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those who believe and work righteousness will be admitted to gardens
 beneath which rivers flow,- to dwell therein for aye with the leave of
 their Lord.
 Their greeting therein will be: "Peace!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou not how Allah sets forth a parable? - A goodly word like a goodly
 tree, whose root is firmly fixed, and its branches (reach) to the heavens,-
 of its Lord.
 So Allah sets forth parables for men, in order that they may receive admonition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It brings forth its fruit at all times, by the leave of its Lord.
 So Allah sets forth parables for men, in order that they may receive admonition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the parable of an evil Word is that of an evil tree: It is torn up by
 the root from the surface of the earth: it has no stability.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah will establish in strength those who believe, with the word that stands
 firm, in this world and in the Hereafter; but Allah will leave, to stray,
 those who do wrong: Allah doeth what He willeth.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Hast thou not turned thy vision to those who have changed the favour of
 Allah.
 Into blasphemy and caused their people to descend to the House of Perdition?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Into Hell? They will burn therein,- an evil place to stay in!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they set up (idols) as equal to Allah, to mislead (men) from the Path!
 Say: "Enjoy (your brief power)! But verily ye are making straightway for
 Hell!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Speak to my servants who have believed, that they may establish regular
 prayers, and spend (in charity) out of the sustenance we have given them,
 secretly and openly, before the coming of a Day in which there will be
 neither mutual bargaining nor befriending.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is Allah Who hath created the heavens and the earth and sendeth down
 rain from the skies, and with it bringeth out fruits wherewith to feed
 you; it is He Who hath made the ships subject to you, that they may sail
 through the sea by His command; and the rivers (also) hath He made subject
 to you.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He hath made subject to you the sun and the moon, both diligently pursuing
 their courses; and the night and the day hath he (also) made subject to
 you.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He giveth you of all that ye ask for.
 But if ye count the favours of Allah, never will ye be able to number them.
 Verily, man is given up to injustice and ingratitude.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Remember Abraham said: "O my Lord! make this city one of peace and security:
 and preserve me and my sons from worshipping idols.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"O my Lord! they have indeed led astray many among mankind; He then who
 follows my (ways) is of me, and he that disobeys me,- but Thou art indeed
 Oft-forgiving, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"O our Lord! I have made some of my offspring to dwell in a valley without
 cultivation, by Thy Sacred House; in order, O our Lord, that they may establish
 regular Prayer: so fill the hearts of some among men with love towards
 them, and feed them with fruits: so that they may give thanks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"O our Lord! truly Thou dost know what we conceal and what we reveal: for
 nothing whatever is hidden from Allah, whether on earth or in heaven.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Praise be to Allah, Who hath granted unto me in old age Isma'il and Isaac:
 for truly my Lord is He, the Hearer of Prayer!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O my Lord! make me one who establishes regular Prayer, and also (raise such)
 among my offspring O our Lord! and accept Thou my Prayer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"O our Lord! cover (us) with Thy Forgiveness - me, my parents, and (all)
 Believers, on the Day that the Reckoning will be established!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Think not that Allah doth not heed the deeds of those who do wrong.
 He but giveth them respite against a Day when the eyes will fixedly stare
 in horror,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They running forward with necks outstretched, their heads uplifted, their
 gaze returning not towards them, and their hearts a (gaping) void!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So warn mankind of the Day when the Wrath will reach them: then will the
 wrong-doers say: "Our Lord! respite us (if only) for a short term: we will
 answer Thy call, and follow the messengers!" "What! were ye not wont to
 swear aforetime that ye should suffer no decline?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And ye dwelt in the dwellings of men who wronged their own souls; ye were
 clearly shown how We dealt with them; and We put forth (many) parables
 in your behoof!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Mighty indeed were the plots which they made, but their plots were (well)
 within the sight of Allah, even though they were such as to shake the hills!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Never think that Allah would fail his messengers in His promise: for Allah
 is Exalted in power, - the Lord of Retribution.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One day the earth will be changed to a different earth, and so will be the
 heavens, and (men) will be marshalled forth, before Allah, the One, the
 Irresistible;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And thou wilt see the sinners that day bound together in fetters;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Their garments of liquid pitch, and their faces covered with Fire;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That Allah may requite each soul according to its deserts; and verily Allah
 is swift in calling to account.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Here is a Message for mankind: Let them take warning therefrom, and let
 them know that He is (no other than) One Allah: let men of understanding
 take heed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
