 L.
 R.
 These are the Ayats of Revelation,- of a Qur'an that makes things clear.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Again and again will those who disbelieve, wish that they had bowed (to
 Allah's will) in Islam.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Leave them alone, to enjoy (the good things of this life) and to please
 themselves: let (false) hope amuse them: soon will knowledge (undeceive
 them).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Never did We destroy a population that had not a term decreed and assigned
 beforehand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Neither can a people anticipate its term, nor delay it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They say: "O thou to whom the Message is being revealed! truly thou art
 mad (or possessed)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Why bringest thou not angels to us if it be that thou hast the Truth?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We send not the angels down except for just cause: if they came (to the
