\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Even if We opened out to them a gate from heaven, and they were to continue
 (all day) ascending therein,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They would only say: "Our eyes have been intoxicated: Nay, we have been
 bewitched by sorcery."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is We Who have set out the zodiacal signs in the heavens, and made them
 fair-seeming to (all) beholders;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And (moreover) We have guarded them from every cursed devil:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But any that gains a hearing by stealth, is pursued by a flaming fire, bright
 (to see).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the earth We have spread out (like a carpet); set thereon mountains
 firm and immovable; and produced therein all kinds of things in due balance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We have provided therein means of subsistence,- for you and for those
 for whose sustenance ye are not responsible.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And there is not a thing but its (sources and) treasures (inexhaustible)
 are with Us; but We only send down thereof in due and ascertainable measures.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We send the fecundating winds, then cause the rain to descend from the
 sky, therewith providing you with water (in abundance), though ye are not
 the guardians of its stores.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And verily, it is We Who give life, and Who give death: it is We Who remain
 inheritors (after all else passes away).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Us are known those of you who hasten forward, and those who lag behind.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Assuredly it is thy Lord Who will gather them together: for He is perfect
 in Wisdom and Knowledge.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We created man from sounding clay, from mud moulded into shape;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Jinn race, We had created before, from the fire of a scorching wind.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold! thy Lord said to the angels: "I am about to create man, from sounding
 clay from mud moulded into shape;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"When I have fashioned him (in due proportion) and breathed into him of
 My spirit, fall ye down in obeisance unto him."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So the angels prostrated themselves, all of them together:
