\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah) said: "Respite is granted thee
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Till the Day of the Time appointed."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Iblis) said: "O my Lord! because Thou hast put me in the wrong, I will
 make (wrong) fair-seeming to them on the earth, and I will put them all
 in the wrong,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Except Thy servants among them, sincere and purified (by Thy Grace)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah) said: "This (way of My sincere servants) is indeed a way that leads
 straight to Me.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"For over My servants no authority shalt thou have, except such as put themselve
s in the wrong and follow thee."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And verily, Hell is the promised abode for them all!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To it are seven gates: for each of those gates is a (special) class (of
 sinners) assigned.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The righteous (will be) amid gardens and fountains (of clear-flowing water).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Their greeting will be): "Enter ye here in peace and security."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We shall remove from their hearts any lurking sense of injury: (they
 will be) brothers (joyfully) facing each other on thrones (of dignity).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There no sense of fatigue shall touch them, nor shall they (ever) be asked
 to leave.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Tell My servants that I am indeed the Oft-forgiving, Most Merciful;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And that My Penalty will be indeed the most grievous Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Tell them about the guests of Abraham.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When they entered his presence and said, "Peace!" He said, "We feel afraid
 of you!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "Fear not! We give thee glad tidings of a son endowed with wisdom."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "Do ye give me glad tidings that old age has seized me? Of what,
 then, is your good news?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "We give thee glad tidings in truth: be not then in despair!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "And who despairs of the mercy of his Lord, but such as go astray?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Abraham said: "What then is the business on which ye (have come), O ye messenger
s (of Allah)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "We have been sent to a people (deep) in sin,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Excepting the adherents of Lut: them we are certainly (charged) to save
 (from harm),- All -
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Except his wife, who, We have ascertained, will be among those who will
 lag behind."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At length when the messengers arrived among the adherents of Lut,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "Ye appear to be uncommon folk."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "Yea, we have come to thee to accomplish that of which they doubt.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"We have brought to thee that which is inevitably due, and assuredly we
 tell the truth.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Then travel by night with thy household, when a portion of the night (yet
 remains), and do thou bring up the rear: let no one amongst you look back,
 but pass on whither ye are ordered."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We made known this decree to him, that the last remnants of those (sinners)
 should be cut off by the morning.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The inhabitants of the city came in (mad) joy (at news of the young men).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Lut said: "These are my guests: disgrace me not:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But fear Allah, and shame me not."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "Did we not forbid thee (to speak) for all and sundry?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "There are my daughters (to marry), if ye must act (so)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily, by thy life (O Prophet), in their wild intoxication, they wander
 in distraction, to and fro.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But the (mighty) Blast overtook them before morning,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We turned (the cities) upside down, and rained down on them brimstones
 hard as baked clay.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold! in this are Signs for those who by tokens do understand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the (cities were) right on the high-road.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold! in this is a sign for those who believed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Companions of the Wood were also wrong-doers;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So We exacted retribution from them.
 They were both on an open highway, plain to see.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Companions of the Rocky Tract also rejected the messengers:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We sent them Our Signs, but they persisted in turning away from them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Out of the mountains did they hew (their) edifices, (feeling themselves)
 secure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But the (mighty) Blast seized them of a morning,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And of no avail to them was all that they did (with such art and care)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We created not the heavens, the earth, and all between them, but for just
 ends.
 And the Hour is surely coming (when this will be manifest).
 So overlook (any human faults) with gracious forgiveness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For verily it is thy Lord who is the Master-Creator, knowing all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We have bestowed upon thee the Seven Oft-repeated (verses) and the Grand
 Qur'an.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Strain not thine eyes.
 (Wistfully) at what We have bestowed on certain classes of them, nor grieve
 over them: but lower thy wing (in gentleness) to the believers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And say: "I am indeed he that warneth openly and without ambiguity,"-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Of just such wrath) as We sent down on those who divided (Scripture into
 arbitrary parts),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(So also on such) as have made Qur'an into shreds (as they please).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore, by the Lord, We will, of a surety, call them to account,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For all their deeds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore expound openly what thou art commanded, and turn away from those
 who join false gods with Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For sufficient are We unto thee against those who scoff,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who adopt, with Allah, another god: but soon will they come to know.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We do indeed know how thy heart is distressed at what they say.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But celebrate the praises of thy Lord, and be of those who prostrate themselves
 in adoration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And serve thy Lord until there come unto thee the Hour that is Certain.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Inevitable) cometh (to pass) the Command of Allah: seek ye not then to
 hasten it: Glory to Him, and far is He above having the partners they ascribe
 unto Him!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He doth send down His angels with inspiration of His Command, to such of
 His servants as He pleaseth, (saying): "Warn (Man) that there is no god
 but I: so do your duty unto Me."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He has created the heavens and the earth for just ends: Far is He above
 having the partners they ascribe to Him!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He has created man from a sperm-drop; and behold this same (man) becomes
 an open disputer!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And cattle He has created for you (men): from them ye derive warmth, and
 numerous benefits, and of their (meat) ye eat.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And ye have a sense of pride and beauty in them as ye drive them home in
 the evening, and as ye lead them forth to pasture in the morning.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they carry your heavy loads to lands that ye could not (otherwise) reach
 except with souls distressed: for your Lord is indeed Most Kind, Most Merciful,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And (He has created) horses, mules, and donkeys, for you to ride and use
 for show; and He has created (other) things of which ye have no knowledge.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And unto Allah leads straight the Way, but there are ways that turn aside:
 if Allah had willed, He could have guided all of you.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He who sends down rain from the sky: from it ye drink, and out of
 it (grows) the vegetation on which ye feed your cattle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With it He produces for you corn, olives, date-palms, grapes and every kind
 of fruit: verily in this is a sign for those who give thought.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He has made subject to you the Night and the Day; the sun and the moon;
 and the stars are in subjection by His Command: verily in this are Signs
 for men who are wise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the things on this earth which He has multiplied in varying colours
 (and qualities): verily in this is a sign for men who celebrate the praises
 of Allah (in gratitude).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who has made the sea subject, that ye may eat thereof flesh that
 is fresh and tender, and that ye may extract therefrom ornaments to wear;
 and thou seest the ships therein that plough the waves, that ye may seek
 (thus) of the bounty of Allah and that ye may be grateful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He has set up on the earth mountains standing firm, lest it should shake
 with you; and rivers and roads; that ye may guide yourselves;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And marks and sign-posts; and by the stars (men) guide themselves.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is then He Who creates like one that creates not? Will ye not receive admonition
?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If ye would count up the favours of Allah, never would ye be able to number
 them: for Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Allah doth know what ye conceal, and what ye reveal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those whom they invoke besides Allah create nothing and are themselves created.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(They are things) dead, lifeless: nor do they know when they will be raised
 up.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Your Allah is one Allah: as to those who believe not in the Hereafter, their
 hearts refuse to know, and they are arrogant.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Undoubtedly Allah doth know what they conceal, and what they reveal: verily
 He loveth not the arrogant.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When it is said to them, "What is it that your Lord has revealed?" they
 say, "Tales of the ancients!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let them bear, on the Day of Judgment, their own burdens in full, and also
 (something) of the burdens of those without knowledge, whom they misled.
 Alas, how grievous the burdens they will bear!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those before them did also plot (against Allah's Way): but Allah took their
 structures from their foundations, and the roof fell down on them from
 above; and the Wrath seized them from directions they did not perceive.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, on the Day of Judgment, He will cover them with shame, and say: "Where
 are My 'partners' concerning whom ye used to dispute (with the godly)?"
 Those endued with knowledge will say: "This Day, indeed, are the Unbelievers
 covered with shame and misery,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"(Namely) those whose lives the angels take in a state of wrong-doing to
 their own souls." Then would they offer submission (with the pretence),
 "We did no evil (knowingly)." (The angels will reply), "Nay, but verily
 Allah knoweth all that ye did;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"So enter the gates of Hell, to dwell therein.
 Thus evil indeed is the abode of the arrogant."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To the righteous (when) it is said, "What is it that your Lord has revealed?"
 they say, "All that is good." To those who do good, there is good in this
 world, and the Home of the Hereafter is even better and excellent indeed
 is the Home of the righteous,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Gardens of Eternity which they will enter: beneath them flow (pleasant)
 rivers: they will have therein all that they wish: thus doth Allah reward
 the righteous,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Namely) those whose lives the angels take in a state of purity, saying
 (to them), "Peace be on you; enter ye the Garden, because of (the good)
 which ye did (in the world)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do the (ungodly) wait until the angels come to them, or there comes the
 Command of thy Lord (for their doom)? So did those who went before them.
 But Allah wronged them not: nay, they wronged their own souls.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But the evil results of their deeds overtook them, and that very (Wrath)
 at which they had scoffed hemmed them in.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The worshippers of false gods say: "If Allah had so willed, we should not
 have worshipped aught but Him - neither we nor our fathers,- nor should
 we have prescribed prohibitions other than His." So did those who went before
 them.
 But what is the mission of messengers but to preach the Clear Message?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For We assuredly sent amongst every People a messenger, (with the Command),
 "Serve Allah, and eschew Evil": of the People were some whom Allah guided,
 and some on whom error became inevitably (established).
 So travel through the earth, and see what was the end of those who denied
 (the Truth).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If thou art anxious for their guidance, yet Allah guideth not such as He
 leaves to stray, and there is none to help them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They swear their strongest oaths by Allah, that Allah will not raise up
 those who die: Nay, but it is a promise (binding) on Him in truth: but
 most among mankind realise it not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(They must be raised up), in order that He may manifest to them the truth
 of that wherein they differ, and that the rejecters of Truth may realise
 that they had indeed (surrendered to) Falsehood.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For to anything which We have willed, We but say the word, "Be", and it
 is.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To those who leave their homes in the cause of Allah, after suffering oppression
,- We will assuredly give a goodly home in this world; but truly the reward
 of the Hereafter will be greater.
 If they only realised (this)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(They are) those who persevere in patience, and put their trust on their
 Lord.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And before thee also the messengers We sent were but men, to whom We granted
 inspiration: if ye realise this not, ask of those who possess the Message.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(We sent them) with Clear Signs and Books of dark prophecies; and We have
 sent down unto thee (also) the Message; that thou mayest explain clearly
 to men what is sent for them, and that they may give thought.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do then those who devise evil (plots) feel secure that Allah will not cause
 the earth to swallow them up, or that the Wrath will not seize them from
 directions they little perceive?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or that He may not call them to account in the midst of their goings to
 and fro, without a chance of their frustrating Him?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or that He may not call them to account by a process of slow wastage - for
 thy Lord is indeed full of kindness and mercy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they not look at Allah's creation, (even) among (inanimate) things,-
 How their (very) shadows turn round, from the right and the left, prostrating
 themselves to Allah, and that in the humblest manner?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And to Allah doth obeisance all that is in the heavens and on earth, whether
 moving (living) creatures or the angels: for none are arrogant (before
 their Lord).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They all revere their Lord, high above them, and they do all that they are
 commanded.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah has said: "Take not (for worship) two gods: for He is just One Allah:
 then fear Me (and Me alone)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and on earth, and to Him is duty
 due always: then will ye fear other than Allah?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And ye have no good thing but is from Allah: and moreover, when ye are touched
 by distress, unto Him ye cry with groans;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yet, when He removes the distress from you, behold! some of you turn to
 other gods to join with their Lord-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(As if) to show their ingratitude for the favours we have bestowed on them!
 then enjoy (your brief day): but soon will ye know (your folly)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they (even) assign, to things they do not know, a portion out of that
 which We have bestowed for their sustenance! By Allah, ye shall certainly
 be called to account for your false inventions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they assign daughters for Allah! - Glory be to Him! - and for themselves
 (sons,- the issue) they desire!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When news is brought to one of them, of (the birth of) a female (child),
 his face darkens, and he is filled with inward grief!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With shame does he hide himself from his people, because of the bad news
 he has had! Shall he retain it on (sufferance and) contempt, or bury it
 in the dust? Ah! what an evil (choice) they decide on?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To those who believe not in the Hereafter, applies the similitude of evil:
 to Allah applies the highest similitude: for He is the Exalted in Power,
 full of Wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If Allah were to punish men for their wrong-doing, He would not leave, on
 the (earth), a single living creature: but He gives them respite for a
 stated Term: When their Term expires, they would not be able to delay (the
 punishment) for a single hour, just as they would not be able to anticipate
 it (for a single hour).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They attribute to Allah what they hate (for themselves), and their tongues
 assert the falsehood that all good things are for themselves: without doubt
 for them is the Fire, and they will be the first to be hastened on into
 it!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By Allah, We (also) sent (Our messengers) to Peoples before thee; but Satan
 made, (to the wicked), their own acts seem alluring: He is also their patron
 today, but they shall have a most grievous penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We sent down the Book to thee for the express purpose, that thou shouldst
 make clear to them those things in which they differ, and that it should
 be a guide and a mercy to those who believe.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Allah sends down rain from the skies, and gives therewith life to the
 earth after its death: verily in this is a Sign for those who listen.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And verily in cattle (too) will ye find an instructive sign.
 From what is within their bodies between excretions and blood, We produce,
 for your drink, milk, pure and agreeable to those who drink it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And from the fruit of the date-palm and the vine, ye get out wholesome drink
 and food: behold, in this also is a sign for those who are wise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And thy Lord taught the Bee to build its cells in hills, on trees, and in
 (men's) habitations;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then to eat of all the produce (of the earth), and find with skill the spacious
 paths of its Lord: there issues from within their bodies a drink of varying
 colours, wherein is healing for men: verily in this is a Sign for those
 who give thought.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is Allah who creates you and takes your souls at death; and of you there
 are some who are sent back to a feeble age, so that they know nothing after
 having known (much): for Allah is All-Knowing, All-Powerful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah has bestowed His gifts of sustenance more freely on some of you than
 on others: those more favoured are not going to throw back their gifts
 to those whom their right hands possess, so as to be equal in that respect.
 Will they then deny the favours of Allah?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Allah has made for you mates (and companions) of your own nature, and
 made for you, out of them, sons and daughters and grandchildren, and provided
 for you sustenance of the best: will they then believe in vain things,
 and be ungrateful for Allah's favours?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And worship others than Allah,- such as have no power of providing them,
 for sustenance, with anything in heavens or earth, and cannot possibly
 have such power?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Invent not similitudes for Allah: for Allah knoweth, and ye know not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah sets forth the Parable (of two men: one) a slave under the dominion
 of another; He has no power of any sort; and (the other) a man on whom
 We have bestowed goodly favours from Ourselves, and he spends thereof (freely),
 privately and publicly: are the two equal? (By no means;) praise be to
 Allah.
 But most of them understand not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah sets forth (another) Parable of two men: one of them dumb, with no
 power of any sort; a wearisome burden is he to his master; whichever way
 be directs him, he brings no good: is such a man equal with one who commands
 Justice, and is on a Straight Way?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Allah belongeth the Mystery of the heavens and the earth.
 And the Decision of the Hour (of Judgment) is as the twingkling of an eye,
 or even quicker: for Allah hath power over all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who brought you forth from the wombs of your mothers when ye knew
 nothing; and He gave you hearing and sight and intelligence and affections:
 that ye may give thanks (to Allah).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they not look at the birds, held poised in the midst of (the air and)
 the sky? Nothing holds them up but (the power of) Allah.
 Verily in this are signs for those who believe.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is Allah Who made your habitations homes of rest and quiet for you; and
 made for you, out of the skins of animals, (tents for) dwellings, which
 ye find so light (and handy) when ye travel and when ye stop (in your travels);
 and out of their wool, and their soft fibres (between wool and hair), and
 their hair, rich stuff and articles of convenience (to serve you) for a
 time.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is Allah Who made out of the things He created, some things to give you
 shade; of the hills He made some for your shelter; He made you garments
 to protect you from heat, and coats of mail to protect you from your (mutual)
 violence.
 Thus does He complete His favours on you, that ye may bow to His Will (in
 Islam).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But if they turn away, thy duty is only to preach the clear Message.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They recognise the favours of Allah; then they deny them; and most of them
 are (creatures) ungrateful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One Day We shall raise from all Peoples a Witness: then will no excuse be
 accepted from Unbelievers, nor will they receive any favours.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the wrong-doers (actually) see the Penalty, then will it in no way
 be mitigated, nor will they then receive respite.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When those who gave partners to Allah will see their "partners", they will
 say: "Our Lord! these are our 'partners,' those whom we used to invoke
 besides Thee." But they will throw back their word at them (and say): "Indeed
 ye are liars!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That Day shall they (openly) show (their) submission to Allah; and all their
 inventions shall leave them in the lurch.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who reject Allah and hinder (men) from the Path of Allah - for them
 will We add Penalty to Penalty; for that they used to spread mischief.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One day We shall raise from all Peoples a witness against them, from amongst
 themselves: and We shall bring thee as a witness against these (thy people):
 and We have sent down to thee the Book explaining all things, a Guide,
 a Mercy, and Glad Tidings to Muslims.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah commands justice, the doing of good, and liberality to kith and kin,
 and He forbids all shameful deeds, and injustice and rebellion: He instructs
 you, that ye may receive admonition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Fulfil the Covenant of Allah when ye have entered into it, and break not
 your oaths after ye have confirmed them; indeed ye have made Allah your
 surety; for Allah knoweth all that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And be not like a woman who breaks into untwisted strands the yarn which
 she has spun, after it has become strong.
 Nor take your oaths to practise deception between yourselves, lest one
 party should be more numerous than another: for Allah will test you by
 this; and on the Day of Judgment He will certainly make clear to you (the
 truth of) that wherein ye disagree.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If Allah so willed, He could make you all one people: But He leaves straying
 whom He pleases, and He guides whom He pleases: but ye shall certainly
 be called to account for all your actions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And take not your oaths, to practise deception between yourselves, with
 the result that someone's foot may slip after it was firmly planted, and
 ye may have to taste the evil (consequences) of having hindered (men) from
 the Path of Allah, and a Mighty Wrath descend on you.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor sell the covenant of Allah for a miserable price: for with Allah is
 (a prize) far better for you, if ye only knew.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What is with you must vanish: what is with Allah will endure.
 And We will certainly bestow, on those who patiently persevere, their reward
 according to the best of their actions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whoever works righteousness, man or woman, and has Faith, verily, to him
 will We give a new Life, a life that is good and pure and We will bestow
 on such their reward according to the best of their actions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When thou dost read the Qur'an, seek Allah's protection from Satan the rejected
 one.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No authority has he over those who believe and put their trust in their
 Lord.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
His authority is over those only, who take him as patron and who join partners
 with Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When We substitute one revelation for another,- and Allah knows best what
 He reveals (in stages),- they say, "Thou art but a forger": but most of
 them understand not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say, the Holy Spirit has brought the revelation from thy Lord in Truth,
 in order to strengthen those who believe, and as a Guide and Glad Tidings
 to Muslims.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We know indeed that they say, "It is a man that teaches him." The tongue
 of him they wickedly point to is notably foreign, while this is Arabic,
 pure and clear.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who believe not in the Signs of Allah,- Allah will not guide them,
 and theirs will be a grievous Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is those who believe not in the Signs of Allah, that forge falsehood:
 it is they who lie!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Any one who, after accepting faith in Allah, utters Unbelief,- except under
 compulsion, his heart remaining firm in Faith - but such as open their
 breast to Unbelief, on them is Wrath from Allah, and theirs will be a dreadful
 Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This because they love the life of this world better than the Hereafter:
 and Allah will not guide those who reject Faith.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those are they whose hearts, ears, and eyes Allah has sealed up, and they
 take no heed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Without doubt, in the Hereafter they will perish.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But verily thy Lord,- to those who leave their homes after trials and persecutio
ns,- and who thereafter strive and fight for the faith and patiently persevere,-
 Thy Lord, after all this is oft-forgiving, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One Day every soul will come up struggling for itself, and every soul will
 be recompensed (fully) for all its actions, and none will be unjustly dealt
 with.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah sets forth a Parable: a city enjoying security and quiet, abundantly
 supplied with sustenance from every place: Yet was it ungrateful for the
 favours of Allah: so Allah made it taste of hunger and terror (in extremes)
 (closing in on it) like a garment (from every side), because of the (evil)
 which (its people) wrought.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And there came to them a Messenger from among themselves, but they falsely
 rejected him; so the Wrath seized them even in the midst of their iniquities.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So eat of the sustenance which Allah has provided for you, lawful and good;
 and be grateful for the favours of Allah, if it is He Whom ye serve.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He has only forbidden you dead meat, and blood, and the flesh of swine,
 and any (food) over which the name of other than Allah has been invoked.
 But if one is forced by necessity, without wilful disobedience, nor transgressi
ng due limits,- then Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But say not - for any false thing that your tongues may put forth,- "This
 is lawful, and this is forbidden," so as to ascribe false things to Allah.
 For those who ascribe false things to Allah, will never prosper.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(In such falsehood) is but a paltry profit; but they will have a most grievous
 Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To the Jews We prohibited such things as We have mentioned to thee before:
 We did them no wrong, but they were used to doing wrong to themselves.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But verily thy Lord,- to those who do wrong in ignorance, but who thereafter
 repent and make amends,- thy Lord, after all this, is Oft-Forgiving, Most
 Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Abraham was indeed a model, devoutly obedient to Allah, (and) true in Faith,
 and he joined not gods with Allah:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He showed his gratitude for the favours of Allah, who chose him, and guided
 him to a Straight Way.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We gave him Good in this world, and he will be, in the Hereafter, in
 the ranks of the Righteous.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So We have taught thee the inspired (Message), "Follow the ways of Abraham
 the True in Faith, and he joined not gods with Allah."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Sabbath was only made (strict) for those who disagreed (as to its observance
); But Allah will judge between them on the Day of Judgment, as to their
 differences.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Invite (all) to the Way of thy Lord with wisdom and beautiful preaching;
 and argue with them in ways that are best and most gracious: for thy Lord
 knoweth best, who have strayed from His Path, and who receive guidance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if ye do catch them out, catch them out no worse than they catch you
 out: But if ye show patience, that is indeed the best (course) for those
 who are patient.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And do thou be patient, for thy patience is but from Allah; nor grieve over
 them: and distress not thyself because of their plots.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For Allah is with those who restrain themselves, and those who do good.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Glory to (Allah) Who did take His servant for a Journey by night from the
 Sacred Mosque to the farthest Mosque, whose precincts We did bless,- in
 order that We might show him some of Our Signs: for He is the One Who heareth
 and seeth (all things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We gave Moses the Book, and made it a Guide to the Children of Israel, (commandi
ng): "Take not other than Me as Disposer of (your) affairs."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye that are sprung from those whom We carried (in the Ark) with Noah!
 Verily he was a devotee most grateful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We gave (Clear) Warning to the Children of Israel in the Book, that
 twice would they do mischief on the earth and be elated with mighty arrogance
 (and twice would they be punished)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the first of the warnings came to pass, We sent against you Our servants
 given to terrible warfare: They entered the very inmost parts of your homes;
 and it was a warning (completely) fulfilled.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then did We grant you the Return as against them: We gave you increase in
 resources and sons, and made you the more numerous in man-power.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If ye did well, ye did well for yourselves; if ye did evil, (ye did it)
 against yourselves.
 So when the second of the warnings came to pass, (We permitted your enemies)
 to disfigure your faces, and to enter your Temple as they had entered it
 before, and to visit with destruction all that fell into their power.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It may be that your Lord may (yet) show Mercy unto you; but if ye revert
 (to your sins), We shall revert (to Our punishments): And we have made
 Hell a prison for those who reject (all Faith).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily this Qur'an doth guide to that which is most right (or stable), and
 giveth the Glad Tidings to the Believers who work deeds of righteousness,
 that they shall have a magnificent reward;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And to those who believe not in the Hereafter, (it announceth) that We have
 prepared for them a Penalty Grievous (indeed).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The prayer that man should make for good, he maketh for evil; for man is
 given to hasty (deeds).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have made the Night and the Day as two (of Our) Signs: the Sign of the
 Night have We obscured, while the Sign of the Day We have made to enlighten
 you; that ye may seek bounty from your Lord, and that ye may know the number
 and count of the years: all things have We explained in detail.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Every man's fate We have fastened on his own neck: On the Day of Judgment
 We shall bring out for him a scroll, which he will see spread open.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It will be said to him:) "Read thine (own) record: Sufficient is thy soul
 this day to make out an account against thee."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who receiveth guidance, receiveth it for his own benefit: who goeth astray
 doth so to his own loss: No bearer of burdens can bear the burden of another:
 nor would We visit with Our Wrath until We had sent an messenger (to give
 warning).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When We decide to destroy a population, We (first) send a definite order
 to those among them who are given the good things of this life and yet
 transgress; so that the word is proved true against them: then (it is)
 We destroy them utterly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
How many generations have We destroyed after Noah? and enough is thy Lord
 to note and see the sins of His servants.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If any do wish for the transitory things (of this life), We readily grant
 them - such things as We will, to such person as We will: in the end have
 We provided Hell for them: they will burn therein, disgraced and rejected.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who do wish for the (things of) the Hereafter, and strive therefor
 with all due striving, and have Faith,- they are the ones whose striving
 is acceptable (to Allah).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Of the bounties of thy Lord We bestow freely on all- These as well as those:
 The bounties of thy Lord are not closed (to anyone).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
See how We have bestowed more on some than on others; but verily the Hereafter
 is more in rank and gradation and more in excellence.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Take not with Allah another object of worship; or thou (O man!) wilt sit
 in disgrace and destitution.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thy Lord hath decreed that ye worship none but Him, and that ye be kind
 to parents.
 Whether one or both of them attain old age in thy life, say not to them
 a word of contempt, nor repel them, but address them in terms of honour.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And, out of kindness, lower to them the wing of humility, and say: "My Lord!
 bestow on them thy Mercy even as they cherished me in childhood."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Your Lord knoweth best what is in your hearts: If ye do deeds of righteousness,
 verily He is Most Forgiving to those who turn to Him again and again (in
 true penitence).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And render to the kindred their due rights, as (also) to those in want,
 and to the wayfarer: But squander not (your wealth) in the manner of a
 spendthrift.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily spendthrifts are brothers of the Evil Ones; and the Evil One is to
 his Lord (himself) ungrateful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And even if thou hast to turn away from them in pursuit of the Mercy from
 thy Lord which thou dost expect, yet speak to them a word of easy kindness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Make not thy hand tied (like a niggard's) to thy neck, nor stretch it forth
 to its utmost reach, so that thou become blameworthy and destitute.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily thy Lord doth provide sustenance in abundance for whom He pleaseth,
 and He provideth in a just measure.
 For He doth know and regard all His servants.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Kill not your children for fear of want: We shall provide sustenance for
 them as well as for you.
 Verily the killing of them is a great sin.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor come nigh to adultery: for it is a shameful (deed) and an evil, opening
 the road (to other evils).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor take life - which Allah has made sacred - except for just cause.
 And if anyone is slain wrongfully, we have given his heir authority (to
 demand qisas or to forgive): but let him not exceed bounds in the matter
 of taking life; for he is helped (by the Law).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Come not nigh to the orphan's property except to improve it, until he attains
 the age of full strength; and fulfil (every) engagement, for (every) engagement
 will be enquired into (on the Day of Reckoning).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Give full measure when ye measure, and weigh with a balance that is straight:
 that is the most fitting and the most advantageous in the final determination.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And pursue not that of which thou hast no knowledge; for every act of hearing,
 or of seeing or of (feeling in) the heart will be enquired into (on the
 Day of Reckoning).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor walk on the earth with insolence: for thou canst not rend the earth
 asunder, nor reach the mountains in height.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Of all such things the evil is hateful in the sight of thy Lord.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These are among the (precepts of) wisdom, which thy Lord has revealed to
 thee.
 Take not, with Allah, another object of worship, lest thou shouldst be
 thrown into Hell, blameworthy and rejected.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Has then your Lord (O Pagans!) preferred for you sons, and taken for Himself
 daughters among the angels? Truly ye utter a most dreadful saying!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have explained (things) in various (ways) in this Qur'an, in order that
 they may receive admonition, but it only increases their flight (from the
 Truth)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: If there had been (other) gods with Him, as they say,- behold, they
 would certainly have sought out a way to the Lord of the Throne!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Glory to Him! He is high above all that they say!- Exalted and Great (beyond
 measure)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The seven heavens and the earth, and all beings therein, declare His glory:
 there is not a thing but celebrates His praise; And yet ye understand not
 how they declare His glory! Verily He is Oft-Forbear, Most Forgiving!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When thou dost recite the Qur'an, We put, between thee and those who believe
 not in the Hereafter, a veil invisible:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We put coverings over their hearts (and minds) lest they should understand
 the Qur'an, and deafness into their ears: when thou dost commemorate thy
 Lord and Him alone in the Qur'an, they turn on their backs, fleeing (from
 the Truth).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We know best why it is they listen, when they listen to thee; and when they
 meet in private conference, behold, the wicked say, "Ye follow none other
 than a man bewitched!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
See what similes they strike for thee: but they have gone astray, and never
 can they find a way.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They say: "What! when we are reduced to bones and dust, should we really
 be raised up (to be) a new creation?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "(Nay!) be ye stones or iron,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Or created matter which, in your minds, is hardest (to be raised up),-
 (Yet shall ye be raised up)!" then will they say: "Who will cause us to
 return?" Say: "He who created you first!" Then will they wag their heads
 towards thee, and say, "When will that be?" Say, "May be it will be quite
 soon!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"It will be on a Day when He will call you, and ye will answer (His call)
 with (words of) His praise, and ye will think that ye tarried but a little
 while!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say to My servants that they should (only) say those things that are best:
 for Satan doth sow dissensions among them: For Satan is to man an avowed
 enemy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is your Lord that knoweth you best: If He please, He granteth you mercy,
 or if He please, punishment: We have not sent thee to be a disposer of
 their affairs for them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And it is your Lord that knoweth best all beings that are in the heavens
 and on earth: We did bestow on some prophets more (and other) gifts than
 on others: and We gave to David (the gift of) the Psalms.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Call on those - besides Him - whom ye fancy: they have neither the
 power to remove your troubles from you nor to change them."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those whom they call upon do desire (for themselves) means of access to
 their Lord, - even those who are nearest: they hope for His Mercy and fear
 His Wrath: for the Wrath of thy Lord is something to take heed of.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There is not a population but We shall destroy it before the Day of Judgment
 or punish it with a dreadful Penalty: that is written in the (eternal)
 Record.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We refrain from sending the signs, only because the men of former generation
s treated them as false: We sent the she-camel to the Thamud to open their
 eyes, but they treated her wrongfully: We only send the Signs by way of
 terror (and warning from evil).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold! We told thee that thy Lord doth encompass mankind round about: We
 granted the vision which We showed thee, but as a trial for men,- as also
 the Cursed Tree (mentioned) in the Qur'an: We put terror (and warning)
 into them, but it only increases their inordinate transgression!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold! We said to the angels: "Bow down unto Adam": They bowed down except
 Iblis: He said, "Shall I bow down to one whom Thou didst create from clay?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "Seest Thou? this is the one whom Thou hast honoured above me!
 If Thou wilt but respite me to the Day of Judgment, I will surely bring
 his descendants under my sway - all but a few!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah) said: "Go thy way; if any of them follow thee, verily Hell will
 be the recompense of you (all)- an ample recompense.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Lead to destruction those whom thou canst among them, with thy (seductive)
 voice; make assaults on them with thy cavalry and thy infantry; mutually
 share with them wealth and children; and make promises to them." But Satan
 promises them nothing but deceit.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"As for My servants, no authority shalt thou have over them:" Enough is
 thy Lord for a Disposer of affairs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Your Lord is He That maketh the Ship go smoothly for you through the sea,
 in order that ye may seek of his Bounty.
 For he is unto you most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When distress seizes you at sea, those that ye call upon - besides Himself
 - leave you in the lurch! but when He brings you back safe to land, ye
 turn away (from Him).
 Most ungrateful is man!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do ye then feel secure that He will not cause you to be swallowed up beneath
 the earth when ye are on land, or that He will not send against you a violent
 tornado (with showers of stones) so that ye shall find no one to carry
 out your affairs for you?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or do ye feel secure that He will not send you back a second time to sea
 and send against you a heavy gale to drown you because of your ingratitude,
 so that ye find no helper.
 Therein against Us?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have honoured the sons of Adam; provided them with transport on land
 and sea; given them for sustenance things good and pure; and conferred
 on them special favours, above a great part of our creation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One day We shall call together all human beings with their (respective)
 Imams: those who are given their record in their right hand will read it
 (with pleasure), and they will not be dealt with unjustly in the least.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those who were blind in this world, will be blind in the hereafter,
 and most astray from the Path.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And their purpose was to tempt thee away from that which We had revealed
 unto thee, to substitute in our name something quite different; (in that
 case), behold! they would certainly have made thee (their) friend!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And had We not given thee strength, thou wouldst nearly have inclined to
 them a little.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In that case We should have made thee taste an equal portion (of punishment)
 in this life, and an equal portion in death: and moreover thou wouldst
 have found none to help thee against Us!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Their purpose was to scare thee off the land, in order to expel thee; but
 in that case they would not have stayed (therein) after thee, except for
 a little while.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(This was Our) way with the messengers We sent before thee: thou wilt find
 no change in Our ways.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Establish regular prayers - at the sun's decline till the darkness of the
 night, and the morning prayer and reading: for the prayer and reading in
 the morning carry their testimony.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And pray in the small watches of the morning: (it would be) an additional
 prayer (or spiritual profit) for thee: soon will thy Lord raise thee to
 a Station of Praise and Glory!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "O my Lord! Let my entry be by the Gate of Truth and Honour, and likewise
 my exit by the Gate of Truth and Honour; and grant me from Thy Presence
 an authority to aid (me)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And say: "Truth has (now) arrived, and Falsehood perished: for Falsehood
 is (by its nature) bound to perish."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We send down (stage by stage) in the Qur'an that which is a healing and
 a mercy to those who believe: to the unjust it causes nothing but loss
 after loss.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yet when We bestow Our favours on man, he turns away and becomes remote
 on his side (instead of coming to Us), and when evil seizes him he gives
 himself up to despair!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Everyone acts according to his own disposition: But your Lord knows
 best who it is that is best guided on the Way."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They ask thee concerning the Spirit (of inspiration).
 Say: "The Spirit (cometh) by command of my Lord: of knowledge it is only
 a little that is communicated to you, (O men!)"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If it were Our Will, We could take away that which We have sent thee by
 inspiration: then wouldst thou find none to plead thy affair in that matter
 as against Us,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Except for Mercy from thy Lord: for his bounty is to thee (indeed) great.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "If the whole of mankind and Jinns were to gather together to produce
 the like of this Qur'an, they could not produce the like thereof, even
 if they backed up each other with help and support.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We have explained to man, in this Qur'an, every kind of similitude:
 yet the greater part of men refuse (to receive it) except with ingratitude!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They say: "We shall not believe in thee, until thou cause a spring to gush
 forth for us from the earth,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Or (until) thou have a garden of date trees and vines, and cause rivers
 to gush forth in their midst, carrying abundant water;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Or thou cause the sky to fall in pieces, as thou sayest (will happen),
 against us; or thou bring Allah and the angels before (us) face to face:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Or thou have a house adorned with gold, or thou mount a ladder right into
 the skies.
 No, we shall not even believe in thy mounting until thou send down to us
 a book that we could read." Say: "Glory to my Lord! Am I aught but a man,-
 a messenger?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What kept men back from belief when Guidance came to them, was nothing but
 this: they said, "Has Allah sent a man (like us) to be (His) Messenger?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say, "If there were settled, on earth, angels walking about in peace and
 quiet, We should certainly have sent them down from the heavens an angel
 for a messenger."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Enough is Allah for a witness between me and you: for He is well acquainte
d with His servants, and He sees (all things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is he whom Allah guides, that is on true Guidance; but he whom He leaves
 astray - for such wilt thou find no protector besides Him.
 On the Day of Judgment We shall gather, them together, prone on their faces,
 blind, dumb, and deaf: their abode will be Hell: every time it shows abatement,
 We shall increase from them the fierceness of the Fire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That is their recompense, because they rejected Our signs, and said, "When
 we are reduced to bones and broken dust, should we really be raised up
 (to be) a new Creation?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
See they not that Allah, Who created the heavens and the earth, has power
 to create the like of them (anew)? Only He has decreed a term appointed,
 of which there is no doubt.
 But the unjust refuse (to receive it) except with ingratitude.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "If ye had control of the Treasures of the Mercy of my Lord, behold,
 ye would keep them back, for fear of spending them: for man is (every)
 niggardly!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Moses We did give Nine Clear Signs: As the Children of Israel: when he
 came to them, Pharaoh said to him: "O Moses! I consider thee, indeed, to
 have been worked upon by sorcery!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moses said, "Thou knowest well that these things have been sent down by
 none but the Lord of the heavens and the earth as eye-opening evidence:
 and I consider thee indeed, O Pharaoh, to be one doomed to destruction!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So he resolved to remove them from the face of the earth: but We did drown
 him and all who were with him.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We said thereafter to the Children of Israel, "Dwell securely in the
 land (of promise)": but when the second of the warnings came to pass, We
 gathered you together in a mingled crowd.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We sent down the (Qur'an) in Truth, and in Truth has it descended: and We
 sent thee but to give Glad Tidings and to warn (sinners).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It is) a Qur'an which We have divided (into parts from time to time), in
 order that thou mightest recite it to men at intervals: We have revealed
 it by stages.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Whether ye believe in it or not, it is true that those who were given
 knowledge beforehand, when it is recited to them, fall down on their faces
 in humble prostration,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And they say: 'Glory to our Lord! Truly has the promise of our Lord been
 fulfilled!'"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They fall down on their faces in tears, and it increases their (earnest)
 humility.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Call upon Allah, or call upon Rahman: by whatever name ye call upon
 Him, (it is well): for to Him belong the Most Beautiful Names.
 Neither speak thy Prayer aloud, nor speak it in a low tone, but seek a
 middle course between."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Praise be to Allah, who begets no son, and has no partner in (His)
 dominion: Nor (needs) He any to protect Him from humiliation: yea, magnify
 Him for His greatness and glory!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Praise be to Allah, Who hath sent to His Servant the Book, and hath allowed
 therein no Crookedness:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(He hath made it) Straight (and Clear) in order that He may warn (the godless)
 of a terrible Punishment from Him, and that He may give Glad Tidings to
 the Believers who work righteous deeds, that they shall have a goodly Reward,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Wherein they shall remain for ever:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Further, that He may warn those (also) who say, "Allah hath begotten a son":
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No knowledge have they of such a thing, nor had their fathers.
 It is a grievous thing that issues from their mouths as a saying what they
 say is nothing but falsehood!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thou wouldst only, perchance, fret thyself to death, following after them,
 in grief, if they believe not in this Message.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That which is on earth we have made but as a glittering show for the earth,
 in order that We may test them - as to which of them are best in conduct.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily what is on earth we shall make but as dust and dry soil (without
 growth or herbage).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or dost thou reflect that the Companions of the Cave and of the Inscription
 were wonders among Our Sign?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, the youths betook themselves to the Cave: they said, "Our Lord!
 bestow on us Mercy from Thyself, and dispose of our affair for us in the
 right way!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then We draw (a veil) over their ears, for a number of years, in the Cave,
 (so that they heard not):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then We roused them, in order to test which of the two parties was best
 at calculating the term of years they had tarried!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We relate to thee their story in truth: they were youths who believed in
 their Lord, and We advanced them in guidance:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We gave strength to their hearts: Behold, they stood up and said: "Our Lord
 is the Lord of the heavens and of the earth: never shall we call upon any
 god other than Him: if we did, we should indeed have uttered an enormity!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"These our people have taken for worship gods other than Him: why do they
 not bring forward an authority clear (and convincing) for what they do?
 Who doth more wrong than such as invent a falsehood against Allah?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"When ye turn away from them and the things they worship other than Allah,
 betake yourselves to the Cave: Your Lord will shower His mercies on you
 and disposes of your affair towards comfort and ease."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thou wouldst have seen the sun, when it rose, declining to the right from
 their Cave, and when it set, turning away from them to the left, while
 they lay in the open space in the midst of the Cave.
 Such are among the Signs of Allah: He whom Allah, guides is rightly guided;
 but he whom Allah leaves to stray,- for him wilt thou find no protector
 to lead him to the Right Way.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thou wouldst have deemed them awake, whilst they were asleep, and We turned
 them on their right and on their left sides: their dog stretching forth
 his two fore-legs on the threshold: if thou hadst come up on to them, thou
 wouldst have certainly turned back from them in flight, and wouldst certainly
 have been filled with terror of them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such (being their state), we raised them up (from sleep), that they might
 question each other.
 Said one of them, "How long have ye stayed (here)?" They said, "We have
 stayed (perhaps) a day, or part of a day." (At length) they (all) said,
 "Allah (alone) knows best how long ye have stayed here....
 Now send ye then one of you with this money of yours to the town: let him
 find out which is the best food (to be had) and bring some to you, that
 (ye may) satisfy your hunger therewith: And let him behave with care and
 courtesy, and let him not inform any one about you.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"For if they should come upon you, they would stone you or force you to
 return to their cult, and in that case ye would never attain prosperity."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus did We make their case known to the people, that they might know that
 the promise of Allah is true, and that there can be no doubt about the
 Hour of Judgment.
 Behold, they dispute among themselves as to their affair.
 (Some) said, "Construct a building over them": Their Lord knows best about
 them: those who prevailed over their affair said, "Let us surely build
 a place of worship over them."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Some) say they were three, the dog being the fourth among them; (others)
 say they were five, the dog being the sixth,- doubtfully guessing at the
 unknown; (yet others) say they were seven, the dog being the eighth.
 Say thou: "My Lord knoweth best their number; It is but few that know their
 (real case)." Enter not, therefore, into controversies concerning them,
 except on a matter that is clear, nor consult any of them about (the affair
 of) the Sleepers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor say of anything, "I shall be sure to do so and so tomorrow"-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Without adding, "So please Allah!" and call thy Lord to mind when thou forgettes
t, and say, "I hope that my Lord will guide me ever closer (even) than this
 to the right road."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So they stayed in their Cave three hundred years, and (some) add nine (more)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Allah knows best how long they stayed: with Him is (the knowledge
 of) the secrets of the heavens and the earth: how clearly He sees, how
 finely He hears (everything)! They have no protector other than Him; nor
 does He share His Command with any person whatsoever.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And recite (and teach) what has been revealed to thee of the Book of thy
 Lord: none can change His Words, and none wilt thou find as a refuge other
 than Him.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And keep thy soul content with those who call on their Lord morning and
 evening, seeking His Face; and let not thine eyes pass beyond them, seeking
 the pomp and glitter of this Life; no obey any whose heart We have permitted
 to neglect the remembrance of Us, one who follows his own desires, whose
 case has gone beyond all bounds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say, "The truth is from your Lord": Let him who will believe, and let him
 who will, reject (it): for the wrong-doers We have prepared a Fire whose
 (smoke and flames), like the walls and roof of a tent, will hem them in:
 if they implore relief they will be granted water like melted brass, that
 will scald their faces, how dreadful the drink! How uncomfortable a couch
 to recline on!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As to those who believe and work righteousness, verily We shall not suffer
 to perish the reward of any who do a (single) righteous deed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For them will be Gardens of Eternity; beneath them rivers will flow; they
 will be adorned therein with bracelets of gold, and they will wear green
 garments of fine silk and heavy brocade: They will recline therein on raised
 thrones.
 How good the recompense! How beautiful a couch to recline on!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Set forth to them the parable of two men: for one of them We provided two
 gardens of grape-vines and surrounded them with date palms; in between
 the two We placed corn-fields.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Each of those gardens brought forth its produce, and failed not in the least
 therein: in the midst of them We caused a river to flow.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Abundant) was the produce this man had: he said to his companion, in the
 course of a mutual argument: "more wealth have I than you, and more honour
 and power in (my following of) men."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He went into his garden in a state (of mind) unjust to his soul: He said,
 "I deem not that this will ever perish,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Nor do I deem that the Hour (of Judgment) will (ever) come: Even if I am
 brought back to my Lord, I shall surely find (there) something better in
 exchange."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
His companion said to him, in the course of the argument with him: "Dost
 thou deny Him Who created thee out of dust, then out of a sperm-drop, then
 fashioned thee into a man?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But (I think) for my part that He is Allah, My Lord, and none shall I associate
 with my Lord.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Why didst thou not, as thou wentest into thy garden, say: 'Allah's will
 (be done)! There is no power but with Allah!' If thou dost see me less
 than thee in wealth and sons,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"It may be that my Lord will give me something better than thy garden, and
 that He will send on thy garden thunderbolts (by way of reckoning) from
 heaven, making it (but) slippery sand!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Or the water of the garden will run off underground so that thou wilt never
 be able to find it."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So his fruits (and enjoyment) were encompassed (with ruin), and he remained
 twisting and turning his hands over what he had spent on his property,
 which had (now) tumbled to pieces to its very foundations, and he could
 only say, "Woe is me! Would I had never ascribed partners to my Lord and
 Cherisher!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor had he numbers to help him against Allah, nor was he able to deliver
 himself.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There, the (only) protection comes from Allah, the True One.
 He is the Best to reward, and the Best to give success.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Set forth to them the similitude of the life of this world: It is like the
 rain which we send down from the skies: the earth's vegetation absorbs
 it, but soon it becomes dry stubble, which the winds do scatter: it is
 (only) Allah who prevails over all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Wealth and sons are allurements of the life of this world: But the things
 that endure, good deeds, are best in the sight of thy Lord, as rewards,
 and best as (the foundation for) hopes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One Day We shall remove the mountains, and thou wilt see the earth as a
 level stretch, and We shall gather them, all together, nor shall We leave
 out any one of them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they will be marshalled before thy Lord in ranks, (with the announcement),
 "Now have ye come to Us (bare) as We created you first: aye, ye thought
 We shall not fulfil the appointment made to you to meet (Us)!":
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Book (of Deeds) will be placed (before you); and thou wilt see the
 sinful in great terror because of what is (recorded) therein; they will
 say, "Ah! woe to us! what a Book is this! It leaves out nothing small or
 great, but takes account thereof!" They will find all that they did, placed
 before them: And not one will thy Lord treat with injustice.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold! We said to the angels, "Bow down to Adam": They bowed down except
 Iblis.
 He was one of the Jinns, and he broke the Command of his Lord.
 Will ye then take him and his progeny as protectors rather than Me? And
 they are enemies to you! Evil would be the exchange for the wrong-doers!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
I called them not to witness the creation of the heavens and the earth,
 nor (even) their own creation: nor is it for helpers such as Me to take
 as lead (men) astray!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One Day He will say, "Call on those whom ye thought to be My partners,"
 and they will call on them, but they will not listen to them; and We shall
 make for them a place of common perdition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Sinful shall see the fire and apprehend that they have to fall therein:
 no means will they find to turn away therefrom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have explained in detail in this Qur'an, for the benefit of mankind,
 every kind of similitude: but man is, in most things, contentious.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And what is there to keep back men from believing, now that Guidance has
 come to them, nor from praying for forgiveness from their Lord, but that
 (they ask that) the ways of the ancients be repeated with them, or the
 Wrath be brought to them face to face?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We only send the messengers to give Glad Tidings and to give warnings: But
 the unbelievers dispute with vain argument, in order therewith to weaken
 the truth, and they treat My Signs as a jest, as also the fact that they
 are warned!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And who doth more wrong than one who is reminded of the Signs of his Lord,
 but turns away from them, forgetting the (deeds) which his hands have sent
 forth? Verily We have set veils over their hearts lest they should understand
 this, and over their ears, deafness, if thou callest them to guidance,
 even then will they never accept guidance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But your Lord is Most forgiving, full of Mercy.
 If He were to call them (at once) to account for what they have earned,
 then surely He would have hastened their punishment: but they have their
 appointed time, beyond which they will find no refuge.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such were the populations we destroyed when they committed iniquities; but
 we fixed an appointed time for their destruction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, Moses said to his attendant, "I will not give up until I reach the
 junction of the two seas or (until) I spend years and years in travel."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But when they reached the Junction, they forgot (about) their Fish, which
 took its course through the sea (straight) as in a tunnel.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When they had passed on (some distance), Moses said to his attendant: "Bring
 us our early meal; truly we have suffered much fatigue at this (stage of)
 our journey."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He replied: "Sawest thou (what happened) when we betook ourselves to the
 rock? I did indeed forget (about) the Fish: none but Satan made me forget
 to tell (you) about it: it took its course through the sea in a marvellous
 way!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moses said: "That was what we were seeking after:" So they went back on
 their footsteps, following (the path they had come).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So they found one of Our servants, on whom We had bestowed Mercy from Ourselves
 and whom We had taught knowledge from Our own Presence.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moses said to him: "May I follow thee, on the footing that thou teach me
 something of the (Higher) Truth which thou hast been taught?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(The other) said: "Verily thou wilt not be able to have patience with me!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And how canst thou have patience about things about which thy understanding
 is not complete?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moses said: "Thou wilt find me, if Allah so will, (truly) patient: nor shall
 I disobey thee in aught."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The other said: "If then thou wouldst follow me, ask me no questions about
 anything until I myself speak to thee concerning it."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So they both proceeded: until, when they were in the boat, he scuttled it.
 Said Moses: "Hast thou scuttled it in order to drown those in it? Truly
 a strange thing hast thou done!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He answered: "Did I not tell thee that thou canst have no patience with
 me?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moses said: "Rebuke me not for forgetting, nor grieve me by raising difficulties
 in my case."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then they proceeded: until, when they met a young man, he slew him.
 Moses said: "Hast thou slain an innocent person who had slain none? Truly
 a foul (unheard of) thing hast thou done!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He answered: "Did I not tell thee that thou canst have no patience with
 me?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Moses) said: "If ever I ask thee about anything after this, keep me not
 in thy company: then wouldst thou have received (full) excuse from my side."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then they proceeded: until, when they came to the inhabitants of a town,
 they asked them for food, but they refused them hospitality.
 They found there a wall on the point of falling down, but he set it up
 straight.
 (Moses) said: "If thou hadst wished, surely thou couldst have exacted some
 recompense for it!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He answered: "This is the parting between me and thee: now will I tell thee
 the interpretation of (those things) over which thou wast unable to hold
 patience.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"As for the boat, it belonged to certain men in dire want: they plied on
 the water: I but wished to render it unserviceable, for there was after
 them a certain king who seized on every boat by force.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"As for the youth, his parents were people of Faith, and we feared that
 he would grieve them by obstinate rebellion and ingratitude (to Allah and
 man).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"So we desired that their Lord would give them in exchange (a son) better
 in purity (of conduct) and closer in affection.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"As for the wall, it belonged to two youths, orphans, in the Town; there
 was, beneath it, a buried treasure, to which they were entitled: their
 father had been a righteous man: So thy Lord desired that they should attain
 their age of full strength and get out their treasure - a mercy (and favour)
 from thy Lord.
 I did it not of my own accord.
 Such is the interpretation of (those things) over which thou wast unable
 to hold patience."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They ask thee concerning Zul-qarnain.
 Say, "I will rehearse to you something of his story."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily We established his power on earth, and We gave him the ways and the
 means to all ends.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One (such) way he followed,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Until, when he reached the setting of the sun, he found it set in a spring
 of murky water: Near it he found a People: We said: "O Zul-qarnain! (thou
 hast authority,) either to punish them, or to treat them with kindness."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "Whoever doth wrong, him shall we punish; then shall he be sent
 back to his Lord; and He will punish him with a punishment unheard-of (before).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But whoever believes, and works righteousness,- he shall have a goodly
 reward, and easy will be his task as We order it by our Command."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then followed he (another) way,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Until, when he came to the rising of the sun, he found it rising on a people
 for whom We had provided no covering protection against the sun.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(He left them) as they were: We completely understood what was before him.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then followed he (another) way,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Until, when he reached (a tract) between two mountains, he found, beneath
 them, a people who scarcely understood a word.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "O Zul-qarnain! the Gog and Magog (People) do great mischief
 on earth: shall we then render thee tribute in order that thou mightest
 erect a barrier between us and them?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "(The power) in which my Lord has established me is better (than
 tribute): Help me therefore with strength (and labour): I will erect a
 strong barrier between you and them:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Bring me blocks of iron." At length, when he had filled up the space between
 the two steep mountain-sides, He said, "Blow (with your bellows)" Then,
 when he had made it (red) as fire, he said: "Bring me, that I may pour
 over it, molten lead."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus were they made powerless to scale it or to dig through it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "This is a mercy from my Lord: But when the promise of my Lord
 comes to pass, He will make it into dust; and the promise of my Lord is
 true."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On that day We shall leave them to surge like waves on one another: the
 trumpet will be blown, and We shall collect them all together.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We shall present Hell that day for Unbelievers to see, all spread out,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Unbelievers) whose eyes had been under a veil from remembrance of Me, and
 who had been unable even to hear.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do the Unbelievers think that they can take My servants as protectors besides
 Me? Verily We have prepared Hell for the Unbelievers for (their) entertainment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Shall we tell you of those who lose most in respect of their deeds?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Those whose efforts have been wasted in this life, while they thought that
 they were acquiring good by their works?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They are those who deny the Signs of their Lord and the fact of their having
 to meet Him (in the Hereafter): vain will be their works, nor shall We,
 on the Day of Judgment, give them any weight.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That is their reward, Hell, because they rejected Faith, and took My Signs
 and My Messengers by way of jest.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As to those who believe and work righteous deeds, they have, for their entertain
ment, the Gardens of Paradise,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Wherein they shall dwell (for aye): no change will they wish for from them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "If the ocean were ink (wherewith to write out) the words of my Lord,
 sooner would the ocean be exhausted than would the words of my Lord, even
 if we added another ocean like it, for its aid."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "I am but a man like yourselves, (but) the inspiration has come to
 me, that your Allah is one Allah: whoever expects to meet his Lord, let
 him work righteousness, and, in the worship of his Lord, admit no one as
 partner.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Kaf.
 Ha.
 Ya.
 'Ain.
 Sad.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(This is) a recital of the Mercy of thy Lord to His servant Zakariya.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold! he cried to his Lord in secret,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Praying: "O my Lord! infirm indeed are my bones, and the hair of my head
 doth glisten with grey: but never am I unblest, O my Lord, in my prayer
 to Thee!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Now I fear (what) my relatives (and colleagues) (will do) after me: but
 my wife is barren: so give me an heir as from Thyself,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"(One that) will (truly) represent me, and represent the posterity of Jacob;
 and make him, O my Lord! one with whom Thou art well-pleased!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(His prayer was answered): "O Zakariya! We give thee good news of a son:
 His name shall be Yahya: on none by that name have We conferred distinction
 before."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "O my Lord! How shall I have a son, when my wife is barren and
 I have grown quite decrepit from old age?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "So (it will be) thy Lord saith, 'that is easy for Me: I did indeed
 create thee before, when thou hadst been nothing!'"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Zakariya) said: "O my Lord! give me a Sign." "Thy Sign," was the answer,
 "Shall be that thou shalt speak to no man for three nights, although thou
 art not dumb."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So Zakariya came out to his people from him chamber: He told them by signs
 to celebrate Allah's praises in the morning and in the evening.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(To his son came the command): "O Yahya! take hold of the Book with might":
 and We gave him Wisdom even as a youth,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And piety (for all creatures) as from Us, and purity: He was devout,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And kind to his parents, and he was not overbearing or rebellious.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So Peace on him the day he was born, the day that he dies, and the day that
 he will be raised up to life (again)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Relate in the Book (the story of) Mary, when she withdrew from her family
 to a place in the East.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
She placed a screen (to screen herself) from them; then We sent her our
 angel, and he appeared before her as a man in all respects.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
She said: "I seek refuge from thee to (Allah) Most Gracious: (come not near)
 if thou dost fear Allah."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "Nay, I am only a messenger from thy Lord, (to announce) to thee
 the gift of a holy son.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
She said: "How shall I have a son, seeing that no man has touched me, and
 I am not unchaste?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "So (it will be): Thy Lord saith, 'that is easy for Me: and (We
 wish) to appoint him as a Sign unto men and a Mercy from Us': It is a matter
 (so) decreed."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So she conceived him, and she retired with him to a remote place.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the pains of childbirth drove her to the trunk of a palm-tree: She cried
 (in her anguish): "Ah! would that I had died before this! would that I
 had been a thing forgotten and out of sight!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But (a voice) cried to her from beneath the (palm-tree): "Grieve not! for
 thy Lord hath provided a rivulet beneath thee;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And shake towards thyself the trunk of the palm-tree: It will let fall
 fresh ripe dates upon thee.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"So eat and drink and cool (thine) eye.
 And if thou dost see any man, say, 'I have vowed a fast to (Allah) Most
 Gracious, and this day will I enter into not talk with any human being'"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At length she brought the (babe) to her people, carrying him (in her arms).
 They said: "O Mary! truly an amazing thing hast thou brought!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"O sister of Aaron! Thy father was not a man of evil, nor thy mother a woman
 unchaste!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But she pointed to the babe.
 They said: "How can we talk to one who is a child in the cradle?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "I am indeed a servant of Allah: He hath given me revelation and
 made me a prophet;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And He hath made me blessed wheresoever I be, and hath enjoined on me Prayer
 and Charity as long as I live;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"(He) hath made me kind to my mother, and not overbearing or miserable;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"So peace is on me the day I was born, the day that I die, and the day that
 I shall be raised up to life (again)"!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such (was) Jesus the son of Mary: (it is) a statement of truth, about which
 they (vainly) dispute.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is not befitting to (the majesty of) Allah that He should beget a son.
 Glory be to Him! when He determines a matter, He only says to it, "Be",
 and it is.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily Allah is my Lord and your Lord: Him therefore serve ye: this is a
 Way that is straight.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But the sects differ among themselves: and woe to the unbelievers because
 of the (coming) Judgment of a Momentous Day!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
How plainly will they see and hear, the Day that they will appear before
 Us! but the unjust today are in error manifest!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But warn them of the Day of Distress, when the matter will be determined:
 for (behold,) they are negligent and they do not believe!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is We Who will inherit the earth, and all beings thereon: to Us will
 they all be returned.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Also mention in the Book (the story of) Abraham: He was a man of Truth,
 a prophet.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, he said to his father: "O my father! why worship that which heareth
 not and seeth not, and can profit thee nothing?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"O my father! to me hath come knowledge which hath not reached thee: so
 follow me: I will guide thee to a way that is even and straight.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"O my father! serve not Satan: for Satan is a rebel against (Allah) Most
 Gracious.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"O my father! I fear lest a Penalty afflict thee from (Allah) Most Gracious,
 so that thou become to Satan a friend."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(The father) replied: "Dost thou hate my gods, O Abraham? If thou forbear
 not, I will indeed stone thee: Now get away from me for a good long while!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Abraham said: "Peace be on thee: I will pray to my Lord for thy forgiveness:
 for He is to me Most Gracious.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And I will turn away from you (all) and from those whom ye invoke besides
 Allah: I will call on my Lord: perhaps, by my prayer to my Lord, I shall
 be not unblest."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When he had turned away from them and from those whom they worshipped besides
 Allah, We bestowed on him Isaac and Jacob, and each one of them We made
 a prophet.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We bestowed of Our Mercy on them, and We granted them lofty honour on
 the tongue of truth.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Also mention in the Book (the story of) Moses: for he was specially chosen,
 and he was a messenger (and) a prophet.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And we called him from the right side of Mount (Sinai), and made him draw
 near to Us, for mystic (converse).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And, out of Our Mercy, We gave him his brother Aaron, (also) a prophet.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Also mention in the Book (the story of) Isma'il: He was (strictly) true
 to what he promised, and he was a messenger (and) a prophet.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He used to enjoin on his people Prayer and Charity, and he was most acceptable
 in the sight of his Lord.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Also mention in the Book the case of Idris: He was a man of truth (and sincerity
), (and) a prophet:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We raised him to a lofty station.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those were some of the prophets on whom Allah did bestow His Grace,- of
 the posterity of Adam, and of those who We carried (in the Ark) with Noah,
 and of the posterity of Abraham and Israel of those whom We guided and
 chose.
 Whenever the Signs of (Allah) Most Gracious were rehearsed to them, they
 would fall down in prostrate adoration and in tears.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But after them there followed a posterity who missed prayers and followed
 after lusts soon, then, will they face Destruction,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Except those who repent and believe, and work righteousness: for these will
 enter the Garden and will not be wronged in the least,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Gardens of Eternity, those which (Allah) Most Gracious has promised to His
 servants in the Unseen: for His promise must (necessarily) come to pass.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will not there hear any vain discourse, but only salutations of Peace:
 And they will have therein their sustenance, morning and evening.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such is the Garden which We give as an inheritance to those of Our servants
 who guard against Evil.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(The angels say:) "We descend not but by command of thy Lord: to Him belongeth
 what is before us and what is behind us, and what is between: and thy Lord
 never doth forget,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Lord of the heavens and of the earth, and of all that is between them;
 so worship Him, and be constant and patient in His worship: knowest thou
 of any who is worthy of the same Name as He?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Man says: "What! When I am dead, shall I then be raised up alive?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But does not man call to mind that We created him before out of nothing?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So, by thy Lord, without doubt, We shall gather them together, and (also)
 the Evil Ones (with them); then shall We bring them forth on their knees
 round about Hell;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then shall We certainly drag out from every sect all those who were worst
 in obstinate rebellion against (Allah) Most Gracious.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And certainly We know best those who are most worthy of being burned therein.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Not one of you but will pass over it: this is, with thy Lord, a Decree which
 must be accomplished.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But We shall save those who guarded against evil, and We shall leave the
 wrong-doers therein, (humbled) to their knees.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When Our Clear Signs are rehearsed to them, the Unbelievers say to those
 who believe, "Which of the two sides is best in point of position? Which
 makes the best show in council?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But how many (countless) generations before them have we destroyed, who
 were even better in equipment and in glitter to the eye?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "If any men go astray, (Allah) Most Gracious extends (the rope) to
 them, until, when they see the warning of Allah (being fulfilled) - either
 in punishment or in (the approach of) the Hour,- they will at length realise
 who is worst in position, and (who) weakest in forces!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And Allah doth advance in guidance those who seek guidance: and the things
 that endure, Good Deeds, are best in the sight of thy Lord, as rewards,
 and best in respect of (their) eventual return."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Hast thou then seen the (sort of) man who rejects Our Signs, yet says: "I
 shall certainly be given wealth and children?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Has he penetrated to the Unseen, or has he taken a contract with (Allah)
 Most Gracious?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay! We shall record what he says, and We shall add and add to his punishment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Us shall return all that he talks of and he shall appear before Us bare
 and alone.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they have taken (for worship) gods other than Allah, to give them power
 and glory!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Instead, they shall reject their worship, and become adversaries against
 them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou not that We have set the Evil Ones on against the unbelievers,
 to incite them with fury?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So make no haste against them, for We but count out to them a (limited)
 number (of days).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The day We shall gather the righteous to (Allah) Most Gracious, like a band
 presented before a king for honours,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We shall drive the sinners to Hell, like thirsty cattle driven down
 to water,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
None shall have the power of intercession, but such a one as has received
 permission (or promise) from (Allah) Most Gracious.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They say: "(Allah) Most Gracious has begotten a son!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Indeed ye have put forth a thing most monstrous!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At it the skies are ready to burst, the earth to split asunder, and the
 mountains to fall down in utter ruin,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That they should invoke a son for (Allah) Most Gracious.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For it is not consonant with the majesty of (Allah) Most Gracious that He
 should beget a son.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Not one of the beings in the heavens and the earth but must come to (Allah)
 Most Gracious as a servant.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He does take an account of them (all), and hath numbered them (all) exactly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And everyone of them will come to Him singly on the Day of Judgment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On those who believe and work deeds of righteousness, will (Allah) Most
 Gracious bestow love.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So have We made the (Qur'an) easy in thine own tongue, that with it thou
 mayest give Glad Tidings to the righteous, and warnings to people given
 to contention.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But how many (countless) generations before them have We destroyed? Canst
 thou find a single one of them (now) or hear (so much as) a whisper of
 them?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ta-Ha.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have not sent down the Qur'an to thee to be (an occasion) for thy distress,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But only as an admonition to those who fear (Allah),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A revelation from Him Who created the earth and the heavens on high.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah) Most Gracious is firmly established on the throne (of authority).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Him belongs what is in the heavens and on earth, and all between them,
 and all beneath the soil.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If thou pronounce the word aloud, (it is no matter): for verily He knoweth
 what is secret and what is yet more hidden.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah! there is no god but He! To Him belong the most Beautiful Names.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Has the story of Moses reached thee?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, he saw a fire: So he said to his family, "Tarry ye; I perceive a
 fire; perhaps I can bring you some burning brand therefrom, or find some
 guidance at the fire."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But when he came to the fire, a voice was heard: "O Moses!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Verily I am thy Lord! therefore (in My presence) put off thy shoes: thou
 art in the sacred valley Tuwa.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"I have chosen thee: listen, then, to the inspiration (sent to thee).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Verily, I am Allah: There is no god but I: So serve thou Me (only), and
 establish regular prayer for celebrating My praise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Verily the Hour is coming - My design is to keep it hidden - for every
 soul to receive its reward by the measure of its Endeavour.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Therefore let not such as believe not therein but follow their own lusts,
 divert thee therefrom, lest thou perish!"..
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And what is that in the right hand, O Moses?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said, "It is my rod: on it I lean; with it I beat down fodder for my
 flocks; and in it I find other uses."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah) said, "Throw it, O Moses!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He threw it, and behold! It was a snake, active in motion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah) said, "Seize it, and fear not: We shall return it at once to its
 former condition"..
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Now draw thy hand close to thy side: It shall come forth white (and shining),
 without harm (or stain),- as another Sign,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"In order that We may show thee (two) of our Greater Signs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Go thou to Pharaoh, for he has indeed transgressed all bounds."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Moses) said: "O my Lord! expand me my breast;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Ease my task for me;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And remove the impediment from my speech,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"So they may understand what I say:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And give me a Minister from my family,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Aaron, my brother;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Add to my strength through him,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And make him share my task:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"That we may celebrate Thy praise without stint,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And remember Thee without stint:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"For Thou art He that (ever) regardeth us."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah) said: "Granted is thy prayer, O Moses!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And indeed We conferred a favour on thee another time (before).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Behold! We sent to thy mother, by inspiration, the message:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"'Throw (the child) into the chest, and throw (the chest) into the river:
 the river will cast him up on the bank, and he will be taken up by one
 who is an enemy to Me and an enemy to him': But I cast (the garment of)
 love over thee from Me: and (this) in order that thou mayest be reared
 under Mine eye.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Behold! thy sister goeth forth and saith, 'shall I show you one who will
 nurse and rear the (child)?' So We brought thee back to thy mother, that
 her eye might be cooled and she should not grieve.
 Then thou didst slay a man, but We saved thee from trouble, and We tried
 thee in various ways.
 Then didst thou tarry a number of years with the people of Midian.
 Then didst thou come hither as ordained, O Moses!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And I have prepared thee for Myself (for service)"..
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Go, thou and thy brother, with My Signs, and slacken not, either of you,
 in keeping Me in remembrance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Go, both of you, to Pharaoh, for he has indeed transgressed all bounds;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But speak to him mildly; perchance he may take warning or fear (Allah)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They (Moses and Aaron) said: "Our Lord! We fear lest he hasten with insolence
 against us, or lest he transgress all bounds."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "Fear not: for I am with you: I hear and see (everything).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"So go ye both to him, and say, 'Verily we are messengers sent by thy Lord:
 Send forth, therefore, the Children of Israel with us, and afflict them
 not: with a Sign, indeed, have we come from thy Lord! and peace to all
 who follow guidance!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"'Verily it has been revealed to us that the Penalty (awaits) those who
 reject and turn away.'"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(When this message was delivered), (Pharaoh) said: "Who, then, O Moses,
 is the Lord of you two?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "Our Lord is He Who gave to each (created) thing its form and nature,
 and further, gave (it) guidance."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Pharaoh) said: "What then is the condition of previous generations?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He replied: "The knowledge of that is with my Lord, duly recorded: my Lord
 never errs, nor forgets,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"He Who has, made for you the earth like a carpet spread out; has enabled
 you to go about therein by roads (and channels); and has sent down water
 from the sky." With it have We produced diverse pairs of plants each separate
 from the others.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Eat (for yourselves) and pasture your cattle: verily, in this are Signs
 for men endued with understanding.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From the (earth) did We create you, and into it shall We return you, and
 from it shall We bring you out once again.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We showed Pharaoh all Our Signs, but he did reject and refuse.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "Hast thou come to drive us out of our land with thy magic, O Moses?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But we can surely produce magic to match thine! So make a tryst between
 us and thee, which we shall not fail to keep - neither we nor thou - in
 a place where both shall have even chances."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moses said: "Your tryst is the Day of the Festival, and let the people be
 assembled when the sun is well up."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So Pharaoh withdrew: He concerted his plan, and then came (back).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moses said to him: Woe to you! Forge not ye a lie against Allah, lest He
 destroy you (at once) utterly by chastisement: the forger must suffer frustrati
on!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So they disputed, one with another, over their affair, but they kept their
 talk secret.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "These two are certainly (expert) magicians: their object is
 to drive you out from your land with their magic, and to do away with your
 most cherished institutions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Therefore concert your plan, and then assemble in (serried) ranks: He wins
 (all along) today who gains the upper hand."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "O Moses! whether wilt thou that thou throw (first) or that we
 be the first to throw?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said, "Nay, throw ye first!" Then behold their ropes and their rods-so
 it seemed to him on account of their magic - began to be in lively motion!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So Moses conceived in his mind a (sort of) fear.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We said: "Fear not! for thou hast indeed the upper hand:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Throw that which is in thy right hand: Quickly will it swallow up that
 which they have faked what they have faked is but a magician's trick: and
 the magician thrives not, (no matter) where he goes."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So the magicians were thrown down to prostration: they said, "We believe
 in the Lord of Aaron and Moses".
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Pharaoh) said: "Believe ye in Him before I give you permission? Surely
 this must be your leader, who has taught you magic! be sure I will cut
 off your hands and feet on opposite sides, and I will have you crucified
 on trunks of palm-trees: so shall ye know for certain, which of us can
 give the more severe and the more lasting punishment!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "Never shall we regard thee as more than the Clear Signs that
 have come to us, or than Him Who created us! so decree whatever thou desirest
 to decree: for thou canst only decree (touching) the life of this world.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"For us, we have believed in our Lord: may He forgive us our faults, and
 the magic to which thou didst compel us: for Allah is Best and Most Abiding."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily he who comes to his Lord as a sinner (at Judgment),- for him is Hell:
 therein shall he neither die nor live.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But such as come to Him as Believers who have worked righteous deeds,- for
 them are ranks exalted,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Gardens of Eternity, beneath which flow rivers: they will dwell therein
 for aye: such is the reward of those who purify themselves (from evil).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We sent an inspiration to Moses: "Travel by night with My servants, and
 strike a dry path for them through the sea, without fear of being overtaken
 (by Pharaoh) and without (any other) fear."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then Pharaoh pursued them with his forces, but the waters completely overwhelmed
 them and covered them up.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Pharaoh led his people astray instead of leading them aright.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye Children of Israel! We delivered you from your enemy, and We made a
 Covenant with you on the right side of Mount (Sinai), and We sent down
 to you Manna and quails:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Saying): "Eat of the good things We have provided for your sustenance,
 but commit no excess therein, lest My Wrath should justly descend on you:
 and those on whom descends My Wrath do perish indeed!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But, without doubt, I am (also) He that forgives again and again, to those
 who repent, believe, and do right, who,- in fine, are ready to receive
 true guidance."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(When Moses was up on the Mount, Allah said:) "What made thee hasten in
 advance of thy people, O Moses?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He replied: "Behold, they are close on my footsteps: I hastened to thee,
 O my Lord, to please thee."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah) said: "We have tested thy people in thy absence: the Samiri has
 led them astray."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So Moses returned to his people in a state of indignation and sorrow.
 He said: "O my people! did not your Lord make a handsome promise to you?
 Did then the promise seem to you long (in coming)? Or did ye desire that
 Wrath should descend from your Lord on you, and so ye broke your promise
 to me?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "We broke not the promise to thee, as far as lay in our power:
 but we were made to carry the weight of the ornaments of the (whole) people,
 and we threw them (into the fire), and that was what the Samiri suggested.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Then he brought out (of the fire) before the (people) the image of a calf:
 It seemed to low: so they said: This is your god, and the god of Moses,
 but (Moses) has forgotten!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Could they not see that it could not return them a word (for answer), and
 that it had no power either to harm them or to do them good?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Aaron had already, before this said to them: "O my people! ye are being
 tested in this: for verily your Lord is (Allah) Most Gracious; so follow
 me and obey my command."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They had said: "We will not abandon this cult, but we will devote ourselves
 to it until Moses returns to us."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Moses) said: "O Aaron! what kept thee back, when thou sawest them going
 wrong,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"From following me? Didst thou then disobey my order?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Aaron) replied: "O son of my mother! Seize (me) not by my beard nor by
 (the hair of) my head! Truly I feared lest thou shouldst say, 'Thou has
 caused a division among the children of Israel, and thou didst not respect
 my word!'"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Moses) said: "What then is thy case, O Samiri?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He replied: "I saw what they saw not: so I took a handful (of dust) from
 the footprint of the Messenger, and threw it (into the calf): thus did
 my soul suggest to me."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Moses) said: "Get thee gone! but thy (punishment) in this life will be
 that thou wilt say, 'touch me not'; and moreover (for a future penalty)
 thou hast a promise that will not fail: Now look at thy god, of whom thou
 hast become a devoted worshipper: We will certainly (melt) it in a blazing
 fire and scatter it broadcast in the sea!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But the god of you all is the One Allah: there is no god but He: all things
 He comprehends in His knowledge.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus do We relate to thee some stories of what happened before: for We have
 sent thee a Message from Our own Presence.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If any do turn away therefrom, verily they will bear a burden on the Day
 of judgment;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will abide in this (state): and grievous will the burden be to them
 on that Day,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day when the Trumpet will be sounded: that Day, We shall gather the
 sinful, blear-eyed (with terror).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In whispers will they consult each other: "Yet tarried not longer than ten
 (Days);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We know best what they will say, when their leader most eminent in conduct
 will say: "Ye tarried not longer than a day!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They ask thee concerning the Mountains: say, "My Lord will uproot them and
 scatter them as dust;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"He will leave them as plains smooth and level;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Nothing crooked or curved wilt thou see in their place."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On that Day will they follow the Caller (straight): no crookedness (can
 they show) him: all sounds shall humble themselves in the Presence of (Allah)
 Most Gracious: nothing shalt thou hear but the tramp of their feet (as
 they march).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On that Day shall no intercession avail except for those for whom permission
 has been granted by (Allah) Most Gracious and whose word is acceptable
 to Him.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He knows what (appears to His creatures as) before or after or behind them:
 but they shall not compass it with their knowledge.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(All) faces shall be humbled before (Him) - the Living, the Self-Subsisting,
 Eternal: hopeless indeed will be the man that carries iniquity (on his
 back).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But he who works deeds of righteousness, and has faith, will have no fear
 of harm nor of any curtailment (of what is his due).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus have We sent this down - an arabic Qur'an - and explained therein in
 detail some of the warnings, in order that they may fear Allah, or that
 it may cause their remembrance (of Him).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
High above all is Allah, the King, the Truth! Be not in haste with the Qur'an
 before its revelation to thee is completed, but say, "O my Lord! advance
 me in knowledge."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We had already, beforehand, taken the covenant of Adam, but he forgot: and
 We found on his part no firm resolve.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When We said to the angels, "Prostrate yourselves to Adam", they prostrated
 themselves, but not Iblis: he refused.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then We said: "O Adam! verily, this is an enemy to thee and thy wife: so
 let him not get you both out of the Garden, so that thou art landed in
 misery.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"There is therein (enough provision) for thee not to go hungry nor to go
 naked,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Nor to suffer from thirst, nor from the sun's heat."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But Satan whispered evil to him: he said, "O Adam! shall I lead thee to
 the Tree of Eternity and to a kingdom that never decays?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the result, they both ate of the tree, and so their nakedness appeared
 to them: they began to sew together, for their covering, leaves from the
 Garden: thus did Adam disobey his Lord, and allow himself to be seduced.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But his Lord chose him (for His Grace): He turned to him, and gave him Guidance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "Get ye down, both of you,- all together, from the Garden, with
 enmity one to another: but if, as is sure, there comes to you Guidance
 from Me, whosoever follows My Guidance, will not lose his way, nor fall
 into misery.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But whosoever turns away from My Message, verily for him is a life narrowed
 down, and We shall raise him up blind on the Day of Judgment."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He will say: "O my Lord! why hast Thou raised me up blind, while I had sight
 (before)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah) will say: "Thus didst Thou, when Our Signs came unto thee, disregard
 them: so wilt thou, this day, be disregarded."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And thus do We recompense him who transgresses beyond bounds and believes
 not in the Signs of his Lord: and the Penalty of the Hereafter is far more
 grievous and more enduring.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is it not a warning to such men (to call to mind) how many generations before
 them We destroyed, in whose haunts they (now) move? Verily, in this are
 Signs for men endued with understanding.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Had it not been for a Word that went forth before from thy Lord, (their
 punishment) must necessarily have come; but there is a Term appointed (for
 respite).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore be patient with what they say, and celebrate (constantly) the
 praises of thy Lord, before the rising of the sun, and before its setting;
 yea, celebrate them for part of the hours of the night, and at the sides
 of the day: that thou mayest have (spiritual) joy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor strain thine eyes in longing for the things We have given for enjoyment
 to parties of them, the splendour of the life of this world, through which
 We test them: but the provision of thy Lord is better and more enduring.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Enjoin prayer on thy people, and be constant therein.
 We ask thee not to provide sustenance: We provide it for thee.
 But the (fruit of) the Hereafter is for righteousness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They say: "Why does he not bring us a sign from his Lord?" Has not a Clear
 Sign come to them of all that was in the former Books of revelation?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if We had inflicted on them a penalty before this, they would have said:
 "Our Lord! If only Thou hadst sent us a messenger, we should certainly
 have followed Thy Signs before we were humbled and put to shame."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Each one (of us) is waiting: wait ye, therefore, and soon shall ye
 know who it is that is on the straight and even way, and who it is that
 has received Guidance."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Closer and closer to mankind comes their Reckoning: yet they heed not and
 they turn away.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Never comes (aught) to them of a renewed Message from their Lord, but they
 listen to it as in jest,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Their hearts toying as with trifles.
 The wrong-doers conceal their private counsels, (saying), "Is this (one)
 more than a man like yourselves? Will ye go to witchcraft with your eyes
 open?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "My Lord knoweth (every) word (spoken) in the heavens and on earth:
 He is the One that heareth and knoweth (all things)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Nay," they say, "(these are) medleys of dream! - Nay, He forged it! - Nay,
 He is (but) a poet! Let him then bring us a Sign like the ones that were
 sent to (Prophets) of old!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(As to those) before them, not one of the populations which We destroyed
 believed: will these believe?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Before thee, also, the messengers We sent were but men, to whom We granted
 inspiration: If ye realise this not, ask of those who possess the Message.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor did We give them bodies that ate no food, nor were they exempt from
 death.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the end We fulfilled to them Our Promise, and We saved them and those
 whom We pleased, but We destroyed those who transgressed beyond bounds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have revealed for you (O men!) a book in which is a Message for you:
 will ye not then understand?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
How many were the populations We utterly destroyed because of their iniquities,
 setting up in their places other peoples?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yet, when they felt Our Punishment (coming), behold, they (tried to) flee
 from it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Flee not, but return to the good things of this life which were given you,
 and to your homes in order that ye may be called to account.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "Ah! woe to us! We were indeed wrong-doers!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And that cry of theirs ceased not, till We made them as a field that is
 mown, as ashes silent and quenched.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Not for (idle) sport did We create the heavens and the earth and all that
 is between!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If it had been Our wish to take (just) a pastime, We should surely have
 taken it from the things nearest to Us, if We would do (such a thing)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, We hurl the Truth against falsehood, and it knocks out its brain, and
 behold, falsehood doth perish! Ah! woe be to you for the (false) things
 ye ascribe (to Us).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Him belong all (creatures) in the heavens and on earth: Even those who
 are in His (very) Presence are not too proud to serve Him, nor are they
 (ever) weary (of His service):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They celebrate His praises night and day, nor do they ever flag or intermit.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or have they taken (for worship) gods from the earth who can raise (the
 dead)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If there were, in the heavens and the earth, other gods besides Allah, there
 would have been confusion in both! but glory to Allah, the Lord of the
 Throne: (High is He) above what they attribute to Him!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He cannot be questioned for His acts, but they will be questioned (for theirs).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or have they taken for worship (other) gods besides him? Say, "Bring your
 convincing proof: this is the Message of those with me and the Message
 of those before me." But most of them know not the Truth, and so turn away.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Not a messenger did We send before thee without this inspiration sent by
 Us to him: that there is no god but I; therefore worship and serve Me.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they say: "(Allah) Most Gracious has begotten offspring." Glory to Him!
 they are (but) servants raised to honour.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They speak not before He speaks, and they act (in all things) by His Command.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He knows what is before them, and what is behind them, and they offer no
 intercession except for those who are acceptable, and they stand in awe
 and reverence of His (Glory).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If any of them should say, "I am a god besides Him", such a one We should
 reward with Hell: thus do We reward those who do wrong.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do not the Unbelievers see that the heavens and the earth were joined together
 (as one unit of creation), before we clove them asunder? We made from water
 every living thing.
 Will they not then believe?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We have set on the earth mountains standing firm, lest it should shake
 with them, and We have made therein broad highways (between mountains)
 for them to pass through: that they may receive Guidance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We have made the heavens as a canopy well guarded: yet do they turn
 away from the Signs which these things (point to)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who created the Night and the Day, and the sun and the moon: all
 (the celestial bodies) swim along, each in its rounded course.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We granted not to any man before thee permanent life (here): if then thou
 shouldst die, would they live permanently?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Every soul shall have a taste of death: and We test you by evil and by good
 by way of trial.
 to Us must ye return.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the Unbelievers see thee, they treat thee not except with ridicule.
 "Is this," (they say), "the one who talks of your gods?" and they blaspheme
 at the mention of (Allah) Most Gracious!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Man is a creature of haste: soon (enough) will I show you My Signs; then
 ye will not ask Me to hasten them!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They say: "When will this promise come to pass, if ye are telling the truth?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If only the Unbelievers knew (the time) when they will not be able to ward
 off the fire from their faces, nor yet from their backs, and (when) no
 help can reach them!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, it may come to them all of a sudden and confound them: no power will
 they have then to avert it, nor will they (then) get respite.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Mocked were (many) messenger before thee; But their scoffers were hemmed
 in by the thing that they mocked.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Who can keep you safe by night and by day from (the Wrath of) (Allah)
 Most Gracious?" Yet they turn away from the mention of their Lord.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or have they gods that can guard them from Us? They have no power to aid
 themselves, nor can they be defended from Us.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, We gave the good things of this life to these men and their fathers
 until the period grew long for them; See they not that We gradually reduce
 the land (in their control) from its outlying borders? Is it then they
 who will win?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say, "I do but warn you according to revelation": But the deaf will not
 hear the call, (even) when they are warned!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If but a breath of the Wrath of thy Lord do touch them, they will then say,
 "Woe to us! we did wrong indeed!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We shall set up scales of justice for the Day of Judgment, so that not a
 soul will be dealt with unjustly in the least, and if there be (no more
 than) the weight of a mustard seed, We will bring it (to account): and
 enough are We to take account.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the past We granted to Moses and Aaron the criterion (for judgment),
 and a Light and a Message for those who would do right,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who fear their Lord in their most secret thoughts, and who hold the
 Hour (of Judgment) in awe.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And this is a blessed Message which We have sent down: will ye then reject
 it?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We bestowed aforetime on Abraham his rectitude of conduct, and well were
 We acquainted with him.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold! he said to his father and his people, "What are these images, to
 which ye are (so assiduously) devoted?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said, "We found our fathers worshipping them."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said, "Indeed ye have been in manifest error - ye and your fathers."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said, "Have you brought us the Truth, or are you one of those who jest?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said, "Nay, your Lord is the Lord of the heavens and the earth, He Who
 created them (from nothing): and I am a witness to this (Truth).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And by Allah, I have a plan for your idols - after ye go away and turn
 your backs"..
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So he broke them to pieces, (all) but the biggest of them, that they might
 turn (and address themselves) to it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said, "Who has done this to our gods? He must indeed be some man of
 impiety!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said, "We heard a youth talk of them: He is called Abraham."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said, "Then bring him before the eyes of the people, that they may
 bear witness."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said, "Art thou the one that did this with our gods, O Abraham?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "Nay, this was done by - this is their biggest one! ask them, if
 they can speak intelligently!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So they turned to themselves and said, "Surely ye are the ones in the wrong!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then were they confounded with shame: (they said), "Thou knowest full well
 that these (idols) do not speak!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Abraham) said, "Do ye then worship, besides Allah, things that can neither
 be of any good to you nor do you harm?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Fie upon you, and upon the things that ye worship besides Allah! Have ye
 no sense?"..
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said, "Burn him and protect your gods, If ye do (anything at all)!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We said, "O Fire! be thou cool, and (a means of) safety for Abraham!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then they sought a stratagem against him: but We made them the ones that
 lost most!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But We delivered him and (his nephew) Lut (and directed them) to the land
 which We have blessed for the nations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We bestowed on him Isaac and, as an additional gift, (a grandson), Jacob,
 and We made righteous men of every one (of them).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We made them leaders, guiding (men) by Our Command, and We sent them
 inspiration to do good deeds, to establish regular prayers, and to practise
 regular charity; and they constantly served Us (and Us only).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And to Lut, too, We gave Judgment and Knowledge, and We saved him from the
 town which practised abominations: truly they were a people given to Evil,
 a rebellious people.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We admitted him to Our Mercy: for he was one of the Righteous.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Remember) Noah, when he cried (to Us) aforetime: We listened to his (prayer)
 and delivered him and his family from great distress.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We helped him against people who rejected Our Signs: truly they were a people
 given to Evil: so We drowned them (in the Flood) all together.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And remember David and Solomon, when they gave judgment in the matter of
 the field into which the sheep of certain people had strayed by night:
 We did witness their judgment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Solomon We inspired the (right) understanding of the matter: to each
 (of them) We gave Judgment and Knowledge; it was Our power that made the
 hills and the birds celebrate Our praises, with David: it was We Who did
 (all these things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It was We Who taught him the making of coats of mail for your benefit, to
 guard you from each other's violence: will ye then be grateful?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It was Our power that made) the violent (unruly) wind flow (tamely) for
 Solomon, to his order, to the land which We had blessed: for We do know
 all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And of the evil ones, were some who dived for him, and did other work besides;
 and it was We Who guarded them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And (remember) Job, when He cried to his Lord, "Truly distress has seized
 me, but Thou art the Most Merciful of those that are merciful."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So We listened to him: We removed the distress that was on him, and We restored
 his people to him, and doubled their number,- as a Grace from Ourselves,
 and a thing for commemoration, for all who serve Us.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And (remember) Isma'il, Idris, and Zul-kifl, all (men) of constancy and
 patience;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We admitted them to Our mercy: for they were of the righteous ones.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And remember Zun-nun, when he departed in wrath: He imagined that We had
 no power over him! But he cried through the deptHs of darkness, "There
 is no god but thou: glory to thee: I was indeed wrong!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So We listened to him: and delivered him from distress: and thus do We deliver
 those who have faith.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And (remember) Zakariya, when he cried to his Lord: "O my Lord! leave me
 not without offspring, though thou art the best of inheritors."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So We listened to him: and We granted him Yahya: We cured his wife's (Barrenness
) for him.
 These (three) were ever quick in emulation in good works; they used to
 call on Us with love and reverence, and humble themselves before Us.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And (remember) her who guarded her chastity: We breathed into her of Our
 spirit, and We made her and her son a sign for all peoples.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily, this brotherhood of yours is a single brotherhood, and I am your
 Lord and Cherisher: therefore serve Me (and no other).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But (later generations) cut off their affair (of unity), one from another:
 (yet) will they all return to Us.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whoever works any act of righteousness and has faith,- His endeavour will
 not be rejected: We shall record it in his favour.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But there is a ban on any population which We have destroyed: that they
 shall not return,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Until the Gog and Magog (people) are let through (their barrier), and they
 swiftly swarm from every hill.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then will the true promise draw nigh (of fulfilment): then behold! the eyes
 of the Unbelievers will fixedly stare in horror: "Ah! Woe to us! we were
 indeed heedless of this; nay, we truly did wrong!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily ye, (unbelievers), and the (false) gods that ye worship besides Allah,
 are (but) fuel for Hell! to it will ye (surely) come!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If these had been gods, they would not have got there! but each one will
 abide therein.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There, sobbing will be their lot, nor will they there hear (aught else).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those for whom the good (record) from Us has gone before, will be removed
 far therefrom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Not the slightest sound will they hear of Hell: what their souls desired,
 in that will they dwell.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Great Terror will bring them no grief: but the angels will meet them
 (with mutual greetings): "This is your Day,- (the Day) that ye were promised."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day that We roll up the heavens like a scroll rolled up for books (completed
),- even as We produced the first creation, so shall We produce a new one:
 a promise We have undertaken: truly shall We fulfil it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Before this We wrote in the Psalms, after the Message (given to Moses):
 My servants the righteous, shall inherit the earth."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily in this (Qur'an) is a Message for people who would (truly) worship
 Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We sent thee not, but as a Mercy for all creatures.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "What has come to me by inspiration is that your Allah is One Allah:
 will ye therefore bow to His Will (in Islam)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But if they turn back, Say: "I have proclaimed the Message to you all alike
 and in truth; but I know not whether that which ye are promised is near
 or far.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"It is He Who knows what is open in speech and what ye hide (in your hearts).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"I know not but that it may be a trial for you, and a grant of (worldly)
 livelihood (to you) for a time."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "O my Lord! judge Thou in truth!" "Our Lord Most Gracious is the One
 Whose assistance should be sought against the blasphemies ye utter!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O mankind! fear your Lord! for the convulsion of the Hour (of Judgment)
 will be a thing terrible!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day ye shall see it, every mother giving suck shall forget her suckling-babe
, and every pregnant female shall drop her load (unformed): thou shalt see
 mankind as in a drunken riot, yet not drunk: but dreadful will be the Wrath
 of Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And yet among men there are such as dispute about Allah, without knowledge,
 and follow every evil one obstinate in rebellion!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
About the (Evil One) it is decreed that whoever turns to him for friendship,
 him will he lead astray, and he will guide him to the Penalty of the Fire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O mankind! if ye have a doubt about the Resurrection, (consider) that We
 created you out of dust, then out of sperm, then out of a leech-like clot,
 then out of a morsel of flesh, partly formed and partly unformed, in order
 that We may manifest (our power) to you; and We cause whom We will to rest
 in the wombs for an appointed term, then do We bring you out as babes,
 then (foster you) that ye may reach your age of full strength; and some
 of you are called to die, and some are sent back to the feeblest old age,
 so that they know nothing after having known (much), and (further), thou
 seest the earth barren and lifeless, but when We pour down rain on it,
 it is stirred (to life), it swells, and it puts forth every kind of beautiful
 growth (in pairs).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is so, because Allah is the Reality: it is He Who gives life to the
 dead, and it is He Who has power over all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And verily the Hour will come: there can be no doubt about it, or about
 (the fact) that Allah will raise up all who are in the graves.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yet there is among men such a one as disputes about Allah, without Knowledge,
 without Guidance, and without a Book of Enlightenment,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Disdainfully) bending his side, in order to lead (men) astray from the
 Path of Allah: for him there is disgrace in this life, and on the Day of
 Judgment We shall make him taste the Penalty of burning (Fire).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It will be said): "This is because of the deeds which thy hands sent forth,
 for verily Allah is not unjust to His servants.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are among men some who serve Allah, as it were, on the verge: if good
 befalls them, they are, therewith, well content; but if a trial comes to
 them, they turn on their faces: they lose both this world and the Hereafter:
 that is loss for all to see!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They call on such deities, besides Allah, as can neither hurt nor profit
 them: that is straying far indeed (from the Way)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Perhaps) they call on one whose hurt is nearer than his profit: evil, indeed,
 is the patron, and evil the companion (or help)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily Allah will admit those who believe and work righteous deeds, to Gardens,
 beneath which rivers flow: for Allah carries out all that He plans.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If any think that Allah will not help him (His Messenger) in this world
 and the Hereafter, let him stretch out a rope to the ceiling and cut (himself)
 off: then let him see whether his plan will remove that which enrages (him)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus have We sent down Clear Signs; and verily Allah doth guide whom He
 will!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who believe (in the Qur'an), those who follow the Jewish (scriptures),
 and the Sabians, Christians, Magians, and Polytheists,- Allah will judge
 between them on the Day of Judgment: for Allah is witness of all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou not that to Allah bow down in worship all things that are in
 the heavens and on earth,- the sun, the moon, the stars; the hills, the
 trees, the animals; and a great number among mankind? But a great number
 are (also) such as are fit for Punishment: and such as Allah shall disgrace,-
 None can raise to honour: for Allah carries out all that He wills.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These two antagonists dispute with each other about their Lord: But those
 who deny (their Lord),- for them will be cut out a garment of Fire: over
 their heads will be poured out boiling water.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With it will be scalded what is within their bodies, as well as (their)
 skins.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In addition there will be maces of iron (to punish) them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Every time they wish to get away therefrom, from anguish, they will be forced
 back therein, and (it will be said), "Taste ye the Penalty of Burning!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah will admit those who believe and work righteous deeds, to Gardens
 beneath which rivers flow: they shall be adorned therein with bracelets
 of gold and pearls; and their garments there will be of silk.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For they have been guided (in this life) to the purest of speeches; they
 have been guided to the Path of Him Who is Worthy of (all) Praise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As to those who have rejected (Allah), and would keep back (men) from the
 Way of Allah, and from the Sacred Mosque, which We have made (open) to
 (all) men - equal is the dweller there and the visitor from the country
 - and any whose purpose therein is profanity or wrong-doing - them will
 We cause to taste of a most Grievous Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold! We gave the site, to Abraham, of the (Sacred) House, (saying): "Associat
e not anything (in worship) with Me; and sanctify My House for those who
 compass it round, or stand up, or bow, or prostrate themselves (therein
 in prayer).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And proclaim the Pilgrimage among men: they will come to thee on foot and
 (mounted) on every kind of camel, lean on account of journeys through deep
 and distant mountain highways;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"That they may witness the benefits (provided) for them, and celebrate the
 name of Allah, through the Days appointed, over the cattle which He has
 provided for them (for sacrifice): then eat ye thereof and feed the distressed
 ones in want.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Then let them complete the rites prescribed for them, perform their vows,
 and (again) circumambulate the Ancient House."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such (is the Pilgrimage): whoever honours the sacred rites of Allah, for
 him it is good in the Sight of his Lord.
 Lawful to you (for food in Pilgrimage) are cattle, except those mentioned
 to you (as exception): but shun the abomination of idols, and shun the
 word that is false,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Being true in faith to Allah, and never assigning partners to Him: if anyone
 assigns partners to Allah, is as if he had fallen from heaven and been
 snatched up by birds, or the wind had swooped (like a bird on its prey)
 and thrown him into a far-distant place.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such (is his state): and whoever holds in honour the symbols of Allah, (in
 the sacrifice of animals), such (honour) should come truly from piety of
 heart.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In them ye have benefits for a term appointed: in the end their place of
 sacrifice is near the Ancient House.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To every people did We appoint rites (of sacrifice), that they might celebrate
 the name of Allah over the sustenance He gave them from animals (fit for
 food).
 But your god is One God: submit then your wills to Him (in Islam): and
 give thou the good news to those who humble themselves,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To those whose hearts when Allah is mentioned, are filled with fear, who
 show patient perseverance over their afflictions, keep up regular prayer,
 and spend (in charity) out of what We have bestowed upon them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The sacrificial camels we have made for you as among the symbols from Allah:
 in them is (much) good for you: then pronounce the name of Allah over them
 as they line up (for sacrifice): when they are down on their sides (after
 slaughter), eat ye thereof, and feed such as (beg not but) live in contentment,
 and such as beg with due humility: thus have We made animals subject to
 you, that ye may be grateful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is not their meat nor their blood, that reaches Allah: it is your piety
 that reaches Him: He has thus made them subject to you, that ye may glorify
 Allah for His Guidance to you and proclaim the good news to all who do
 right.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily Allah will defend (from ill) those who believe: verily, Allah loveth
 not any that is a traitor to faith, or show ingratitude.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To those against whom war is made, permission is given (to fight), because
 they are wronged;- and verily, Allah is most powerful for their aid;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(They are) those who have been expelled from their homes in defiance of
 right,- (for no cause) except that they say, "our Lord is Allah".
 Did not Allah check one set of people by means of another, there would
 surely have been pulled down monasteries, churches, synagogues, and mosques,
 in which the name of Allah is commemorated in abundant measure.
 Allah will certainly aid those who aid his (cause);- for verily Allah is
 full of Strength, Exalted in Might, (able to enforce His Will).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(They are) those who, if We establish them in the land, establish regular
 prayer and give regular charity, enjoin the right and forbid wrong: with
 Allah rests the end (and decision) of (all) affairs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If they treat thy (mission) as false, so did the peoples before them (with
 their prophets),- the People of Noah, and 'Ad and Thamud;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those of Abraham and Lut;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Companions of the Madyan People; and Moses was rejected (in the
 same way).
 But I granted respite to the Unbelievers, and (only) after that did I punish
 them: but how (terrible) was my rejection (of them)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
How many populations have We destroyed, which were given to wrong-doing?
 They tumbled down on their roofs.
 And how many wells are lying idle and neglected, and castles lofty and
 well-built?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they not travel through the land, so that their hearts (and minds) may
 thus learn wisdom and their ears may thus learn to hear? Truly it is not
 their eyes that are blind, but their hearts which are in their breasts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yet they ask thee to hasten on the Punishment! But Allah will not fail in
 His Promise.
 Verily a Day in the sight of thy Lord is like a thousand years of your
 reckoning.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And to how many populations did I give respite, which were given to wrong-doing?
 in the end I punished them.
 To me is the destination (of all).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "O men! I am (sent) to you only to give a Clear Warning:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Those who believe and work righteousness, for them is forgiveness and a
 sustenance most generous.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But those who strive against Our Signs, to frustrate them,- they will be
 Companions of the Fire."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Never did We send a messenger or a prophet before thee, but, when he framed
 a desire, Satan threw some (vanity) into his desire: but Allah will cancel
 anything (vain) that Satan throws in, and Allah will confirm (and establish)
 His Signs: for Allah is full of Knowledge and Wisdom:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That He may make the suggestions thrown in by Satan, but a trial for those
 in whose hearts is a disease and who are hardened of heart: verily the
 wrong-doers are in a schism far (from the Truth):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And that those on whom knowledge has been bestowed may learn that the (Qur'an)
 is the Truth from thy Lord, and that they may believe therein, and their
 hearts may be made humbly (open) to it: for verily Allah is the Guide of
 those who believe, to the Straight Way.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who reject Faith will not cease to be in doubt concerning (Revelation)
 until the Hour (of Judgment) comes suddenly upon them, or there comes to
 them the Penalty of a Day of Disaster.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On that Day of Dominion will be that of Allah: He will judge between them:
 so those who believe and work righteous deeds will be in Gardens of Delight.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And for those who reject Faith and deny our Signs, there will be a humiliating
 Punishment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who leave their homes in the cause of Allah, and are then slain or
 die,- On them will Allah bestow verily a goodly Provision: Truly Allah
 is He Who bestows the best provision.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily He will admit them to a place with which they shall be well pleased:
 for Allah is All-Knowing, Most Forbearing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That (is so).
 And if one has retaliated to no greater extent than the injury he received,
 and is again set upon inordinately, Allah will help him: for Allah is One
 that blots out (sins) and forgives (again and again).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That is because Allah merges night into day, and He merges day into night,
 and verily it is Allah Who hears and sees (all things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That is because Allah - He is the Reality; and those besides Him whom they
 invoke,- they are but vain Falsehood: verily Allah is He, Most High, Most
 Great.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou not that Allah sends down rain from the sky, and forthwith the
 earth becomes clothed with green? for Allah is He Who understands the finest
 mysteries, and is well-acquainted (with them).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Him belongs all that is in the heavens and on earth: for verily Allah,-
 He is free of all wants, Worthy of all Praise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou not that Allah has made subject to you (men) all that is on the
 earth, and the ships that sail through the sea by His Command? He withholds
 the sky (rain) from failing on the earth except by His leave: for Allah
 is Most Kind and Most Merciful to man.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who gave you life, will cause you to die, and will again give you
 life: Truly man is a most ungrateful creature!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To every People have We appointed rites and ceremonies which they must follow:
 let them not then dispute with thee on the matter, but do thou invite (them)
 to thy Lord: for thou art assuredly on the Right Way.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If they do wrangle with thee, say, "Allah knows best what it is ye are doing."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Allah will judge between you on the Day of Judgment concerning the matters
 in which ye differ."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Knowest thou not that Allah knows all that is in heaven and on earth? Indeed
 it is all in a Record, and that is easy for Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yet they worship, besides Allah, things for which no authority has been
 sent down to them, and of which they have (really) no knowledge: for those
 that do wrong there is no helper.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When Our Clear Signs are rehearsed to them, thou wilt notice a denial on
 the faces of the Unbelievers! they nearly attack with violence those who
 rehearse Our Signs to them.
 Say, "Shall I tell you of something (far) worse than these Signs? It is
 the Fire (of Hell)! Allah has promised it to the Unbelievers! and evil
 is that destination!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O men! Here is a parable set forth! listen to it! Those on whom, besides
 Allah, ye call, cannot create (even) a fly, if they all met together for
 the purpose! and if the fly should snatch away anything from them, they
 would have no power to release it from the fly.
 Feeble are those who petition and those whom they petition!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No just estimate have they made of Allah: for Allah is He Who is strong
 and able to Carry out His Will.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah chooses messengers from angels and from men for Allah is He Who hears
 and sees (all things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He knows what is before them and what is behind them: and to Allah go back
 all questions (for decision).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! bow down, prostrate yourselves, and adore your Lord; and
 do good; that ye may prosper.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And strive in His cause as ye ought to strive, (with sincerity and under
 discipline).
 He has chosen you, and has imposed no difficulties on you in religion;
 it is the cult of your father Abraham.
 It is He Who has named you Muslims, both before and in this (Revelation);
 that the Messenger may be a witness for you, and ye be witnesses for mankind!
 So establish regular Prayer, give regular Charity, and hold fast to Allah!
 He is your Protector - the Best to protect and the Best to help!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The believers must (eventually) win through,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who humble themselves in their prayers;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who avoid vain talk;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who are active in deeds of charity;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who abstain from sex,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Except with those joined to them in the marriage bond, or (the captives)
 whom their right hands possess,- for (in their case) they are free from
 blame,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those whose desires exceed those limits are transgressors;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who faithfully observe their trusts and their covenants;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And who (strictly) guard their prayers;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These will be the heirs,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who will inherit Paradise: they will dwell therein (for ever).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Man We did create from a quintessence (of clay);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then We placed him as (a drop of) sperm in a place of rest, firmly fixed;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then We made the sperm into a clot of congealed blood; then of that clot
 We made a (foetus) lump; then we made out of that lump bones and clothed
 the bones with flesh; then we developed out of it another creature.
 So blessed be Allah, the best to create!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
After that, at length ye will die
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Again, on the Day of Judgment, will ye be raised up.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We have made, above you, seven tracts; and We are never unmindful of
 (our) Creation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We send down water from the sky according to (due) measure, and We cause
 it to soak in the soil; and We certainly are able to drain it off (with
 ease).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With it We grow for you gardens of date-palms and vines: in them have ye
 abundant fruits: and of them ye eat (and have enjoyment),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Also a tree springing out of Mount Sinai, which produces oil, and relish
 for those who use it for food.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And in cattle (too) ye have an instructive example: from within their bodies
 We produce (milk) for you to drink; there are, in them, (besides), numerous
 (other) benefits for you; and of their (meat) ye eat;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And on them, as well as in ships, ye ride.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Further, We sent a long line of prophets for your instruction).
 We sent Noah to his people: He said, "O my people! worship Allah! Ye have
 no other god but Him.
 Will ye not fear (Him)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The chiefs of the Unbelievers among his people said: "He is no more than
 a man like yourselves: his wish is to assert his superiority over you:
 if Allah had wished (to send messengers), He could have sent down angels;
 never did we hear such a thing (as he says), among our ancestors of old."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(And some said): "He is only a man possessed: wait (and have patience) with
 him for a time."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Noah) said: "O my Lord! help me: for that they accuse me of falsehood!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So We inspired him (with this message): "Construct the Ark within Our sight
 and under Our guidance: then when comes Our Command, and the fountains
 of the earth gush forth, take thou on board pairs of every species, male
 and female, and thy family- except those of them against whom the Word
 has already gone forth: And address Me not in favour of the wrong-doers;
 for they shall be drowned (in the Flood).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when thou hast embarked on the Ark - thou and those with thee,- say:
 "Praise be to Allah, Who has saved us from the people who do wrong."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And say: "O my Lord! enable me to disembark with thy blessing: for Thou
 art the Best to enable (us) to disembark."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily in this there are Signs (for men to understand); (thus) do We try
 (men).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then We raised after them another generation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We sent to them a messenger from among themselves, (saying), "Worship
 Allah! ye have no other god but Him.
 Will ye not fear (Him)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the chiefs of his people, who disbelieved and denied the Meeting in
 the Hereafter, and on whom We had bestowed the good things of this life,
 said: "He is no more than a man like yourselves: he eats of that of which
 ye eat, and drinks of what ye drink.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"If ye obey a man like yourselves, behold, it is certain ye will be lost.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Does he promise that when ye die and become dust and bones, ye shall be
 brought forth (again)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Far, very far is that which ye are promised!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"There is nothing but our life in this world! We shall die and we live!
 But we shall never be raised up again!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"He is only a man who invents a lie against Allah, but we are not the ones
 to believe in him!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(The prophet) said: "O my Lord! help me: for that they accuse me of falsehood."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah) said: "In but a little while, they are sure to be sorry!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then the Blast overtook them with justice, and We made them as rubbish of
 dead leaves (floating on the stream of Time)! So away with the people who
 do wrong!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then We raised after them other generations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No people can hasten their term, nor can they delay (it).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then sent We our messengers in succession: every time there came to a people
 their messenger, they accused him of falsehood: so We made them follow
 each other (in punishment): We made them as a tale (that is told): So away
 with a people that will not believe!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then We sent Moses and his brother Aaron, with Our Signs and authority manifest,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Pharaoh and his Chiefs: But these behaved insolently: they were an arrogant
 people.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "Shall we believe in two men like ourselves? And their people
 are subject to us!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So they accused them of falsehood, and they became of those who were destroyed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We gave Moses the Book, in order that they might receive guidance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We made the son of Mary and his mother as a Sign: We gave them both
 shelter on high ground, affording rest and security and furnished with
 springs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye messengers! enjoy (all) things good and pure, and work righteousness:
 for I am well-acquainted with (all) that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And verily this Brotherhood of yours is a single Brotherhood, and I am your
 Lord and Cherisher: therefore fear Me (and no other).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But people have cut off their affair (of unity), between them, into sects:
 each party rejoices in that which is with itself.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But leave them in their confused ignorance for a time.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they think that because We have granted them abundance of wealth and
 sons,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We would hasten them on in every good? Nay, they do not understand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily those who live in awe for fear of their Lord;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who believe in the Signs of their Lord;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who join not (in worship) partners with their Lord;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who dispense their charity with their hearts full of fear, because
 they will return to their Lord;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is these who hasten in every good work, and these who are foremost in
 them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On no soul do We place a burden greater than it can bear: before Us is a
 record which clearly shows the truth: they will never be wronged.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But their hearts are in confused ignorance of this; and there are, besides
 that, deeds of theirs, which they will (continue) to do,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Until, when We seize in Punishment those of them who received the good things
 of this world, behold, they will groan in supplication!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It will be said): "Groan not in supplication this day: for ye shall certainly
 not be helped by Us.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"My Signs used to be rehearsed to you, but ye used to turn back on your
 heels-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"In arrogance: talking nonsense about the (Qur'an), like one telling fables
 by night."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they not ponder over the Word (of Allah), or has anything (new) come
 to them that did not come to their fathers of old?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or do they not recognise their Messenger, that they deny him?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or do they say, "He is possessed"? Nay, he has brought them the Truth, but
 most of them hate the Truth.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If the Truth had been in accord with their desires, truly the heavens and
 the earth, and all beings therein would have been in confusion and corruption!
 Nay, We have sent them their admonition, but they turn away from their
 admonition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or is it that thou askest them for some recompense? But the recompense of
 thy Lord is best: He is the Best of those who give sustenance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But verily thou callest them to the Straight Way;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And verily those who believe not in the Hereafter are deviating from that
 Way.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If We had mercy on them and removed the distress which is on them, they
 would obstinately persist in their transgression, wandering in distraction
 to and fro.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We inflicted Punishment on them, but they humbled not themselves to their
 Lord, nor do they submissively entreat (Him)!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Until We open on them a gate leading to a severe Punishment: then Lo! they
 will be plunged in despair therein!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who has created for you (the faculties of) hearing, sight, feeling
 and understanding: little thanks it is ye give!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He has multiplied you through the earth, and to Him shall ye be gathered
 back.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who gives life and death, and to Him (is due) the alternation of
 Night and Day: will ye not then understand?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On the contrary they say things similar to what the ancients said.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They say: "What! when we die and become dust and bones, could we really
 be raised up again?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Such things have been promised to us and to our fathers before! they are
 nothing but tales of the ancients!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "To whom belong the earth and all beings therein? (say) if ye know!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say, "To Allah!" say: "Yet will ye not receive admonition?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Who is the Lord of the seven heavens, and the Lord of the Throne (of
 Glory) Supreme?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say, "(They belong) to Allah." Say: "Will ye not then be filled
 with awe?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Who is it in whose hands is the governance of all things,- who protects
 (all), but is not protected (of any)? (say) if ye know."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say, "(It belongs) to Allah." Say: "Then how are ye deluded?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have sent them the Truth: but they indeed practise falsehood!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No son did Allah beget, nor is there any god along with Him: (if there were
 many gods), behold, each god would have taken away what he had created,
 and some would have lorded it over others! Glory to Allah! (He is free)
 from the (sort of) things they attribute to Him!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He knows what is hidden and what is open: too high is He for the partners
 they attribute to Him!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "O my Lord! if Thou wilt show me (in my lifetime) that which they are
 warned against,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Then, O my Lord! put me not amongst the people who do wrong!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We are certainly able to show thee (in fulfilment) that against which
 they are warned.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Repel evil with that which is best: We are well acquainted with the things
 they say.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And say "O my Lord! I seek refuge with Thee from the suggestions of the
 Evil Ones.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And I seek refuge with Thee O my Lord! lest they should come near me."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(In Falsehood will they be) Until, when death comes to one of them, he says:
 "O my Lord! send me back (to life),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"In order that I may work righteousness in the things I neglected." - "By
 no means! It is but a word he says."- Before them is a Partition till the
 Day they are raised up.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then when the Trumpet is blown, there will be no more relationships between
 them that Day, nor will one ask after another!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then those whose balance (of good deeds) is heavy,- they will attain salvation:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those whose balance is light, will be those who have lost their souls,
 in Hell will they abide.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Fire will burn their faces, and they will therein grin, with their lips
 displaced.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Were not My Signs rehearsed to you, and ye did but treat them as falsehood?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say: "our Lord! Our misfortune overwhelmed us, and we became a
 people astray!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Our Lord! bring us out of this: if ever we return (to Evil), then shall
 we be wrong-doers indeed!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He will say: "Be ye driven into it (with ignominy)! And speak ye not to
 Me!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"A part of My servants there was, who used to pray 'our Lord! we believe;
 then do Thou forgive us, and have mercy upon us: For Thou art the Best
 of those who show mercy!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But ye treated them with ridicule, so much so that (ridicule of) them made
 you forget My Message while ye were laughing at them!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"I have rewarded them this Day for their patience and constancy: they are
 indeed the ones that have achieved Bliss..."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He will say: "What number of years did ye stay on earth?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say: "We stayed a day or part of a day: but ask those who keep
 account."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He will say: "Ye stayed not but a little,- if ye had only known!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Did ye then think that We had created you in jest, and that ye would not
 be brought back to Us (for account)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore exalted be Allah, the King, the Reality: there is no god but He,
 the Lord of the Throne of Honour!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If anyone invokes, besides Allah, Any other god, he has no authority therefor;
 and his reckoning will be only with his Lord! and verily the Unbelievers
 will fail to win through!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So say: "O my Lord! grant Thou forgiveness and mercy for Thou art the Best
 of those who show mercy!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A sura which We have sent down and which We have ordained in it have We
 sent down Clear Signs, in order that ye may receive admonition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The woman and the man guilty of adultery or fornication,- flog each of them
 with a hundred stripes: Let not compassion move you in their case, in a
 matter prescribed by Allah, if ye believe in Allah and the Last Day: and
 let a party of the Believers witness their punishment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let no man guilty of adultery or fornication marry and but a woman similarly
 guilty, or an Unbeliever: nor let any but such a man or an Unbeliever marry
 such a woman: to the Believers such a thing is forbidden.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who launch a charge against chaste women, and produce not four
 witnesses (to support their allegations),- flog them with eighty stripes;
 and reject their evidence ever after: for such men are wicked transgressors;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Unless they repent thereafter and mend (their conduct); for Allah is Oft-Forgivi
ng, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And for those who launch a charge against their spouses, and have (in support)
 no evidence but their own,- their solitary evidence (can be received) if
 they bear witness four times (with an oath) by Allah that they are solemnly
 telling the truth;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the fifth (oath) (should be) that they solemnly invoke the curse of
 Allah on themselves if they tell a lie.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But it would avert the punishment from the wife, if she bears witness four
 times (with an oath) By Allah, that (her husband) is telling a lie;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the fifth (oath) should be that she solemnly invokes the wrath of Allah
 on herself if (her accuser) is telling the truth.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If it were not for Allah's grace and mercy on you, and that Allah is Oft-Returni
ng, full of Wisdom,- (Ye would be ruined indeed).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who brought forward the lie are a body among yourselves: think it
 not to be an evil to you; On the contrary it is good for you: to every
 man among them (will come the punishment) of the sin that he earned, and
 to him who took on himself the lead among them, will be a penalty grievous.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Why did not the believers - men and women - when ye heard of the affair,-
 put the best construction on it in their own minds and say, "This (charge)
 is an obvious lie"?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Why did they not bring four witnesses to prove it? When they have not brought
 the witnesses, such men, in the sight of Allah, (stand forth) themselves
 as liars!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Were it not for the grace and mercy of Allah on you, in this world and the
 Hereafter, a grievous penalty would have seized you in that ye rushed glibly
 into this affair.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, ye received it on your tongues, and said out of your mouths things
 of which ye had no knowledge; and ye thought it to be a light matter, while
 it was most serious in the sight of Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And why did ye not, when ye heard it, say? - "It is not right of us to speak
 of this: Glory to Allah! this is a most serious slander!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah doth admonish you, that ye may never repeat such (conduct), if ye
 are (true) Believers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Allah makes the Signs plain to you: for Allah is full of knowledge and
 wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who love (to see) scandal published broadcast among the Believers,
 will have a grievous Penalty in this life and in the Hereafter: Allah knows,
 and ye know not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Were it not for the grace and mercy of Allah on you, and that Allah is full
 of kindness and mercy, (ye would be ruined indeed).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! follow not Satan's footsteps: if any will follow the footsteps
 of Satan, he will (but) command what is shameful and wrong: and were it
 not for the grace and mercy of Allah on you, not one of you would ever
 have been pure: but Allah doth purify whom He pleases: and Allah is One
 Who hears and knows (all things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let not those among you who are endued with grace and amplitude of means
 resolve by oath against helping their kinsmen, those in want, and those
 who have left their homes in Allah's cause: let them forgive and overlook,
 do you not wish that Allah should forgive you? For Allah is Oft-Forgiving,
 Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who slander chaste women, indiscreet but believing, are cursed in
 this life and in the Hereafter: for them is a grievous Penalty,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On the Day when their tongues, their hands, and their feet will bear witness
 against them as to their actions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On that Day Allah will pay them back (all) their just dues, and they will
 realise that Allah is the (very) Truth, that makes all things manifest.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Women impure are for men impure, and men impure for women impure and women
 of purity are for men of purity, and men of purity are for women of purity:
 these are not affected by what people say: for them there is forgiveness,
 and a provision honourable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! enter not houses other than your own, until ye have asked
 permission and saluted those in them: that is best for you, in order that
 ye may heed (what is seemly).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If ye find no one in the house, enter not until permission is given to you:
 if ye are asked to go back, go back: that makes for greater purity for
 yourselves: and Allah knows well all that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is no fault on your part to enter houses not used for living in, which
 serve some (other) use for you: And Allah has knowledge of what ye reveal
 and what ye conceal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say to the believing men that they should lower their gaze and guard their
 modesty: that will make for greater purity for them: And Allah is well
 acquainted with all that they do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And say to the believing women that they should lower their gaze and guard
 their modesty; that they should not display their beauty and ornaments
 except what (must ordinarily) appear thereof; that they should draw their
 veils over their bosoms and not display their beauty except to their husbands,
 their fathers, their husband's fathers, their sons, their husbands' sons,
 their brothers or their brothers' sons, or their sisters' sons, or their
 women, or the slaves whom their right hands possess, or male servants free
 of physical needs, or small children who have no sense of the shame of
 sex; and that they should not strike their feet in order to draw attention
 to their hidden ornaments.
 And O ye Believers! turn ye all together towards Allah, that ye may attain
 Bliss.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Marry those among you who are single, or the virtuous ones among yourselves,
 male or female: if they are in poverty, Allah will give them means out
 of His grace: for Allah encompasseth all, and he knoweth all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let those who find not the wherewithal for marriage keep themselves chaste,
 until Allah gives them means out of His grace.
 And if any of your slaves ask for a deed in writing (to enable them to
 earn their freedom for a certain sum), give them such a deed if ye know
 any good in them: yea, give them something yourselves out of the means
 which Allah has given to you.
 But force not your maids to prostitution when they desire chastity, in
 order that ye may make a gain in the goods of this life.
 But if anyone compels them, yet, after such compulsion, is Allah, Oft-Forgiving
, Most Merciful (to them),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have already sent down to you verses making things clear, an illustration
 from (the story of) people who passed away before you, and an admonition
 for those who fear (Allah).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah is the Light of the heavens and the earth.
 The Parable of His Light is as if there were a Niche and within it a Lamp:
 the Lamp enclosed in Glass: the glass as it were a brilliant star: Lit
 from a blessed Tree, an Olive, neither of the east nor of the west, whose
 oil is well-nigh luminous, though fire scarce touched it: Light upon Light!
 Allah doth guide whom He will to His Light: Allah doth set forth Parables
 for men: and Allah doth know all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Lit is such a Light) in houses, which Allah hath permitted to be raised
 to honour; for the celebration, in them, of His name: In them is He glorified
 in the mornings and in the evenings, (again and again),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By men whom neither traffic nor merchandise can divert from the Remembrance
 of Allah, nor from regular Prayer, nor from the practice of regular Charity:
 Their (only) fear is for the Day when hearts and eyes will be transformed
 (in a world wholly new),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That Allah may reward them according to the best of their deeds, and add
 even more for them out of His Grace: for Allah doth provide for those whom
 He will, without measure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But the Unbelievers,- their deeds are like a mirage in sandy deserts, which
 the man parched with thirst mistakes for water; until when he comes up
 to it, he finds it to be nothing: But he finds Allah (ever) with him, and
 Allah will pay him his account: and Allah is swift in taking account.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or (the Unbelievers' state) is like the depths of darkness in a vast deep
 ocean, overwhelmed with billow topped by billow, topped by (dark) clouds:
 depths of darkness, one above another: if a man stretches out his hands,
 he can hardly see it! for any to whom Allah giveth not light, there is
 no light!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou not that it is Allah Whose praises all beings in the heavens
 and on earth do celebrate, and the birds (of the air) with wings outspread?
 Each one knows its own (mode of) prayer and praise.
 And Allah knows well all that they do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yea, to Allah belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth; and to
 Allah is the final goal (of all).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou not that Allah makes the clouds move gently, then joins them
 together, then makes them into a heap? - then wilt thou see rain issue
 forth from their midst.
 And He sends down from the sky mountain masses (of clouds) wherein is hail:
 He strikes therewith whom He pleases and He turns it away from whom He
 pleases, the vivid flash of His lightning well-nigh blinds the sight.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is Allah Who alternates the Night and the Day: verily in these things
 is an instructive example for those who have vision!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Allah has created every animal from water: of them there are some that
 creep on their bellies; some that walk on two legs; and some that walk
 on four.
 Allah creates what He wills for verily Allah has power over all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have indeed sent down signs that make things manifest: and Allah guides
 whom He wills to a way that is straight.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They say, "We believe in Allah and in the messenger, and we obey": but even
 after that, some of them turn away: they are not (really) Believers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When they are summoned to Allah and His messenger, in order that He may
 judge between them, behold some of them decline (to come).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But if the right is on their side, they come to him with all submission.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is it that there is a disease in their hearts? or do they doubt, or are
 they in fear, that Allah and His Messenger will deal unjustly with them?
 Nay, it is they themselves who do wrong.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The answer of the Believers, when summoned to Allah and His Messenger, in
 order that He may judge between them, is no other than this: they say,
 "We hear and we obey": it is such as these that will attain felicity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is such as obey Allah and His Messenger, and fear Allah and do right,
 that will win (in the end),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They swear their strongest oaths by Allah that, if only thou wouldst command
 them, they would leave (their homes).
 Say: "Swear ye not; Obedience is (more) reasonable; verily, Allah is well
 acquainted with all that ye do."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Obey Allah, and obey the Messenger: but if ye turn away, he is only
 responsible for the duty placed on him and ye for that placed on you.
 If ye obey him, ye shall be on right guidance.
 The Messenger's duty is only to preach the clear (Message).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah has promised, to those among you who believe and work righteous deeds,
 that He will, of a surety, grant them in the land, inheritance (of power),
 as He granted it to those before them; that He will establish in authority
 their religion - the one which He has chosen for them; and that He will
 change (their state), after the fear in which they (lived), to one of security
 and peace: 'They will worship Me (alone) and not associate aught with Me.
 'If any do reject Faith after this, they are rebellious and wicked.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So establish regular Prayer and give regular Charity; and obey the Messenger;
 that ye may receive mercy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Never think thou that the Unbelievers are going to frustrate (Allah's Plan)
 on earth: their abode is the Fire,- and it is indeed an evil refuge!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! let those whom your right hands possess, and the (children)
 among you who have not come of age ask your permission (before they come
 to your presence), on three occasions: before morning prayer; the while
 ye doff your clothes for the noonday heat; and after the late-night prayer:
 these are your three times of undress: outside those times it is not wrong
 for you or for them to move about attending to each other: Thus does Allah
 make clear the Signs to you: for Allah is full of knowledge and wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But when the children among you come of age, let them (also) ask for permission,
 as do those senior to them (in age): Thus does Allah make clear His Signs
 to you: for Allah is full of knowledge and wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such elderly women as are past the prospect of marriage,- there is no blame
 on them if they lay aside their (outer) garments, provided they make not
 a wanton display of their beauty: but it is best for them to be modest:
 and Allah is One Who sees and knows all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is no fault in the blind nor in one born lame, nor in one afflicted with
 illness, nor in yourselves, that ye should eat in your own houses, or those
 of your fathers, or your mothers, or your brothers, or your sisters, or
 your father's brothers or your father's sisters, or your mother's brothers,
 or your mother's sisters, or in houses of which the keys are in your possession
, or in the house of a sincere friend of yours: there is no blame on you,
 whether ye eat in company or separately.
 But if ye enter houses, salute each other - a greeting of blessing and
 purity as from Allah.
 Thus does Allah make clear the signs to you: that ye may understand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Only those are believers, who believe in Allah and His Messenger: when they
 are with him on a matter requiring collective action, they do not depart
 until they have asked for his leave; those who ask for thy leave are those
 who believe in Allah and His Messenger; so when they ask for thy leave,
 for some business of theirs, give leave to those of them whom thou wilt,
 and ask Allah for their forgiveness: for Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Deem not the summons of the Messenger among yourselves like the summons
 of one of you to another: Allah doth know those of you who slip away under
 shelter of some excuse: then let those beware who withstand the Messenger's
 order, lest some trial befall them, or a grievous penalty be inflicted
 on them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Be quite sure that to Allah doth belong whatever is in the heavens and on
 earth.
 Well doth He know what ye are intent upon: and one day they will be brought
 back to Him, and He will tell them the truth of what they did: for Allah
 doth know all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Blessed is He who sent down the criterion to His servant, that it may be
 an admonition to all creatures;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He to whom belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth: no son has
 He begotten, nor has He a partner in His dominion: it is He who created
 all things, and ordered them in due proportions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yet have they taken, besides him, gods that can create nothing but are themselve
s created; that have no control of hurt or good to themselves; nor can they
 control death nor life nor resurrection.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But the misbelievers say: "Naught is this but a lie which he has forged,
 and others have helped him at it." In truth it is they who have put forward
 an iniquity and a falsehood.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they say: "Tales of the ancients, which he has caused to be written:
 and they are dictated before him morning and evening."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "The (Qur'an) was sent down by Him who knows the mystery (that is)
 in the heavens and the earth: verily He is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they say: "What sort of a messenger is this, who eats food, and walks
 through the streets? Why has not an angel been sent down to him to give
 admonition with him?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Or (Why) has not a treasure been bestowed on him, or why has he (not) a
 garden for enjoyment?" The wicked say: "Ye follow none other than a man
 bewitched."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
See what kinds of comparisons they make for thee! But they have gone astray,
 and never a way will they be able to find!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Blessed is He who, if that were His will, could give thee better (things)
 than those,- Gardens beneath which rivers flow; and He could give thee
 palaces (secure to dwell in).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay they deny the hour (of the judgment to come): but We have prepared a
 blazing fire for such as deny the hour:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When it sees them from a place far off, they will hear its fury and its
 ranging sigh.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when they are cast, bound together into a constricted place therein,
 they will plead for destruction there and then!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"This day plead not for a single destruction: plead for destruction oft-repeated
!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Is that best, or the eternal garden, promised to the righteous? for
 them, that is a reward as well as a goal (of attainment).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"For them there will be therein all that they wish for: they will dwell
 (there) for aye: A promise to be prayed for from thy Lord."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The day He will gather them together as well as those whom they worship
 besides Allah, He will ask: "Was it ye who let these My servants astray,
 or did they stray from the Path themselves?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say: "Glory to Thee! not meet was it for us that we should take
 for protectors others besides Thee: But Thou didst bestow, on them and
 their fathers, good things (in life), until they forgot the Message: for
 they were a people (worthless and) lost."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah will say): "Now have they proved you liars in what ye say: so ye
 cannot avert (your penalty) nor (get) help." And whoever among you does
 wrong, him shall We cause to taste of a grievous Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the messengers whom We sent before thee were all (men) who ate food
 and walked through the streets: We have made some of you as a trial for
 others: will ye have patience? for Allah is One Who sees (all things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such as fear not the meeting with Us (for Judgment) say: "Why are not the
 angels sent down to us, or (why) do we not see our Lord?" Indeed they have
 an arrogant conceit of themselves, and mighty is the insolence of their
 impiety!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day they see the angels,- no joy will there be to the sinners that Day:
 The (angels) will say: "There is a barrier forbidden (to you) altogether!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We shall turn to whatever deeds they did (in this life), and We shall
 make such deeds as floating dust scattered about.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Companions of the Garden will be well, that Day, in their abode, and
 have the fairest of places for repose.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day the heaven shall be rent asunder with clouds, and angels shall be
 sent down, descending (in ranks),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That Day, the dominion as of right and truth, shall be (wholly) for (Allah)
 Most Merciful: it will be a Day of dire difficulty for the misbelievers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day that the wrong-doer will bite at his hands, he will say, "Oh! would
 that I had taken a (straight) path with the Messenger!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Ah! woe is me! Would that I had never taken such a one for a friend!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"He did lead me astray from the Message (of Allah) after it had come to
 me! Ah! the Evil One is but a traitor to man!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then the Messenger will say: "O my Lord! Truly my people took this Qur'an
 for just foolish nonsense."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus have We made for every prophet an enemy among the sinners: but enough
 is thy Lord to guide and to help.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who reject Faith say: "Why is not the Qur'an revealed to him all at
 once? Thus (is it revealed), that We may strengthen thy heart thereby,
 and We have rehearsed it to thee in slow, well-arranged stages, gradually.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And no question do they bring to thee but We reveal to thee the truth and
 the best explanation (thereof).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who will be gathered to Hell (prone) on their faces,- they will be
 in an evil plight, and, as to Path, most astray.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Before this,) We sent Moses The Book, and appointed his brother Aaron with
 him as minister;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We command: "Go ye both, to the people who have rejected our Signs:"
 And those (people) We destroyed with utter destruction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the people of Noah,- when they rejected the messengers, We drowned them,
 and We made them as a Sign for mankind; and We have prepared for (all)
 wrong-doers a grievous Penalty;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As also 'Ad and Thamud, and the Companions of the Rass, and many a generation
 between them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To each one We set forth Parables and examples; and each one We broke to
 utter annihilation (for their sins).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the (Unbelievers) must indeed have passed by the town on which was rained
 a shower of evil: did they not then see it (with their own eyes)? But they
 fear not the Resurrection.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When they see thee, they treat thee no otherwise than in mockery: "Is this
 the one whom Allah has sent as a messenger?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"He indeed would well-nigh have misled us from our gods, had it not been
 that we were constant to them!" - Soon will they know, when they see the
 Penalty, who it is that is most misled in Path!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou such a one as taketh for his god his own passion (or impulse)?
 Couldst thou be a disposer of affairs for him?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or thinkest thou that most of them listen or understand? They are only like
 cattle;- nay, they are worse astray in Path.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Hast thou not turned thy vision to thy Lord?- How He doth prolong the shadow!
 If He willed, He could make it stationary! then do We make the sun its
 guide;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then We draw it in towards Ourselves,- a contraction by easy stages.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He it is Who makes the Night as a Robe for you, and Sleep as Repose,
 and makes the Day (as it were) a Resurrection.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He it is Who sends the winds as heralds of glad tidings, going before
 His mercy, and We send down pure water from the sky,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That with it We may give life to a dead land, and slake the thirst of things
 We have created,- cattle and men in great numbers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We have distributed the (water) amongst them, in order that they may
 celebrate (our) praises, but most men are averse (to aught) but (rank)
 ingratitude.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Had it been Our Will, We could have sent a warner to every centre of population.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore listen not to the Unbelievers, but strive against them with the
 utmost strenuousness, with the (Qur'an).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who has let free the two bodies of flowing water: One palatable
 and sweet, and the other salt and bitter; yet has He made a barrier between
 them, a partition that is forbidden to be passed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who has created man from water: then has He established relationships
 of lineage and marriage: for thy Lord has power (over all things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yet do they worship, besides Allah, things that can neither profit them
 nor harm them: and the Misbeliever is a helper (of Evil), against his own
 Lord!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But thee We only sent to give glad tidings and admonition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "No reward do I ask of you for it but this: that each one who will
 may take a (straight) Path to his Lord."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And put thy trust in Him Who lives and dies not; and celebrate his praise;
 and enough is He to be acquainted with the faults of His servants;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He Who created the heavens and the earth and all that is between, in six
 days, and is firmly established on the Throne (of Authority): Allah Most
 Gracious: ask thou, then, about Him of any acquainted (with such things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When it is said to them, "Prostrate to (Allah) Most Gracious!", they say,
 "And what is (Allah) Most Gracious? Shall we prostrate to that which thou
 commandest us?" And it increases their flight (from the Truth).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Blessed is He Who made constellations in the skies, and placed therein a
 Lamp and a Moon giving light;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And it is He Who made the Night and the Day to follow each other: for such
 as have the will to celebrate His praises or to show their gratitude.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the servants of (Allah) Most Gracious are those who walk on the earth
 in humility, and when the ignorant address them, they say, "Peace!";
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who spend the night in adoration of their Lord prostrate and standing;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who say, "Our Lord! avert from us the Wrath of Hell, for its Wrath
 is indeed an affliction grievous,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Evil indeed is it as an abode, and as a place to rest in";
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who, when they spend, are not extravagant and not niggardly, but hold
 a just (balance) between those (extremes);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who invoke not, with Allah, any other god, nor slay such life as Allah
 has made sacred except for just cause, nor commit fornication; - and any
 that does this (not only) meets punishment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(But) the Penalty on the Day of Judgment will be doubled to him, and he
 will dwell therein in ignominy,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Unless he repents, believes, and works righteous deeds, for Allah will change
 the evil of such persons into good, and Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And whoever repents and does good has truly turned to Allah with an (acceptable)
 conversion;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who witness no falsehood, and, if they pass by futility, they pass
 by it with honourable (avoidance);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who, when they are admonished with the Signs of their Lord, droop
 not down at them as if they were deaf or blind;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who pray, "Our Lord! Grant unto us wives and offspring who will
 be the comfort of our eyes, and give us (the grace) to lead the righteous."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those are the ones who will be rewarded with the highest place in heaven,
 because of their patient constancy: therein shall they be met with salutations
 and peace,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Dwelling therein;- how beautiful an abode and place of rest!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say (to the Rejecters): "My Lord is not uneasy because of you if ye call
 not on Him: But ye have indeed rejected (Him), and soon will come the inevitabl
e (punishment)!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ta.
 Sin.
 Mim.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These are verses of the Book that makes (things) clear.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It may be thou frettest thy soul with grief, that they do not become Believers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If (such) were Our Will, We could send down to them from the sky a Sign,
 to which they would bend their necks in humility.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But there comes not to them a newly-revealed Message from (Allah) Most Gracious,
 but they turn away therefrom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They have indeed rejected (the Message): so they will know soon (enough)
 the truth of what they mocked at!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they not look at the earth,- how many noble things of all kinds We have
 produced therein?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily, in this is a Sign: but most of them do not believe.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And verily, thy Lord is He, the Exalted in Might, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, thy Lord called Moses: "Go to the people of iniquity,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"The people of the Pharaoh: will they not fear Allah?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "O my Lord! I do fear that they will charge me with falsehood:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"My breast will be straitened.
 And my speech may not go (smoothly): so send unto Aaron.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And (further), they have a charge of crime against me; and I fear they
 may slay me."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah said: "By no means! proceed then, both of you, with Our Signs; We
 are with you, and will listen (to your call).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"So go forth, both of you, to Pharaoh, and say: 'We have been sent by the
 Lord and Cherisher of the worlds;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"'Send thou with us the Children of Israel.'"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Pharaoh) said: "Did we not cherish thee as a child among us, and didst
 thou not stay in our midst many years of thy life?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And thou didst a deed of thine which (thou knowest) thou didst, and thou
 art an ungrateful (wretch)!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moses said: "I did it then, when I was in error.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"So I fled from you (all) when I feared you; but my Lord has (since) invested
 me with judgment (and wisdom) and appointed me as one of the messengers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And this is the favour with which thou dost reproach me,- that thou hast
 enslaved the Children of Israel!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Pharaoh said: "And what is the 'Lord and Cherisher of the worlds'?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Moses) said: "The Lord and Cherisher of the heavens and the earth, and
 all between,- if ye want to be quite sure."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Pharaoh) said to those around: "Did ye not listen (to what he says)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Moses) said: "Your Lord and the Lord of your fathers from the beginning!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Pharaoh) said: "Truly your messenger who has been sent to you is a veritable
 madman!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Moses) said: "Lord of the East and the West, and all between! if ye only
 had sense!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Pharaoh) said: "If thou dost put forward any god other than me, I will
 certainly put thee in prison!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Moses) said: "Even if I showed you something clear (and) convincing?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Pharaoh) said: "Show it then, if thou tellest the truth!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So (Moses) threw his rod, and behold, it was a serpent, plain (for all to
 see)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And he drew out his hand, and behold, it was white to all beholders!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Pharaoh) said to the Chiefs around him: "This is indeed a sorcerer well-versed:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"His plan is to get you out of your land by his sorcery; then what is it
 ye counsel?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "Keep him and his brother in suspense (for a while), and dispatch
 to the Cities heralds to collect-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And bring up to thee all (our) sorcerers well-versed."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So the sorcerers were got together for the appointment of a day well-known,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the people were told: "Are ye (now) assembled?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"That we may follow the sorcerers (in religion) if they win?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So when the sorcerers arrived, they said to Pharaoh: "Of course - shall
 we have a (suitable) reward if we win?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
