 and we have submitted to Allah (in Islam)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And he diverted her from the worship of others besides Allah: for she was
 (sprung) of a people that had no faith.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
She was asked to enter the lofty Palace: but when she saw it, she thought
 it was a lake of water, and she (tucked up her skirts), uncovering her
 legs.
 He said: "This is but a palace paved smooth with slabs of glass." She said:
 "O my Lord! I have indeed wronged my soul: I do (now) submit (in Islam),
 with Solomon, to the Lord of the Worlds."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We sent (aforetime), to the Thamud, their brother Salih, saying, "Serve
 Allah": But behold, they became two factions quarrelling with each other.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "O my people! why ask ye to hasten on the evil in preference to
 the good? If only ye ask Allah for forgiveness, ye may hope to receive
 mercy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "Ill omen do we augur from thee and those that are with thee".
 He said: "Your ill omen is with Allah; yea, ye are a people under trial."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There were in the city nine men of a family, who made mischief in the land,
 and would not reform.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "Swear a mutual oath by Allah that we shall make a secret night
 attack on him and his people, and that we shall then say to his heir (when
 he seeks vengeance): 'We were not present at the slaughter of his people,
 and we are positively telling the truth.'"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They plotted and planned, but We too planned, even while they perceived
 it not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then see what was the end of their plot!- this, that We destroyed them and
 their people, all (of them).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now such were their houses, - in utter ruin, - because they practised wrong-doin
g.
 Verily in this is a Sign for people of knowledge.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We saved those who believed and practised righteousness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(We also sent) Lut (as a messenger): behold, He said to his people, "Do
 ye do what is shameful though ye see (its iniquity)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Would ye really approach men in your lusts rather than women? Nay, ye are
 a people (grossly) ignorant!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But his people gave no other answer but this: they said, "Drive out the
 followers of Lut from your city: these are indeed men who want to be clean
 and pure!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But We saved him and his family, except his wife; her We destined to be
 of those who lagged behind.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We rained down on them a shower (of brimstone): and evil was the shower
 on those who were admonished (but heeded not)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: Praise be to Allah, and Peace on his servants whom He has chosen (for
 his Message).
 (Who) is better?- Allah or the false gods they associate (with Him)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or, Who has created the heavens and the earth, and Who sends you down rain
 from the sky? Yea, with it We cause to grow well-planted orchards full
 of beauty of delight: it is not in your power to cause the growth of the
 trees in them.
 (Can there be another) god besides Allah? Nay, they are a people who swerve
 from justice.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or, Who has made the earth firm to live in; made rivers in its midst; set
 thereon mountains immovable; and made a separating bar between the two
 bodies of flowing water? (can there be another) god besides Allah? Nay,
 most of them know not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or, Who listens to the (soul) distressed when it calls on Him, and Who relieves
 its suffering, and makes you (mankind) inheritors of the earth? (Can there
 be another) god besides Allah? Little it is that ye heed!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or, Who guides you through the depths of darkness on land and sea, and Who
 sends the winds as heralds of glad tidings, going before His Mercy? (Can
 there be another) god besides Allah?- High is Allah above what they associate
 with Him!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or, Who originates creation, then repeats it, and who gives you sustenance
 from heaven and earth? (Can there be another) god besides Allah? Say, "Bring
 forth your argument, if ye are telling the truth!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: None in the heavens or on earth, except Allah, knows what is hidden:
 nor can they perceive when they shall be raised up (for Judgment).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Still less can their knowledge comprehend the Hereafter: Nay, they are in
 doubt and uncertainty thereanent; nay, they are blind thereunto!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Unbelievers say: "What! when we become dust,- we and our fathers,- shall
 we really be raised (from the dead)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"It is true we were promised this,- we and our fathers before (us): these
 are nothing but tales of the ancients."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Go ye through the earth and see what has been the end of those guilty
 (of sin)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But grieve not over them, nor distress thyself because of their plots.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They also say: "When will this promise (come to pass)? (Say) if ye are truthful."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "It may be that some of the events which ye wish to hasten on may be
 (close) in your pursuit!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But verily thy Lord is full of grace to mankind: Yet most of them are ungrateful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And verily thy Lord knoweth all that their hearts do hide.
 As well as all that they reveal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor is there aught of the unseen, in heaven or earth, but is (recorded)
 in a clear record.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily this Qur'an doth explain to the Children of Israel most of the matters
 in which they disagree.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And it certainly is a Guide and a Mercy to those who believe.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily thy Lord will decide between them by His Decree: and He is Exalted
 in Might, All-Knowing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So put thy trust in Allah: for thou art on (the path of) manifest Truth.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly thou canst not cause the dead to listen, nor canst thou cause the
 deaf to hear the call, (especially) when they turn back in retreat.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor canst thou be a guide to the blind, (to prevent them) from straying:
 only those wilt thou get to listen who believe in Our Signs, and they will
 bow in Islam.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when the Word is fulfilled against them (the unjust), we shall produce
 from the earth a beast to (face) them: He will speak to them, for that
 mankind did not believe with assurance in Our Signs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One day We shall gather together from every people a troop of those who
 reject our Signs, and they shall be kept in ranks,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Until, when they come (before the Judgment-seat), (Allah) will say: "Did
 ye reject My Signs, though ye comprehended them not in knowledge, or what
 was it ye did?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Word will be fulfilled against them, because of their wrong-doing,
 and they will be unable to speak (in plea).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
See they not that We have made the Night for them to rest in and the Day
 to give them light? Verily in this are Signs for any people that believe!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Day that the Trumpet will be sounded - then will be smitten with
 terror those who are in the heavens, and those who are on earth, except
 such as Allah will please (to exempt): and all shall come to His (Presence)
 as beings conscious of their lowliness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thou seest the mountains and thinkest them firmly fixed: but they shall
 pass away as the clouds pass away: (such is) the artistry of Allah, who
 disposes of all things in perfect order: for he is well acquainted with
 all that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If any do good, good will (accrue) to them therefrom; and they will be secure
 from terror that Day.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if any do evil, their faces will be thrown headlong into the Fire: "Do
 ye receive a reward other than that which ye have earned by your deeds?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For me, I have been commanded to serve the Lord of this city, Him Who has
 sanctified it and to Whom (belong) all things: and I am commanded to be
 of those who bow in Islam to Allah's Will,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And to rehearse the Qur'an: and if any accept guidance, they do it for the
 good of their own souls, and if any stray, say: "I am only a Warner".
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And say: "Praise be to Allah, Who will soon show you His Signs, so that
 ye shall know them"; and thy Lord is not unmindful of all that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ta.
 Sin.
 Mim.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These are Verses of the Book that makes (things) clear.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We rehearse to thee some of the story of Moses and Pharaoh in Truth, for
 people who believe.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly Pharaoh elated himself in the land and broke up its people into sections,
 depressing a small group among them: their sons he slew, but he kept alive
 their females: for he was indeed a maker of mischief.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We wished to be Gracious to those who were being depressed in the land,
 to make them leaders (in Faith) and make them heirs,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To establish a firm place for them in the land, and to show Pharaoh, Haman,
 and their hosts, at their hands, the very things against which they were
 taking precautions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So We sent this inspiration to the mother of Moses: "Suckle (thy child),
 but when thou hast fears about him, cast him into the river, but fear not
 nor grieve: for We shall restore him to thee, and We shall make him one
 of Our messengers."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then the people of Pharaoh picked him up (from the river): (It was intended)
 that (Moses) should be to them an adversary and a cause of sorrow: for
 Pharaoh and Haman and (all) their hosts were men of sin.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The wife of Pharaoh said: "(Here is) joy of the eye, for me and for thee:
 slay him not.
 It may be that he will be use to us, or we may adopt him as a son." And
 they perceived not (what they were doing)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But there came to be a void in the heart of the mother of Moses: She was
 going almost to disclose his (case), had We not strengthened her heart
 (with faith), so that she might remain a (firm) believer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And she said to the sister of (Moses), "Follow him" so she (the sister)
 watched him in the character of a stranger.
 And they knew not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And we ordained that he refused suck at first, until (His sister came up
 and) said: "Shall I point out to you the people of a house that will nourish
 and bring him up for you and be sincerely attached to him?"...
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus did We restore him to his mother, that her eye might be comforted,
 that she might not grieve, and that she might know that the promise of
 Allah is true: but most of them do not understand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When he reached full age, and was firmly established (in life), We bestowed
 on him wisdom and knowledge: for thus do We reward those who do good.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And he entered the city at a time when its people were not watching: and
 he found there two men fighting,- one of his own religion, and the other,
 of his foes.
 Now the man of his own religion appealed to him against his foe, and Moses
 struck him with his fist and made an end of him.
 He said: "This is a work of Evil (Satan): for he is an enemy that manifestly
 misleads!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He prayed: "O my Lord! I have indeed wronged my soul! Do Thou then forgive
 me!" So (Allah) forgave him: for He is the Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "O my Lord! For that Thou hast bestowed Thy Grace on me, never
 shall I be a help to those who sin!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So he saw the morning in the city, looking about, in a state of fear, when
 behold, the man who had, the day before, sought his help called aloud for
 his help (again).
 Moses said to him: "Thou art truly, it is clear, a quarrelsome fellow!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, when he decided to lay hold of the man who was an enemy to both of
 them, that man said: "O Moses! Is it thy intention to slay me as thou slewest
 a man yesterday? Thy intention is none other than to become a powerful
 violent man in the land, and not to be one who sets things right!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And there came a man, running, from the furthest end of the City.
 He said: "O Moses! the Chiefs are taking counsel together about thee, to
 slay thee: so get thee away, for I do give thee sincere advice."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He therefore got away therefrom, looking about, in a state of fear.
 He prayed "O my Lord! save me from people given to wrong-doing."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, when he turned his face towards (the land of) Madyan, he said: "I
 do hope that my Lord will show me the smooth and straight Path."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when he arrived at the watering (place) in Madyan, he found there a
 group of men watering (their flocks), and besides them he found two women
 who were keeping back (their flocks).
 He said: "What is the matter with you?" They said: "We cannot water (our
 flocks) until the shepherds take back (their flocks): And our father is
 a very old man."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So he watered (their flocks) for them; then he turned back to the shade,
 and said:"O my Lord! truly am I in (desperate) need of any good that Thou
 dost send me!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Afterwards one of the (damsels) came (back) to him, walking bashfully.
 She said: "My father invites thee that he may reward thee for having watered
 (our flocks) for us." So when he came to him and narrated the story, he
 said: "Fear thou not: (well) hast thou escaped from unjust people."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Said one of the (damsels): "O my (dear) father! engage him on wages: truly
 the best of men for thee to employ is the (man) who is strong and trusty"....
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "I intend to wed one of these my daughters to thee, on condition
 that thou serve me for eight years; but if thou complete ten years, it
 will be (grace) from thee.
 But I intend not to place thee under a difficulty: thou wilt find me, indeed,
 if Allah wills, one of the righteous."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "Be that (the agreement) between me and thee: whichever of the
 two terms I fulfil, let there be no ill-will to me.
 Be Allah a witness to what we say."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now when Moses had fulfilled the term, and was travelling with his family,
 he perceived a fire in the direction of Mount Tur.
 He said to his family: "Tarry ye; I perceive a fire; I hope to bring you
 from there some information, or a burning firebrand, that ye may warm yourselve
s."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But when he came to the (fire), a voice was heard from the right bank of
 the valley, from a tree in hallowed ground: "O Moses! Verily I am Allah,
 the Lord of the Worlds....
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Now do thou throw thy rod!" but when he saw it moving (of its own accord)
 as if it had been a snake, he turned back in retreat, and retraced not
 his steps: O Moses!" (It was said), "Draw near, and fear not: for thou
 art of those who are secure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Move thy hand into thy bosom, and it will come forth white without stain
 (or harm), and draw thy hand close to thy side (to guard) against fear.
 Those are the two credentials from thy Lord to Pharaoh and his Chiefs:
 for truly they are a people rebellious and wicked."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "O my Lord! I have slain a man among them, and I fear lest they
 slay me.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And my brother Aaron - He is more eloquent in speech than I: so send him
 with me as a helper, to confirm (and strengthen) me: for I fear that they
 may accuse me of falsehood."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "We will certainly strengthen thy arm through thy brother, and
 invest you both with authority, so they shall not be able to touch you:
 with Our Sign shall ye triumph,- you two as well as those who follow you."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When Moses came to them with Our clear signs, they said: "This is nothing
 but sorcery faked up: never did we head the like among our fathers of old!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moses said: "My Lord knows best who it is that comes with guidance from
 Him and whose end will be best in the Hereafter: certain it is that the
 wrong-doers will not prosper."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Pharaoh said: "O Chiefs! no god do I know for you but myself: therefore,
 O Haman! light me a (kiln to bake bricks) out of clay, and build me a lofty
 palace, that I may mount up to the god of Moses: but as far as I am concerned,
 I think (Moses) is a liar!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And he was arrogant and insolent in the land, beyond reason,- He and his
 hosts: they thought that they would not have to return to Us!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So We seized him and his hosts, and We flung them into the sea: Now behold
 what was the end of those who did wrong!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And we made them (but) leaders inviting to the Fire; and on the Day of Judgment
 no help shall they find.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
in this world We made a curse to follow them and on the Day of Judgment
 they will be among the loathed (and despised).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We did reveal to Moses the Book after We had destroyed the earlier generations,
 (to give) Insight to men, and guidance and Mercy, that they might receive
 admonition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thou wast not on the Western side when We decreed the Commission to Moses,
 nor wast thou a witness (of those events).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But We raised up (new) generations, and long were the ages that passed over
 them; but thou wast not a dweller among the people of Madyan, rehearsing
 Our Signs to them; but it is We Who send messengers (with inspiration).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor wast thou at the side of (the Mountain of) Tur when we called (to Moses).
 Yet (art thou sent) as Mercy from thy Lord, to give warning to a people
 to whom no warner had come before thee: in order that they may receive
 admonition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If (We had) not (sent thee to the Quraish),- in case a calamity should seize
 them for (the deeds) that their hands have sent forth, they might say:
 "Our Lord! why didst Thou not sent us a messenger? We should then have
 followed Thy Signs and been amongst those who believe!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But (now), when the Truth has come to them from Ourselves, they say, "Why
 are not (Signs) sent to him, like those which were sent to Moses?" Do they
 not then reject (the Signs) which were formerly sent to Moses? They say:
 "Two kinds of sorcery, each assisting the other!" And they say: "For us,
 we reject all (such things)!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Then bring ye a Book from Allah, which is a better guide than either
 of them, that I may follow it! (do), if ye are truthful!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But if they hearken not to thee, know that they only follow their own lusts:
 and who is more astray than one who follow his own lusts, devoid of guidance
 from Allah? for Allah guides not people given to wrong-doing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now have We caused the Word to reach them themselves, in order that they
 may receive admonition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those to whom We sent the Book before this,- they do believe in this (revelation
):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when it is recited to them, they say: "We believe therein, for it is
 the Truth from our Lord: indeed we have been Muslims (bowing to Allah's
 Will) from before this.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Twice will they be given their reward, for that they have persevered, that
 they avert Evil with Good, and that they spend (in charity) out of what
 We have given them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when they hear vain talk, they turn away therefrom and say: "To us our
 deeds, and to you yours; peace be to you: we seek not the ignorant."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is true thou wilt not be able to guide every one, whom thou lovest; but
 Allah guides those whom He will and He knows best those who receive guidance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They say: "If we were to follow the guidance with thee, we should be snatched
 away from our land." Have We not established for them a secure sanctuary,
 to which are brought as tribute fruits of all kinds,- a provision from
 Ourselves? but most of them understand not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And how many populations We destroyed, which exulted in their life (of ease
 and plenty)! now those habitations of theirs, after them, are deserted,-
 All but a (miserable) few! and We are their heirs!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor was thy Lord the one to destroy a population until He had sent to its
 centre a messenger, rehearsing to them Our Signs; nor are We going to destroy
 a population except when its members practise iniquity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The (material) things which ye are given are but the conveniences of this
 life and the glitter thereof; but that which is with Allah is better and
 more enduring: will ye not then be wise?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Are (these two) alike?- one to whom We have made a goodly promise, and who
 is going to reach its (fulfilment), and one to whom We have given the good
 things of this life, but who, on the Day of Judgment, is to be among those
 brought up (for punishment)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That Day (Allah) will call to them, and say "Where are my 'partners'?- whom
 ye imagined (to be such)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those against whom the charge will be proved, will say: "Our Lord! These
 are the ones whom we led astray: we led them astray, as we were astray
 ourselves: we free ourselves (from them) in Thy presence: it was not us
 they worshipped."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It will be said (to them): "Call upon your 'partners' (for help)": they
 will call upon them, but they will not listen to them; and they will see
 the Penalty (before them); (how they will wish) 'if only they had been
 open to guidance!'
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That Day (Allah) will call to them, and say: "What was the answer ye gave
 to the messengers?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then the (whole) story that Day will seem obscure to them (like light to
 the blind) and they will not be able (even) to question each other.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But any that (in this life) had repented, believed, and worked righteousness,
 will have hopes to be among those who achieve salvation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thy Lord does create and choose as He pleases: no choice have they (in the
 matter): Glory to Allah! and far is He above the partners they ascribe
 (to Him)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And thy Lord knows all that their hearts conceal and all that they reveal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He is Allah: There is no god but He.
 To Him be praise, at the first and at the last: for Him is the Command,
 and to Him shall ye (all) be brought back.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: See ye? If Allah were to make the night perpetual over you to the Day
 of Judgment, what god is there other than Allah, who can give you enlightenment
? Will ye not then hearken?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: See ye? If Allah were to make the day perpetual over you to the Day
 of Judgment, what god is there other than Allah, who can give you a night
 in which ye can rest? Will ye not then see?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is out of His Mercy that He has made for you Night and Day,- that ye
 may rest therein, and that ye may seek of his Grace;- and in order that
 ye may be grateful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day that He will call on them, He will say: "Where are my 'partners'?
 whom ye imagined (to be such)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And from each people shall We draw a witness, and We shall say: "Produce
 your Proof": then shall they know that the Truth is in Allah (alone), and
 the (lies) which they invented will leave them in lurch.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Qarun was doubtless, of the people of Moses; but he acted insolently towards
 them: such were the treasures We had bestowed on him that their very keys
 would have been a burden to a body of strong men, behold, his people said
 to him: "Exult not, for Allah loveth not those who exult (in riches).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But seek, with the (wealth) which Allah has bestowed on thee, the Home
 of the Hereafter, nor forget thy portion in this world: but do thou good,
 as Allah has been good to thee, and seek not (occasions for) mischief in
 the land: for Allah loves not those who do mischief."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "This has been given to me because of a certain knowledge which
 I have." Did he not know that Allah had destroyed, before him, (whole) generatio
ns,- which were superior to him in strength and greater in the amount (of
 riches) they had collected? but the wicked are not called (immediately)
 to account for their sins.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So he went forth among his people in the (pride of his wordly) glitter.
 Said those whose aim is the Life of this World: "Oh! that we had the like
 of what Qarun has got! for he is truly a lord of mighty good fortune!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those who had been granted (true) knowledge said: "Alas for you! The
 reward of Allah (in the Hereafter) is best for those who believe and work
 righteousness: but this none shall attain, save those who steadfastly persevere
 (in good)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then We caused the earth to swallow up him and his house; and he had not
 (the least little) party to help him against Allah, nor could he defend
 himself.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who had envied his position the day before began to say on the
 morrow: "Ah! it is indeed Allah Who enlarges the provision or restricts
 it, to any of His servants He pleases! had it not been that Allah was gracious
 to us, He could have caused the earth to swallow us up! Ah! those who reject
 Allah will assuredly never prosper."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That Home of the Hereafter We shall give to those who intend not high-handedness
 or mischief on earth: and the end is (best) for the righteous.
