 noble creature, in pairs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such is the Creation of Allah: now show Me what is there that others besides
 Him have created: nay, but the Transgressors are in manifest error.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
we bestowed (in the past) Wisdom on Luqman: "Show (thy) gratitude to Allah."
 Any who is (so) grateful does so to the profit of his own soul: but if
 any is ungrateful, verily Allah is free of all wants, Worthy of all praise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, Luqman said to his son by way of instruction: "O my son! join not
 in worship (others) with Allah: for false worship is indeed the highest
 wrong-doing."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We have enjoined on man (to be good) to his parents: in travail upon
 travail did his mother bear him, and in years twain was his weaning: (hear
 the command), "Show gratitude to Me and to thy parents: to Me is (thy final)
 Goal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But if they strive to make thee join in worship with Me things of which
 thou hast no knowledge, obey them not; yet bear them company in this life
 with justice (and consideration), and follow the way of those who turn
 to me (in love): in the end the return of you all is to Me, and I will
 tell you the truth (and meaning) of all that ye did."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"O my son!" (said Luqman), "If there be (but) the weight of a mustard-seed
 and it were (hidden) in a rock, or (anywhere) in the heavens or on earth,
 Allah will bring it forth: for Allah understands the finest mysteries,
 (and) is well-acquainted (with them).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"O my son! establish regular prayer, enjoin what is just, and forbid what
 is wrong: and bear with patient constancy whatever betide thee; for this
 is firmness (of purpose) in (the conduct of) affairs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And swell not thy cheek (for pride) at men, nor walk in insolence through
 the earth; for Allah loveth not any arrogant boaster.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And be moderate in thy pace, and lower thy voice; for the harshest of sounds
 without doubt is the braying of the ass."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do ye not see that Allah has subjected to your (use) all things in the heavens
 and on earth, and has made his bounties flow to you in exceeding measure,
 (both) seen and unseen? Yet there are among men those who dispute about
 Allah, without knowledge and without guidance, and without a Book to enlighten
 them!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When they are told to follow the (Revelation) that Allah has sent down,
 they say: "Nay, we shall follow the ways that we found our fathers (following).
 "What! even if it is Satan beckoning them to the Penalty of the (Blazing)
 Fire?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whoever submits his whole self to Allah, and is a doer of good, has grasped
 indeed the most trustworthy hand-hold: and with Allah rests the End and
 Decision of (all) affairs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But if any reject Faith, let not his rejection grieve thee: to Us is their
 return, and We shall tell them the truth of their deeds: for Allah knows
 well all that is in (men's) hearts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We grant them their pleasure for a little while: in the end shall We drive
 them to a chastisement unrelenting.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If thou ask them, who it is that created the heavens and the earth.
 They will certainly say, "Allah".
 Say: "Praise be to Allah!" But most of them understand not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Allah belong all things in heaven and earth: verily Allah is He (that
 is) free of all wants, worthy of all praise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if all the trees on earth were pens and the ocean (were ink), with seven
 oceans behind it to add to its (supply), yet would not the words of Allah
 be exhausted (in the writing): for Allah is Exalted in Power, full of Wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And your creation or your resurrection is in no wise but as an individual
 soul: for Allah is He Who hears and sees (all things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou not that Allah merges Night into Day and he merges Day into Night;
 that He has subjected the sun, and the moon (to his Law), each running
 its course for a term appointed; and that Allah is well-acquainted with
 all that ye do?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That is because Allah is the (only) Reality, and because whatever else they
 invoke besides Him is Falsehood; and because Allah,- He is the Most High,
 Most Great.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou not that the ships sail through the ocean by the Grace of Allah?-
 that He may show you of His Signs? Verily in this are Signs for all who
 constantly persevere and give thanks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When a wave covers them like the canopy (of clouds), they call to Allah,
 offering Him sincere devotion.
 But when He has delivered them safely to land, there are among them those
 that halt between (right and wrong).
 But none reject Our Signs except only a perfidious ungrateful (wretch)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O mankind! do your duty to your Lord, and fear (the coming of) a Day when
 no father can avail aught for his son, nor a son avail aught for his father.
 Verily, the promise of Allah is true: let not then this present life deceive
 you, nor let the chief Deceiver deceive you about Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily the knowledge of the Hour is with Allah (alone).
 It is He Who sends down rain, and He Who knows what is in the wombs.
 Nor does any one know what it is that he will earn on the morrow: Nor does
 any one know in what land he is to die.
 Verily with Allah is full knowledge and He is acquainted (with all things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A.
 L.
 M.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(This is) the Revelation of the Book in which there is no doubt,- from the
 Lord of the Worlds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or do they say, "He has forged it"? Nay, it is the Truth from thy Lord,
 that thou mayest admonish a people to whom no warner has come before thee:
 in order that they may receive guidance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is Allah Who has created the heavens and the earth, and all between them,
 in six Days, and is firmly established on the Throne (of Authority): ye
 have none, besides Him, to protect or intercede (for you): will ye not
 then receive admonition?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He rules (all) affairs from the heavens to the earth: in the end will (all
 affairs) go up to Him, on a Day, the space whereof will be (as) a thousand
 years of your reckoning.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such is He, the Knower of all things, hidden and open, the Exalted (in power),
 the Merciful;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He Who has made everything which He has created most good: He began the
 creation of man with (nothing more than) clay,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And made his progeny from a quintessence of the nature of a fluid despised:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But He fashioned him in due proportion, and breathed into him something
 of His spirit.
 And He gave you (the faculties of) hearing and sight and feeling (and understan
ding): little thanks do ye give!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they say: "What! when we lie, hidden and lost, in the earth, shall we
 indeed be in a Creation renewed? Nay, they deny the Meeting with their
 Lord.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "The Angel of Death, put in charge of you, will (duly) take your souls:
 then shall ye be brought back to your Lord."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If only thou couldst see when the guilty ones will bend low their heads
 before their Lord, (saying:) "Our Lord! We have seen and we have heard:
 Now then send us back (to the world): we will work righteousness: for we
 do indeed (now) believe."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If We had so willed, We could certainly have brought every soul its true
 guidance: but the Word from Me will come true, "I will fill Hell with Jinns
 and men all together."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Taste ye then - for ye forgot the Meeting of this Day of yours, and We
 too will forget you - taste ye the Penalty of Eternity for your (evil)
 deeds!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Only those believe in Our Signs, who, when they are recited to them, fall
 down in prostration, and celebrate the praises of their Lord, nor are they
 (ever) puffed up with pride.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Their limbs do forsake their beds of sleep, the while they call on their
 Lord, in Fear and Hope: and they spend (in charity) out of the sustenance
 which We have bestowed on them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now no person knows what delights of the eye are kept hidden (in reserve)
 for them - as a reward for their (good) deeds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is then the man who believes no better than the man who is rebellious and
 wicked? Not equal are they.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For those who believe and do righteous deeds are Gardens as hospitable homes,
 for their (good) deeds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As to those who are rebellious and wicked, their abode will be the Fire:
 every time they wish to get away therefrom, they will be forced thereinto,
 and it will be said to them: "Taste ye the Penalty of the Fire, the which
 ye were wont to reject as false."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And indeed We will make them taste of the Penalty of this (life) prior to
 the supreme Penalty, in order that they may (repent and) return.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And who does more wrong than one to whom are recited the Signs of his Lord,
 and who then turns away therefrom? Verily from those who transgress We
 shall exact (due) Retribution.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We did indeed aforetime give the Book to Moses: be not then in doubt of
 its reaching (thee): and We made it a guide to the Children of Israel.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We appointed, from among them, leaders, giving guidance under Our command,
 so long as they persevered with patience and continued to have faith in
 Our Signs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily thy Lord will judge between them on the Day of Judgment, in the matters
 wherein they differ (among themselves)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Does it not teach them a lesson, how many generations We destroyed before
 them, in whose dwellings they (now) go to and fro? Verily in that are Signs:
 Do they not then listen?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And do they not see that We do drive rain to parched soil (bare of herbage),
 and produce therewith crops, providing food for their cattle and themselves?
 Have they not the vision?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They say: "When will this decision be, if ye are telling the truth?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "On the Day of Decision, no profit will it be to Unbelievers if they
 (then) believe! nor will they be granted a respite."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So turn away from them, and wait: they too are waiting.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O Prophet! Fear Allah, and hearken not to the Unbelievers and the Hypocrites:
 verily Allah is full of Knowledge and Wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But follow that which comes to thee by inspiration from thy Lord: for Allah
 is well acquainted with (all) that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And put thy trust in Allah, and enough is Allah as a disposer of affairs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah has not made for any man two hearts in his (one) body: nor has He
 made your wives whom ye divorce by Zihar your mothers: nor has He made
 your adopted sons your sons.
 Such is (only) your (manner of) speech by your mouths.
 But Allah tells (you) the Truth, and He shows the (right) Way.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Call them by (the names of) their fathers: that is juster in the sight of
 Allah.
 But if ye know not their father's (names, call them) your Brothers in faith,
 or your maulas.
 But there is no blame on you if ye make a mistake therein: (what counts
 is) the intention of your hearts: and Allah is Oft-Returning, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Prophet is closer to the Believers than their own selves, and his wives
 are their mothers.
 Blood-relations among each other have closer personal ties, in the Decree
 of Allah.
 Than (the Brotherhood of) Believers and Muhajirs: nevertheless do ye what
 is just to your closest friends: such is the writing in the Decree (of
 Allah).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And remember We took from the prophets their covenant: As (We did) from
 thee: from Noah, Abraham, Moses, and Jesus the son of Mary: We took from
 them a solemn covenant:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That (Allah) may question the (custodians) of Truth concerning the Truth
 they (were charged with): And He has prepared for the Unbelievers a grievous
 Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Remember the Grace of Allah, (bestowed) on you, when there
 came down on you hosts (to overwhelm you): But We sent against them a hurricane
 and forces that ye saw not: but Allah sees (clearly) all that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold! they came on you from above you and from below you, and behold,
 the eyes became dim and the hearts gaped up to the throats, and ye imagined
 various (vain) thoughts about Allah!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In that situation were the Believers tried: they were shaken as by a tremendous
 shaking.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And behold! The Hypocrites and those in whose hearts is a disease (even)
 say: "Allah and His Messenger promised us nothing but delusion!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold! A party among them said: "Ye men of Yathrib! ye cannot stand (the
 attack)! therefore go back!" And a band of them ask for leave of the Prophet,
 saying, "Truly our houses are bare and exposed," though they were not exposed
 they intended nothing but to run away.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if an entry had been effected to them from the sides of the (city),
 and they had been incited to sedition, they would certainly have brought
 it to pass, with none but a brief delay!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And yet they had already covenanted with Allah not to turn their backs,
 and a covenant with Allah must (surely) be answered for.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Running away will not profit you if ye are running away from death
 or slaughter; and even if (ye do escape), no more than a brief (respite)
 will ye be allowed to enjoy!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Who is it that can screen you from Allah if it be His wish to give
 you punishment or to give you Mercy?" Nor will they find for themselves,
 besides Allah, any protector or helper.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily Allah knows those among you who keep back (men) and those who say
 to their brethren, "Come along to us", but come not to the fight except
 for just a little while.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Covetous over you.
 Then when fear comes, thou wilt see them looking to thee, their eyes revolving,
 like (those of) one over whom hovers death: but when the fear is past,
 they will smite you with sharp tongues, covetous of goods.
 Such men have no faith, and so Allah has made their deeds of none effect:
 and that is easy for Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They think that the Confederates have not withdrawn; and if the Confederates
 should come (again), they would wish they were in the deserts (wandering)
 among the Bedouins, and seeking news about you (from a safe distance);
 and if they were in your midst, they would fight but little.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ye have indeed in the Messenger of Allah a beautiful pattern (of conduct)
 for any one whose hope is in Allah and the Final Day, and who engages much
 in the Praise of Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the Believers saw the Confederate forces, they said: "This is what
 Allah and his Messenger had promised us, and Allah and His Messenger told
 us what was true." And it only added to their faith and their zeal in obedience.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Among the Believers are men who have been true to their covenant with Allah:
 of them some have completed their vow (to the extreme), and some (still)
 wait: but they have never changed (their determination) in the least:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That Allah may reward the men of Truth for their Truth, and punish the Hypocrite
s if that be His Will, or turn to them in Mercy: for Allah is Oft-Forgiving,
 Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Allah turned back the Unbelievers for (all) their fury: no advantage
 did they gain; and enough is Allah for the believers in their fight.
 And Allah is full of Strength, able to enforce His Will.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those of the People of the Book who aided them - Allah did take them
 down from their strongholds and cast terror into their hearts.
 (So that) some ye slew, and some ye made prisoners.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He made you heirs of their lands, their houses, and their goods, and
 of a land which ye had not frequented (before).
 And Allah has power over all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O Prophet! Say to thy Consorts: "If it be that ye desire the life of this
 World, and its glitter,- then come! I will provide for your enjoyment and
 set you free in a handsome manner.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But if ye seek Allah and His Messenger, and the Home of the Hereafter, verily
 Allah has prepared for the well-doers amongst you a great reward.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O Consorts of the Prophet! If any of you were guilty of evident unseemly
 conduct, the Punishment would be doubled to her, and that is easy for Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But any of you that is devout in the service of Allah and His Messenger,
 and works righteousness,- to her shall We grant her reward twice: and We
 have prepared for her a generous Sustenance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O Consorts of the Prophet! Ye are not like any of the (other) women: if
 ye do fear (Allah), be not too complacent of speech, lest one in whose
 heart is a disease should be moved with desire: but speak ye a speech (that
 is) just.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And stay quietly in your houses, and make not a dazzling display, like that
 of the former Times of Ignorance; and establish regular Prayer, and give
 regular Charity; and obey Allah and His Messenger.
 And Allah only wishes to remove all abomination from you, ye members of
 the Family, and to make you pure and spotless.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And recite what is rehearsed to you in your homes, of the Signs of Allah
 and His Wisdom: for Allah understands the finest mysteries and is well-acquaint
ed (with them).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For Muslim men and women,- for believing men and women, for devout men and
 women, for true men and women, for men and women who are patient and constant,
 for men and women who humble themselves, for men and women who give in
 Charity, for men and women who fast (and deny themselves), for men and
 women who guard their chastity, and for men and women who engage much in
 Allah's praise,- for them has Allah prepared forgiveness and great reward.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is not fitting for a Believer, man or woman, when a matter has been decided
 by Allah and His Messenger to have any option about their decision: if
 any one disobeys Allah and His Messenger, he is indeed on a clearly wrong
 Path.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold! Thou didst say to one who had received the grace of Allah and thy
 favour: "Retain thou (in wedlock) thy wife, and fear Allah." But thou didst
 hide in thy heart that which Allah was about to make manifest: thou didst
 fear the people, but it is more fitting that thou shouldst fear Allah.
 Then when Zaid had dissolved (his marriage) with her, with the necessary
 (formality), We joined her in marriage to thee: in order that (in future)
 there may be no difficulty to the Believers in (the matter of) marriage
 with the wives of their adopted sons, when the latter have dissolved with
 the necessary (formality) (their marriage) with them.
 And Allah's command must be fulfilled.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There can be no difficulty to the Prophet in what Allah has indicated to
 him as a duty.
 It was the practice (approved) of Allah amongst those of old that have
 passed away.
 And the command of Allah is a decree determined.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It is the practice of those) who preach the Messages of Allah, and fear
 Him, and fear none but Allah.
 And enough is Allah to call (men) to account.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Muhammad is not the father of any of your men, but (he is) the Messenger
 of Allah, and the Seal of the Prophets: and Allah has full knowledge of
 all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Celebrate the praises of Allah, and do this often;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And glorify Him morning and evening.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He it is Who sends blessings on you, as do His angels, that He may bring
 you out from the depths of Darkness into Light: and He is Full of Mercy
 to the Believers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Their salutation on the Day they meet Him will be "Peace!"; and He has prepared
 for them a generous Reward.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O Prophet! Truly We have sent thee as a Witness, a Bearer of Glad Tidings,
 and Warner,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And as one who invites to Allah's (grace) by His leave, and as a lamp spreading
 light.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then give the Glad Tidings to the Believers, that they shall have from Allah
 a very great Bounty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And obey not (the behests) of the Unbelievers and the Hypocrites, and heed
 not their annoyances, but put thy Trust in Allah.
 For enough is Allah as a Disposer of affairs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! When ye marry believing women, and then divorce them before
 ye have touched them, no period of 'Iddat have ye to count in respect of
 them: so give them a present.
 And set them free in a handsome manner.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O Prophet! We have made lawful to thee thy wives to whom thou hast paid
 their dowers; and those whom thy right hand possesses out of the prisoners
 of war whom Allah has assigned to thee; and daughters of thy paternal uncles
 and aunts, and daughters of thy maternal uncles and aunts, who migrated
 (from Makka) with thee; and any believing woman who dedicates her soul
 to the Prophet if the Prophet wishes to wed her;- this only for thee, and
 not for the Believers (at large); We know what We have appointed for them
 as to their wives and the captives whom their right hands possess;- in
 order that there should be no difficulty for thee.
 And Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thou mayest defer (the turn of) any of them that thou pleasest, and thou
 mayest receive any thou pleasest: and there is no blame on thee if thou
 invite one whose (turn) thou hadst set aside.
 This were nigher to the cooling of their eyes, the prevention of their
 grief, and their satisfaction - that of all of them - with that which thou
 hast to give them: and Allah knows (all) that is in your hearts: and Allah
 is All-Knowing, Most Forbearing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is not lawful for thee (to marry more) women after this, nor to change
 them for (other) wives, even though their beauty attract thee, except any
 thy right hand should possess (as handmaidens): and Allah doth watch over
 all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Enter not the Prophet's houses,- until leave is given
 you,- for a meal, (and then) not (so early as) to wait for its preparation:
 but when ye are invited, enter; and when ye have taken your meal, disperse,
 without seeking familiar talk.
 Such (behaviour) annoys the Prophet: he is ashamed to dismiss you, but
 Allah is not ashamed (to tell you) the truth.
 And when ye ask (his ladies) for anything ye want, ask them from before
 a screen: that makes for greater purity for your hearts and for theirs.
 Nor is it right for you that ye should annoy Allah's Messenger, or that
 ye should marry his widows after him at any time.
 Truly such a thing is in Allah's sight an enormity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whether ye reveal anything or conceal it, verily Allah has full knowledge
 of all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There is no blame (on these ladies if they appear) before their fathers
 or their sons, their brothers, or their brother's sons, or their sisters'
 sons, or their women, or the (slaves) whom their right hands possess.
 And, (ladies), fear Allah; for Allah is Witness to all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah and His angels send blessings on the Prophet: O ye that believe! Send
 ye blessings on him, and salute him with all respect.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who annoy Allah and His Messenger - Allah has cursed them in this
 World and in the Hereafter, and has prepared for them a humiliating Punishment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who annoy believing men and women undeservedly, bear (on themselves)
 a calumny and a glaring sin.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O Prophet! Tell thy wives and daughters, and the believing women, that they
 should cast their outer garments over their persons (when abroad): that
 is most convenient, that they should be known (as such) and not molested.
 And Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly, if the Hypocrites, and those in whose hearts is a disease, and those
 who stir up sedition in the City, desist not, We shall certainly stir thee
 up against them: Then will they not be able to stay in it as thy neighbours
 for any length of time:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They shall have a curse on them: whenever they are found, they shall be
 seized and slain (without mercy).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Such was) the practice (approved) of Allah among those who lived aforetime:
 No change wilt thou find in the practice (approved) of Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Men ask thee concerning the Hour: Say, "The knowledge thereof is with Allah
 (alone)": and what will make thee understand?- perchance the Hour is nigh!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily Allah has cursed the Unbelievers and prepared for them a Blazing
 Fire,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To dwell therein for ever: no protector will they find, nor helper.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day that their faces will be turned upside down in the Fire, they will
 say: "Woe to us! Would that we had obeyed Allah and obeyed the Messenger!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they would say: "Our Lord! We obeyed our chiefs and our great ones,
 and they misled us as to the (right) Path.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Our Lord! Give them double Penalty and curse them with a very great Curse!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Be ye not like those who vexed and insulted Moses, but
 Allah cleared him of the (calumnies) they had uttered: and he was honourable
 in Allah's sight.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Fear Allah, and (always) say a word directed to the Right:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That He may make your conduct whole and sound and forgive you your sins:
 He that obeys Allah and His Messenger, has already attained the highest
 achievement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We did indeed offer the Trust to the Heavens and the Earth and the Mountains;
 but they refused to undertake it, being afraid thereof: but man undertook
 it;- He was indeed unjust and foolish;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(With the result) that Allah has to punish the Hypocrites, men and women,
 and the Unbelievers, men and women, and Allah turns in Mercy to the Believers,
 men and women: for Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Praise be to Allah, to Whom belong all things in the heavens and on earth:
 to Him be Praise in the Hereafter: and He is Full of Wisdom, acquainted
 with all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He knows all that goes into the earth, and all that comes out thereof; all
 that comes down from the sky and all that ascends thereto and He is the
 Most Merciful, the Oft-Forgiving.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Unbelievers say, "Never to us will come the Hour": Say, "Nay! but most
 surely, by my Lord, it will come upon you;- by Him Who knows the unseen,-
 from Whom is not hidden the least little atom in the heavens or on earth:
 Nor is there anything less than that, or greater, but is in the Record
 Perspicuous:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That He may reward those who believe and work deeds of righteousness: for
 such is Forgiveness and a Sustenance Most Generous."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those who strive against Our Signs, to frustrate them,- for such will
 be a Penalty,- a Punishment most humiliating.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those to whom knowledge has come see that the (Revelation) sent down
 to thee from thy Lord - that is the Truth, and that it guides to the Path
 of the Exalted (in might), Worthy of all praise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Unbelievers say (in ridicule): "Shall we point out to you a man that
 will tell you, when ye are all scattered to pieces in disintegration, that
 ye shall (then be raised) in a New Creation?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Has he invented a falsehood against Allah, or has a spirit (seized) him?"-
 Nay, it is those who believe not in the Hereafter, that are in (real) Penalty,
 and in farthest error.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
See they not what is before them and behind them, of the sky and the earth?
 If We wished, We could cause the earth to swallow them up, or cause a piece
 of the sky to fall upon them.
 Verily in this is a Sign for every devotee that turns to Allah (in repentance).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We bestowed Grace aforetime on David from ourselves: "O ye Mountains! Sing
 ye back the Praises of Allah with him! and ye birds (also)! And We made
 the iron soft for him;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Commanding), "Make thou coast of mail, balancing well the rings of chain
 armour, and work ye righteousness; for be sure I see (clearly) all that
 ye do."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And to Solomon (We made) the Wind (obedient): Its early morning (stride)
 was a month's (journey), and its evening (stride) was a month's (journey);
 and We made a Font of molten brass to flow for him; and there were Jinns
 that worked in front of him, by the leave of his Lord, and if any of them
 turned aside from our command, We made him taste of the Penalty of the
 Blazing Fire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They worked for him as he desired, (making) arches, images, basons as large
 as reservoirs, and (cooking) cauldrons fixed (in their places): "Work ye,
 sons of David, with thanks! but few of My servants are grateful!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, when We decreed (Solomon's) death, nothing showed them his death except
 a little worm of the earth, which kept (slowly) gnawing away at his staff:
 so when he fell down, the Jinns saw plainly that if they had known the
 unseen, they would not have tarried in the humiliating Penalty (of their
 Task).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There was, for Saba, aforetime, a Sign in their home-land - two Gardens
 to the right and to the left.
 "Eat of the Sustenance (provided) by your Lord, and be grateful to Him:
 a territory fair and happy, and a Lord Oft-Forgiving!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But they turned away (from Allah), and We sent against them the Flood (released)
 from the dams, and We converted their two garden (rows) into "gardens"
 producing bitter fruit, and tamarisks, and some few (stunted) Lote-trees.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That was the Requital We gave them because they ungratefully rejected Faith:
 and never do We give (such) requital except to such as are ungrateful rejecters.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Between them and the Cities on which We had poured our blessings, We had
 placed Cities in prominent positions, and between them We had appointed
 stages of journey in due proportion: "Travel therein, secure, by night
 and by day."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But they said: "Our Lord! Place longer distances between our journey-stages":
 but they wronged themselves (therein).
 At length We made them as a tale (that is told), and We dispersed them
 all in scattered fragments.
 Verily in this are Signs for every (soul that is) patiently constant and
 grateful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And on them did Satan prove true his idea, and they followed him, all but
 a party that believed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But he had no authority over them,- except that We might test the man who
 believes in the Hereafter from him who is in doubt concerning it: and thy
 Lord doth watch over all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Call upon other (gods) whom ye fancy, besides Allah: They have no
 power,- not the weight of an atom,- in the heavens or on earth: No (sort
 of) share have they therein, nor is any of them a helper to Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"No intercession can avail in His Presence, except for those for whom He
 has granted permission.
 So far (is this the case) that, when terror is removed from their hearts
 (at the Day of Judgment, then) will they say, 'what is it that your Lord
 commanded?' they will say, 'That which is true and just; and He is the
 Most High Most Great'."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Who gives you sustenance, from the heavens and the earth?" Say: "It
 is Allah; and certain it is that either we or ye are on right guidance
 or in manifest error!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Ye shall not be questioned as to our sins, nor shall we be questioned
 as to what ye do."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Our Lord will gather us together and will in the end decide the matter
 between us (and you) in truth and justice: and He is the one to decide,
 the One Who knows all."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Show me those whom ye have joined with Him as partners: by no means
 (can ye).
 Nay, He is Allah, the Exalted in Power, the Wise."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have not sent thee but as a universal (Messenger) to men, giving them
 glad tidings, and warning them (against sin), but most men understand not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They say: "When will this promise (come to pass) if ye are telling the truth?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "The appointment to you is for a Day, which ye cannot put back for
 an hour nor put forward."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Unbelievers say: "We shall neither believe in this scripture nor in
 (any) that (came) before it." Couldst thou but see when the wrong-doers
 will be made to stand before their Lord, throwing back the word (of blame)
 on one another! Those who had been despised will say to the arrogant ones:
 "Had it not been for you, we should certainly have been believers!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The arrogant ones will say to those who had been despised: "Was it we who
 kept you back from Guidance after it reached you? Nay, rather, it was ye
 who transgressed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who had been despised will say to the arrogant ones: "Nay! it was
 a plot (of yours) by day and by night: Behold! Ye (constantly) ordered
 us to be ungrateful to Allah and to attribute equals to Him!" They will
 declare (their) repentance when they see the Penalty: We shall put yokes
 on the necks of the Unbelievers: It would only be a requital for their
 (ill) Deeds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Never did We send a warner to a population, but the wealthy ones among them
 said: "We believe not in the (Message) with which ye have been sent."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "We have more in wealth and in sons, and we cannot be punished."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Verily my Lord enlarges and restricts the Provision to whom He pleases,
 but most men understand not."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is not your wealth nor your sons, that will bring you nearer to Us in
 degree: but only those who believe and work righteousness - these are the
 ones for whom there is a multiplied Reward for their deeds, while secure
 they (reside) in the dwellings on high!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who strive against Our Signs, to frustrate them, will be given over
 into Punishment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Verily my Lord enlarges and restricts the Sustenance to such of his
 servants as He pleases: and nothing do ye spend in the least (in His cause)
 but He replaces it: for He is the Best of those who grant Sustenance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One Day He will gather them all together, and say to the angels, "Was it
 you that these men used to worship?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say, "Glory to Thee! our (tie) is with Thee - as Protector - not
 with them.
 Nay, but they worshipped the Jinns: most of them believed in them."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So on that Day no power shall they have over each other, for profit or harm:
 and We shall say to the wrong-doers, "Taste ye the Penalty of the Fire,-
 the which ye were wont to deny!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When Our Clear Signs are rehearsed to them, they say, "This is only a man
 who wishes to hinder you from the (worship) which your fathers practised."
 And they say, "This is only a falsehood invented!" and the Unbelievers
 say of the Truth when it comes to them, "This is nothing but evident magic!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But We had not given them Books which they could study, nor sent messengers
 to them before thee as Warners.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And their predecessors rejected (the Truth); these have not received a tenth
 of what We had granted to those: yet when they rejected My messengers,
 how (terrible) was My rejection (of them)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "I do admonish you on one point: that ye do stand up before Allah,-
 (It may be) in pairs, or (it may be) singly,- and reflect (within yourselves):
 your Companion is not possessed: he is no less than a warner to you, in
 face of a terrible Penalty."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "No reward do I ask of you: it is (all) in your interest: my reward
 is only due from Allah: And He is witness to all things."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Verily my Lord doth cast the (mantle of) Truth (over His servants),-
 He that has full knowledge of (all) that is hidden."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "The Truth has arrived, and Falsehood neither creates anything new,
 nor restores anything."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "If I am astray, I only stray to the loss of my own soul: but if I
 receive guidance, it is because of the inspiration of my Lord to me: it
 is He Who hears all things, and is (ever) near."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If thou couldst but see when they will quake with terror; but then there
 will be no escape (for them), and they will be seized from a position (quite)
 near.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they will say, "We do believe (now) in the (Truth)"; but how could they
 receive (Faith) from a position (so far off,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seeing that they did reject Faith (entirely) before, and that they (continually)
 cast (slanders) on the unseen from a position far off?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And between them and their desires, is placed a barrier, as was done in
 the past with their partisans: for they were indeed in suspicious (disquieting)
 doubt.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Praise be to Allah, Who created (out of nothing) the heavens and the earth,
 Who made the angels, messengers with wings,- two, or three, or four (pairs):
 He adds to Creation as He pleases: for Allah has power over all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What Allah out of his Mercy doth bestow on mankind there is none can withhold:
 what He doth withhold, there is none can grant, apart from Him: and He
 is the Exalted in Power, full of Wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O men! Call to mind the grace of Allah unto you! is there a creator, other
 than Allah, to give you sustenance from heaven or earth? There is no god
 but He: how then are ye deluded away from the Truth?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if they reject thee, so were messengers rejected before thee: to Allah
 back for decision all affairs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O men! Certainly the promise of Allah is true.
 Let not then this present life deceive you, nor let the Chief Deceiver
 deceive you about Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily Satan is an enemy to you: so treat him as an enemy.
 He only invites his adherents, that they may become Companions of the Blazing
 Fire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For those who reject Allah, is a terrible Penalty: but for those who believe
 and work righteous deeds, is Forgiveness, and a magnificent Reward.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is he, then, to whom the evil of his conduct is made alluring, so that he
 looks upon it as good, (equal to one who is rightly guided)? For Allah
 leaves to stray whom He wills, and guides whom He wills.
 So let not thy soul go out in (vainly) sighing after them: for Allah knows
 well all that they do!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is Allah Who sends forth the Winds, so that they raise up the Clouds,
 and We drive them to a land that is dead, and revive the earth therewith
 after its death: even so (will be) the Resurrection!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If any do seek for glory and power,- to Allah belong all glory and power.
 To Him mount up (all) Words of Purity: It is He Who exalts each Deed of
 Righteousness.
 Those that lay Plots of Evil,- for them is a Penalty terrible; and the
 plotting of such will be void (of result).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Allah did create you from dust; then from a sperm-drop; then He made
 you in pairs.
 And no female conceives, or lays down (her load), but with His knowledge.
 Nor is a man long-lived granted length of days, nor is a part cut off from
 his life, but is in a Decree (ordained).
 All this is easy to Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor are the two bodies of flowing water alike,- the one palatable, sweet,
 and pleasant to drink, and the other, salt and bitter.
 Yet from each (kind of water) do ye eat flesh fresh and tender, and ye
 extract ornaments to wear; and thou seest the ships therein that plough
 the waves, that ye may seek (thus) of the Bounty of Allah that ye may be
 grateful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He merges Night into Day, and he merges Day into Night, and he has subjected
 the sun and the moon (to his Law): each one runs its course for a term
 appointed.
 Such is Allah your Lord: to Him belongs all Dominion.
 And those whom ye invoke besides Him have not the least power.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If ye invoke them, they will not listen to your call, and if they were to
 listen, they cannot answer your (prayer).
 On the Day of Judgment they will reject your "Partnership".
 and none, (O man!) can tell thee (the Truth) like the One Who is acquainted
 with all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye men! It is ye that have need of Allah: but Allah is the One Free of
 all wants, worthy of all praise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If He so pleased, He could blot you out and bring in a New Creation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor is that (at all) difficult for Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor can a bearer of burdens bear another's burdens if one heavily laden
 should call another to (bear) his load.
 Not the least portion of it can be carried (by the other).
 Even though he be nearly related.
 Thou canst but admonish such as fear their Lord unseen and establish regular
 Prayer.
 And whoever purifies himself does so for the benefit of his own soul; and
 the destination (of all) is to Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The blind and the seeing are not alike;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor are the depths of Darkness and the Light;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor are the (chilly) shade and the (genial) heat of the sun:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor are alike those that are living and those that are dead.
 Allah can make any that He wills to hear; but thou canst not make those
 to hear who are (buried) in graves.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thou art no other than a warner.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily We have sent thee in truth, as a bearer of glad tidings, and as a
 warner: and there never was a people, without a warner having lived among
 them (in the past).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if they reject thee, so did their predecessors, to whom came their messenger
s with Clear Signs, Books of dark prophecies, and the Book of Enlightenment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the end did I punish those who rejected Faith: and how (terrible) was
 My rejection (of them)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou not that Allah sends down rain from the sky? With it We then
 bring out produce of various colours.
 And in the mountains are tracts white and red, of various shades of colour,
 and black intense in hue.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And so amongst men and crawling creatures and cattle, are they of various
 colours.
 Those truly fear Allah, among His Servants, who have knowledge: for Allah
 is Exalted in Might, Oft-Forgiving.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who rehearse the Book of Allah, establish regular Prayer, and spend
 (in Charity) out of what We have provided for them, secretly and openly,
 hope for a commerce that will never fail:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For He will pay them their meed, nay, He will give them (even) more out
 of His Bounty: for He is Oft-Forgiving, Most Ready to appreciate (service).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That which We have revealed to thee of the Book is the Truth,- confirming
 what was (revealed) before it: for Allah is assuredly- with respect to
 His Servants - well acquainted and Fully Observant.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then We have given the Book for inheritance to such of Our Servants as We
 have chosen: but there are among them some who wrong their own souls; some
 who follow a middle course; and some who are, by Allah's leave, foremost
 in good deeds; that is the highest Grace.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Gardens of Eternity will they enter: therein will they be adorned with bracelets
 of gold and pearls; and their garments there will be of silk.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they will say: "Praise be to Allah, Who has removed from us (all) sorrow:
 for our Lord is indeed Oft-Forgiving Ready to appreciate (service):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Who has, out of His Bounty, settled us in a Home that will last: no toil
 nor sense of weariness shall touch us therein."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those who reject (Allah) - for them will be the Fire of Hell: No term
 shall be determined for them, so they should die, nor shall its Penalty
 be lightened for them.
 Thus do We reward every ungrateful one!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therein will they cry aloud (for assistance): "Our Lord! Bring us out: we
 shall work righteousness, not the (deeds) we used to do!" - "Did We not
 give you long enough life so that he that would should receive admonition?
 and (moreover) the warner came to you.
 So taste ye (the fruits of your deeds): for the wrong-doers there is no
 helper."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily Allah knows (all) the hidden things of the heavens and the earth:
 verily He has full knowledge of all that is in (men's) hearts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He it is That has made you inheritors in the earth: if, then, any do reject
 (Allah), their rejection (works) against themselves: their rejection but
 adds to the odium for the Unbelievers in the sight of their Lord: their
 rejection but adds to (their own) undoing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Have ye seen (these) 'Partners' of yours whom ye call upon besides
 Allah? Show Me what it is they have created in the (wide) earth.
 Or have they a share in the heavens? Or have We given them a Book from
 which they (can derive) clear (evidence)?- Nay, the wrong-doers promise
 each other nothing but delusions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is Allah Who sustains the heavens and the earth, lest they cease (to
 function): and if they should fail, there is none - not one - can sustain
 them thereafter: Verily He is Most Forbearing, Oft-Forgiving.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They swore their strongest oaths by Allah that if a warner came to them,
 they would follow his guidance better than any (other) of the Peoples:
 But when a warner came to them, it has only increased their flight (from
 righteousness),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On account of their arrogance in the land and their plotting of Evil, but
 the plotting of Evil will hem in only the authors thereof.
 Now are they but looking for the way the ancients were dealt with? But
 no change wilt thou find in Allah's way (of dealing): no turning off wilt
 thou find in Allah's way (of dealing).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they not travel through the earth, and see what was the End of those
 before them,- though they were superior to them in strength? Nor is Allah
 to be frustrated by anything whatever in the heavens or on earth: for He
 is All-Knowing.
 All-Powerful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If Allah were to punish men according to what they deserve.
 He would not leave on the back of the (earth) a single living creature:
 but He gives them respite for a stated Term: when their Term expires, verily
 Allah has in His sight all His Servants.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ya Sin.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Qur'an, full of Wisdom,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thou art indeed one of the messengers,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On a Straight Way.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is a Revelation sent down by (Him), the Exalted in Might, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In order that thou mayest admonish a people, whose fathers had received
 no admonition, and who therefore remain heedless (of the Signs of Allah).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Word is proved true against the greater part of them: for they do not
 believe.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have put yokes round their necks right up to their chins, so that their
 heads are forced up (and they cannot see).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We have put a bar in front of them and a bar behind them, and further,
 We have covered them up; so that they cannot see.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The same is it to them whether thou admonish them or thou do not admonish
 them: they will not believe.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thou canst but admonish such a one as follows the Message and fears the
 (Lord) Most Gracious, unseen: give such a one, therefore, good tidings,
 of Forgiveness and a Reward most generous.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily We shall give life to the dead, and We record that which they send
 before and that which they leave behind, and of all things have We taken
 account in a clear Book (of evidence).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Set forth to them, by way of a parable, the (story of) the Companions of
 the City.
 Behold!, there came messengers to it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When We (first) sent to them two messengers, they rejected them: But We
 strengthened them with a third: they said, "Truly, we have been sent on
 a mission to you."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The (people) said: "Ye are only men like ourselves; and (Allah) Most Gracious
 sends no sort of revelation: ye do nothing but lie."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "Our Lord doth know that we have been sent on a mission to you:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And our duty is only to proclaim the clear Message."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The (people) said: "for us, we augur an evil omen from you: if ye desist
 not, we will certainly stone you.
 And a grievous punishment indeed will be inflicted on you by us."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "Your evil omens are with yourselves: (deem ye this an evil omen).
 If ye are admonished? Nay, but ye are a people transgressing all bounds!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then there came running, from the farthest part of the City, a man, saying,
 "O my people! Obey the messengers:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Obey those who ask no reward of you (for themselves), and who have themselves
 received Guidance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"It would not be reasonable in me if I did not serve Him Who created me,
 and to Whom ye shall (all) be brought back.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Shall I take (other) gods besides Him? If (Allah) Most Gracious should
 intend some adversity for me, of no use whatever will be their intercession
 for me, nor can they deliver me.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"I would indeed, if I were to do so, be in manifest Error.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"For me, I have faith in the Lord of you (all): listen, then, to me!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It was said: "Enter thou the Garden." He said: "Ah me! Would that my People
 knew (what I know)!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"For that my Lord has granted me Forgiveness and has enrolled me among those
 held in honour!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We sent not down against his People, after him, any hosts from heaven,
 nor was it needful for Us so to do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It was no more than a single mighty Blast, and behold! they were (like ashes)
 quenched and silent.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ah! Alas for (My) Servants! There comes not a messenger to them but they
 mock him!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
See they not how many generations before them we destroyed? Not to them
 will they return:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But each one of them all - will be brought before Us (for judgment).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A Sign for them is the earth that is dead: We do give it life, and produce
 grain therefrom, of which ye do eat.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We produce therein orchard with date-palms and vines, and We cause springs
 to gush forth therein:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That they may enjoy the fruits of this (artistry): It was not their hands
 that made this: will they not then give thanks?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Glory to Allah, Who created in pairs all things that the earth produces,
 as well as their own (human) kind and (other) things of which they have
 no knowledge.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And a Sign for them is the Night: We withdraw therefrom the Day, and behold
 they are plunged in darkness;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the sun runs his course for a period determined for him: that is the
 decree of (Him), the Exalted in Might, the All-Knowing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Moon,- We have measured for her mansions (to traverse) till she
 returns like the old (and withered) lower part of a date-stalk.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is not permitted to the Sun to catch up the Moon, nor can the Night outstrip
 the Day: Each (just) swims along in (its own) orbit (according to Law).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And a Sign for them is that We bore their race (through the Flood) in the
 loaded Ark;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We have created for them similar (vessels) on which they ride.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If it were Our Will, We could drown them: then would there be no helper
 (to hear their cry), nor could they be delivered,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Except by way of Mercy from Us, and by way of (world) convenience (to serve
 them) for a time.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When they are told, "Fear ye that which is before you and that which will
 be after you, in order that ye may receive Mercy," (they turn back).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Not a Sign comes to them from among the Signs of their Lord, but they turn
 away therefrom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when they are told, "Spend ye of (the bounties) with which Allah has
 provided you," the Unbelievers say to those who believe: "Shall we then
 feed those whom, if Allah had so willed, He would have fed, (Himself)?-
 Ye are in nothing but manifest error."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Further, they say, "When will this promise (come to pass), if what ye say
 is true?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will not (have to) wait for aught but a single Blast: it will seize
 them while they are yet disputing among themselves!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No (chance) will they then have, by will, to dispose (of their affairs),
 nor to return to their own people!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The trumpet shall be sounded, when behold! from the sepulchres (men) will
 rush forth to their Lord!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say: "Ah! Woe unto us! Who hath raised us up from our beds of
 repose?"...
 (A voice will say:) "This is what (Allah) Most Gracious had promised.
 And true was the word of the messengers!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It will be no more than a single Blast, when lo! they will all be brought
 up before Us!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, on that Day, not a soul will be wronged in the least, and ye shall
 but be repaid the meeds of your past Deeds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily the Companions of the Garden shall that Day have joy in all that
 they do;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They and their associates will be in groves of (cool) shade, reclining on
 Thrones (of dignity);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Every) fruit (enjoyment) will be there for them; they shall have whatever
 they call for;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Peace!" - a word (of salutation) from a Lord Most Merciful!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And O ye in sin! Get ye apart this Day!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Did I not enjoin on you, O ye Children of Adam, that ye should not worship
 Satan; for that he was to you an enemy avowed?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And that ye should worship Me, (for that) this was the Straight Way?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But he did lead astray a great multitude of you.
 Did ye not, then, understand?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"This is the Hell of which ye were (repeatedly) warned!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Embrace ye the (fire) this Day, for that ye (persistently) rejected (Truth)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That Day shall We set a seal on their mouths.
 But their hands will speak to us, and their feet bear witness, to all that
 they did.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If it had been our Will, We could surely have blotted out their eyes; then
 should they have run about groping for the Path, but how could they have
 seen?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if it had been Our Will, We could have transformed them (to remain)
 in their places; then should they have been unable to move about, nor could
 they have returned (after error).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If We grant long life to any, We cause him to be reversed in nature: Will
 they not then understand?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have not instructed the (Prophet) in Poetry, nor is it meet for him:
 this is no less than a Message and a Qur'an making things clear:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That it may give admonition to any (who are) alive, and that the charge
 may be proved against those who reject (Truth).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
See they not that it is We Who have created for them - among the things
 which Our hands have fashioned - cattle, which are under their dominion?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And that We have subjected them to their (use)? of them some do carry them
 and some they eat:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they have (other) profits from them (besides), and they get (milk) to
 drink.
 Will they not then be grateful?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yet they take (for worship) gods other than Allah, (hoping) that they might
 be helped!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They have not the power to help them: but they will be brought up (before
 Our Judgment-seat) as a troop (to be condemned).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let not their speech, then, grieve thee.
 Verily We know what they hide as well as what they disclose.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Doth not man see that it is We Who created him from sperm? yet behold! he
 (stands forth) as an open adversary!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And he makes comparisons for Us, and forgets his own (origin and) Creation:
 He says, "Who can give life to (dry) bones and decomposed ones (at that)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say, "He will give them life Who created them for the first time! for He
 is Well-versed in every kind of creation!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"The same Who produces for you fire out of the green tree, when behold!
 ye kindle therewith (your own fires)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Is not He Who created the heavens and the earth able to create the like
 thereof?" - Yea, indeed! for He is the Creator Supreme, of skill and knowledge
 (infinite)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily, when He intends a thing, His Command is, "be", and it is!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So glory to Him in Whose hands is the dominion of all things: and to Him
 will ye be all brought back.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By those who range themselves in ranks,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And so are strong in repelling (evil),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And thus proclaim the Message (of Allah)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily, verily, your Allah is one!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Lord of the heavens and of the earth and all between them, and Lord of every
 point at the rising of the sun!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have indeed decked the lower heaven with beauty (in) the stars,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(For beauty) and for guard against all obstinate rebellious evil spirits,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(So) they should not strain their ears in the direction of the Exalted Assembly
 but be cast away from every side,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Repulsed, for they are under a perpetual penalty,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Except such as snatch away something by stealth, and they are pursued by
 a flaming fire, of piercing brightness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Just ask their opinion: are they the more difficult to create, or the (other)
 beings We have created? Them have We created out of a sticky clay!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly dost thou marvel, while they ridicule,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And, when they are admonished, pay no heed,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And, when they see a Sign, turn it to mockery,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And say, "This is nothing but evident sorcery!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"What! when we die, and become dust and bones, shall we (then) be raised
 up (again)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And also our fathers of old?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say thou: "Yea, and ye shall then be humiliated (on account of your evil)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then it will be a single (compelling) cry; and behold, they will begin to
 see!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say, "Ah! Woe to us! This is the Day of Judgment!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(A voice will say,) "This is the Day of Sorting Out, whose truth ye (once)
 denied!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Bring ye up", it shall be said, "The wrong-doers and their wives, and the
 things they worshipped-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Besides Allah, and lead them to the Way to the (Fierce) Fire!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But stop them, for they must be asked:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"'What is the matter with you that ye help not each other?'"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, but that day they shall submit (to Judgment);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they will turn to one another, and question one another.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say: "It was ye who used to come to us from the right hand (of
 power and authority)!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will reply: "Nay, ye yourselves had no Faith!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Nor had we any authority over you.
 Nay, it was ye who were a people in obstinate rebellion!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"So now has been proved true, against us, the word of our Lord that we shall
 indeed (have to) taste (the punishment of our sins).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"We led you astray: for truly we were ourselves astray."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly, that Day, they will (all) share in the Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily that is how We shall deal with Sinners.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For they, when they were told that there is no god except Allah, would puff
 themselves up with Pride,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And say: "What! shall we give up our gods for the sake of a Poet possessed?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay! he has come with the (very) Truth, and he confirms (the Message of)
 the messengers (before him).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ye shall indeed taste of the Grievous Penalty;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But it will be no more than the retribution of (the Evil) that ye have wrought;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But the sincere (and devoted) Servants of Allah,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For them is a Sustenance determined,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Fruits (Delights); and they (shall enjoy) honour and dignity,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In Gardens of Felicity,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Facing each other on Thrones (of Dignity):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Round will be passed to them a Cup from a clear-flowing fountain,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Crystal-white, of a taste delicious to those who drink (thereof),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Free from headiness; nor will they suffer intoxication therefrom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And besides them will be chaste women, restraining their glances, with big
 eyes (of wonder and beauty).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As if they were (delicate) eggs closely guarded.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then they will turn to one another and question one another.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One of them will start the talk and say: "I had an intimate companion (on
 the earth),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Who used to say, 'what! art thou amongst those who bear witness to the
 Truth (of the Message)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"'When we die and become dust and bones, shall we indeed receive rewards
 and punishments?'"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(A voice) said: "Would ye like to look down?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He looked down and saw him in the midst of the Fire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "By Allah! thou wast little short of bringing me to perdition!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Had it not been for the Grace of my Lord, I should certainly have been
 among those brought (there)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Is it (the case) that we shall not die,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Except our first death, and that we shall not be punished?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily this is the supreme achievement!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For the like of this let all strive, who wish to strive.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is that the better entertainment or the Tree of Zaqqum?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For We have truly made it (as) a trial for the wrong-doers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For it is a tree that springs out of the bottom of Hell-Fire:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The shoots of its fruit-stalks are like the heads of devils:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly they will eat thereof and fill their bellies therewith.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then on top of that they will be given a mixture made of boiling water.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then shall their return be to the (Blazing) Fire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly they found their fathers on the wrong Path;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So they (too) were rushed down on their footsteps!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And truly before them, many of the ancients went astray;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But We sent aforetime, among them, (messengers) to admonish them;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then see what was the end of those who were admonished (but heeded not),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Except the sincere (and devoted) Servants of Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(In the days of old), Noah cried to Us, and We are the best to hear prayer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We delivered him and his people from the Great Calamity,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And made his progeny to endure (on this earth);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We left (this blessing) for him among generations to come in later times:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Peace and salutation to Noah among the nations!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus indeed do we reward those who do right.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For he was one of our believing Servants.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then the rest we overwhelmed in the Flood.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily among those who followed his Way was Abraham.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold! he approached his Lord with a sound heart.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold! he said to his father and to his people, "What is that which ye
 worship?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Is it a falsehood- gods other than Allah- that ye desire?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Then what is your idea about the Lord of the worlds?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then did he cast a glance at the Stars.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And he said, "I am indeed sick (at heart)!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So they turned away from him, and departed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then did he turn to their gods and said, "will ye not eat (of the offerings
 before you)?...
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"What is the matter with you that ye speak not (intelligently)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then did he turn upon them, striking (them) with the right hand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then came (the worshippers) with hurried steps, and faced (him).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "Worship ye that which ye have (yourselves) carved?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But Allah has created you and your handwork!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said, "Build him a furnace, and throw him into the blazing fire!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(This failing), they then sought a stratagem against him, but We made them
 the ones most humiliated!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "I will go to my Lord! He will surely guide me!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"O my Lord! Grant me a righteous (son)!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So We gave him the good news of a boy ready to suffer and forbear.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, when (the son) reached (the age of) (serious) work with him, he said:
 "O my son! I see in vision that I offer thee in sacrifice: Now see what
 is thy view!" (The son) said: "O my father! Do as thou art commanded: thou
 will find me, if Allah so wills one practising Patience and Constancy!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So when they had both submitted their wills (to Allah), and he had laid
 him prostrate on his forehead (for sacrifice),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We called out to him "O Abraham!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Thou hast already fulfilled the vision!" - thus indeed do We reward those
 who do right.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For this was obviously a trial-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We ransomed him with a momentous sacrifice:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We left (this blessing) for him among generations (to come) in later
 times:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Peace and salutation to Abraham!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus indeed do We reward those who do right.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For he was one of our believing Servants.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We gave him the good news of Isaac - a prophet,- one of the Righteous.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We blessed him and Isaac: but of their progeny are (some) that do right,
 and (some) that obviously do wrong, to their own souls.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Again (of old) We bestowed Our favour on Moses and Aaron,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We delivered them and their people from (their) Great Calamity;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We helped them, so they overcame (their troubles);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We gave them the Book which helps to make things clear;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We guided them to the Straight Way.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We left (this blessing) for them among generations (to come) in later
 times:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Peace and salutation to Moses and Aaron!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus indeed do We reward those who do right.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For they were two of our believing Servants.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So also was Elias among those sent (by Us).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, he said to his people, "Will ye not fear (Allah)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Will ye call upon Baal and forsake the Best of Creators,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Allah, your Lord and Cherisher and the Lord and Cherisher of your fathers
 of old?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But they rejected him, and they will certainly be called up (for punishment),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Except the sincere and devoted Servants of Allah (among them).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We left (this blessing) for him among generations (to come) in later
 times:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Peace and salutation to such as Elias!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus indeed do We reward those who do right.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For he was one of our believing Servants.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So also was Lut among those sent (by Us).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, We delivered him and his adherents, all
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Except an old woman who was among those who lagged behind:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then We destroyed the rest.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily, ye pass by their (sites), by day-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And by night: will ye not understand?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So also was Jonah among those sent (by Us).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When he ran away (like a slave from captivity) to the ship (fully) laden,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He (agreed to) cast lots, and he was condemned:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then the big Fish did swallow him, and he had done acts worthy of blame.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Had it not been that he (repented and) glorified Allah,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He would certainly have remained inside the Fish till the Day of Resurrection.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But We cast him forth on the naked shore in a state of sickness,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We caused to grow, over him, a spreading plant of the gourd kind.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We sent him (on a mission) to a hundred thousand (men) or more.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they believed; so We permitted them to enjoy (their life) for a while.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now ask them their opinion: Is it that thy Lord has (only) daughters, and
 they have sons?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or that We created the angels female, and they are witnesses (thereto)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is it not that they say, from their own invention,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Allah has begotten children"? but they are liars!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Did He (then) choose daughters rather than sons?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What is the matter with you? How judge ye?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Will ye not then receive admonition?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or have ye an authority manifest?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then bring ye your Book (of authority) if ye be truthful!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they have invented a blood-relationship between Him and the Jinns: but
 the Jinns know (quite well) that they have indeed to appear (before his
 Judgment-Seat)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Glory to Allah! (He is free) from the things they ascribe (to Him)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Not (so do) the Servants of Allah, sincere and devoted.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For, verily, neither ye nor those ye worship-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Can lead (any) into temptation concerning Allah,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Except such as are (themselves) going to the blazing Fire!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Those ranged in ranks say): "Not one of us but has a place appointed;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And we are verily ranged in ranks (for service);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And we are verily those who declare (Allah's) glory!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And there were those who said,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"If only we had had before us a Message from those of old,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"We should certainly have been Servants of Allah, sincere (and devoted)!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But (now that the Qur'an has come), they reject it: But soon will they know!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Already has Our Word been passed before (this) to our Servants sent (by
 Us),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That they would certainly be assisted,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And that Our forces,- they surely must conquer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So turn thou away from them for a little while,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And watch them (how they fare), and they soon shall see (how thou farest)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they wish (indeed) to hurry on our Punishment?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But when it descends into the open space before them, evil will be the morning
 for those who were warned (and heeded not)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So turn thou away from them for a little while,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And watch (how they fare) and they soon shall see (how thou farest)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Glory to thy Lord, the Lord of Honour and Power! (He is free) from what
 they ascribe (to Him)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Peace on the messengers!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Praise to Allah, the Lord and Cherisher of the Worlds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Sad: By the Qur'an, Full of Admonition: (This is the Truth).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But the Unbelievers (are steeped) in self-glory and Separatism.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
How many generations before them did We destroy? In the end they cried (for
 mercy)- when there was no longer time for being saved!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So they wonder that a Warner has come to them from among themselves! and
 the Unbelievers say, "This is a sorcerer telling lies!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Has he made the gods (all) into one Allah? Truly this is a wonderful thing!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the leader among them go away (impatiently), (saying), "Walk ye away,
 and remain constant to your gods! For this is truly a thing designed (against
 you)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"We never heard (the like) of this among the people of these latter days:
 this is nothing but a made-up tale!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"What! has the Message been sent to him - (Of all persons) among us?"...
 but they are in doubt concerning My (Own) Message! Nay, they have not yet
 tasted My Punishment!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or have they the treasures of the mercy of thy Lord,- the Exalted in Power,
 the Grantor of Bounties without measure?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or have they the dominion of the heavens and the earth and all between?
 If so, let them mount up with the ropes and means (to reach that end)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But there - will be put to flight even a host of confederates.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Before them (were many who) rejected messengers,- the people of Noah, and
 'Ad, and Pharaoh, the Lord of Stakes,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Thamud, and the people of Lut, and the Companions of the Wood; - such
 were the Confederates.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Not one (of them) but rejected the messengers, but My punishment came justly
 and inevitably (on them).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These (today) only wait for a single mighty Blast, which (when it comes)
 will brook no delay.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They say: "Our Lord! hasten to us our sentence (even) before the Day of
 Account!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Have patience at what they say, and remember our servant David, the man
 of strength: for he ever turned (to Allah).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It was We that made the hills declare, in unison with him, Our Praises,
 at eventide and at break of day,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the birds gathered (in assemblies): all with him did turn (to Allah).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We strengthened his kingdom, and gave him wisdom and sound judgment in speech
 and decision.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Has the Story of the Disputants reached thee? Behold, they climbed over
 the wall of the private chamber;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When they entered the presence of David, and he was terrified of them, they
 said: "Fear not: we are two disputants, one of whom has wronged the other:
 Decide now between us with truth, and treat us not with injustice, but
 guide us to the even Path..
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"This man is my brother: He has nine and ninety ewes, and I have (but) one:
 Yet he says, 'commit her to my care,' and is (moreover) harsh to me in
 speech."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(David) said: "He has undoubtedly wronged thee in demanding thy (single)
 ewe to be added to his (flock of) ewes: truly many are the partners (in
 business) who wrong each other: Not so do those who believe and work deeds
 of righteousness, and how few are they?"...
 and David gathered that We had tried him: he asked forgiveness of his Lord,
 fell down, bowing (in prostration), and turned (to Allah in repentance).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So We forgave him this (lapse): he enjoyed, indeed, a Near Approach to Us,
 and a beautiful place of (Final) Return.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O David! We did indeed make thee a vicegerent on earth: so judge thou between
 men in truth (and justice): Nor follow thou the lusts (of thy heart), for
 they will mislead thee from the Path of Allah: for those who wander astray
 from the Path of Allah, is a Penalty Grievous, for that they forget the
 Day of Account.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Not without purpose did We create heaven and earth and all between! that
 were the thought of Unbelievers! but woe to the Unbelievers because of
 the Fire (of Hell)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Shall We treat those who believe and work deeds of righteousness, the same
 as those who do mischief on earth? Shall We treat those who guard against
 evil, the same as those who turn aside from the right?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Here is) a Book which We have sent down unto thee, full of blessings, that
 they may mediate on its Signs, and that men of understanding may receive
 admonition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To David We gave Solomon (for a son),- How excellent in Our service! Ever
 did he turn (to Us)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, there were brought before him, at eventide coursers of the highest
 breeding, and swift of foot;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And he said, "Truly do I love the love of good, with a view to the glory
 of my Lord,"- until (the sun) was hidden in the veil (of night):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Bring them back to me." then began he to pass his hand over (their) legs
 and their necks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We did try Solomon: We placed on his throne a body (without life); but
 he did turn (to Us in true devotion):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said, "O my Lord! Forgive me, and grant me a kingdom which, (it may be),
 suits not another after me: for Thou art the Grantor of Bounties (without
 measure).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then We subjected the wind to his power, to flow gently to his order, Whithersoe
ver he willed,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As also the evil ones, (including) every kind of builder and diver,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As also others bound together in fetters.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Such are Our Bounties: whether thou bestow them (on others) or withhold
 them, no account will be asked."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And he enjoyed, indeed, a Near Approach to Us, and a beautiful Place of
 (Final) Return.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Commemorate Our Servant Job.
 Behold he cried to his Lord: "The Evil One has afflicted me with distress
 and suffering!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(The command was given:) "Strike with thy foot: here is (water) wherein
 to wash, cool and refreshing, and (water) to drink."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We gave him (back) his people, and doubled their number,- as a Grace
 from Ourselves, and a thing for commemoration, for all who have Understanding.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And take in thy hand a little grass, and strike therewith: and break not
 (thy oath)." Truly We found him full of patience and constancy.
 How excellent in Our service! ever did he turn (to Us)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And commemorate Our Servants Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, possessors of Power
 and Vision.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily We did choose them for a special (purpose)- proclaiming the Message
 of the Hereafter.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They were, in Our sight, truly, of the company of the Elect and the Good.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And commemorate Isma'il, Elisha, and Zul-Kifl: Each of them was of the Company
 of the Good.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is a Message (of admonition): and verily, for the righteous, is a beautiful
 Place of (Final) Return,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Gardens of Eternity, whose doors will (ever) be open to them;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therein will they recline (at ease): Therein can they call (at pleasure)
 for fruit in abundance, and (delicious) drink;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And beside them will be chaste women restraining their glances, (companions)
 of equal age.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such is the Promise made, to you for the Day of Account!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly such will be Our Bounty (to you); it will never fail;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yea, such! but - for the wrong-doers will be an evil place of (Final) Return!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Hell!- they will burn therein, - an evil bed (indeed, to lie on)!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yea, such! - then shall they taste it,- a boiling fluid, and a fluid dark,
 murky, intensely cold!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And other Penalties of a similar kind, to match them!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Here is a troop rushing headlong with you! No welcome for them! truly, they
 shall burn in the Fire!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(The followers shall cry to the misleaders:) "Nay, ye (too)! No welcome
 for you! It is ye who have brought this upon us! Now evil is (this) place
 to stay in!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say: "Our Lord! whoever brought this upon us,- Add to him a double
 Penalty in the Fire!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they will say: "What has happened to us that we see not men whom we
 used to number among the bad ones?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Did we treat them (as such) in ridicule, or have (our) eyes failed to perceive
 them?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly that is just and fitting,- the mutual recriminations of the People
 of the Fire!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Truly am I a Warner: no god is there but the one Allah, Supreme and
 Irresistible,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"The Lord of the heavens and the earth, and all between,- Exalted in Might,
 able to enforce His Will, forgiving again and again."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "That is a Message Supreme (above all),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"From which ye do turn away!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"No knowledge have I of the Chiefs on high, when they discuss (matters)
 among themselves.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
'Only this has been revealed to me: that I am to give warning plainly and
 publicly."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, thy Lord said to the angels: "I am about to create man from clay:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"When I have fashioned him (in due proportion) and breathed into him of
 My spirit, fall ye down in obeisance unto him."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So the angels prostrated themselves, all of them together:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Not so Iblis: he was haughty, and became one of those who reject Faith.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah) said: "O Iblis! What prevents thee from prostrating thyself to one
 whom I have created with my hands? Art thou haughty? Or art thou one of
 the high (and mighty) ones?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Iblis) said: "I am better than he: thou createdst me from fire, and him
 thou createdst from clay."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah) said: "Then get thee out from here: for thou art rejected, accursed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And My curse shall be on thee till the Day of Judgment."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Iblis) said: "O my Lord! Give me then respite till the Day the (dead) are
 raised."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah) said: "Respite then is granted thee-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Till the Day of the Time Appointed."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Iblis) said: "Then, by Thy power, I will put them all in the wrong,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Except Thy Servants amongst them, sincere and purified (by Thy Grace)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah) said: "Then it is just and fitting- and I say what is just and fitting-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"That I will certainly fill Hell with thee and those that follow thee,-
 every one."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "No reward do I ask of you for this (Qur'an), nor am I a pretender.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"This is no less than a Message to (all) the Worlds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And ye shall certainly know the truth of it (all) after a while."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The revelation of this Book is from Allah, the Exalted in Power, full of
 Wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily it is We Who have revealed the Book to thee in Truth: so serve Allah,
 offering Him sincere devotion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is it not to Allah that sincere devotion is due? But those who take for
 protectors other than Allah (say): "We only serve them in order that they
 may bring us nearer to Allah." Truly Allah will judge between them in that
 wherein they differ.
 But Allah guides not such as are false and ungrateful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Had Allah wished to take to Himself a son, He could have chosen whom He
 pleased out of those whom He doth create: but Glory be to Him! (He is above
 such things.) He is Allah, the One, the Irresistible.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He created the heavens and the earth in true (proportions): He makes the
 Night overlap the Day, and the Day overlap the Night: He has subjected
 the sun and the moon (to His law): Each one follows a course for a time
 appointed.
 Is not He the Exalted in Power - He Who forgives again and again?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He created you (all) from a single person: then created, of like nature,
 his mate; and he sent down for you eight head of cattle in pairs: He makes
 you, in the wombs of your mothers, in stages, one after another, in three
 veils of darkness.
 such is Allah, your Lord and Cherisher: to Him belongs (all) dominion.
 There is no god but He: then how are ye turned away (from your true Centre)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If ye reject (Allah), Truly Allah hath no need of you; but He liketh not
 ingratitude from His servants: if ye are grateful, He is pleased with you.
 No bearer of burdens can bear the burden of another.
 In the end, to your Lord is your Return, when He will tell you the truth
 of all that ye did (in this life).
 for He knoweth well all that is in (men's) hearts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When some trouble toucheth man, he crieth unto his Lord, turning to Him
 in repentance: but when He bestoweth a favour upon him as from Himself,
 (man) doth forget what he cried and prayed for before, and he doth set
 up rivals unto Allah, thus misleading others from Allah's Path.
 Say, "Enjoy thy blasphemy for a little while: verily thou art (one) of
 the Companions of the Fire!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is one who worships devoutly during the hour of the night prostrating himself
 or standing (in adoration), who takes heed of the Hereafter, and who places
 his hope in the Mercy of his Lord - (like one who does not)? Say: "Are
 those equal, those who know and those who do not know? It is those who
 are endued with understanding that receive admonition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "O ye my servants who believe! Fear your Lord, good is (the reward)
 for those who do good in this world.
 Spacious is Allah's earth! those who patiently persevere will truly receive
 a reward without measure!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Verily, I am commanded to serve Allah with sincere devotion;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And I am commanded to be the first of those who bow to Allah in Islam."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "I would, if I disobeyed my Lord, indeed have fear of the Penalty of
 a Mighty Day."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "It is Allah I serve, with my sincere (and exclusive) devotion:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Serve ye what ye will besides him." Say: "Truly, those in loss are those
 who lose their own souls and their People on the Day of Judgment: Ah! that
 is indeed the (real and) evident Loss!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They shall have Layers of Fire above them, and Layers (of Fire) below them:
 with this doth Allah warn off his servants: "O My Servants! then fear ye
 Me!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who eschew Evil,- and fall not into its worship,- and turn to Allah
 (in repentance),- for them is Good News: so announce the Good News to My
 Servants,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who listen to the Word, and follow the best (meaning) in it: those
 are the ones whom Allah has guided, and those are the ones endued with
 understanding.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is, then, one against whom the decree of Punishment is justly due (equal
 to one who eschews Evil)? Wouldst thou, then, deliver one (who is) in the
 Fire?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But it is for those who fear their Lord.
 That lofty mansions, one above another, have been built: beneath them flow
 rivers (of delight): (such is) the Promise of Allah: never doth Allah fail
 in (His) promise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou not that Allah sends down rain from the sky, and leads it through
 springs in the earth? Then He causes to grow, therewith, produce of various
 colours: then it withers; thou wilt see it grow yellow; then He makes it
 dry up and crumble away.
 Truly, in this, is a Message of remembrance to men of understanding.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is one whose heart Allah has opened to Islam, so that he has received Enlightenm
ent from Allah, (no better than one hard-hearted)? Woe to those whose hearts
 are hardened against celebrating the praises of Allah! they are manifestly
 wandering (in error)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah has revealed (from time to time) the most beautiful Message in the
 form of a Book, consistent with itself, (yet) repeating (its teaching in
 various aspects): the skins of those who fear their Lord tremble thereat;
 then their skins and their hearts do soften to the celebration of Allah's
 praises.
 Such is the guidance of Allah: He guides therewith whom He pleases, but
 such as Allah leaves to stray, can have none to guide.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is, then, one who has to fear the brunt of the Penalty on the Day of Judgment
 (and receive it) on his face, (like one guarded therefrom)? It will be
 said to the wrong-doers: "Taste ye (the fruits of) what ye earned!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those before them (also) rejected (revelation), and so the Punishment came
 to them from directions they did not perceive.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So Allah gave them a taste of humiliation in the present life, but greater
 is the punishment of the Hereafter, if they only knew!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have put forth for men, in this Qur'an every kind of Parable, in order
 that they may receive admonition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It is) a Qur'an in Arabic, without any crookedness (therein): in order
 that they may guard against Evil.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah puts forth a Parable a man belonging to many partners at variance
 with each other, and a man belonging entirely to one master: are those
 two equal in comparison? Praise be to Allah! but most of them have no knowledge.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly thou wilt die (one day), and truly they (too) will die (one day).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the end will ye (all), on the Day of Judgment, settle your disputes in
 the presence of your Lord.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who, then, doth more wrong than one who utters a lie concerning Allah, and
 rejects the Truth when it comes to him; is there not in Hell an abode for
 blasphemers?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And he who brings the Truth and he who confirms (and supports) it - such
 are the men who do right.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They shall have all that they wish for, in the presence of their Lord: such
 is the reward of those who do good:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So that Allah will turn off from them (even) the worst in their deeds and
 give them their reward according to the best of what they have done.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is not Allah enough for his Servant? But they try to frighten thee with
 other (gods) besides Him! for such as Allah leaves to stray, there can
 be no guide.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And such as Allah doth guide there can be none to lead astray.
 Is not Allah Exalted in Power, (Able to enforce His Will), Lord of Retribution?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If indeed thou ask them who it is that created the heavens and the earth,
 they would be sure to say, "Allah".
 Say: "See ye then? the things that ye invoke besides Allah,- can they,
 if Allah wills some Penalty for me, remove His Penalty?- Or if He wills
 some Grace for me, can they keep back his Grace?" Say: "Sufficient is Allah
 for me! In Him trust those who put their trust."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "O my People! Do whatever ye can: I will do (my part): but soon will
 ye know-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Who it is to whom comes a Penalty of ignominy, and on whom descends a Penalty
 that abides."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily We have revealed the Book to thee in Truth, for (instructing) mankind.
 He, then, that receives guidance benefits his own soul: but he that strays
 injures his own soul.
 Nor art thou set over them to dispose of their affairs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is Allah that takes the souls (of men) at death; and those that die not
 (He takes) during their sleep: those on whom He has passed the decree of
 death, He keeps back (from returning to life), but the rest He sends (to
 their bodies) for a term appointed verily in this are Signs for those who
 reflect.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What! Do they take for intercessors others besides Allah? Say: "Even if
 they have no power whatever and no intelligence?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "To Allah belongs exclusively (the right to grant) intercession: to
 Him belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth: In the End, it is
 to Him that ye shall be brought back."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When Allah, the One and Only, is mentioned, the hearts of those who believe
 not in the Hereafter are filled with disgust and horror; but when (gods)
 other than He are mentioned, behold, they are filled with joy!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "O Allah! Creator of the heavens and the earth! Knower of all that
 is hidden and open! it is Thou that wilt judge between Thy Servants in
 those matters about which they have differed."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Even if the wrong-doers had all that there is on earth, and as much more,
 (in vain) would they offer it for ransom from the pain of the Penalty on
 the Day of Judgment: but something will confront them from Allah, which
 they could never have counted upon!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For the evils of their Deeds will confront them, and they will be (completely)
 encircled by that which they used to mock at!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now, when trouble touches man, he cries to Us: But when We bestow a favour
 upon him as from Ourselves, he says, "This has been given to me because
 of a certain knowledge (I have)!" Nay, but this is but a trial, but most
 of them understand not!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus did the (generations) before them say! But all that they did was of
 no profit to them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, the evil results of their Deeds overtook them.
 And the wrong-doers of this (generation)- the evil results of their Deeds
 will soon overtake them (too), and they will never be able to frustrate
 (Our Plan)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Know they not that Allah enlarges the provision or restricts it, for any
 He pleases? Verily, in this are Signs for those who believe!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "O my Servants who have transgressed against their souls! Despair not
 of the Mercy of Allah: for Allah forgives all sins: for He is Oft-Forgiving,
 Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Turn ye to our Lord (in repentance) and bow to His (Will), before the Penalty
 comes on you: after that ye shall not be helped.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And follow the best of (the courses) revealed to you from your Lord, before
 the Penalty comes on you - of a sudden while ye perceive not!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Lest the soul should (then) say: 'Ah! Woe is me!- In that I neglected (my
 duty) towards Allah, and was but among those who mocked!'-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Or (lest) it should say: 'If only Allah had guided me, I should certainly
 have been among the righteous!'-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Or (lest) it should say when it (actually) sees the penalty: 'If only I
 had another chance, I should certainly be among those who do good!'
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"(The reply will be:) 'Nay, but there came to thee my Signs, and thou didst
 reject them: thou wast Haughty, and became one of those who reject faith!'"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On the Day of Judgment wilt thou see those who told lies against Allah;-
 their faces will be turned black; Is there not in Hell an abode for the
 Haughty?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But Allah will deliver the righteous to their place of salvation: no evil
 shall touch them, nor shall they grieve.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah is the Creator of all things, and He is the Guardian and Disposer
 of all affairs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Him belong the keys of the heavens and the earth: and those who reject
 the Signs of Allah,- it is they who will be in loss.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Is it some one other than Allah that ye order me to worship, O ye
 ignorant ones?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But it has already been revealed to thee,- as it was to those before thee,-
 "If thou wert to join (gods with Allah), truly fruitless will be thy work
 (in life), and thou wilt surely be in the ranks of those who lose (all
 spiritual good)".
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, but worship Allah, and be of those who give thanks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No just estimate have they made of Allah, such as is due to Him: On the
 Day of Judgment the whole of the earth will be but His handful, and the
 heavens will be rolled up in His right hand: Glory to Him! High is He above
 the Partners they attribute to Him!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Trumpet will (just) be sounded, when all that are in the heavens and
 on earth will swoon, except such as it will please Allah (to exempt).
 Then will a second one be sounded, when, behold, they will be standing
 and looking on!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Earth will shine with the Glory of its Lord: the Record (of Deeds)
 will be placed (open); the prophets and the witnesses will be brought forward
 and a just decision pronounced between them; and they will not be wronged
 (in the least).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And to every soul will be paid in full (the fruit) of its Deeds; and (Allah)
 knoweth best all that they do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Unbelievers will be led to Hell in crowd: until, when they arrive, there,
 its gates will be opened.
 And its keepers will say, "Did not messengers come to you from among yourselves
, rehearsing to you the Signs of your Lord, and warning you of the Meeting
 of This Day of yours?" The answer will be: "True: but the Decree of Punishment
 has been proved true against the Unbelievers!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(To them) will be said: "Enter ye the gates of Hell, to dwell therein: and
 evil is (this) Abode of the Arrogant!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who feared their Lord will be led to the Garden in crowds: until
 behold, they arrive there; its gates will be opened; and its keepers will
 say: "Peace be upon you! well have ye done! enter ye here, to dwell therein."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say: "Praise be to Allah, Who has truly fulfilled His Promise
 to us, and has given us (this) land in heritage: We can dwell in the Garden
 as we will: how excellent a reward for those who work (righteousness)!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And thou wilt see the angels surrounding the Throne (Divine) on all sides,
 singing Glory and Praise to their Lord.
 The Decision between them (at Judgment) will be in (perfect) justice, and
 the cry (on all sides) will be, "Praise be to Allah, the Lord of the Worlds!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ha Mim
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The revelation of this Book is from Allah, Exalted in Power, Full of Knowledge,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who forgiveth sin, accepteth repentance, is strict in punishment, and hath
 a long reach (in all things).
 there is no god but He: to Him is the final goal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
None can dispute about the Signs of Allah but the Unbelievers.
 Let not, then, their strutting about through the land deceive thee!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But (there were people) before them, who denied (the Signs),- the People
 of Noah, and the Confederates (of Evil) after them; and every People plotted
 against their prophet, to seize him, and disputed by means of vanities,
 therewith to condemn the Truth; but it was I that seized them! and how
 (terrible) was My Requital!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus was the Decree of thy Lord proved true against the Unbelievers; that
 truly they are Companions of the Fire!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who sustain the Throne (of Allah) and those around it Sing Glory and
 Praise to their Lord; believe in Him; and implore Forgiveness for those
 who believe: "Our Lord! Thy Reach is over all things, in Mercy and Knowledge.
 Forgive, then, those who turn in Repentance, and follow Thy Path; and preserve
 them from the Penalty of the Blazing Fire!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And grant, our Lord! that they enter the Gardens of Eternity, which Thou
 hast promised to them, and to the righteous among their fathers, their
 wives, and their posterity! For Thou art (He), the Exalted in Might, Full
 of Wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And preserve them from (all) ills; and any whom Thou dost preserve from
 ills that Day,- on them wilt Thou have bestowed Mercy indeed: and that
 will be truly (for them) the highest Achievement".
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Unbelievers will be addressed: "Greater was the aversion of Allah to
 you than (is) your aversion to yourselves, seeing that ye were called to
 the Faith and ye used to refuse."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say: "Our Lord! twice hast Thou made us without life, and twice
 hast Thou given us Life! Now have we recognised our sins: Is there any
 way out (of this)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(The answer will be:) "This is because, when Allah was invoked as the Only
 (object of worship), ye did reject Faith, but when partners were joined
 to Him, ye believed! the Command is with Allah, Most High, Most Great!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He it is Who showeth you his Signs, and sendeth down sustenance for you
 from the sky: but only those receive admonition who turn (to Allah).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Call ye, then, upon Allah with sincere devotion to Him, even though the
 Unbelievers may detest it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Raised high above ranks (or degrees), (He is) the Lord of the Throne (of
 Authority): by His Command doth He send the Spirit (of inspiration) to
 any of His servants he pleases, that it may warn (men) of the Day of Mutual
 Meeting,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day whereon they will (all) come forth: not a single thing concerning
 them is hidden from Allah.
 Whose will be the dominion that Day?" That of Allah, the One the Irresistible!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That Day will every soul be requited for what it earned; no injustice will
 there be that Day, for Allah is Swift in taking account.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Warn them of the Day that is (ever) drawing near, when the hearts will (come)
 right up to the throats to choke (them); No intimate friend nor intercessor
 will the wrong-doers have, who could be listened to.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah) knows of (the tricks) that deceive with the eyes, and all that the
 hearts (of men) conceal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Allah will judge with (justice and) Truth: but those whom (men) invoke
 besides Him, will not (be in a position) to judge at all.
 Verily it is Allah (alone) Who hears and sees (all things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they not travel through the earth and see what was the End of those before
 them? They were even superior to them in strength, and in the traces (they
 have left) in the land: but Allah did call them to account for their sins,
 and none had they to defend them against Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That was because there came to them their messengers with Clear (Signs),
 but they rejected them: So Allah called them to account: for He is Full
 of Strength, Strict in Punishment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Of old We sent Moses, with Our Signs and an authority manifest,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Pharaoh, Haman, and Qarun; but they called (him)" a sorcerer telling
 lies!"...
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now, when he came to them in Truth, from Us, they said, "Slay the sons of
 those who believe with him, and keep alive their females," but the plots
 of Unbelievers (end) in nothing but errors (and delusions)!...
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Said Pharaoh: "Leave me to slay Moses; and let him call on his Lord! What
 I fear is lest he should change your religion, or lest he should cause
 mischief to appear in the land!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moses said: "I have indeed called upon my Lord and your Lord (for protection)
 from every arrogant one who believes not in the Day of Account!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A believer, a man from among the people of Pharaoh, who had concealed his
 faith, said: "Will ye slay a man because he says, 'My Lord is Allah'?-
 when he has indeed come to you with Clear (Signs) from your Lord? and if
 he be a liar, on him is (the sin of) his lie: but, if he is telling the
 Truth, then will fall on you something of the (calamity) of which he warns
 you: Truly Allah guides not one who transgresses and lies!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"O my People! Yours is the dominion this day: Ye have the upper hand in
 the land: but who will help us from the Punishment of Allah, should it
 befall us?" Pharaoh said: "I but point out to you that which I see (myself);
 Nor do I guide you but to the Path of Right!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then said the man who believed: "O my people! Truly I do fear for you something
 like the Day (of disaster) of the Confederates (in sin)!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Something like the fate of the People of Noah, the 'Ad, and the Thamud,
 and those who came after them: but Allah never wishes injustice to his
 Servants.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And O my people! I fear for you a Day when there will be Mutual calling
 (and wailing),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"A Day when ye shall turn your backs and flee: No defender shall ye have
 from Allah: Any whom Allah leaves to stray, there is none to guide...
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And to you there came Joseph in times gone by, with Clear Signs, but ye
 ceased not to doubt of the (Mission) for which he had come: At length,
 when he died, ye said: 'No messenger will Allah send after him.' thus doth
 Allah leave to stray such as transgress and live in doubt,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"(Such) as dispute about the Signs of Allah, without any authority that
 hath reached them, grievous and odious (is such conduct) in the sight of
 Allah and of the Believers.
 Thus doth Allah, seal up every heart - of arrogant and obstinate Transgressors."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Pharaoh said: "O Haman! Build me a lofty palace, that I may attain the ways
 and means-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"The ways and means of (reaching) the heavens, and that I may mount up to
 the god of Moses: But as far as I am concerned, I think (Moses) is a liar!"
 Thus was made alluring, in Pharaoh's eyes, the evil of his deeds, and he
 was hindered from the Path; and the plot of Pharaoh led to nothing but
 perdition (for him).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The man who believed said further: "O my people! Follow me: I will lead
 you to the Path of Right.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"O my people! This life of the present is nothing but (temporary) convenience:
 It is the Hereafter that is the Home that will last.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"He that works evil will not be requited but by the like thereof: and he
 that works a righteous deed - whether man or woman - and is a Believer-
 such will enter the Garden (of Bliss): Therein will they have abundance
 without measure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And O my people! How (strange) it is for me to call you to Salvation while
 ye call me to the Fire!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Ye do call upon me to blaspheme against Allah, and to join with Him partners
 of whom I have no knowledge; and I call you to the Exalted in Power, Who
 forgives again and again!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Without doubt ye do call me to one who is not fit to be called to, whether
 in this world, or in the Hereafter; our return will be to Allah; and the
 Transgressors will be Companions of the Fire!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Soon will ye remember what I say to you (now), My (own) affair I commit
 to Allah: for Allah (ever) watches over His Servants."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then Allah saved him from (every) ill that they plotted (against him), but
 the burnt of the Penalty encompassed on all sides the People of Pharaoh.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In front of the Fire will they be brought, morning and evening: And (the
 sentence will be) on the Day that Judgment will be established: "Cast ye
 the People of Pharaoh into the severest Penalty!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, they will dispute with each other in the Fire! The weak ones (who
 followed) will say to those who had been arrogant, "We but followed you:
 Can ye then take (on yourselves) from us some share of the Fire?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who had been arrogant will say: "We are all in this (Fire)! Truly,
 Allah has judged between (his) Servants!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those in the Fire will say to the Keepers of Hell: "Pray to your Lord to
 lighten us the Penalty for a day (at least)!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say: "Did there not come to you your messengers with Clear Signs?"
 They will say, "Yes".
 They will reply, "Then pray (as ye like)! But the prayer of those without
 Faith is nothing but (futile wandering) in (mazes of) error!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We will, without doubt, help our messengers and those who believe, (both)
 in this world's life and on the Day when the Witnesses will stand forth,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day when no profit will it be to Wrong-doers to present their excuses,
 but they will (only) have the Curse and the Home of Misery.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We did aforetime give Moses the (Book of) Guidance, and We gave the book
 in inheritance to the Children of Israel,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A Guide and a Message to men of Understanding.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Patiently, then, persevere: for the Promise of Allah is true: and ask forgivenes
s for thy fault, and celebrate the Praises of thy Lord in the evening and
 in the morning.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who dispute about the signs of Allah without any authority bestowed
 on them,- there is nothing in their breasts but (the quest of) greatness,
 which they shall never attain to: seek refuge, then, in Allah: It is He
 Who hears and sees (all things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Assuredly the creation of the heavens and the earth is a greater (matter)
 than the creation of men: Yet most men understand not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Not equal are the blind and those who (clearly) see: Nor are (equal) those
 who believe and work deeds of righteousness, and those who do evil.
 Little do ye learn by admonition!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Hour will certainly come: Therein is no doubt: Yet most men believe
 not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And your Lord says: "Call on Me; I will answer your (Prayer): but those
 who are too arrogant to serve Me will surely find themselves in Hell -
 in humiliation!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is Allah Who has made the Night for you, that ye may rest therein, and
 the days as that which helps (you) to see.
 Verily Allah is full of Grace and Bounty to men: yet most men give no thanks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such is Allah, your Lord, the Creator of all things, there is no god but
 He: Then how ye are deluded away from the Truth!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus are deluded those who are wont to reject the Signs of Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is Allah Who has made for you the earth as a resting place, and the sky
 as a canopy, and has given you shape- and made your shapes beautiful,-
 and has provided for you Sustenance, of things pure and good;- such is
 Allah your Lord.
 So Glory to Allah, the Lord of the Worlds!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He is the Living (One): There is no god but He: Call upon Him, giving Him
 sincere devotion.
 Praise be to Allah, Lord of the Worlds!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "I have been forbidden to invoke those whom ye invoke besides Allah,-
 seeing that the Clear Signs have come to me from my Lord; and I have been
 commanded to bow (in Islam) to the Lord of the Worlds."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who has created you from dust then from a sperm-drop, then from
 a leech-like clot; then does he get you out (into the light) as a child:
 then lets you (grow and) reach your age of full strength; then lets you
 become old,- though of you there are some who die before;- and lets you
 reach a Term appointed; in order that ye may learn wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who gives Life and Death; and when He decides upon an affair, He
 says to it, "Be", and it is.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou not those that dispute concerning the Signs of Allah? How are
 they turned away (from Reality)?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who reject the Book and the (revelations) with which We sent our messenger
s: but soon shall they know,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the yokes (shall be) round their necks, and the chains; they shall
 be dragged along-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the boiling fetid fluid: then in the Fire shall they be burned;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then shall it be said to them: "Where are the (deities) to which ye gave
 part-worship-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"In derogation of Allah?" They will reply: "They have left us in the lurch:
 Nay, we invoked not, of old, anything (that had real existence)." Thus does
 Allah leave the Unbelievers to stray.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"That was because ye were wont to rejoice on the earth in things other than
 the Truth, and that ye were wont to be insolent.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Enter ye the gates of Hell, to dwell therein: and evil is (this) abode
 of the arrogant!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So persevere in patience; for the Promise of Allah is true: and whether
 We show thee (in this life) some part of what We promise them,- or We take
 thy soul (to Our Mercy) (before that),-(in any case) it is to Us that they
 shall (all) return.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We did aforetime send messengers before thee: of them there are some whose
 story We have related to thee, and some whose story We have not related
 to thee.
 It was not (possible) for any messenger to bring a sign except by the leave
 of Allah: but when the Command of Allah issued, the matter was decided
 in truth and justice, and there perished, there and then those who stood
 on Falsehoods.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is Allah Who made cattle for you, that ye may use some for riding and
 some for food;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And there are (other) advantages in them for you (besides); that ye may
 through them attain to any need (there may be) in your hearts; and on them
 and on ships ye are carried.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He shows you (always) His Signs: then which of the Signs of Allah will
 ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they not travel through the earth and see what was the End of those before
 them? They were more numerous than these and superior in strength and in
 the traces (they have left) in the land: Yet all that they accomplished
 was of no profit to them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For when their messengers came to them with Clear Signs, they exulted in
 such knowledge (and skill) as they had; but that very (Wrath) at which
 they were wont to scoff hemmed them in.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But when they saw Our Punishment, they said: "We believe in Allah,- the
 one Allah - and we reject the partners we used to join with Him."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But their professing the Faith when they (actually) saw Our Punishment was
 not going to profit them.
 (Such has been) Allah's Way of dealing with His Servants (from the most
 ancient times).
 And even thus did the Rejecters of Allah perish (utterly)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ha Mim:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A Revelation from (Allah), Most Gracious, Most Merciful;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A Book, whereof the verses are explained in detail;- a Qur'an in Arabic,
 for people who understand;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Giving good news and admonition: yet most of them turn away, and so they
 hear not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They say: "Our hearts are under veils, (concealed) from that to which thou
 dost invite us, and in our ears in a deafness, and between us and thee
 is a screen: so do thou (what thou wilt); for us, we shall do (what we
 will!)"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say thou: "I am but a man like you: It is revealed to me by Inspiration,
 that your Allah is one Allah: so stand true to Him, and ask for His Forgiveness.
" And woe to those who join gods with Allah,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who practise not regular Charity, and who even deny the Hereafter.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For those who believe and work deeds of righteousness is a reward that will
 never fail.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: Is it that ye deny Him Who created the earth in two Days? And do ye
 join equals with Him? He is the Lord of (all) the Worlds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He set on the (earth), mountains standing firm, high above it, and bestowed
 blessings on the earth, and measure therein all things to give them nourishment
 in due proportion, in four Days, in accordance with (the needs of) those
 who seek (Sustenance).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Moreover He comprehended in His design the sky, and it had been (as) smoke:
 He said to it and to the earth: "Come ye together, willingly or unwillingly."
 They said: "We do come (together), in willing obedience."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So He completed them as seven firmaments in two Days, and He assigned to
 each heaven its duty and command.
 And We adorned the lower heaven with lights, and (provided it) with guard.
 Such is the Decree of (Him) the Exalted in Might, Full of Knowledge.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But if they turn away, say thou: "I have warned you of a stunning Punishment
 (as of thunder and lightning) like that which (overtook) the 'Ad and the
 Thamud!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, the messengers came to them, from before them and behind them, (preachin
g): "Serve none but Allah." They said, "If our Lord had so pleased, He would
 certainly have sent down angels (to preach).
 Now we reject your mission (altogether)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now the 'Ad behaved arrogantly through the land, against (all) truth and
 reason, and said: "Who is superior to us in strength?" What! did they not
 see that Allah, Who created them, was superior to them in strength? But
 they continued to reject Our Signs!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So We sent against them a furious Wind through days of disaster, that We
 might give them a taste of a Penalty of humiliation in this life; but the
 Penalty of a Hereafter will be more humiliating still: and they will find
 no help.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As to the Thamud, We gave them Guidance, but they preferred blindness (of
 heart) to Guidance: so the stunning Punishment of humiliation seized them,
 because of what they had earned.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But We delivered those who believed and practised righteousness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On the Day that the enemies of Allah will be gathered together to the Fire,
 they will be marched in ranks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At length, when they reach the (Fire), their hearing, their sight, and their
 skins will bear witness against them, as to (all) their deeds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say to their skins: "Why bear ye witness against us?" They will
 say: "Allah hath given us speech,- (He) Who giveth speech to everything:
 He created you for the first time, and unto Him were ye to return.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Ye did not seek to hide yourselves, lest your hearing, your sight, and
 your skins should bear witness against you! But ye did think that Allah
 knew not many of the things that ye used to do!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But this thought of yours which ye did entertain concerning your Lord,
 hath brought you to destruction, and (now) have ye become of those utterly
 lost!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If, then, they have patience, the Fire will be a home for them! and if they
 beg to be received into favour, into favour will they not (then) be received.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We have destined for them intimate companions (of like nature), who
 made alluring to them what was before them and behind them; and the sentence
 among the previous generations of Jinns and men, who have passed away,
 is proved against them; for they are utterly lost.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Unbelievers say: "Listen not to this Qur'an, but talk at random in the
 midst of its (reading), that ye may gain the upper hand!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But We will certainly give the Unbelievers a taste of a severe Penalty,
 and We will requite them for the worst of their deeds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such is the requital of the enemies of Allah,- the Fire: therein will be
 for them the Eternal Home: a (fit) requital, for that they were wont to
 reject Our Signs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Unbelievers will say: "Our Lord! Show us those, among Jinns and
 men, who misled us: We shall crush them beneath our feet, so that they
 become the vilest (before all)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the case of those who say, "Our Lord is Allah", and, further, stand straight
 and steadfast, the angels descend on them (from time to time): "Fear ye
 not!" (they suggest), "Nor grieve! but receive the Glad Tidings of the
 Garden (of Bliss), the which ye were promised!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"We are your protectors in this life and in the Hereafter: therein shall
 ye have all that your souls shall desire; therein shall ye have all that
 ye ask for!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"A hospitable gift from one Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who is better in speech than one who calls (men) to Allah, works righteousness,
 and says, "I am of those who bow in Islam"?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor can goodness and Evil be equal.
 Repel (Evil) with what is better: Then will he between whom and thee was
 hatred become as it were thy friend and intimate!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And no one will be granted such goodness except those who exercise patience
 and self-restraint,- none but persons of the greatest good fortune.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if (at any time) an incitement to discord is made to thee by the Evil
 One, seek refuge in Allah.
 He is the One Who hears and knows all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Among His Signs are the Night and the Day, and the Sun and the Moon.
 Do not prostrate to the sun and the moon, but prostrate to Allah, Who created
 them, if it is Him ye wish to serve.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But is the (Unbelievers) are arrogant, (no matter): for in the presence
 of thy Lord are those who celebrate His praises by night and by day.
 And they never flag (nor feel themselves above it).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And among His Signs in this: thou seest the earth barren and desolate; but
 when We send down rain to it, it is stirred to life and yields increase.
 Truly, He Who gives life to the (dead) earth can surely give life to (men)
 who are dead.
 For He has power over all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who pervert the Truth in Our Signs are not hidden from Us.
 Which is better?- he that is cast into the Fire, or he that comes safe
 through, on the Day of Judgment? Do what ye will: verily He seeth (clearly)
 all that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who reject the Message when it comes to them (are not hidden from
 Us).
 And indeed it is a Book of exalted power.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No falsehood can approach it from before or behind it: It is sent down by
 One Full of Wisdom, Worthy of all Praise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nothing is said to thee that was not said to the messengers before thee:
 that thy lord has at his Command (all) forgiveness as well as a most Grievous
 Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Had We sent this as a Qur'an (in the language) other than Arabic, they would
 have said: "Why are not its verses explained in detail? What! (a Book)
 not in Arabic and (a Messenger an Arab?" Say: "It is a Guide and a Healing
 to those who believe; and for those who believe not, there is a deafness
 in their ears, and it is blindness in their (eyes): They are (as it were)
 being called from a place far distant!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We certainly gave Moses the Book aforetime: but disputes arose therein.
 Had it not been for a Word that went forth before from thy Lord, (their
 differences) would have been settled between them: but they remained in
 suspicious disquieting doubt thereon.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whoever works righteousness benefits his own soul; whoever works evil, it
 is against his own soul: nor is thy Lord ever unjust (in the least) to
 His Servants.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Him is referred the Knowledge of the Hour (of Judgment: He knows all):
 No date-fruit comes out of its sheath, nor does a female conceive (within
 her womb) nor bring forth the Day that (Allah) will propound to them the
 (question), "Where are the partners (ye attributed to Me?" They will say,
 "We do assure thee not one of us can bear witness!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The (deities) they used to invoke aforetime will leave them in the lurch,
 and they will perceive that they have no way of escape.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Man does not weary of asking for good (things), but if ill touches him,
 he gives up all hope (and) is lost in despair.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When we give him a taste of some Mercy from Ourselves, after some adversity
 has touched him, he is sure to say, "This is due to my (merit): I think
 not that the Hour (of Judgment) will (ever) be established; but if I am
 brought back to my Lord, I have (much) good (stored) in His sight!" But
 We will show the Unbelievers the truth of all that they did, and We shall
 give them the taste of a severe Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When We bestow favours on man, he turns away, and gets himself remote on
 his side (instead of coming to Us); and when evil seizes him, (he comes)
 full of prolonged prayer!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "See ye if the (Revelation) is (really) from Allah, and yet do ye reject
 it? Who is more astray than one who is in a schism far (from any purpose)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Soon will We show them our Signs in the (furthest) regions (of the earth),
 and in their own souls, until it becomes manifest to them that this is
 the Truth.
 Is it not enough that thy Lord doth witness all things?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ah indeed! Are they in doubt concerning the Meeting with their Lord? Ah
 indeed! It is He that doth encompass all things!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ha-Mim
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
'Ain.
 Sin.
 Qaf.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus doth (He) send inspiration to thee as (He did) to those before thee,-
 Allah, Exalted in Power, Full of Wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Him belongs all that is in the heavens and on earth: and He is Most High,
 Most Great.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The heavens are almost rent asunder from above them (by Him Glory): and
 the angels celebrate the Praises of their Lord, and pray for forgiveness
 for (all) beings on earth: Behold! Verily Allah is He, the Oft-Forgiving,
 Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who take as protectors others besides Him,- Allah doth watch over
 them; and thou art not the disposer of their affairs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus have We sent by inspiration to thee an Arabic Qur'an: that thou mayest
 warn the Mother of Cities and all around her,- and warn (them) of the Day
 of Assembly, of which there is no doubt: (when) some will be in the Garden,
 and some in the Blazing Fire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If Allah had so willed, He could have made them a single people; but He
 admits whom He will to His Mercy; and the Wrong-doers will have no protector
 nor helper.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What! Have they taken (for worship) protectors besides Him? But it is Allah,-
 He is the Protector, and it is He Who gives life to the dead: It is He
 Who has power over all things,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whatever it be wherein ye differ, the decision thereof is with Allah: such
 is Allah my Lord: In Him I trust, and to Him I turn.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(He is) the Creator of the heavens and the earth: He has made for you pairs
 from among yourselves, and pairs among cattle: by this means does He multiply
 you: there is nothing whatever like unto Him, and He is the One that hears
 and sees (all things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Him belong the keys of the heavens and the earth: He enlarges and restricts.
 The Sustenance to whom He will: for He knows full well all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The same religion has He established for you as that which He enjoined on
 Noah - the which We have sent by inspiration to thee - and that which We
 enjoined on Abraham, Moses, and Jesus: Namely, that ye should remain steadfast
 in religion, and make no divisions therein: to those who worship other
 things than Allah, hard is the (way) to which thou callest them.
 Allah chooses to Himself those whom He pleases, and guides to Himself those
 who turn (to Him).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they became divided only after Knowledge reached them,- through selfish
 envy as between themselves.
 Had it not been for a Word that went forth before from thy Lord, (tending)
 to a Term appointed, the matter would have been settled between them: But
 truly those who have inherited the Book after them are in suspicious (disquieti
ng) doubt concerning it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now then, for that (reason), call (them to the Faith), and stand steadfast
 as thou art commanded, nor follow thou their vain desires; but say: "I
 believe in the Book which Allah has sent down; and I am commanded to judge
 justly between you.
 Allah is our Lord and your Lord: for us (is the responsibility for) our
 deeds, and for you for your deeds.
 There is no contention between us and you.
 Allah will bring us together, and to Him is (our) Final Goal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those who dispute concerning Allah after He has been accepted,- futile
 is their dispute in the Sight of their Lord: on them will be a Penalty
 terrible.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is Allah Who has sent down the Book in Truth, and the Balance (by which
 to weigh conduct).
 And what will make thee realise that perhaps the Hour is close at hand?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Only those wish to hasten it who believe not in it: those who believe hold
 it in awe, and know that it is the Truth.
 Behold, verily those that dispute concerning the Hour are far astray.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Gracious is Allah to His servants: He gives Sustenance to whom He pleases:
 and He has power and can carry out His Will.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To any that desires the tilth of the Hereafter, We give increase in his
 tilth, and to any that desires the tilth of this world, We grant somewhat
 thereof, but he has no share or lot in the Hereafter.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What! have they partners (in godhead), who have established for them some
 religion without the permission of Allah? Had it not been for the Decree
 of Judgment, the matter would have been decided between them (at once).
 But verily the Wrong-doers will have a grievous Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thou wilt see the Wrong-doers in fear on account of what they have earned,
 and (the burden of) that must (necessarily) fall on them.
 But those who believe and work righteous deeds will be in the luxuriant
 meads of the Gardens: they shall have, before their Lord, all that they
 wish for.
 That will indeed be the magnificent Bounty (of Allah).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That is (the Bounty) whereof Allah gives Glad Tidings to His Servants who
 believe and do righteous deeds.
 Say: "No reward do I ask of you for this except the love of those near
 of kin." And if any one earns any good, We shall give him an increase of
 good in respect thereof: for Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Ready to appreciate
 (service).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What! Do they say, "He has forged a falsehood against Allah"? But if Allah
 willed, He could seal up thy heart.
 And Allah blots out Vanity, and proves the Truth by His Words.
 For He knows well the secrets of all hearts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He is the One that accepts repentance from His Servants and forgives sins:
 and He knows all that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He listens to those who believe and do deeds of righteousness, and gives
 them increase of His Bounty: but for the Unbelievers their is a terrible
 Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If Allah were to enlarge the provision for His Servants, they would indeed
 transgress beyond all bounds through the earth; but he sends (it) down
 in due measure as He pleases.
 For He is with His Servants Well-acquainted, Watchful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He is the One that sends down rain (even) after (men) have given up all
 hope, and scatters His Mercy (far and wide).
 And He is the Protector, Worthy of all Praise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And among His Signs is the creation of the heavens and the earth, and the
 living creatures that He has scattered through them: and He has power to
 gather them together when He wills.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whatever misfortune happens to you, is because on the things your hands
 have wrought, and for many (of them) He grants forgiveness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor can ye frustrate (aught), (fleeing) through the earth; nor have ye,
 besides Allah, any one to protect or to help.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And among His Signs are the ships, smooth-running through the ocean, (tall)
 as mountains.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If it be His Will He can still the Wind: then would they become motionless
 on the back of the (ocean).
 Verily in this are Signs for everyone who patiently perseveres and is grateful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or He can cause them to perish because of the (evil) which (the men) have
 earned; but much doth He forgive.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But let those know, who dispute about Our Signs, that there is for them
 no way of escape.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whatever ye are given (here) is (but) a convenience of this life: but that
 which is with Allah is better and more lasting: (it is) for those who believe
 and put their trust in their Lord:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who avoid the greater crimes and shameful deeds, and, when they are
 angry even then forgive;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who hearken to their Lord, and establish regular Prayer; who (conduct)
 their affairs by mutual Consultation; who spend out of what We bestow on
 them for Sustenance;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who, when an oppressive wrong is inflicted on them, (are not cowed
 but) help and defend themselves.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The recompense for an injury is an injury equal thereto (in degree): but
 if a person forgives and makes reconciliation, his reward is due from Allah:
 for (Allah) loveth not those who do wrong.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But indeed if any do help and defend themselves after a wrong (done) to
 them, against such there is no cause of blame.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The blame is only against those who oppress men and wrong-doing and insolently
 transgress beyond bounds through the land, defying right and justice: for
 such there will be a penalty grievous.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But indeed if any show patience and forgive, that would truly be an exercise
 of courageous will and resolution in the conduct of affairs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For any whom Allah leaves astray, there is no protector thereafter.
 And thou wilt see the Wrong-doers, when in sight of the Penalty, Say: "Is
 there any way (to effect) a return?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And thou wilt see them brought forward to the (Penalty), in a humble frame
 of mind because of (their) disgrace, (and) looking with a stealthy glance.
 And the Believers will say: "Those are indeed in loss, who have given to
 perdition their own selves and those belonging to them on the Day of Judgment.
 Behold! Truly the Wrong-doers are in a lasting Penalty!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And no protectors have they to help them, other than Allah.
 And for any whom Allah leaves to stray, there is no way (to the Goal).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Hearken ye to your Lord, before there come a Day which there will be no
 putting back, because of (the Ordainment of) Allah! that Day there will
 be for you no place of refuge nor will there be for you any room for denial
 (of your sins)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If then they run away, We have not sent thee as a guard over them.
 Thy duty is but to convey (the Message).
 And truly, when We give man a taste of a Mercy from Ourselves, he doth
 exult thereat, but when some ill happens to him, on account of the deeds
 which his hands have sent forth, truly then is man ungrateful!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Allah belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth.
 He creates what He wills (and plans).
 He bestows (children) male or female according to His Will (and Plan),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or He bestows both males and females, and He leaves barren whom He will:
 for He is full of Knowledge and Power.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is not fitting for a man that Allah should speak to him except by inspiration
, or from behind a veil, or by the sending of a messenger to reveal, with
 Allah's permission, what Allah wills: for He is Most High, Most Wise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And thus have We, by Our Command, sent inspiration to thee: thou knewest
 not (before) what was Revelation, and what was Faith; but We have made
 the (Qur'an) a Light, wherewith We guide such of Our servants as We will;
 and verily thou dost guide (men) to the Straight Way,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Way of Allah, to Whom belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever
 is on earth.
 Behold (how) all affairs tend towards Allah!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ha-Mim
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Book that makes things clear,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have made it a Qur'an in Arabic, that ye may be able to understand (and
 learn wisdom).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And verily, it is in the Mother of the Book, in Our Presence, high (in dignity),
 full of wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Shall We then take away the Message from you and repel (you), for that ye
 are a people transgressing beyond bounds?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But how many were the prophets We sent amongst the peoples of old?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And never came there a prophet to them but they mocked him.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So We destroyed (them)- stronger in power than these;- and (thus) has passed
 on the Parable of the peoples of old.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If thou wert to question them, 'Who created the heavens and the earth?'
 They would be sure to reply, 'they were created by (Him), the Exalted in
 Power, Full of Knowledge';-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Yea, the same that) has made for you the earth (like a carpet) spread out,
 and has made for you roads (and channels) therein, in order that ye may
 find guidance (on the way);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That sends down (from time to time) rain from the sky in due measure;- and
 We raise to life therewith a land that is dead; even so will ye be raised
 (from the dead);-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That has created pairs in all things, and has made for you ships and cattle
 on which ye ride,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In order that ye may sit firm and square on their backs, and when so seated,
 ye may celebrate the (kind) favour of your Lord, and say, "Glory to Him
 Who has subjected these to our (use), for we could never have accomplished
 this (by ourselves),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And to our Lord, surely, must we turn back!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yet they attribute to some of His servants a share with Him (in his godhead)!
 truly is man a blasphemous ingrate avowed!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What! has He taken daughters out of what He himself creates, and granted
 to you sons for choice?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When news is brought to one of them of (the birth of) what he sets up as
 a likeness to (Allah) Most Gracious, his face darkens, and he is filled
 with inward grief!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is then one brought up among trinkets, and unable to give a clear account
 in a dispute (to be associated with Allah)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they make into females angels who themselves serve Allah.
 Did they witness their creation? Their evidence will be recorded, and they
 will be called to account!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
("Ah!") they say, "If it had been the will of (Allah) Most Gracious, we
 should not have worshipped such (deities)!" Of that they have no knowledge!
 they do nothing but lie!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What! have We given them a Book before this, to which they are holding fast?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay! they say: "We found our fathers following a certain religion, and we
 do guide ourselves by their footsteps."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Just in the same way, whenever We sent a Warner before thee to any people,
 the wealthy ones among them said: "We found our fathers following a certain
 religion, and we will certainly follow in their footsteps."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "What! Even if I brought you better guidance than that which ye
 found your fathers following?" They said: "For us, we deny that ye (prophets)
 are sent (on a mission at all)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So We exacted retribution from them: now see what was the end of those who
 rejected (Truth)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold! Abraham said to his father and his people: "I do indeed clear myself
 of what ye worship:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"(I worship) only Him Who made me, and He will certainly guide me."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And he left it as a Word to endure among those who came after him, that
 they may turn back (to Allah).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yea, I have given the good things of this life to these (men) and their
 fathers, until the Truth has come to them, and a messenger making things
 clear.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But when the Truth came to them, they said: "This is sorcery, and we do
 reject it."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Also, they say: "Why is not this Qur'an sent down to some leading man in
 either of the two (chief) cities?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is it they who would portion out the Mercy of thy Lord? It is We Who portion
 out between them their livelihood in the life of this world: and We raise
 some of them above others in ranks, so that some may command work from
 others.
 But the Mercy of thy Lord is better than the (wealth) which they amass.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And were it not that (all) men might become of one (evil) way of life, We
 would provide, for everyone that blasphemes against (Allah) Most Gracious,
 silver roofs for their houses and (silver) stair-ways on which to go up,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And (silver) doors to their houses, and thrones (of silver) on which they
 could recline,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And also adornments of gold.
 But all this were nothing but conveniences of the present life: The Hereafter,
 in the sight of thy Lord is for the Righteous.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If anyone withdraws himself from remembrance of (Allah) Most Gracious, We
 appoint for him an evil one, to be an intimate companion to him.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such (evil ones) really hinder them from the Path, but they think that they
 are being guided aright!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At length, when (such a one) comes to Us, he says (to his evil companion):
 "Would that between me and thee were the distance of East and West!" Ah!
 evil is the companion (indeed)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When ye have done wrong, it will avail you nothing, that Day, that ye shall
 be partners in Punishment!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Canst thou then make the deaf to hear, or give direction to the blind or
 to such as (wander) in manifest error?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Even if We take thee away, We shall be sure to exact retribution from them,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or We shall show thee that (accomplished) which We have promised them: for
 verily We shall prevail over them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So hold thou fast to the Revelation sent down to thee; verily thou art on
 a Straight Way.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The (Qur'an) is indeed the message, for thee and for thy people; and soon
 shall ye (all) be brought to account.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And question thou our messengers whom We sent before thee; did We appoint
 any deities other than (Allah) Most Gracious, to be worshipped?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We did send Moses aforetime, with Our Signs, to Pharaoh and his Chiefs:
 He said, "I am a messenger of the Lord of the Worlds."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But when he came to them with Our Signs, behold they ridiculed them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We showed them Sign after Sign, each greater than its fellow, and We seized
 them with Punishment, in order that they might turn (to Us).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they said, "O thou sorcerer! Invoke thy Lord for us according to His
 covenant with thee; for we shall truly accept guidance."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But when We removed the Penalty from them, behold, they broke their word.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Pharaoh proclaimed among his people, saying: "O my people! Does not
 the dominion of Egypt belong to me, (witness) these streams flowing underneath
 my (palace)? What! see ye not then?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Am I not better than this (Moses), who is a contemptible wretch and can
 scarcely express himself clearly?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Then why are not gold bracelets bestowed on him, or (why) come (not) with
 him angels accompanying him in procession?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus did he make fools of his people, and they obeyed him: truly were they
 a people rebellious (against Allah).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When at length they provoked Us, We exacted retribution from them, and We
 drowned them all.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We made them (a people) of the Past and an Example to later ages.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When (Jesus) the son of Mary is held up as an example, behold, thy people
 raise a clamour thereat (in ridicule)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they say, "Are our gods best, or he?" This they set forth to thee, only
 by way of disputation: yea, they are a contentious people.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He was no more than a servant: We granted Our favour to him, and We made
 him an example to the Children of Israel.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if it were Our Will, We could make angels from amongst you, succeeding
 each other on the earth.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And (Jesus) shall be a Sign (for the coming of) the Hour (of Judgment):
 therefore have no doubt about the (Hour), but follow ye Me: this is a Straight
 Way.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let not the Evil One hinder you: for he is to you an enemy avowed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When Jesus came with Clear Signs, he said: "Now have I come to you with
 Wisdom, and in order to make clear to you some of the (points) on which
 ye dispute: therefore fear Allah and obey me.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"For Allah, He is my Lord and your Lord: so worship ye Him: this is a Straight
 Way."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But sects from among themselves fell into disagreement: then woe to the
 wrong-doers, from the Penalty of a Grievous Day!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they only wait for the Hour - that it should come on them all of a sudden,
 while they perceive not?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Friends on that day will be foes, one to another,- except the Righteous.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
My devotees! no fear shall be on you that Day, nor shall ye grieve,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Being) those who have believed in Our Signs and bowed (their wills to Ours)
 in Islam.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Enter ye the Garden, ye and your wives, in (beauty and) rejoicing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To them will be passed round, dishes and goblets of gold: there will be
 there all that the souls could desire, all that their eyes could delight
 in: and ye shall abide therein (for eye).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such will be the Garden of which ye are made heirs for your (good) deeds
 (in life).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ye shall have therein abundance of fruit, from which ye shall have satisfaction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The sinners will be in the Punishment of Hell, to dwell therein (for aye):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nowise will the (Punishment) be lightened for them, and in despair will
 they be there overwhelmed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nowise shall We be unjust to them: but it is they who have been unjust themselve
s.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will cry: "O Malik! would that thy Lord put an end to us!" He will
 say, "Nay, but ye shall abide!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily We have brought the Truth to you: but most of you have a hatred for
 Truth.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What! have they settled some plan (among themselves)? But it is We Who settle
 things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or do they think that We hear not their secrets and their private counsels?
 Indeed (We do), and Our messengers are by them, to record.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "If (Allah) Most Gracious had a son, I would be the first to worship."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Glory to the Lord of the heavens and the earth, the Lord of the Throne (of
 Authority)! (He is free) from the things they attribute (to him)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So leave them to babble and play (with vanities) until they meet that Day
 of theirs, which they have been promised.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who is Allah in heaven and Allah on earth; and He is full of Wisdom
 and Knowledge.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And blessed is He to Whom belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth,
 and all between them: with Him is the Knowledge of the Hour (of Judgment):
 and to Him shall ye be brought back.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those whom they invoke besides Allah have no power of intercession;-
 only he who bears witness to the Truth, and they know (him).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If thou ask them, who created them, they will certainly say, Allah: How
 then are they deluded away (from the Truth)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah has knowledge) of the (Prophet's) cry, "O my Lord! Truly these are
 people who will not believe!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But turn away from them, and say "Peace!" But soon shall they know!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ha-Mim.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Book that makes things clear;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We sent it down during a Blessed Night: for We (ever) wish to warn (against
 Evil).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the (Night) is made distinct every affair of wisdom,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By command, from Our Presence.
 For We (ever) send (revelations),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As Mercy from thy Lord: for He hears and knows (all things);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Lord of the heavens and the earth and all between them, if ye (but)
 have an assured faith.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There is no god but He: It is He Who gives life and gives death,- The Lord
 and Cherisher to you and your earliest ancestors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yet they play about in doubt.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then watch thou for the Day that the sky will bring forth a kind of smoke
 (or mist) plainly visible,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Enveloping the people: this will be a Penalty Grievous.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(They will say:) "Our Lord! remove the Penalty from us, for we do really
 believe!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
How shall the message be (effectual) for them, seeing that an Messenger
 explaining things clearly has (already) come to them,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yet they turn away from him and say: "Tutored (by others), a man possessed!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We shall indeed remove the Penalty for a while, (but) truly ye will revert
 (to your ways).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One day We shall seize you with a mighty onslaught: We will indeed (then)
 exact Retribution!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We did, before them, try the people of Pharaoh: there came to them a messenger
 most honourable,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Saying: "Restore to me the Servants of Allah: I am to you an messenger worthy
 of all trust;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And be not arrogant as against Allah: for I come to you with authority
 manifest.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"For me, I have sought safety with my Lord and your Lord, against your injuring
 me.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"If ye believe me not, at least keep yourselves away from me."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(But they were aggressive:) then he cried to his Lord: "These are indeed
 a people given to sin."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(The reply came:) "March forth with My Servants by night: for ye are sure
 to be pursued.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And leave the sea as a furrow (divided): for they are a host (destined)
 to be drowned."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
How many were the gardens and springs they left behind,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And corn-fields and noble buildings,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And wealth (and conveniences of life), wherein they had taken such delight!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus (was their end)! And We made other people inherit (those things)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And neither heaven nor earth shed a tear over them: nor were they given
 a respite (again).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We did deliver aforetime the Children of Israel from humiliating Punishment,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Inflicted by Pharaoh, for he was arrogant (even) among inordinate transgressors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We chose them aforetime above the nations, knowingly,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And granted them Signs in which there was a manifest trial
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As to these (Quraish), they say forsooth:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"There is nothing beyond our first death, and we shall not be raised again.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Then bring (back) our forefathers, if what ye say is true!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What! Are they better than the people of Tubba and those who were before
 them? We destroyed them because they were guilty of sin.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We created not the heavens, the earth, and all between them, merely in (idle)
 sport:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We created them not except for just ends: but most of them do not understand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily the Day of sorting out is the time appointed for all of them,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day when no protector can avail his client in aught, and no help can
 they receive,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Except such as receive Allah's Mercy: for He is Exalted in Might, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily the tree of Zaqqum
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Will be the food of the Sinful,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Like molten brass; it will boil in their insides.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Like the boiling of scalding water.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(A voice will cry: "Seize ye him and drag him into the midst of the Blazing
 Fire!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Then pour over his head the Penalty of Boiling Water,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Taste thou (this)! Truly wast thou mighty, full of honour!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Truly this is what ye used to doubt!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As to the Righteous (they will be) in a position of Security,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Among Gardens and Springs;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Dressed in fine silk and in rich brocade, they will face each other;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So; and We shall join them to fair women with beautiful, big, and lustrous
 eyes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There can they call for every kind of fruit in peace and security;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor will they there taste Death, except the first death; and He will preserve
 them from the Penalty of the Blazing Fire,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As a Bounty from thy Lord! that will be the supreme achievement!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily, We have made this (Qur'an) easy, in thy tongue, in order that they
 may give heed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So wait thou and watch; for they (too) are waiting.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ha-Mim.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The revelation of the Book is from Allah the Exalted in Power, Full of Wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily in the heavens and the earth, are Signs for those who believe.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And in the creation of yourselves and the fact that animals are scattered
 (through the earth), are Signs for those of assured Faith.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And in the alternation of Night and Day, and the fact that Allah sends down
 Sustenance from the sky, and revives therewith the earth after its death,
 and in the change of the winds,- are Signs for those that are wise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such are the Signs of Allah, which We rehearse to thee in Truth; then in
 what exposition will they believe after (rejecting) Allah and His Signs?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Woe to each sinful dealer in Falsehoods:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He hears the Signs of Allah rehearsed to him, yet is obstinate and lofty,
 as if he had not heard them: then announce to him a Penalty Grievous!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when he learns something of Our Signs, he takes them in jest: for such
 there will be a humiliating Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In front of them is Hell: and of no profit to them is anything they may
 have earned, nor any protectors they may have taken to themselves besides
 Allah: for them is a tremendous Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is (true) Guidance and for those who reject the Signs of their Lord,
 is a grievous Penalty of abomination.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is Allah Who has subjected the sea to you, that ships may sail through
 it by His command, that ye may seek of his Bounty, and that ye may be grateful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He has subjected to you, as from Him, all that is in the heavens and
 on earth: Behold, in that are Signs indeed for those who reflect.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Tell those who believe, to forgive those who do not look forward to the
 Days of Allah: It is for Him to recompense (for good or ill) each People
 according to what they have earned.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If any one does a righteous deed, it ensures to the benefit of his own soul;
 if he does evil, it works against (his own soul).
 In the end will ye (all) be brought back to your Lord.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We did aforetime grant to the Children of Israel the Book the Power of Command,
 and Prophethood; We gave them, for Sustenance, things good and pure; and
 We favoured them above the nations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We granted them Clear Signs in affairs (of Religion): it was only after
 knowledge had been granted to them that they fell into schisms, through
 insolent envy among themselves.
 Verily thy Lord will judge between them on the Day of Judgment as to those
 matters in which they set up differences.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then We put thee on the (right) Way of Religion: so follow thou that (Way),
 and follow not the desires of those who know not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will be of no use to thee in the sight of Allah: it is only Wrong-doers
 (that stand as) protectors, one to another: but Allah is the Protector
 of the Righteous.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These are clear evidences to men and a Guidance and Mercy to those of assured
 Faith.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What! Do those who seek after evil ways think that We shall hold them equal
 with those who believe and do righteous deeds,- that equal will be their
 life and their death? Ill is the judgment that they make.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah created the heavens and the earth for just ends, and in order that
 each soul may find the recompense of what it has earned, and none of them
 be wronged.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then seest thou such a one as takes as his god his own vain desire? Allah
 has, knowing (him as such), left him astray, and sealed his hearing and
 his heart (and understanding), and put a cover on his sight.
 Who, then, will guide him after Allah (has withdrawn Guidance)? Will ye
 not then receive admonition?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they say: "What is there but our life in this world? We shall die and
 we live, and nothing but time can destroy us." But of that they have no
 knowledge: they merely conjecture:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when Our Clear Signs are rehearsed to them their argument is nothing
 but this: They say, "Bring (back) our forefathers, if what ye say is true!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "It is Allah Who gives you life, then gives you death; then He will
 gather you together for the Day of Judgment about which there is no doubt":
 But most men do not understand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Allah belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth, and the Day
 that the Hour of Judgment is established,- that Day will the dealers in
 Falsehood perish!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And thou wilt see every sect bowing the knee: Every sect will be called
 to its Record: "This Day shall ye be recompensed for all that ye did!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"This Our Record speaks about you with truth: For We were wont to put on
 Record all that ye did."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, as to those who believed and did righteous deeds, their Lord will
 admit them to His Mercy that will be the achievement for all to see.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But as to those who rejected Allah, (to them will be said): "Were not Our
 Signs rehearsed to you? But ye were arrogant, and were a people given to
 sin!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And when it was said that the promise of Allah was true, and that the Hour-
 there was no doubt about its (coming), ye used to say, 'We know not what
 is the hour: we only think it is an idea, and we have no firm assurance.'"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then will appear to them the evil (fruits) of what they did, and they will
 be completely encircled by that which they used to mock at!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It will also be said: "This Day We will forget you as ye forgot the meeting
 of this Day of yours! and your abode is the Fire, and no helpers have ye!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"This, because ye used to take the Signs of Allah in jest, and the life
 of the world deceived you:" (From) that Day, therefore, they shall not
 be taken out thence, nor shall they be received into Grace.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then Praise be to Allah, Lord of the heavens and Lord of the earth,- Lord
 and Cherisher of all the Worlds!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Him be glory throughout the heavens and the earth: and He is Exalted
 in Power, Full of Wisdom!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ha-Mim.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Revelation of the Book is from Allah the Exalted in Power, Full of Wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We created not the heavens and the earth and all between them but for just
 ends, and for a Term Appointed: But those who reject Faith turn away from
 that whereof they are warned.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Do ye see what it is ye invoke besides Allah? Show me what it is they
 have created on earth, or have they a share in the heavens bring me a book
 (revealed) before this, or any remnant of knowledge (ye may have), if ye
 are telling the truth!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And who is more astray than one who invokes besides Allah, such as will
 not answer him to the Day of Judgment, and who (in fact) are unconscious
 of their call (to them)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when mankind are gathered together (at the Resurrection), they will
 be hostile to them and reject their worship (altogether)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When Our Clear Signs are rehearsed to them, the Unbelievers say, of the
 Truth when it comes to them: "This is evident sorcery!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or do they say, "He has forged it"? Say: "Had I forged it, then can ye obtain
 no single (blessing) for me from Allah.
 He knows best of that whereof ye talk (so glibly)! Enough is He for a witness
 between me and you! And he is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "I am no bringer of new-fangled doctrine among the messengers, nor
 do I know what will be done with me or with you.
 I follow but that which is revealed to me by inspiration; I am but a Warner
 open and clear."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "See ye? If (this teaching) be from Allah, and ye reject it, and a
 witness from among the Children of Israel testifies to its similarity (with
 earlier scripture), and has believed while ye are arrogant, (how unjust
 ye are!) truly, Allah guides not a people unjust."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Unbelievers say of those who believe: "If (this Message) were a good
 thing, (such men) would not have gone to it first, before us!" And seeing
 that they guide not themselves thereby, they will say, "this is an (old,)
 falsehood!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And before this, was the Book of Moses as a guide and a mercy: And this
 Book confirms (it) in the Arabic tongue; to admonish the unjust, and as
 Glad Tidings to those who do right.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily those who say, "Our Lord is Allah," and remain firm (on that Path),-
 on them shall be no fear, nor shall they grieve.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such shall be Companions of the Gardens, dwelling therein (for aye): a recompens
e for their (good) deeds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have enjoined on man kindness to his parents: In pain did his mother
 bear him, and in pain did she give him birth.
 The carrying of the (child) to his weaning is (a period of) thirty months.
 At length, when he reaches the age of full strength and attains forty years,
 he says, "O my Lord! Grant me that I may be grateful for Thy favour which
 Thou has bestowed upon me, and upon both my parents, and that I may work
 righteousness such as Thou mayest approve; and be gracious to me in my
 issue.
 Truly have I turned to Thee and truly do I bow (to Thee) in Islam."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such are they from whom We shall accept the best of their deeds and pass
 by their ill deeds: (They shall be) among the Companions of the Garden:
 a promise! of truth, which was made to them (in this life).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But (there is one) who says to his parents, "Fie on you! Do ye hold out
 the promise to me that I shall be raised up, even though generations have
 passed before me (without rising again)?" And they two seek Allah's aid,
 (and rebuke the son): "Woe to thee! Have faith! for the promise of Allah
 is true." But he says, "This is nothing but tales of the ancients!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such are they against whom is proved the sentence among the previous generations
 of Jinns and men, that have passed away; for they will be (utterly) lost.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And to all are (assigned) degrees according to the deeds which they (have
 done), and in order that (Allah) may recompense their deeds, and no injustice
 be done to them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And on the Day that the Unbelievers will be placed before the Fire, (It
 will be said to them): "Ye received your good things in the life of the
 world, and ye took your pleasure out of them: but today shall ye be recompensed
 with a Penalty of humiliation: for that ye were arrogant on earth without
 just cause, and that ye (ever) transgressed."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Mention (Hud) one of 'Ad's (own) brethren: Behold, he warned his people
 about the winding Sand-tracts: but there have been warners before him and
 after him: "Worship ye none other than Allah: Truly I fear for you the
 Penalty of a Mighty Day."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "Hast thou come in order to turn us aside from our gods? Then
 bring upon us the (calamity) with which thou dost threaten us, if thou
 art telling the truth?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "The Knowledge (of when it will come) is only with Allah: I proclaim
 to you the mission on which I have been sent: But I see that ye are a people
 in ignorance!"..
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, when they saw the (Penalty in the shape of) a cloud traversing the
 sky, coming to meet their valleys, they said, "This cloud will give us
 rain!" "Nay, it is the (Calamity) ye were asking to be hastened!- A wind
 wherein is a Grievous Penalty!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Everything will it destroy by the command of its Lord!" Then by the morning
 they - nothing was to be seen but (the ruins of) their houses! thus do
 We recompense those given to sin!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We had firmly established them in a (prosperity and) power which We
 have not given to you (ye Quraish!) and We had endowed them with (faculties
 of) hearing, seeing, heart and intellect: but of no profit to them were
 their (faculties of) hearing, sight, and heart and intellect, when they
 went on rejecting the Signs of Allah; and they were (completely) encircled
 by that which they used to mock at!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We destroyed aforetime populations round about you; and We have shown the
 Signs in various ways, that they may turn (to Us).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Why then was no help forthcoming to them from those whom they worshipped
 as gods, besides Allah, as a means of access (to Allah)? Nay, they left
 them in the lurch: but that was their falsehood and their invention.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, We turned towards thee a company of Jinns (quietly) listening to
 the Qur'an: when they stood in the presence thereof, they said, "Listen
 in silence!" When the (reading) was finished, they returned to their people,
 to warn (them of their sins).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said, "O our people! We have heard a Book revealed after Moses, confirming
 what came before it: it guides (men) to the Truth and to a Straight Path.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"O our people, hearken to the one who invites (you) to Allah, and believe
 in him: He will forgive you your faults, and deliver you from a Penalty
 Grievous.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"If any does not hearken to the one who invites (us) to Allah, he cannot
 frustrate (Allah's Plan) on earth, and no protectors can he have besides
 Allah: such men (wander) in manifest error."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
See they not that Allah, Who created the heavens and the earth, and never
 wearied with their creation, is able to give life to the dead? Yea, verily
 He has power over all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And on the Day that the Unbelievers will be placed before the Fire, (they
 will be asked,) "Is this not the Truth?" they will say, "Yea, by our Lord!"
 (One will say:) "Then taste ye the Penalty, for that ye were wont to deny
 (Truth)!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore patiently persevere, as did (all) messengers of inflexible purpose;
 and be in no haste about the (Unbelievers).
 On the Day that they see the (Punishment) promised them, (it will be) as
 if they had not tarried more than an hour in a single day.
 (Thine but) to proclaim the Message: but shall any be destroyed except
 those who transgress?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who reject Allah and hinder (men) from the Path of Allah,- their deeds
 will Allah render astray (from their mark).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those who believe and work deeds of righteousness, and believe in the
 (Revelation) sent down to Muhammad - for it is the Truth from their Lord,-
 He will remove from them their ills and improve their condition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This because those who reject Allah follow vanities, while those who believe
 follow the Truth from their Lord: Thus does Allah set forth for men their
 lessons by similitudes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore, when ye meet the Unbelievers (in fight), smite at their necks;
 At length, when ye have thoroughly subdued them, bind a bond firmly (on
 them): thereafter (is the time for) either generosity or ransom: Until
 the war lays down its burdens.
 Thus (are ye commanded): but if it had been Allah's Will, He could certainly
 have exacted retribution from them (Himself); but (He lets you fight) in
 order to test you, some with others.
 But those who are slain in the Way of Allah,- He will never let their deeds
 be lost.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Soon will He guide them and improve their condition,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And admit them to the Garden which He has announced for them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! If ye will aid (the cause of) Allah, He will aid you,
 and plant your feet firmly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those who reject (Allah),- for them is destruction, and (Allah) will
 render their deeds astray (from their mark).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That is because they hate the Revelation of Allah; so He has made their
 deeds fruitless.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they not travel through the earth, and see what was the End of those
 before them (who did evil)? Allah brought utter destruction on them, and
 similar (fates await) those who reject Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That is because Allah is the Protector of those who believe, but those who
 reject Allah have no protector.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily Allah will admit those who believe and do righteous deeds, to Gardens
 beneath which rivers flow; while those who reject Allah will enjoy (this
 world) and eat as cattle eat; and the Fire will be their abode.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And how many cities, with more power than thy city which has driven thee
 out, have We destroyed (for their sins)? and there was none to aid them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is then one who is on a clear (Path) from his Lord, no better than one to
 whom the evil of his conduct seems pleasing, and such as follow their own
 lusts?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Here is) a Parable of the Garden which the righteous are promised: in it
 are rivers of water incorruptible; rivers of milk of which the taste never
 changes; rivers of wine, a joy to those who drink; and rivers of honey
 pure and clear.
 In it there are for them all kinds of fruits; and Grace from their Lord.
 (Can those in such Bliss) be compared to such as shall dwell for ever in
 the Fire, and be given, to drink, boiling water, so that it cuts up their
 bowels (to pieces)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And among them are men who listen to thee, but in the end, when they go
 out from thee, they say to those who have received Knowledge, "What is
 it he said just then?" Such are men whose hearts Allah has sealed, and
 who follow their own lusts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But to those who receive Guidance, He increases the (light of) Guidance,
 and bestows on them their Piety and Restraint (from evil).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they then only wait for the Hour,- that it should come on them of a sudden?
 But already have come some tokens thereof, and when it (actually) is on
 them, how can they benefit then by their admonition?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Know, therefore, that there is no god but Allah, and ask forgiveness for
 thy fault, and for the men and women who believe: for Allah knows how ye
 move about and how ye dwell in your homes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who believe say, "Why is not a sura sent down (for us)?" But when
 a sura of basic or categorical meaning is revealed, and fighting is mentioned
 therein, thou wilt see those in whose hearts is a disease looking at thee
 with a look of one in swoon at the approach of death.
 But more fitting for them-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Were it to obey and say what is just, and when a matter is resolved on,
 it were best for them if they were true to Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, is it to be expected of you, if ye were put in authority, that ye
 will do mischief in the land, and break your ties of kith and kin?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such are the men whom Allah has cursed for He has made them deaf and blinded
 their sight.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they not then earnestly seek to understand the Qur'an, or are their hearts
 locked up by them?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who turn back as apostates after Guidance was clearly shown to them,-
 the Evil One has instigated them and busied them up with false hopes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This, because they said to those who hate what Allah has revealed, "We will
 obey you in part of (this) matter"; but Allah knows their (inner) secrets.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But how (will it be) when the angels take their souls at death, and smite
 their faces and their backs?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This because they followed that which called forth the Wrath of Allah, and
 they hated Allah's good pleasure; so He made their deeds of no effect.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or do those in whose hearts is a disease, think that Allah will not bring
 to light all their rancour?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Had We so wiled, We could have shown them up to thee, and thou shouldst
 have known them by their marks: but surely thou wilt know them by the tone
 of their speech! And Allah knows all that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We shall try you until We test those among you who strive their utmost
 and persevere in patience; and We shall try your reported (mettle).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who reject Allah, hinder (men) from the Path of Allah, and resist
 the Messenger, after Guidance has been clearly shown to them, will not
 injure Allah in the least, but He will make their deeds of no effect.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Obey Allah, and obey the messenger, and make not vain
 your deeds!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who reject Allah, and hinder (men) from the Path of Allah, then die
 rejecting Allah,- Allah will not forgive them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Be not weary and faint-hearted, crying for peace, when ye should be uppermost:
 for Allah is with you, and will never put you in loss for your (good) deeds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The life of this world is but play and amusement: and if ye believe and
 guard against Evil, He will grant you your recompense, and will not ask
 you (to give up) your possessions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If He were to ask you for all of them, and press you, ye would covetously
 withhold, and He would bring out all your ill-feeling.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, ye are those invited to spend (of your substance) in the Way of
 Allah: But among you are some that are niggardly.
 But any who are niggardly are so at the expense of their own souls.
 But Allah is free of all wants, and it is ye that are needy.
 If ye turn back (from the Path), He will substitute in your stead another
 people; then they would not be like you!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily We have granted thee a manifest Victory:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That Allah may forgive thee thy faults of the past and those to follow;
 fulfil His favour to thee; and guide thee on the Straight Way;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And that Allah may help thee with powerful help.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who sent down tranquillity into the hearts of the Believers, that
 they may add faith to their faith;- for to Allah belong the Forces of the
 heavens and the earth; and Allah is Full of Knowledge and Wisdom;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That He may admit the men and women who believe, to Gardens beneath which
 rivers flow, to dwell therein for aye, and remove their ills from them;-
 and that is, in the sight of Allah, the highest achievement (for man),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And that He may punish the Hypocrites, men and women, and the Polytheists
 men and women, who imagine an evil opinion of Allah.
 On them is a round of Evil: the Wrath of Allah is on them: He has cursed
 them and got Hell ready for them: and evil is it for a destination.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For to Allah belong the Forces of the heavens and the earth; and Allah is
 Exalted in Power, Full of Wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have truly sent thee as a witness, as a bringer of Glad Tidings, and
 as a Warner:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In order that ye (O men) may believe in Allah and His Messenger, that ye
 may assist and honour Him, and celebrate His praise morning and evening.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily those who plight their fealty to thee do no less than plight their
 fealty to Allah: the Hand of Allah is over their hands: then any one who
 violates his oath, does so to the harm of his own soul, and any one who
 fulfils what he has covenanted with Allah,- Allah will soon grant him a
 great Reward.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The desert Arabs who lagged behind will say to thee: "We were engaged in
 (looking after) our flocks and herds, and our families: do thou then ask
 forgiveness for us." They say with their tongues what is not in their hearts.
 Say: "Who then has any power at all (to intervene) on your behalf with
 Allah, if His Will is to give you some loss or to give you some profit?
 But Allah is well acquainted with all that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Nay, ye thought that the Messenger and the Believers would never return
 to their families; this seemed pleasing in your hearts, and ye conceived
 an evil thought, for ye are a people lost (in wickedness)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if any believe not in Allah and His Messenger, We have prepared, for
 those who reject Allah, a Blazing Fire!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Allah belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth: He forgives
 whom He wills, and He punishes whom He wills: but Allah is Oft-Forgiving,
 Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who lagged behind (will say), when ye (are free to) march and take
 booty (in war): "Permit us to follow you." They wish to change Allah's decree:
 Say: "Not thus will ye follow us: Allah has already declared (this) beforehand"
: then they will say, "But ye are jealous of us." Nay, but little do they
 understand (such things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say to the desert Arabs who lagged behind: "Ye shall be summoned (to fight)
 against a people given to vehement war: then shall ye fight, or they shall
 submit.
 Then if ye show obedience, Allah will grant you a goodly reward, but if
 ye turn back as ye did before, He will punish you with a grievous Penalty."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No blame is there on the blind, nor is there blame on the lame, nor on one
 ill (if he joins not the war): But he that obeys Allah and his Messenger,-
 (Allah) will admit him to Gardens beneath which rivers flow; and he who
 turns back, (Allah) will punish him with a grievous Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah's Good Pleasure was on the Believers when they swore Fealty to thee
 under the Tree: He knew what was in their hearts, and He sent down Tranquillity
 to them; and He rewarded them with a speedy Victory;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And many gains will they acquire (besides): and Allah is Exalted in Power,
 Full of Wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah has promised you many gains that ye shall acquire, and He has given
 you these beforehand; and He has restrained the hands of men from you;
 that it may be a Sign for the Believers, and that He may guide you to a
 Straight Path;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And other gains (there are), which are not within your power, but which
 Allah has compassed: and Allah has power over all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If the Unbelievers should fight you, they would certainly turn their backs;
 then would they find neither protector nor helper.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Such has been) the practice (approved) of Allah already in the past: no
 change wilt thou find in the practice (approved) of Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And it is He Who has restrained their hands from you and your hands from
 them in the midst of Makka, after that He gave you the victory over them.
 And Allah sees well all that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They are the ones who denied Revelation and hindered you from the Sacred
 Mosque and the sacrificial animals, detained from reaching their place
 of sacrifice.
 Had there not been believing men and believing women whom ye did not know
 that ye were trampling down and on whose account a crime would have accrued
 to you without (your) knowledge, (Allah would have allowed you to force
 your way, but He held back your hands) that He may admit to His Mercy whom
 He will.
 If they had been apart, We should certainly have punished the Unbelievers
 among them with a grievous Punishment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
While the Unbelievers got up in their hearts heat and cant - the heat and
 cant of ignorance,- Allah sent down His Tranquillity to his Messenger and
 to the Believers, and made them stick close to the command of self-restraint;
 and well were they entitled to it and worthy of it.
 And Allah has full knowledge of all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly did Allah fulfil the vision for His Messenger: ye shall enter the
 Sacred Mosque, if Allah wills, with minds secure, heads shaved, hair cut
 short, and without fear.
 For He knew what ye knew not, and He granted, besides this, a speedy victory.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who has sent His Messenger with Guidance and the Religion of Truth,
 to proclaim it over all religion: and enough is Allah for a Witness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Muhammad is the messenger of Allah; and those who are with him are strong
 against Unbelievers, (but) compassionate amongst each other.
 Thou wilt see them bow and prostrate themselves (in prayer), seeking Grace
 from Allah and (His) Good Pleasure.
 On their faces are their marks, (being) the traces of their prostration.
 This is their similitude in the Taurat; and their similitude in the Gospel
 is: like a seed which sends forth its blade, then makes it strong; it then
 becomes thick, and it stands on its own stem, (filling) the sowers with
 wonder and delight.
 As a result, it fills the Unbelievers with rage at them.
 Allah has promised those among them who believe and do righteous deeds
 forgiveness, and a great Reward.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O Ye who believe! Put not yourselves forward before Allah and His Messenger;
 but fear Allah: for Allah is He Who hears and knows all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Raise not your voices above the voice of the Prophet,
 nor speak aloud to him in talk, as ye may speak aloud to one another, lest
 your deeds become vain and ye perceive not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those that lower their voices in the presence of Allah's Messenger,- their
 hearts has Allah tested for piety: for them is Forgiveness and a great
 Reward.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who shout out to thee from without the inner apartments - most of
 them lack understanding.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If only they had patience until thou couldst come out to them, it would
 be best for them: but Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! If a wicked person comes to you with any news, ascertain
 the truth, lest ye harm people unwittingly, and afterwards become full
 of repentance for what ye have done.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And know that among you is Allah's Messenger: were he, in many matters,
 to follow your (wishes), ye would certainly fall into misfortune: But Allah
 has endeared the Faith to you, and has made it beautiful in your hearts,
 and He has made hateful to you Unbelief, wickedness, and rebellion: such
 indeed are those who walk in righteousness;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A Grace and Favour from Allah; and Allah is full of Knowledge and Wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If two parties among the Believers fall into a quarrel, make ye peace between
 them: but if one of them transgresses beyond bounds against the other,
 then fight ye (all) against the one that transgresses until it complies
 with the command of Allah; but if it complies, then make peace between
 them with justice, and be fair: for Allah loves those who are fair (and
 just).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Believers are but a single Brotherhood: So make peace and reconciliation
 between your two (contending) brothers; and fear Allah, that ye may receive
 Mercy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Let not some men among you laugh at others: It may be
 that the (latter) are better than the (former): Nor let some women laugh
 at others: It may be that the (latter are better than the (former): Nor
 defame nor be sarcastic to each other, nor call each other by (offensive)
 nicknames: Ill-seeming is a name connoting wickedness, (to be used of one)
 after he has believed: And those who do not desist are (indeed) doing wrong.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Avoid suspicion as much (as possible): for suspicion in
 some cases is a sin: And spy not on each other behind their backs.
 Would any of you like to eat the flesh of his dead brother? Nay, ye would
 abhor it...
 But fear Allah: For Allah is Oft-Returning, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O mankind! We created you from a single (pair) of a male and a female, and
 made you into nations and tribes, that ye may know each other (not that
 ye may despise (each other).
 Verily the most honoured of you in the sight of Allah is (he who is) the
 most righteous of you.
 And Allah has full knowledge and is well acquainted (with all things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The desert Arabs say, "We believe." Say, "Ye have no faith; but ye (only)
 say, 'We have submitted our wills to Allah,' For not yet has Faith entered
 your hearts.
 But if ye obey Allah and His Messenger, He will not belittle aught of your
 deeds: for Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Only those are Believers who have believed in Allah and His Messenger, and
 have never since doubted, but have striven with their belongings and their
 persons in the Cause of Allah: Such are the sincere ones.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "What! Will ye instruct Allah about your religion? But Allah knows
 all that is in the heavens and on earth: He has full knowledge of all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They impress on thee as a favour that they have embraced Islam.
 Say, "Count not your Islam as a favour upon me: Nay, Allah has conferred
 a favour upon you that He has guided you to the faith, if ye be true and
 sincere.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Verily Allah knows the secrets of the heavens and the earth: and Allah
 Sees well all that ye do."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Qaf: By the Glorious Qur'an (Thou art Allah's Messenger).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But they wonder that there has come to them a Warner from among themselves.
 So the Unbelievers say: "This is a wonderful thing!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"What! When we die and become dust, (shall we live again?) That is a (sort
 of) return far (from our understanding)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We already know how much of them the earth takes away: With Us is a record
 guarding (the full account).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But they deny the Truth when it comes to them: so they are in a confused
 state.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they not look at the sky above them?- How We have made it and adorned
 it, and there are no flaws in it?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the earth- We have spread it out, and set thereon mountains standing
 firm, and produced therein every kind of beautiful growth (in pairs)-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To be observed and commemorated by every devotee turning (to Allah).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We send down from the sky rain charted with blessing, and We produce
 therewith gardens and Grain for harvests;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And tall (and stately) palm-trees, with shoots of fruit-stalks, piled one
 over another;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As sustenance for (Allah's) Servants;- and We give (new) life therewith
 to land that is dead: Thus will be the Resurrection.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Before them was denied (the Hereafter) by the People of Noah, the Companions
 of the Rass, the Thamud,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 'Ad, Pharaoh, the brethren of Lut,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Companions of the Wood, and the People of Tubba'; each one (of them)
 rejected the messengers, and My warning was duly fulfilled (in them).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Were We then weary with the first Creation, that they should be in confused
 doubt about a new Creation?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It was We Who created man, and We know what dark suggestions his soul makes
 to him: for We are nearer to him than (his) jugular vein.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, two (guardian angels) appointed to learn (his doings) learn (and
 noted them), one sitting on the right and one on the left.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Not a word does he utter but there is a sentinel by him, ready (to note
 it).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the stupor of death will bring Truth (before his eyes): "This was the
 thing which thou wast trying to escape!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Trumpet shall be blown: that will be the Day whereof Warning (had
 been given).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And there will come forth every soul: with each will be an (angel) to drive,
 and an (angel) to bear witness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It will be said:) "Thou wast heedless of this; now have We removed thy
 veil, and sharp is thy sight this Day!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And his Companion will say: "Here is (his Record) ready with me!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(The sentence will be:) "Throw, throw into Hell every contumacious Rejecter
 (of Allah)!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Who forbade what was good, transgressed all bounds, cast doubts and suspicions;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Who set up another god beside Allah: Throw him into a severe penalty."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
His Companion will say: "Our Lord! I did not make him transgress, but he
 was (himself) far astray."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He will say: "Dispute not with each other in My Presence: I had already
 in advance sent you Warning.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"The Word changes not before Me, and I do not the least injustice to My
 Servants."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One Day We will ask Hell, "Art thou filled to the full?" It will say, "Are
 there any more (to come)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Garden will be brought nigh to the Righteous,- no more a thing distant.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(A voice will say:) "This is what was promised for you,- for every one who
 turned (to Allah) in sincere repentance, who kept (His Law),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Who feared (Allah) Most Gracious Unseen, and brought a heart turned in
 devotion (to Him):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Enter ye therein in Peace and Security; this is a Day of Eternal Life!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There will be for them therein all that they wish,- and more besides in
 Our Presence.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But how many generations before them did We destroy (for their sins),- stronger
 in power than they? Then did they wander through the land: was there any
 place of escape (for them)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily in this is a Message for any that has a heart and understanding or
 who gives ear and earnestly witnesses (the truth).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We created the heavens and the earth and all between them in Six Days, nor
 did any sense of weariness touch Us.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Bear, then, with patience, all that they say, and celebrate the praises
 of thy Lord, before the rising of the sun and before (its) setting.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And during part of the night, (also,) celebrate His praises, and (so likewise)
 after the postures of adoration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And listen for the Day when the Caller will call out from a place quiet
 near,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day when they will hear a (mighty) Blast in (very) truth: that will
 be the Day of Resurrection.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily it is We Who give Life and Death; and to Us is the Final Goal-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day when the Earth will be rent asunder, from (men) hurrying out: that
 will be a gathering together,- quite easy for Us.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We know best what they say; and thou art not one to overawe them by force.
 So admonish with the Qur'an such as fear My Warning!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the (Winds) that scatter broadcast;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those that lift and bear away heavy weights;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those that flow with ease and gentleness;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those that distribute and apportion by Command;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily that which ye are promised is true;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And verily Judgment and Justice must indeed come to pass.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Sky with (its) numerous Paths,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly ye are in a doctrine discordant,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Through which are deluded (away from the Truth) such as would be deluded.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Woe to the falsehood-mongers,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who (flounder) heedless in a flood of confusion:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They ask, "When will be the Day of Judgment and Justice?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It will be) a Day when they will be tried (and tested) over the Fire!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Taste ye your trial! This is what ye used to ask to be hastened!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As to the Righteous, they will be in the midst of Gardens and Springs,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Taking joy in the things which their Lord gives them, because, before then,
 they lived a good life.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They were in the habit of sleeping but little by night,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And in the hour of early dawn, they (were found) praying for Forgiveness;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And in their wealth and possessions (was remembered) the right of the (needy,)
 him who asked, and him who (for some reason) was prevented (from asking).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On the earth are signs for those of assured Faith,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As also in your own selves: Will ye not then see?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And in heaven is your Sustenance, as (also) that which ye are promised.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, by the Lord of heaven and earth, this is the very Truth, as much as
 the fact that ye can speak intelligently to each other.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Has the story reached thee, of the honoured guests of Abraham?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, they entered his presence, and said: "Peace!" He said, "Peace!"
 (and thought, "These seem) unusual people."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then he turned quickly to his household, brought out a fatted calf,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And placed it before them..
 he said, "Will ye not eat?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(When they did not eat), He conceived a fear of them.
 They said, "Fear not," and they gave him glad tidings of a son endowed
 with knowledge.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But his wife came forward (laughing) aloud: she smote her forehead and said:
 "A barren old woman!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said, "Even so has thy Lord spoken: and He is full of Wisdom and Knowledge."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Abraham) said: "And what, O ye Messengers, is your errand (now)?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said, "We have been sent to a people (deep) in sin;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"To bring on, on them, (a shower of) stones of clay (brimstone),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Marked as from thy Lord for those who trespass beyond bounds."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then We evacuated those of the Believers who were there,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But We found not there any just (Muslim) persons except in one house:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We left there a Sign for such as fear the Grievous Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And in Moses (was another Sign): Behold, We sent him to Pharaoh, with authority
 manifest.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But (Pharaoh) turned back with his Chiefs, and said, "A sorcerer, or one
 possessed!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So We took him and his forces, and threw them into the sea; and his was
 the blame.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And in the 'Ad (people) (was another Sign): Behold, We sent against them
 the devastating Wind:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It left nothing whatever that it came up against, but reduced it to ruin
 and rottenness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And in the Thamud (was another Sign): Behold, they were told, "Enjoy (your
 brief day) for a little while!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But they insolently defied the Command of their Lord: So the stunning noise
 (of an earthquake) seized them, even while they were looking on.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then they could not even stand (on their feet), nor could they help themselves.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So were the People of Noah before them for they wickedly transgressed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With power and skill did We construct the Firmament: for it is We Who create
 the vastness of pace.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We have spread out the (spacious) earth: How excellently We do spread
 out!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And of every thing We have created pairs: That ye may receive instruction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Hasten ye then (at once) to Allah: I am from Him a Warner to you, clear
 and open!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And make not another an object of worship with Allah: I am from Him a Warner
 to you, clear and open!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Similarly, no messenger came to the Peoples before them, but they said (of
 him) in like manner, "A sorcerer, or one possessed"!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is this the legacy they have transmitted, one to another? Nay, they are
 themselves a people transgressing beyond bounds!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So turn away from them: not thine is the blame.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But teach (thy Message) for teaching benefits the Believers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
I have only created Jinns and men, that they may serve Me.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No Sustenance do I require of them, nor do I require that they should feed
 Me.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For Allah is He Who gives (all) Sustenance,- Lord of Power,- Steadfast (for
 ever).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For the Wrong-doers, their portion is like unto the portion of their fellows
 (of earlier generations): then let them not ask Me to hasten (that portion)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Woe, then, to the Unbelievers, on account of that Day of theirs which they
 have been promised!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Mount (of Revelation);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By a Decree inscribed
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In a Scroll unfolded;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the much-frequented Fane;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Canopy Raised High;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And by the Ocean filled with Swell;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily, the Doom of thy Lord will indeed come to pass;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There is none can avert it;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On the Day when the firmament will be in dreadful commotion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the mountains will fly hither and thither.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then woe that Day to those that treat (Truth) as Falsehood;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That play (and paddle) in shallow trifles.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That Day shall they be thrust down to the Fire of Hell, irresistibly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"This:, it will be said, "Is the Fire,- which ye were wont to deny!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Is this then a fake, or is it ye that do not see?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Burn ye therein: the same is it to you whether ye bear it with patience,
 or not: Ye but receive the recompense of your (own) deeds."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As to the Righteous, they will be in Gardens, and in Happiness,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Enjoying the (Bliss) which their Lord hath bestowed on them, and their Lord
 shall deliver them from the Penalty of the Fire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(To them will be said:) "Eat and drink ye, with profit and health, because
 of your (good) deeds."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will recline (with ease) on Thrones (of dignity) arranged in ranks;
 and We shall join them to Companions, with beautiful big and lustrous eyes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who believe and whose families follow them in Faith,- to them
 shall We join their families: Nor shall We deprive them (of the fruit)
 of aught of their works: (Yet) is each individual in pledge for his deeds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We shall bestow on them, of fruit and meat, anything they shall desire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They shall there exchange, one with another, a (loving) cup free of frivolity,
 free of all taint of ill.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Round about them will serve, (devoted) to them, young male servants (handsome)
 as Pearls well-guarded.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will advance to each other, engaging in mutual enquiry.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say: "Aforetime, we were not without fear for the sake of our
 people.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But Allah has been good to us, and has delivered us from the Penalty of
 the Scorching Wind.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Truly, we did call unto Him from of old: truly it is He, the Beneficent,
 the Merciful!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore proclaim thou the praises (of thy Lord): for by the Grace of thy
 Lord, thou art no (vulgar) soothsayer, nor art thou one possessed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or do they say:- "A Poet! we await for him some calamity (hatched) by Time!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say thou: "Await ye!- I too will wait along with you!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is it that their faculties of understanding urge them to this, or are they
 but a people transgressing beyond bounds?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or do they say, "He fabricated the (Message)"? Nay, they have no faith!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let them then produce a recital like unto it,- If (it be) they speak the
 truth!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Were they created of nothing, or were they themselves the creators?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or did they create the heavens and the earth? Nay, they have no firm belief.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or are the Treasures of thy Lord with them, or are they the managers (of
 affairs)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or have they a ladder, by which they can (climb up to heaven and) listen
 (to its secrets)? Then let (such a) listener of theirs produce a manifest
 proof.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or has He only daughters and ye have sons?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or is it that thou dost ask for a reward, so that they are burdened with
 a load of debt?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or that the Unseen in it their hands, and they write it down?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or do they intend a plot (against thee)? But those who defy Allah are themselves
 involved in a Plot!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or have they a god other than Allah? Exalted is Allah far above the things
 they associate with Him!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Were they to see a piece of the sky falling (on them), they would (only)
 say: "Clouds gathered in heaps!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So leave them alone until they encounter that Day of theirs, wherein they
 shall (perforce) swoon (with terror),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day when their plotting will avail them nothing and no help shall be
 given them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And verily, for those who do wrong, there is another punishment besides
 this: But most of them understand not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now await in patience the command of thy Lord: for verily thou art in Our
 eyes: and celebrate the praises of thy Lord the while thou standest forth,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And for part of the night also praise thou Him,- and at the retreat of the
 stars!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Star when it goes down,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Your Companion is neither astray nor being misled.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor does he say (aught) of (his own) Desire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is no less than inspiration sent down to him:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He was taught by one Mighty in Power,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Endued with Wisdom: for he appeared (in stately form);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
While he was in the highest part of the horizon:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then he approached and came closer,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And was at a distance of but two bow-lengths or (even) nearer;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So did (Allah) convey the inspiration to His Servant- (conveyed) what He
 (meant) to convey.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The (Prophet's) (mind and) heart in no way falsified that which he saw.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Will ye then dispute with him concerning what he saw?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For indeed he saw him at a second descent,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Near the Lote-tree beyond which none may pass:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Near it is the Garden of Abode.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, the Lote-tree was shrouded (in mystery unspeakable!)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(His) sight never swerved, nor did it go wrong!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For truly did he see, of the Signs of his Lord, the Greatest!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Have ye seen Lat.
 and 'Uzza,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And another, the third (goddess), Manat?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What! for you the male sex, and for Him, the female?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, such would be indeed a division most unfair!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These are nothing but names which ye have devised,- ye and your fathers,-
 for which Allah has sent down no authority (whatever).
 They follow nothing but conjecture and what their own souls desire!- Even
 though there has already come to them Guidance from their Lord!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, shall man have (just) anything he hankers after?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But it is to Allah that the End and the Beginning (of all things) belong.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
How many-so-ever be the angels in the heavens, their intercession will avail
 nothing except after Allah has given leave for whom He pleases and that
 he is acceptable to Him.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who believe not in the Hereafter, name the angels with female names.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But they have no knowledge therein.
 They follow nothing but conjecture; and conjecture avails nothing against
 Truth.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore shun those who turn away from Our Message and desire nothing but
 the life of this world.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That is as far as knowledge will reach them.
 Verily thy Lord knoweth best those who stray from His Path, and He knoweth
 best those who receive guidance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yea, to Allah belongs all that is in the heavens and on earth: so that He
 rewards those who do evil, according to their deeds, and He rewards those
 who do good, with what is best.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who avoid great sins and shameful deeds, only (falling into) small
 faults,- verily thy Lord is ample in forgiveness.
 He knows you well when He brings you out of the earth, And when ye are
 hidden in your mothers' wombs.
 Therefore justify not yourselves: He knows best who it is that guards against
 evil.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou one who turns back,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Gives a little, then hardens (his heart)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What! Has he knowledge of the Unseen so that he can see?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, is he not acquainted with what is in the Books of Moses-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And of Abraham who fulfilled his engagements?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Namely, that no bearer of burdens can bear the burden of another;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That man can have nothing but what he strives for;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That (the fruit of) his striving will soon come in sight:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then will he be rewarded with a reward complete;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That to thy Lord is the final Goal;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That it is He Who granteth Laughter and Tears;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That it is He Who granteth Death and Life;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That He did create in pairs,- male and female,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From a seed when lodged (in its place);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That He hath promised a Second Creation (Raising of the Dead);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That it is He Who giveth wealth and satisfaction;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That He is the Lord of Sirius (the Mighty Star);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And that it is He Who destroyed the (powerful) ancient 'Ad (people),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Thamud nor gave them a lease of perpetual life.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And before them, the people of Noah, for that they were (all) most unjust
 and most insolent transgressors,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He destroyed the Overthrown Cities (of Sodom and Gomorrah).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So that (ruins unknown) have covered them up.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the gifts of thy Lord, (O man,) wilt thou dispute about?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is a Warner, of the (series of) Warners of old!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The (Judgment) ever approaching draws nigh:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No (soul) but Allah can lay it bare.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do ye then wonder at this recital?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And will ye laugh and not weep,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Wasting your time in vanities?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But fall ye down in prostration to Allah, and adore (Him)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Hour (of Judgment) is nigh, and the moon is cleft asunder.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But if they see a Sign, they turn away, and say, "This is (but) transient
 magic."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They reject (the warning) and follow their (own) lusts but every matter
 has its appointed time.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There have already come to them Recitals wherein there is (enough) to check
 (them),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Mature wisdom;- but (the preaching of) Warners profits them not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore, (O Prophet,) turn away from them.
 The Day that the Caller will call (them) to a terrible affair,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will come forth,- their eyes humbled - from (their) graves, (torpid)
 like locusts scattered abroad,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Hastening, with eyes transfixed, towards the Caller!- "Hard is this Day!",
 the Unbelievers will say.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Before them the People of Noah rejected (their messenger): they rejected
 Our servant, and said, "Here is one possessed!", and he was driven out.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then he called on his Lord: "I am one overcome: do Thou then help (me)!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So We opened the gates of heaven, with water pouring forth.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We caused the earth to gush forth with springs, so the waters met (and
 rose) to the extent decreed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But We bore him on an (Ark) made of broad planks and caulked with palm-fibre:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
She floats under our eyes (and care): a recompense to one who had been rejected
 (with scorn)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We have left this as a Sign (for all time): then is there any that will
 receive admonition?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But how (terrible) was My Penalty and My Warning?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We have indeed made the Qur'an easy to understand and remember: then
 is there any that will receive admonition?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The 'Ad (people) (too) rejected (Truth): then how terrible was My Penalty
 and My Warning?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For We sent against them a furious wind, on a Day of violent Disaster,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Plucking out men as if they were roots of palm-trees torn up (from the ground).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Yea, how (terrible) was My Penalty and My Warning!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But We have indeed made the Qur'an easy to understand and remember: then
 is there any that will receive admonition?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Thamud (also) rejected (their) Warners.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For they said: "What! a man! a Solitary one from among ourselves! shall
 we follow such a one? Truly should we then be straying in mind, and mad!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Is it that the Message is sent to him, of all people amongst us? Nay, he
 is a liar, an insolent one!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ah! they will know on the morrow, which is the liar, the insolent one!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For We will send the she-camel by way of trial for them.
 So watch them, (O Salih), and possess thyself in patience!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And tell them that the water is to be divided between them: Each one's right
 to drink being brought forward (by suitable turns).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But they called to their companion, and he took a sword in hand, and hamstrung
 (her).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ah! how (terrible) was My Penalty and My Warning!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For We sent against them a single Mighty Blast, and they became like the
 dry stubble used by one who pens cattle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We have indeed made the Qur'an easy to understand and remember: then
 is there any that will receive admonition?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The people of Lut rejected (his) warning.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We sent against them a violent Tornado with showers of stones, (which destroyed
 them), except Lut's household: them We delivered by early Dawn,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As a Grace from Us: thus do We reward those who give thanks.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And (Lut) did warn them of Our Punishment, but they disputed about the Warning.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they even sought to snatch away his guests from him, but We blinded
 their eyes.
 (They heard:) "Now taste ye My Wrath and My Warning."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Early on the morrow an abiding Punishment seized them:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"So taste ye My Wrath and My Warning."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We have indeed made the Qur'an easy to understand and remember: then
 is there any that will receive admonition?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To the People of Pharaoh, too, aforetime, came Warners (from Allah).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The (people) rejected all Our Signs; but We seized them with such Penalty
 (as comes) from One Exalted in Power, able to carry out His Will.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Are your Unbelievers, (O Quraish), better than they? Or have ye an immunity
 in the Sacred Books?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or do they say: "We acting together can defend ourselves"?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Soon will their multitude be put to flight, and they will show their backs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, the Hour (of Judgment) is the time promised them (for their full recompense
): And that Hour will be most grievous and most bitter.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly those in sin are the ones straying in mind, and mad.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day they will be dragged through the Fire on their faces, (they will
 hear:) "Taste ye the touch of Hell!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily, all things have We created in proportion and measure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Our Command is but a single (Act),- like the twinkling of an eye.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And (oft) in the past, have We destroyed gangs like unto you: then is there
 any that will receive admonition?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
All that they do is noted in (their) Books (of Deeds):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Every matter, small and great, is on record.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As to the Righteous, they will be in the midst of Gardens and Rivers,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In an Assembly of Truth, in the Presence of a Sovereign Omnipotent.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Allah) Most Gracious!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who has taught the Qur'an.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He has created man:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He has taught him speech (and intelligence).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The sun and the moon follow courses (exactly) computed;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the herbs and the trees - both (alike) prostrate in adoration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Firmament has He raised high, and He has set up the Balance (of
 Justice),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In order that ye may not transgress (due) balance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So establish weight with justice and fall not short in the balance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who has spread out the earth for (His) creatures:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therein is fruit and date-palms, producing spathes (enclosing dates);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Also corn, with (its) leaves and stalk for fodder, and sweet-smelling plants.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He created man from sounding clay like unto pottery,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He created Jinns from fire free of smoke:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(He is) Lord of the two Easts and Lord of the two Wests:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He has let free the two bodies of flowing water, meeting together:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Between them is a Barrier which they do not transgress:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Out of them come Pearls and Coral:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And His are the Ships sailing smoothly through the seas, lofty as mountains:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
All that is on earth will perish:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But will abide (for ever) the Face of thy Lord,- full of Majesty, Bounty
 and Honour.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Of Him seeks (its need) every creature in the heavens and on earth: every
 day in (new) Splendour doth He (shine)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Soon shall We settle your affairs, O both ye worlds!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye assembly of Jinns and men! If it be ye can pass beyond the zones of
 the heavens and the earth, pass ye! not without authority shall ye be able
 to pass!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On you will be sent (O ye evil ones twain!) a flame of fire (to burn) and
 a smoke (to choke): no defence will ye have:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the sky is rent asunder, and it becomes red like ointment:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On that Day no question will be asked of man or Jinn as to his sin.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(For) the sinners will be known by their marks: and they will be seized
 by their forelocks and their feet.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This is the Hell which the Sinners deny:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In its midst and in the midst of boiling hot water will they wander round!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But for such as fear the time when they will stand before (the Judgment
 Seat of) their Lord, there will be two Gardens-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Containing all kinds (of trees and delights);-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In them (each) will be two Springs flowing (free);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In them will be Fruits of every kind, two and two.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will recline on Carpets, whose inner linings will be of rich brocade:
 the Fruit of the Gardens will be near (and easy of reach).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In them will be (Maidens), chaste, restraining their glances, whom no man
 or Jinn before them has touched;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Like unto Rubies and coral.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is there any Reward for Good - other than Good?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And besides these two, there are two other Gardens,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Dark-green in colour (from plentiful watering).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In them (each) will be two Springs pouring forth water in continuous abundance:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In them will be Fruits, and dates and pomegranates:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In them will be fair (Companions), good, beautiful;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Companions restrained (as to their glances), in (goodly) pavilions;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whom no man or Jinn before them has touched;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Reclining on green Cushions and rich Carpets of beauty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then which of the favours of your Lord will ye deny?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Blessed be the name of thy Lord, full of Majesty, Bounty and Honour.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the Event inevitable cometh to pass,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then will no (soul) entertain falsehood concerning its coming.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Many) will it bring low; (many) will it exalt;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the earth shall be shaken to its depths,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the mountains shall be crumbled to atoms,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Becoming dust scattered abroad,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And ye shall be sorted out into three classes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then (there will be) the Companions of the Right Hand;- What will be the
 Companions of the Right Hand?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Companions of the Left Hand,- what will be the Companions of the
 Left Hand?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those Foremost (in Faith) will be Foremost (in the Hereafter).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
These will be those Nearest to Allah:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In Gardens of Bliss:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A number of people from those of old,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And a few from those of later times.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(They will be) on Thrones encrusted (with gold and precious stones),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Reclining on them, facing each other.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Round about them will (serve) youths of perpetual (freshness),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With goblets, (shining) beakers, and cups (filled) out of clear-flowing
 fountains:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No after-ache will they receive therefrom, nor will they suffer intoxication:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And with fruits, any that they may select:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the flesh of fowls, any that they may desire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And (there will be) Companions with beautiful, big, and lustrous eyes,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Like unto Pearls well-guarded.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A Reward for the deeds of their past (life).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Not frivolity will they hear therein, nor any taint of ill,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Only the saying, "Peace! Peace".
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Companions of the Right Hand,- what will be the Companions of the Right
 Hand?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(They will be) among Lote-trees without thorns,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Among Talh trees with flowers (or fruits) piled one above another,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In shade long-extended,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By water flowing constantly,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And fruit in abundance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whose season is not limited, nor (supply) forbidden,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And on Thrones (of Dignity), raised high.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have created (their Companions) of special creation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And made them virgin - pure (and undefiled), -
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Beloved (by nature), equal in age,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For the Companions of the Right Hand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A (goodly) number from those of old,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And a (goodly) number from those of later times.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Companions of the Left Hand,- what will be the Companions of the Left
 Hand?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(They will be) in the midst of a Fierce Blast of Fire and in Boiling Water,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And in the shades of Black Smoke:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nothing (will there be) to refresh, nor to please:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For that they were wont to be indulged, before that, in wealth (and luxury),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And persisted obstinately in wickedness supreme!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they used to say, "What! when we die and become dust and bones, shall
 we then indeed be raised up again?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"(We) and our fathers of old?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "Yea, those of old and those of later times,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"All will certainly be gathered together for the meeting appointed for a
 Day well-known.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Then will ye truly,- O ye that go wrong, and treat (Truth) as Falsehood!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Ye will surely taste of the Tree of Zaqqum.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Then will ye fill your insides therewith,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And drink Boiling Water on top of it:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Indeed ye shall drink like diseased camels raging with thirst!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such will be their entertainment on the Day of Requital!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is We Who have created you: why will ye not witness the Truth?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do ye then see?- The (human Seed) that ye throw out,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is it ye who create it, or are We the Creators?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have decreed Death to be your common lot, and We are not to be frustrated
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
from changing your Forms and creating you (again) in (forms) that ye know
 not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And ye certainly know already the first form of creation: why then do ye
 not celebrate His praises?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
See ye the seed that ye sow in the ground?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is it ye that cause it to grow, or are We the Cause?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Were it Our Will, We could crumble it to dry powder, and ye would be left
 in wonderment,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Saying), "We are indeed left with debts (for nothing):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Indeed are we shut out (of the fruits of our labour)"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
See ye the water which ye drink?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do ye bring it down (in rain) from the cloud or do We?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Were it Our Will, We could make it salt (and unpalatable): then why do ye
 not give thanks?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
See ye the Fire which ye kindle?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is it ye who grow the tree which feeds the fire, or do We grow it?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have made it a memorial (of Our handiwork), and an article of comfort
 and convenience for the denizens of deserts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then celebrate with praises the name of thy Lord, the Supreme!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Furthermore I call to witness the setting of the Stars,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And that is indeed a mighty adjuration if ye but knew,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That this is indeed a qur'an Most Honourable,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In Book well-guarded,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Which none shall touch but those who are clean:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A Revelation from the Lord of the Worlds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is it such a Message that ye would hold in light esteem?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And have ye made it your livelihood that ye should declare it false?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then why do ye not (intervene) when (the soul of the dying man) reaches
 the throat,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And ye the while (sit) looking on,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But We are nearer to him than ye, and yet see not,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then why do ye not,- If you are exempt from (future) account,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Call back the soul, if ye are true (in the claim of independence)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus, then, if he be of those Nearest to Allah,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(There is for him) Rest and Satisfaction, and a Garden of Delights.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if he be of the Companions of the Right Hand,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(For him is the salutation), "Peace be unto thee", from the Companions of
 the Right Hand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if he be of those who treat (Truth) as Falsehood, who go wrong,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For him is Entertainment with Boiling Water.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And burning in Hell-Fire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily, this is the Very Truth and Certainly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So celebrate with praises the name of thy Lord, the Supreme.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whatever is in the heavens and on earth,- let it declare the Praises and
 Glory of Allah: for He is the Exalted in Might, the Wise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Him belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth: It is He Who gives
 Life and Death; and He has Power over all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He is the First and the Last, the Evident and the Immanent: and He has full
 knowledge of all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He it is Who created the heavens and the earth in Six Days, and is moreover
 firmly established on the Throne (of Authority).
 He knows what enters within the earth and what comes forth out of it, what
 comes down from heaven and what mounts up to it.
 And He is with you wheresoever ye may be.
 And Allah sees well all that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To Him belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth: and all affairs
 are referred back to Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He merges Night into Day, and He merges Day into Night; and He has full
 knowledge of the secrets of (all) hearts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Believe in Allah and His messenger, and spend (in charity) out of the (substance
) whereof He has made you heirs.
 For, those of you who believe and spend (in charity),- for them is a great
 Reward.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What cause have ye why ye should not believe in Allah?- and the Messenger
 invites you to believe in your Lord, and has indeed taken your Covenant,
 if ye are men of Faith.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He is the One Who sends to His Servant Manifest Signs, that He may lead
 you from the depths of Darkness into the Light and verily Allah is to you
 most kind and Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And what cause have ye why ye should not spend in the cause of Allah?- For
 to Allah belongs the heritage of the heavens and the earth.
 Not equal among you are those who spent (freely) and fought, before the
 Victory, (with those who did so later).
 Those are higher in rank than those who spent (freely) and fought afterwards.
 But to all has Allah promised a goodly (reward).
 And Allah is well acquainted with all that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who is he that will Loan to Allah a beautiful loan? for (Allah) will increase
 it manifold to his credit, and he will have (besides) a liberal Reward.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One Day shalt thou see the believing men and the believing women- how their
 Light runs forward before them and by their right hands: (their greeting
 will be): "Good News for you this Day! Gardens beneath which flow rivers!
 to dwell therein for aye! This is indeed the highest Achievement!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One Day will the Hypocrites- men and women - say to the Believers: "Wait
 for us! Let us borrow (a Light) from your Light!" It will be said: "Turn
 ye back to your rear! then seek a Light (where ye can)!" So a wall will
 be put up betwixt them, with a gate therein.
 Within it will be Mercy throughout, and without it, all alongside, will
 be (Wrath and) Punishment!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Those without) will call out, "Were we not with you?" (The others) will
 reply, "True! but ye led yourselves into temptation; ye looked forward
 (to our ruin); ye doubted (Allah's Promise); and (your false) desires deceived
 you; until there issued the Command of Allah.
 And the Deceiver deceived you in respect of Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"This Day shall no ransom be accepted of you, nor of those who rejected
 Allah." Your abode is the Fire: that is the proper place to claim you: and
 an evil refuge it is!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Has not the Time arrived for the Believers that their hearts in all humility
 should engage in the remembrance of Allah and of the Truth which has been
 revealed (to them), and that they should not become like those to whom
 was given Revelation aforetime, but long ages passed over them and their
 hearts grew hard? For many among them are rebellious transgressors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Know ye (all) that Allah giveth life to the earth after its death! already
 have We shown the Signs plainly to you, that ye may learn wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For those who give in Charity, men and women, and loan to Allah a Beautiful
 Loan, it shall be increased manifold (to their credit), and they shall
 have (besides) a liberal reward.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who believe in Allah and His messengers- they are the Sincere
 (lovers of Truth), and the witnesses (who testify), in the eyes of their
 Lord: They shall have their Reward and their Light.
 But those who reject Allah and deny Our Signs,- they are the Companions
 of Hell-Fire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Know ye (all), that the life of this world is but play and amusement, pomp
 and mutual boasting and multiplying, (in rivalry) among yourselves, riches
 and children.
 Here is a similitude: How rain and the growth which it brings forth, delight
 (the hearts of) the tillers; soon it withers; thou wilt see it grow yellow;
 then it becomes dry and crumbles away.
 But in the Hereafter is a Penalty severe (for the devotees of wrong).
 And Forgiveness from Allah and (His) Good Pleasure (for the devotees of
 Allah).
 And what is the life of this world, but goods and chattels of deception?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Be ye foremost (in seeking) Forgiveness from your Lord, and a Garden (of
 Bliss), the width whereof is as the width of heaven and earth, prepared
 for those who believe in Allah and His messengers: that is the Grace of
 Allah, which He bestows on whom he pleases: and Allah is the Lord of Grace
 abounding.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No misfortune can happen on earth or in your souls but is recorded in a
 decree before We bring it into existence: That is truly easy for Allah:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In order that ye may not despair over matters that pass you by, nor exult
 over favours bestowed upon you.
 For Allah loveth not any vainglorious boaster,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such persons as are covetous and commend covetousness to men.
 And if any turn back (from Allah's Way), verily Allah is Free of all Needs,
 Worthy of all Praise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We sent aforetime our messengers with Clear Signs and sent down with them
 the Book and the Balance (of Right and Wrong), that men may stand forth
 in justice; and We sent down Iron, in which is (material for) mighty war,
 as well as many benefits for mankind, that Allah may test who it is that
 will help, Unseen, Him and His messengers: For Allah is Full of Strength,
 Exalted in Might (and able to enforce His Will).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We sent Noah and Abraham, and established in their line Prophethood
 and Revelation: and some of them were on right guidance.
 But many of them became rebellious transgressors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, in their wake, We followed them up with (others of) Our messengers:
 We sent after them Jesus the son of Mary, and bestowed on him the Gospel;
 and We ordained in the hearts of those who followed him Compassion and
 Mercy.
 But the Monasticism which they invented for themselves, We did not prescribe
 for them: (We commanded) only the seeking for the Good Pleasure of Allah;
 but that they did not foster as they should have done.
 Yet We bestowed, on those among them who believed, their (due) reward,
 but many of them are rebellious transgressors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye that believe! Fear Allah, and believe in His Messenger, and He will
 bestow on you a double portion of His Mercy: He will provide for you a
 Light by which ye shall walk (straight in your path), and He will forgive
 you (your past): for Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That the People of the Book may know that they have no power whatever over
 the Grace of Allah, that (His) Grace is (entirely) in His Hand, to bestow
 it on whomsoever He wills.
 For Allah is the Lord of Grace abounding.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah has indeed heard (and accepted) the statement of the woman who pleads
 with thee concerning her husband and carries her complaint (in prayer)
 to Allah: and Allah (always) hears the arguments between both sides among
 you: for Allah hears and sees (all things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If any men among you divorce their wives by Zihar (calling them mothers),
 they cannot be their mothers: None can be their mothers except those who
 gave them birth.
 And in fact they use words (both) iniquitous and false: but truly Allah
 is one that blots out (sins), and forgives (again and again).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those who divorce their wives by Zihar, then wish to go back on the
 words they uttered,- (It is ordained that such a one) should free a slave
 before they touch each other: Thus are ye admonished to perform: and Allah
 is well-acquainted with (all) that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if any has not (the wherewithal), he should fast for two months consecutivel
y before they touch each other.
 But if any is unable to do so, he should feed sixty indigent ones, this,
 that ye may show your faith in Allah and His Messenger.
 Those are limits (set by) Allah.
 For those who reject (Him), there is a grievous Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who resist Allah and His Messenger will be humbled to dust, as were
 those before them: for We have already sent down Clear Signs.
 And the Unbelievers (will have) a humiliating Penalty,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On the Day that Allah will raise them all up (again) and show them the Truth
 (and meaning) of their conduct.
 Allah has reckoned its (value), though they may have forgotten it, for
 Allah is Witness to all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou not that Allah doth know (all) that is in the heavens and on
 earth? There is not a secret consultation between three, but He makes the
 fourth among them, - Nor between five but He makes the sixth,- nor between
 fewer nor more, but He is in their midst, wheresoever they be: In the end
 will He tell them the truth of their conduct, on the Day of Judgment.
 For Allah has full knowledge of all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Turnest thou not thy sight towards those who were forbidden secret counsels
 yet revert to that which they were forbidden (to do)? And they hold secret
 counsels among themselves for iniquity and hostility, and disobedience
 to the Messenger.
 And when they come to thee, they salute thee, not as Allah salutes thee,
 (but in crooked ways): And they say to themselves, "Why does not Allah
 punish us for our words?" Enough for them is Hell: In it will they burn,
 and evil is that destination!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! When ye hold secret counsel, do it not for iniquity and
 hostility, and disobedience to the Prophet; but do it for righteousness
 and self-restraint; and fear Allah, to Whom ye shall be brought back.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Secret counsels are only (inspired) by the Evil One, in order that he may
 cause grief to the Believers; but he cannot harm them in the least, except
 as Allah permits; and on Allah let the Believers put their trust.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! When ye are told to make room in the assemblies, (spread
 out and) make room: (ample) room will Allah provide for you.
 And when ye are told to rise up, rise up Allah will rise up, to (suitable)
 ranks (and degrees), those of you who believe and who have been granted
 (mystic) Knowledge.
 And Allah is well-acquainted with all ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! When ye consult the Messenger in private, spend something
 in charity before your private consultation.
 That will be best for you, and most conducive to purity (of conduct).
 But if ye find not (the wherewithal), Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is it that ye are afraid of spending sums in charity before your private
 consultation (with him)? If, then, ye do not so, and Allah forgives you,
 then (at least) establish regular prayer; practise regular charity; and
 obey Allah and His Messenger.
 And Allah is well-acquainted with all that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Turnest thou not thy attention to those who turn (in friendship) to such
 as have the Wrath of Allah upon them? They are neither of you nor of them,
 and they swear to falsehood knowingly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah has prepared for them a severe Penalty: evil indeed are their deeds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They have made their oaths a screen (for their misdeeds): thus they obstruct
 (men) from the Path of Allah: therefore shall they have a humiliating Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Of no profit whatever to them, against Allah, will be their riches nor their
 sons: they will be Companions of the Fire, to dwell therein (for aye)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One day will Allah raise them all up (for Judgment): then will they swear
 to Him as they swear to you: And they think that they have something (to
 stand upon).
 No, indeed! they are but liars!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Evil One has got the better of them: so he has made them lose the remembranc
e of Allah.
 They are the Party of the Evil One.
 Truly, it is the Party of the Evil One that will perish!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who resist Allah and His Messenger will be among those most humiliated.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah has decreed: "It is I and My messengers who must prevail": For Allah
 is One full of strength, able to enforce His Will.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thou wilt not find any people who believe in Allah and the Last Day, loving
 those who resist Allah and His Messenger, even though they were their fathers
 or their sons, or their brothers, or their kindred.
 For such He has written Faith in their hearts, and strengthened them with
 a spirit from Himself.
 And He will admit them to Gardens beneath which Rivers flow, to dwell therein
 (for ever).
 Allah will be well pleased with them, and they with Him.
 They are the Party of Allah.
 Truly it is the Party of Allah that will achieve Felicity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whatever is in the heavens and on earth, let it declare the Praises and
 Glory of Allah: for He is the Exalted in Might, the Wise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who got out the Unbelievers among the People of the Book from their
 homes at the first gathering (of the forces).
 Little did ye think that they would get out: And they thought that their
 fortresses would defend them from Allah! But the (Wrath of) Allah came
 to them from quarters from which they little expected (it), and cast terror
 into their hearts, so that they destroyed their dwellings by their own
 hands and the hands of the Believers, take warning, then, O ye with eyes
 (to see)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And had it not been that Allah had decreed banishment for them, He would
 certainly have punished them in this world: And in the Hereafter they shall
 (certainly) have the Punishment of the Fire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That is because they resisted Allah and His Messenger: and if any one resists
 Allah, verily Allah is severe in Punishment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whether ye cut down (O ye Muslim!) The tender palm-trees, or ye left them
 standing on their roots, it was by leave of Allah, and in order that He
 might cover with shame the rebellious transgresses.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What Allah has bestowed on His Messenger (and taken away) from them - for
 this ye made no expedition with either cavalry or camelry: but Allah gives
 power to His messengers over any He pleases: and Allah has power over all
 things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What Allah has bestowed on His Messenger (and taken away) from the people
 of the townships,- belongs to Allah,- to His Messenger and to kindred and
 orphans, the needy and the wayfarer; In order that it may not (merely)
 make a circuit between the wealthy among you.
 So take what the Messenger assigns to you, and deny yourselves that which
 he withholds from you.
 And fear Allah; for Allah is strict in Punishment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Some part is due) to the indigent Muhajirs, those who were expelled from
 their homes and their property, while seeking Grace from Allah and (His)
 Good Pleasure, and aiding Allah and His Messenger: such are indeed the
 sincere ones:-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those who before them, had homes (in Medina) and had adopted the Faith,-
 show their affection to such as came to them for refuge, and entertain
 no desire in their hearts for things given to the (latter), but give them
 preference over themselves, even though poverty was their (own lot).
 And those saved from the covetousness of their own souls,- they are the
 ones that achieve prosperity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who came after them say: "Our Lord! Forgive us, and our brethren
 who came before us into the Faith, and leave not, in our hearts, rancour
 (or sense of injury) against those who have believed.
 Our Lord! Thou art indeed Full of Kindness, Most Merciful."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Hast thou not observed the Hypocrites say to their misbelieving brethren
 among the People of the Book? - "If ye are expelled, we too will go out
 with you, and we will never hearken to any one in your affair; and if ye
 are attacked (in fight) we will help you".
 But Allah is witness that they are indeed liars.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If they are expelled, never will they go out with them; and if they are
 attacked (in fight), they will never help them; and if they do help them,
 they will turn their backs; so they will receive no help.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Of a truth ye are stronger (than they) because of the terror in their hearts,
 (sent) by Allah.
 This is because they are men devoid of understanding.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will not fight you (even) together, except in fortified townships,
 or from behind walls.
 Strong is their fighting (spirit) amongst themselves: thou wouldst think
 they were united, but their hearts are divided: that is because they are
 a people devoid of wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Like those who lately preceded them, they have tasted the evil result of
 their conduct; and (in the Hereafter there is) for them a grievous Penalty;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Their allies deceived them), like the Evil One, when he says to man, "Deny
 Allah": but when (man) denies Allah, (the Evil One) says, "I am free of
 thee: I do fear Allah, the Lord of the Worlds!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The end of both will be that they will go into the Fire, dwelling therein
 for ever.
 Such is the reward of the wrong-doers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Fear Allah, and let every soul look to what (provision)
 He has sent forth for the morrow.
 Yea, fear Allah: for Allah is well-acquainted with (all) that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And be ye not like those who forgot Allah; and He made them forget their
 own souls! Such are the rebellious transgressors!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Not equal are the Companions of the Fire and the Companions of the Garden:
 it is the Companions of the Garden, that will achieve Felicity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Had We sent down this Qur'an on a mountain, verily, thou wouldst have seen
 it humble itself and cleave asunder for fear of Allah.
 Such are the similitudes which We propound to men, that they may reflect.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah is He, than Whom there is no other god;- Who knows (all things) both
 secret and open; He, Most Gracious, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah is He, than Whom there is no other god;- the Sovereign, the Holy One,
 the Source of Peace (and Perfection), the Guardian of Faith, the Preserver
 of Safety, the Exalted in Might, the Irresistible, the Supreme: Glory to
 Allah! (High is He) above the partners they attribute to Him.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He is Allah, the Creator, the Evolver, the Bestower of Forms (or Colours).
 To Him belong the Most Beautiful Names: whatever is in the heavens and
 on earth, doth declare His Praises and Glory: and He is the Exalted in
 Might, the Wise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Take not my enemies and yours as friends (or protectors),-
 offering them (your) love, even though they have rejected the Truth that
 has come to you, and have (on the contrary) driven out the Prophet and
 yourselves (from your homes), (simply) because ye believe in Allah your
 Lord! If ye have come out to strive in My Way and to seek My Good Pleasure,
 (take them not as friends), holding secret converse of love (and friendship)
 with them: for I know full well all that ye conceal and all that ye reveal.
 And any of you that does this has strayed from the Straight Path.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If they were to get the better of you, they would behave to you as enemies,
 and stretch forth their hands and their tongues against you for evil: and
 they desire that ye should reject the Truth.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Of no profit to you will be your relatives and your children on the Day
 of Judgment: He will judge between you: for Allah sees well all that ye
 do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There is for you an excellent example (to follow) in Abraham and those with
 him, when they said to their people: "We are clear of you and of whatever
 ye worship besides Allah: we have rejected you, and there has arisen, between
 us and you, enmity and hatred for ever,- unless ye believe in Allah and
 Him alone": But not when Abraham said to his father: "I will pray for forgivene
ss for thee, though I have no power (to get) aught on thy behalf from Allah."
 (They prayed): "Our Lord! in Thee do we trust, and to Thee do we turn in
 repentance: to Thee is (our) Final Goal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Our Lord! Make us not a (test and) trial for the Unbelievers, but forgive
 us, our Lord! for Thou art the Exalted in Might, the Wise."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There was indeed in them an excellent example for you to follow,- for those
 whose hope is in Allah and in the Last Day.
 But if any turn away, truly Allah is Free of all Wants, Worthy of all Praise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It may be that Allah will grant love (and friendship) between you and those
 whom ye (now) hold as enemies.
 For Allah has power (over all things); And Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most
 Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah forbids you not, with regard to those who fight you not for (your)
 Faith nor drive you out of your homes, from dealing kindly and justly with
 them: for Allah loveth those who are just.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah only forbids you, with regard to those who fight you for (your) Faith,
 and drive you out of your homes, and support (others) in driving you out,
 from turning to them (for friendship and protection).
 It is such as turn to them (in these circumstances), that do wrong.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! When there come to you believing women refugees, examine
 (and test) them: Allah knows best as to their Faith: if ye ascertain that
 they are Believers, then send them not back to the Unbelievers.
 They are not lawful (wives) for the Unbelievers, nor are the (Unbelievers)
 lawful (husbands) for them.
 But pay the Unbelievers what they have spent (on their dower), and there
 will be no blame on you if ye marry them on payment of their dower to them.
 But hold not to the guardianship of unbelieving women: ask for what ye
 have spent on their dowers, and let the (Unbelievers) ask for what they
 have spent (on the dowers of women who come over to you).
 Such is the command of Allah: He judges (with justice) between you.
 And Allah is Full of Knowledge and Wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if any of your wives deserts you to the Unbelievers, and ye have an
 accession (by the coming over of a woman from the other side), then pay
 to those whose wives have deserted the equivalent of what they had spent
 (on their dower).
 And fear Allah, in Whom ye believe.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O Prophet! When believing women come to thee to take the oath of fealty
 to thee, that they will not associate in worship any other thing whatever
 with Allah, that they will not steal, that they will not commit adultery
 (or fornication), that they will not kill their children, that they will
 not utter slander, intentionally forging falsehood, and that they will
 not disobey thee in any just matter,- then do thou receive their fealty,
 and pray to Allah for the forgiveness (of their sins): for Allah is Oft-Forgivi
ng, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Turn not (for friendship) to people on whom is the Wrath
 of Allah, of the Hereafter they are already in despair, just as the Unbelievers
 are in despair about those (buried) in graves.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whatever is in the heavens and on earth, let it declare the Praises and
 Glory of Allah: for He is the Exalted in Might, the Wise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Why say ye that which ye do not?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Grievously odious is it in the sight of Allah that ye say that which ye
 do not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly Allah loves those who fight in His Cause in battle array, as if they
 were a solid cemented structure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And remember, Moses said to his people: "O my people! why do ye vex and
 insult me, though ye know that I am the messenger of Allah (sent) to you?"
 Then when they went wrong, Allah let their hearts go wrong.
 For Allah guides not those who are rebellious transgressors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And remember, Jesus, the son of Mary, said: "O Children of Israel! I am
 the messenger of Allah (sent) to you, confirming the Law (which came) before
 me, and giving Glad Tidings of a Messenger to come after me, whose name
 shall be Ahmad." But when he came to them with Clear Signs, they said, "this
 is evident sorcery!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who doth greater wrong than one who invents falsehood against Allah, even
 as he is being invited to Islam? And Allah guides not those who do wrong.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Their intention is to extinguish Allah's Light (by blowing) with their mouths:
 But Allah will complete (the revelation of) His Light, even though the
 Unbelievers may detest (it).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who has sent His Messenger with Guidance and the Religion of Truth,
 that he may proclaim it over all religion, even though the Pagans may detest
 (it).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Shall I lead you to a bargain that will save you from
 a grievous Penalty?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That ye believe in Allah and His Messenger, and that ye strive (your utmost)
 in the Cause of Allah, with your property and your persons: That will be
 best for you, if ye but knew!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He will forgive you your sins, and admit you to Gardens beneath which Rivers
 flow, and to beautiful mansions in Gardens of Eternity: that is indeed
 the Supreme Achievement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And another (favour will He bestow,) which ye do love,- help from Allah
 and a speedy victory.
 So give the Glad Tidings to the Believers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Be ye helpers of Allah: As said Jesus the son of Mary
 to the Disciples, "Who will be my helpers to (the work of) Allah?" Said
 the disciples, "We are Allah's helpers!" then a portion of the Children
 of Israel believed, and a portion disbelieved: But We gave power to those
 who believed, against their enemies, and they became the ones that prevailed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whatever is in the heavens and on earth, doth declare the Praises and Glory
 of Allah,- the Sovereign, the Holy One, the Exalted in Might, the Wise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who has sent amongst the Unlettered a messenger from among themselves,
 to rehearse to them His Signs, to sanctify them, and to instruct them in
 Scripture and Wisdom,- although they had been, before, in manifest error;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As well as (to confer all these benefits upon) others of them, who have
 not already joined them: And He is exalted in Might, Wise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such is the Bounty of Allah, which He bestows on whom He will: and Allah
 is the Lord of the highest bounty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The similitude of those who were charged with the (obligations of the) Mosaic
 Law, but who subsequently failed in those (obligations), is that of a donkey
 which carries huge tomes (but understands them not).
 Evil is the similitude of people who falsify the Signs of Allah: and Allah
 guides not people who do wrong.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "O ye that stand on Judaism! If ye think that ye are friends to Allah,
 to the exclusion of (other) men, then express your desire for Death, if
 ye are truthful!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But never will they express their desire (for Death), because of the (deeds)
 their hands have sent on before them! and Allah knows well those that do
 wrong!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "The Death from which ye flee will truly overtake you: then will ye
 be sent back to the Knower of things secret and open: and He will tell
 you (the truth of) the things that ye did!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! When the call is proclaimed to prayer on Friday (the Day
 of Assembly), hasten earnestly to the Remembrance of Allah, and leave off
 business (and traffic): That is best for you if ye but knew!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when the Prayer is finished, then may ye disperse through the land,
 and seek of the Bounty of Allah: and celebrate the Praises of Allah often
 (and without stint): that ye may prosper.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But when they see some bargain or some amusement, they disperse headlong
 to it, and leave thee standing.
 Say: "The (blessing) from the Presence of Allah is better than any amusement
 or bargain! and Allah is the Best to provide (for all needs)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the Hypocrites come to thee, they say, "We bear witness that thou art
 indeed the Messenger of Allah." Yea, Allah knoweth that thou art indeed
 His Messenger, and Allah beareth witness that the Hypocrites are indeed
 liars.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They have made their oaths a screen (for their misdeeds): thus they obstruct
 (men) from the Path of Allah: truly evil are their deeds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That is because they believed, then they rejected Faith: So a seal was set
 on their hearts: therefore they understand not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When thou lookest at them, their exteriors please thee; and when they speak,
 thou listenest to their words.
 They are as (worthless as hollow) pieces of timber propped up, (unable
 to stand on their own).
 They think that every cry is against them.
 They are the enemies; so beware of them.
 The curse of Allah be on them! How are they deluded (away from the Truth)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when it is said to them, "Come, the Messenger of Allah will pray for
 your forgiveness", they turn aside their heads, and thou wouldst see them
 turning away their faces in arrogance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is equal to them whether thou pray for their forgiveness or not.
 Allah will not forgive them.
 Truly Allah guides not rebellious transgressors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They are the ones who say, "Spend nothing on those who are with Allah's
 Messenger, to the end that they may disperse (and quit Medina)." But to
 Allah belong the treasures of the heavens and the earth; but the Hypocrites
 understand not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They say, "If we return to Medina, surely the more honourable (element)
 will expel therefrom the meaner." But honour belongs to Allah and His Messenger,
 and to the Believers; but the Hypocrites know not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Let not your riches or your children divert you from the
 remembrance of Allah.
 If any act thus, the loss is their own.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
and spend something (in charity) out of the substance which We have bestowed
 on you, before Death should come to any of you and he should say, "O my
 Lord! why didst Thou not give me respite for a little while? I should then
 have given (largely) in charity, and I should have been one of the doers
 of good".
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But to no soul will Allah grant respite when the time appointed (for it)
 has come; and Allah is well acquainted with (all) that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Whatever is in the heavens and on earth, doth declare the Praises and Glory
 of Allah: to Him belongs dominion, and to Him belongs praise: and He has
 power over all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who has created you; and of you are some that are Unbelievers,
 and some that are Believers: and Allah sees well all that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He has created the heavens and the earth in just proportions, and has given
 you shape, and made your shapes beautiful: and to Him is the final Goal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He knows what is in the heavens and on earth; and He knows what ye conceal
 and what ye reveal: yea, Allah knows well the (secrets) of (all) hearts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Has not the story reached you, of those who rejected Faith aforetime? So
 they tasted the evil result of their conduct; and they had a grievous Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That was because there came to them messengers with Clear Signs, but they
 said: "Shall (mere) human beings direct us?" So they rejected (the Message)
 and turned away.
 But Allah can do without (them): and Allah is free of all needs, worthy
 of all praise.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Unbelievers think that they will not be raised up (for Judgment).
 Say: "Yea, By my Lord, Ye shall surely be raised up: then shall ye be told
 (the truth) of all that ye did.
 And that is easy for Allah."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Believe, therefore, in Allah and His Messenger, and in the Light which we
 have sent down.
 And Allah is well acquainted with all that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day that He assembles you (all) for a Day of Assembly,- that will be
 a Day of mutual loss and gain (among you), and those who believe in Allah
 and work righteousness,- He will remove from them their ills, and He will
 admit them to Gardens beneath which Rivers flow, to dwell therein for ever:
 that will be the Supreme Achievement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those who reject Faith and treat Our Signs as falsehoods, they will
 be Companions of the Fire, to dwell therein for aye: and evil is that Goal.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No kind of calamity can occur, except by the leave of Allah: and if any
 one believes in Allah, (Allah) guides his heart (aright): for Allah knows
 all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So obey Allah, and obey His Messenger: but if ye turn back, the duty of
 Our Messenger is but to proclaim (the Message) clearly and openly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah! There is no god but He: and on Allah, therefore, let the Believers
 put their trust.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Truly, among your wives and your children are (some that
 are) enemies to yourselves: so beware of them! But if ye forgive and overlook,
 and cover up (their faults), verily Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Your riches and your children may be but a trial: but in the Presence of
 Allah, is the highest, Reward.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So fear Allah as much as ye can; listen and obey and spend in charity for
 the benefit of your own soul and those saved from the covetousness of their
 own souls,- they are the ones that achieve prosperity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If ye loan to Allah, a beautiful loan, He will double it to your (credit),
 and He will grant you Forgiveness: for Allah is most Ready to appreciate
 (service), Most Forbearing,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Knower of what is open, Exalted in Might, Full of Wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O Prophet! When ye do divorce women, divorce them at their prescribed periods,
 and count (accurately), their prescribed periods: And fear Allah your Lord:
 and turn them not out of their houses, nor shall they (themselves) leave,
 except in case they are guilty of some open lewdness, those are limits
 set by Allah: and any who transgresses the limits of Allah, does verily
 wrong his (own) soul: thou knowest not if perchance Allah will bring about
 thereafter some new situation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus when they fulfil their term appointed, either take them back on equitable
 terms or part with them on equitable terms; and take for witness two persons
 from among you, endued with justice, and establish the evidence (as) before
 Allah.
 Such is the admonition given to him who believes in Allah and the Last
 Day.
 And for those who fear Allah, He (ever) prepares a way out,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He provides for him from (sources) he never could imagine.
 And if any one puts his trust in Allah, sufficient is (Allah) for him.
 For Allah will surely accomplish his purpose: verily, for all things has
 Allah appointed a due proportion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such of your women as have passed the age of monthly courses, for them the
 prescribed period, if ye have any doubts, is three months, and for those
 who have no courses (it is the same): for those who carry (life within
 their wombs), their period is until they deliver their burdens: and for
 those who fear Allah, He will make their path easy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That is the Command of Allah, which He has sent down to you: and if any
 one fears Allah, He will remove his ills, from him, and will enlarge his
 reward.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let the women live (in 'iddat) in the same style as ye live, according to
 your means: Annoy them not, so as to restrict them.
 And if they carry (life in their wombs), then spend (your substance) on
 them until they deliver their burden: and if they suckle your (offspring),
 give them their recompense: and take mutual counsel together, according
 to what is just and reasonable.
 And if ye find yourselves in difficulties, let another woman suckle (the
 child) on the (father's) behalf.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let the man of means spend according to his means: and the man whose resources
 are restricted, let him spend according to what Allah has given him.
 Allah puts no burden on any person beyond what He has given him.
 After a difficulty, Allah will soon grant relief.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
How many populations that insolently opposed the Command of their Lord and
 of His messengers, did We not then call to account,- to severe account?-
 and We imposed on them an exemplary Punishment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then did they taste the evil result of their conduct, and the End of their
 conduct was Perdition.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah has prepared for them a severe Punishment (in the Hereafter).
 Therefore fear Allah, O ye men of understanding - who have believed!- for
 Allah hath indeed sent down to you a Message,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
An Messenger, who rehearses to you the Signs of Allah containing clear explanati
ons, that he may lead forth those who believe and do righteous deeds from
 the depths of Darkness into Light.
 And those who believe in Allah and work righteousness, He will admit to
 Gardens beneath which Rivers flow, to dwell therein for ever: Allah has
 indeed granted for them a most excellent Provision.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah is He Who created seven Firmaments and of the earth a similar number.
 Through the midst of them (all) descends His Command: that ye may know
 that Allah has power over all things, and that Allah comprehends, all things
 in (His) Knowledge.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O Prophet! Why holdest thou to be forbidden that which Allah has made lawful
 to thee? Thou seekest to please thy consorts.
 But Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah has already ordained for you, (O men), the dissolution of your oaths
 (in some cases): and Allah is your Protector, and He is Full of Knowledge
 and Wisdom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the Prophet disclosed a matter in confidence to one of his consorts,
 and she then divulged it (to another), and Allah made it known to him,
 he confirmed part thereof and repudiated a part.
 Then when he told her thereof, she said, "Who told thee this? "He said,
 "He told me Who knows and is well-acquainted (with all things)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
If ye two turn in repentance to Him, your hearts are indeed so inclined;
 But if ye back up each other against him, truly Allah is his Protector,
 and Gabriel, and (every) righteous one among those who believe,- and furthermor
e, the angels - will back (him) up.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It may be, if he divorced you (all), that Allah will give him in exchange
 consorts better than you,- who submit (their wills), who believe, who are
 devout, who turn to Allah in repentance, who worship (in humility), who
 travel (for Faith) and fast,- previously married or virgins.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! save yourselves and your families from a Fire whose fuel
 is Men and Stones, over which are (appointed) angels stern (and) severe,
 who flinch not (from executing) the Commands they receive from Allah, but
 do (precisely) what they are commanded.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(They will say), "O ye Unbelievers! Make no excuses this Day! Ye are being
 but requited for all that ye did!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O ye who believe! Turn to Allah with sincere repentance: In the hope that
 your Lord will remove from you your ills and admit you to Gardens beneath
 which Rivers flow,- the Day that Allah will not permit to be humiliated
 the Prophet and those who believe with him.
 Their Light will run forward before them and by their right hands, while
 they say, "Our Lord! Perfect our Light for us, and grant us Forgiveness:
 for Thou hast power over all things."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O Prophet! Strive hard against the Unbelievers and the Hypocrites, and be
 firm against them.
 Their abode is Hell,- an evil refuge (indeed).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah sets forth, for an example to the Unbelievers, the wife of Noah and
 the wife of Lut: they were (respectively) under two of our righteous servants,
 but they were false to their (husbands), and they profited nothing before
 Allah on their account, but were told: "Enter ye the Fire along with (others)
 that enter!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Allah sets forth, as an example to those who believe the wife of Pharaoh:
 Behold she said: "O my Lord! Build for me, in nearness to Thee, a mansion
 in the Garden, and save me from Pharaoh and his doings, and save me from
 those that do wrong";
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Mary the daughter of 'Imran, who guarded her chastity; and We breathed
 into (her body) of Our spirit; and she testified to the truth of the words
 of her Lord and of His Revelations, and was one of the devout (servants).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Blessed be He in Whose hands is Dominion; and He over all things hath Power;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He Who created Death and Life, that He may try which of you is best in deed:
 and He is the Exalted in Might, Oft-Forgiving;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He Who created the seven heavens one above another: No want of proportion
 wilt thou see in the Creation of (Allah) Most Gracious.
 So turn thy vision again: seest thou any flaw?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Again turn thy vision a second time: (thy) vision will come back to thee
 dull and discomfited, in a state worn out.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And we have, (from of old), adorned the lowest heaven with Lamps, and We
 have made such (Lamps) (as) missiles to drive away the Evil Ones, and have
 prepared for them the Penalty of the Blazing Fire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For those who reject their Lord (and Cherisher) is the Penalty of Hell:
 and evil is (such), Destination.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When they are cast therein, they will hear the (terrible) drawing in of
 its breath even as it blazes forth,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Almost bursting with fury: Every time a Group is cast therein, its Keepers
 will ask, "Did no Warner come to you?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will say: "Yes indeed; a Warner did come to us, but we rejected him
 and said, 'Allah never sent down any (Message): ye are nothing but an egregious
 delusion!'"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will further say: "Had we but listened or used our intelligence, we
 should not (now) be among the Companions of the Blazing Fire!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They will then confess their sins: but far will be (Forgiveness) from the
 Companions of the Blazing Fire!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As for those who fear their Lord unseen, for them is Forgiveness and a great
 Reward.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And whether ye hide your word or publish it, He certainly has (full) knowledge,
 of the secrets of (all) hearts.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Should He not know,- He that created? and He is the One that understands
 the finest mysteries (and) is well-acquainted (with them).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who has made the earth manageable for you, so traverse ye through
 its tracts and enjoy of the Sustenance which He furnishes: but unto Him
 is the Resurrection.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do ye feel secure that He Who is in heaven will not cause you to be swallowed
 up by the earth when it shakes (as in an earthquake)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or do ye feel secure that He Who is in Heaven will not send against you
 a violent tornado (with showers of stones), so that ye shall know how (terrible
) was My warning?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But indeed men before them rejected (My warning): then how (terrible) was
 My rejection (of them)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they not observe the birds above them, spreading their wings and folding
 them in? None can uphold them except (Allah) Most Gracious: Truly (Allah)
 Most Gracious: Truly it is He that watches over all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, who is there that can help you, (even as) an army, besides (Allah)
 Most Merciful? In nothing but delusion are the Unbelievers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or who is there that can provide you with Sustenance if He were to withhold
 His provision? Nay, they obstinately persist in insolent impiety and flight
 (from the Truth).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is then one who walks headlong, with his face grovelling, better guided,-
 or one who walks evenly on a Straight Way?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "It is He Who has created you (and made you grow), and made for you
 the faculties of hearing, seeing, feeling and understanding: little thanks
 it is ye give.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "It is He Who has multiplied you through the earth, and to Him shall
 ye be gathered together."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They ask: When will this promise be (fulfilled)? - If ye are telling the
 truth.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "As to the knowledge of the time, it is with Allah alone: I am (sent)
 only to warn plainly in public."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At length, when they see it close at hand, grieved will be the faces of
 the Unbelievers, and it will be said (to them): "This is (the promise fulfilled
), which ye were calling for!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "See ye?- If Allah were to destroy me, and those with me, or if He
 bestows His Mercy on us,- yet who can deliver the Unbelievers from a grievous
 Penalty?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "He is (Allah) Most Gracious: We have believed in Him, and on Him have
 we put our trust: So, soon will ye know which (of us) it is that is in
 manifest error."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "See ye?- If your stream be some morning lost (in the underground earth),
 who then can supply you with clear-flowing water?"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nun.
 By the Pen and the (Record) which (men) write,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thou art not, by the Grace of thy Lord, mad or possessed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, verily for thee is a Reward unfailing:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And thou (standest) on an exalted standard of character.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Soon wilt thou see, and they will see,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Which of you is afflicted with madness.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily it is thy Lord that knoweth best, which (among men) hath strayed
 from His Path: and He knoweth best those who receive (true) Guidance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So hearken not to those who deny (the Truth).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Their desire is that thou shouldst be pliant: so would they be pliant.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Heed not the type of despicable men,- ready with oaths,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A slanderer, going about with calumnies,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Habitually) hindering (all) good, transgressing beyond bounds, deep in
 sin,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Violent (and cruel),- with all that, base-born,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Because he possesses wealth and (numerous) sons.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When to him are rehearsed Our Signs, "Tales of the ancients", he cries!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Soon shall We brand (the beast) on the snout!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily We have tried them as We tried the People of the Garden, when they
 resolved to gather the fruits of the (garden) in the morning.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But made no reservation, ("If it be Allah's Will").
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then there came on the (garden) a visitation from thy Lord, (which swept
 away) all around, while they were asleep.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So the (garden) became, by the morning, like a dark and desolate spot, (whose
 fruit had been gathered).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As the morning broke, they called out, one to another,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Go ye to your tilth (betimes) in the morning, if ye would gather the fruits."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So they departed, conversing in secret low tones, (saying)-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Let not a single indigent person break in upon you into the (garden) this
 day."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they opened the morning, strong in an (unjust) resolve.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But when they saw the (garden), they said: "We have surely lost our way:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Indeed we are shut out (of the fruits of our labour)!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Said one of them, more just (than the rest): "Did I not say to you, 'Why
 not glorify (Allah)?'"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "Glory to our Lord! Verily we have been doing wrong!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then they turned, one against another, in reproach.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They said: "Alas for us! We have indeed transgressed!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"It may be that our Lord will give us in exchange a better (garden) than
 this: for we do turn to Him (in repentance)!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such is the Punishment (in this life); but greater is the Punishment in
 the Hereafter,- if only they knew!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily, for the Righteous, are Gardens of Delight, in the Presence of their
 Lord.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Shall We then treat the People of Faith like the People of Sin?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What is the matter with you? How judge ye?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or have ye a book through which ye learn-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That ye shall have, through it whatever ye choose?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or have ye Covenants with Us to oath, reaching to the Day of Judgment, (providin
g) that ye shall have whatever ye shall demand?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ask thou of them, which of them will stand surety for that!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or have they some "Partners" (in Allahhead)? Then let them produce their
 "partners", if they are truthful!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day that the shin shall be laid bare, and they shall be summoned to
 bow in adoration, but they shall not be able,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Their eyes will be cast down,- ignominy will cover them; seeing that they
 had been summoned aforetime to bow in adoration, while they were whole,
 (and had refused).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then leave Me alone with such as reject this Message: by degrees shall We
 punish them from directions they perceive not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A (long) respite will I grant them: truly powerful is My Plan.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or is it that thou dost ask them for a reward, so that they are burdened
 with a load of debt?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or that the Unseen is in their hands, so that they can write it down?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So wait with patience for the Command of thy Lord, and be not like the Companion
 of the Fish,- when he cried out in agony.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Had not Grace from his Lord reached him, he would indeed have been cast
 off on the naked shore, in disgrace.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thus did his Lord choose him and make him of the Company of the Righteous.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Unbelievers would almost trip thee up with their eyes when they
 hear the Message; and they say: "Surely he is possessed!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But it is nothing less than a Message to all the worlds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Sure Reality!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What is the Sure Reality?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And what will make thee realise what the Sure Reality is?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Thamud and the 'Ad People (branded) as false the Stunning Calamity!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But the Thamud,- they were destroyed by a terrible Storm of thunder and
 lightning!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the 'Ad, they were destroyed by a furious Wind, exceedingly violent;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He made it rage against them seven nights and eight days in succession:
 so that thou couldst see the (whole) people lying prostrate in its (path),
 as they had been roots of hollow palm-trees tumbled down!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then seest thou any of them left surviving?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Pharaoh, and those before him, and the Cities Overthrown, committed
 habitual Sin.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And disobeyed (each) the messenger of their Lord; so He punished them with
 an abundant Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We, when the water (of Noah's Flood) overflowed beyond its limits, carried
 you (mankind), in the floating (Ark),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That We might make it a Message unto you, and that ears (that should hear
 the tale and) retain its memory should bear its (lessons) in remembrance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, when one blast is sounded on the Trumpet,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the earth is moved, and its mountains, and they are crushed to powder
 at one stroke,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On that Day shall the (Great) Event come to pass.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the sky will be rent asunder, for it will that Day be flimsy,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the angels will be on its sides, and eight will, that Day, bear the
 Throne of thy Lord above them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That Day shall ye be brought to Judgment: not an act of yours that ye hide
 will be hidden.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then he that will be given his Record in his right hand will say: "Ah here!
 Read ye my Record!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"I did really understand that my Account would (One Day) reach me!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And he will be in a life of Bliss,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In a Garden on high,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Fruits whereof (will hang in bunches) low and near.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Eat ye and drink ye, with full satisfaction; because of the (good) that
 ye sent before you, in the days that are gone!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And he that will be given his Record in his left hand, will say: "Ah! Would
 that my Record had not been given to me!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And that I had never realised how my account (stood)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Ah! Would that (Death) had made an end of me!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Of no profit to me has been my wealth!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"My power has perished from me!"...
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(The stern command will say): "Seize ye him, and bind ye him,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And burn ye him in the Blazing Fire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Further, make him march in a chain, whereof the length is seventy cubits!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"This was he that would not believe in Allah Most High.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And would not encourage the feeding of the indigent!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"So no friend hath he here this Day.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Nor hath he any food except the corruption from the washing of wounds,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Which none do eat but those in sin."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So I do call to witness what ye see,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And what ye see not,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That this is verily the word of an honoured messenger;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is not the word of a poet: little it is ye believe!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor is it the word of a soothsayer: little admonition it is ye receive.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(This is) a Message sent down from the Lord of the Worlds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And if the messenger were to invent any sayings in Our name,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We should certainly seize him by his right hand,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We should certainly then cut off the artery of his heart:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor could any of you withhold him (from Our wrath).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But verily this is a Message for the Allah-fearing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We certainly know that there are amongst you those that reject (it).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But truly (Revelation) is a cause of sorrow for the Unbelievers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But verily it is Truth of assured certainty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So glorify the name of thy Lord Most High.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A questioner asked about a Penalty to befall-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Unbelievers, the which there is none to ward off,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(A Penalty) from Allah, Lord of the Ways of Ascent.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The angels and the spirit ascend unto him in a Day the measure whereof is
 (as) fifty thousand years:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore do thou hold Patience,- a Patience of beautiful (contentment).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They see the (Day) indeed as a far-off (event):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But We see it (quite) near.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day that the sky will be like molten brass,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the mountains will be like wool,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And no friend will ask after a friend,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Though they will be put in sight of each other,- the sinner's desire will
 be: Would that he could redeem himself from the Penalty of that Day by
 (sacrificing) his children,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
His wife and his brother,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
His kindred who sheltered him,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And all, all that is on earth,- so it could deliver him:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By no means! for it would be the Fire of Hell!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Plucking out (his being) right to the skull!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Inviting (all) such as turn their backs and turn away their faces (from
 the Right).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And collect (wealth) and hide it (from use)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly man was created very impatient;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Fretful when evil touches him;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And niggardly when good reaches him;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Not so those devoted to Prayer;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who remain steadfast to their prayer;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those in whose wealth is a recognised right.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For the (needy) who asks and him who is prevented (for some reason from
 asking);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who hold to the truth of the Day of Judgment;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who fear the displeasure of their Lord,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For their Lord's displeasure is the opposite of Peace and Tranquillity;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who guard their chastity,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Except with their wives and the (captives) whom their right hands possess,-
 for (then) they are not to be blamed,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those who trespass beyond this are transgressors;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who respect their trusts and covenants;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who stand firm in their testimonies;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And those who guard (the sacredness) of their worship;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such will be the honoured ones in the Gardens (of Bliss).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now what is the matter with the Unbelievers that they rush madly before
 thee-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From the right and from the left, in crowds?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Does every man of them long to enter the Garden of Bliss?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By no means! For We have created them out of the (base matter) they know!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now I do call to witness the Lord of all points in the East and the West
 that We can certainly-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Substitute for them better (men) than they; And We are not to be defeated
 (in Our Plan).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So leave them to plunge in vain talk and play about, until they encounter
 that Day of theirs which they have been promised!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day whereon they will issue from their sepulchres in sudden haste as
 if they were rushing to a goal-post (fixed for them),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Their eyes lowered in dejection,- ignominy covering them (all over)! such
 is the Day the which they are promised!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We sent Noah to his People (with the Command): "Do thou warn thy People
 before there comes to them a grievous Penalty."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "O my People! I am to you a Warner, clear and open:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"That ye should worship Allah, fear Him and obey me:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"So He may forgive you your sins and give you respite for a stated Term:
 for when the Term given by Allah is accomplished, it cannot be put forward:
 if ye only knew."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He said: "O my Lord! I have called to my People night and day:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"But my call only increases (their) flight (from the Right).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And every time I have called to them, that Thou mightest forgive them,
 they have (only) thrust their fingers into their ears, covered themselves
 up with their garments, grown obstinate, and given themselves up to arrogance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"So I have called to them aloud;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Further I have spoken to them in public and secretly in private,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Saying, 'Ask forgiveness from your Lord; for He is Oft-Forgiving;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"'He will send rain to you in abundance;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"'Give you increase in wealth and sons; and bestow on you gardens and bestow
 on you rivers (of flowing water).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"'What is the matter with you, that ye place not your hope for kindness
 and long-suffering in Allah,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"'Seeing that it is He that has created you in diverse stages?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"'See ye not how Allah has created the seven heavens one above another,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"'And made the moon a light in their midst, and made the sun as a (Glorious)
 Lamp?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"'And Allah has produced you from the earth growing (gradually),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"'And in the End He will return you into the (earth), and raise you forth
 (again at the Resurrection)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"'And Allah has made the earth for you as a carpet (spread out),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"'That ye may go about therein, in spacious roads.'"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Noah said: "O my Lord! They have disobeyed me, but they follow (men) whose
 wealth and children give them no increase but only Loss.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And they have devised a tremendous Plot.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And they have said (to each other), 'Abandon not your gods: Abandon neither
 Wadd nor Suwa', neither Yaguth nor Ya'uq, nor Nasr';-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"They have already misled many; and grant Thou no increase to the wrong-doers
 but in straying (from their mark)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Because of their sins they were drowned (in the flood), and were made to
 enter the Fire (of Punishment): and they found- in lieu of Allah- none
 to help them.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Noah, said: "O my Lord! Leave not of the Unbelievers, a single one on
 earth!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"For, if Thou dost leave (any of) them, they will but mislead Thy devotees,
 and they will breed none but wicked ungrateful ones.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"O my Lord! Forgive me, my parents, all who enter my house in Faith, and
 (all) believing men and believing women: and to the wrong-doers grant Thou
 no increase but in perdition!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: It has been revealed to me that a company of Jinns listened (to the
 Qur'an).
 They said, 'We have really heard a wonderful Recital!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
'It gives guidance to the Right, and we have believed therein: we shall
 not join (in worship) any (gods) with our Lord.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
'And Exalted is the Majesty of our Lord: He has taken neither a wife nor
 a son.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
'There were some foolish ones among us, who used to utter extravagant lies
 against Allah;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
'But we do think that no man or spirit should say aught that untrue against
 Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
'True, there were persons among mankind who took shelter with persons among
 the Jinns, but they increased them in folly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
'And they (came to) think as ye thought, that Allah would not raise up any
 one (to Judgment).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
'And we pried into the secrets of heaven; but we found it filled with stern
 guards and flaming fires.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
'We used, indeed, to sit there in (hidden) stations, to (steal) a hearing;
 but any who listen now will find a flaming fire watching him in ambush.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
'And we understand not whether ill is intended to those on earth, or whether
 their Lord (really) intends to guide them to right conduct.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
'There are among us some that are righteous, and some the contrary: we follow
 divergent paths.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
'But we think that we can by no means frustrate Allah throughout the earth,
 nor can we frustrate Him by flight.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
'And as for us, since we have listened to the Guidance, we have accepted
 it: and any who believes in his Lord has no fear, either of a short (account)
 or of any injustice.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
'Amongst us are some that submit their wills (to Allah), and some that swerve
 from justice.
 Now those who submit their wills - they have sought out (the path) of right
 conduct:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
'But those who swerve,- they are (but) fuel for Hell-fire'-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(And Allah's Message is): "If they (the Pagans) had (only) remained on the
 (right) Way, We should certainly have bestowed on them Rain in abundance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"That We might try them by that (means).
 But if any turns away from the remembrance of his Lord, He will cause him
 to undergo a severe Penalty.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"And the places of worship are for Allah (alone): So invoke not any one
 along with Allah;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Yet when the Devotee of Allah stands forth to invoke Him, they just make
 round him a dense crowd."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "I do no more than invoke my Lord, and I join not with Him any (false
 god)."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "It is not in my power to cause you harm, or to bring you to right
 conduct."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "No one can deliver me from Allah (If I were to disobey Him), nor should
 I find refuge except in Him,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Unless I proclaim what I receive from Allah and His Messages: for any that
 disobey Allah and His Messenger,- for them is Hell: they shall dwell therein
 for ever."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At length, when they see (with their own eyes) that which they are promised,-
 then will they know who it is that is weakest in (his) helper and least
 important in point of numbers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: "I know not whether the (Punishment) which ye are promised is near,
 or whether my Lord will appoint for it a distant term.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"He (alone) knows the Unseen, nor does He make any one acquainted with His
 Mysteries,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Except a messenger whom He has chosen: and then He makes a band of watchers
 march before him and behind him,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"That He may know that they have (truly) brought and delivered the Messages
 of their Lord: and He surrounds (all the mysteries) that are with them,
 and takes account of every single thing."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O thou folded in garments!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Stand (to prayer) by night, but not all night,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Half of it,- or a little less,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or a little more; and recite the Qur'an in slow, measured rhythmic tones.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Soon shall We send down to thee a weighty Message.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly the rising by night is most potent for governing (the soul), and most
 suitable for (framing) the Word (of Prayer and Praise).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
True, there is for thee by day prolonged occupation with ordinary duties:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But keep in remembrance the name of thy Lord and devote thyself to Him whole-hea
rtedly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(He is) Lord of the East and the West: there is no god but He: take Him
 therefore for (thy) Disposer of Affairs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And have patience with what they say, and leave them with noble (dignity).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And leave Me (alone to deal with) those in possession of the good things
 of life, who (yet) deny the Truth; and bear with them for a little while.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With Us are Fetters (to bind them), and a Fire (to burn them),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And a Food that chokes, and a Penalty Grievous.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
One Day the earth and the mountains will be in violent commotion.
 And the mountains will be as a heap of sand poured out and flowing down.
