And the mountains hath He firmly fixed;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For use and convenience to you and your cattle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore, when there comes the great, overwhelming (Event),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day when man shall remember (all) that he strove for,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Hell-Fire shall be placed in full view for (all) to see,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, for such as had transgressed all bounds,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And had preferred the life of this world,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Abode will be Hell-Fire;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And for such as had entertained the fear of standing before their Lord's
 (tribunal) and had restrained (their) soul from lower desires,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Their abode will be the Garden.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They ask thee about the Hour,-'When will be its appointed time?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Wherein art thou (concerned) with the declaration thereof?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With thy Lord in the Limit fixed therefor.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thou art but a Warner for such as fear it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day they see it, (It will be) as if they had tarried but a single evening,
 or (at most till) the following morn!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(The Prophet) frowned and turned away,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Because there came to him the blind man (interrupting).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But what could tell thee but that perchance he might grow (in spiritual
 understanding)?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or that he might receive admonition, and the teaching might profit him?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As to one who regards Himself as self-sufficient,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To him dost thou attend;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Though it is no blame to thee if he grow not (in spiritual understanding).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But as to him who came to thee striving earnestly,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And with fear (in his heart),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Of him wast thou unmindful.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By no means (should it be so)! For it is indeed a Message of instruction:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore let whoso will, keep it in remembrance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It is) in Books held (greatly) in honour,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Exalted (in dignity), kept pure and holy,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Written) by the hands of scribes-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Honourable and Pious and Just.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Woe to man! What hath made him reject Allah;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From what stuff hath He created him?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From a sperm-drop: He hath created him, and then mouldeth him in due proportions
;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then doth He make His path smooth for him;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then He causeth him to die, and putteth him in his grave;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, when it is His Will, He will raise him up (again).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By no means hath he fulfilled what Allah hath commanded him.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then let man look at his food, (and how We provide it):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For that We pour forth water in abundance,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We split the earth in fragments,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And produce therein corn,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Grapes and nutritious plants,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Olives and Dates,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And enclosed Gardens, dense with lofty trees,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And fruits and fodder,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For use and convenience to you and your cattle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At length, when there comes the Deafening Noise,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That Day shall a man flee from his own brother,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And from his mother and his father,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And from his wife and his children.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Each one of them, that Day, will have enough concern (of his own) to make
 him indifferent to the others.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Some faces that Day will be beaming,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Laughing, rejoicing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And other faces that Day will be dust-stained,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Blackness will cover them:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such will be the Rejecters of Allah, the doers of iniquity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the sun (with its spacious light) is folded up;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the stars fall, losing their lustre;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the mountains vanish (like a mirage);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the she-camels, ten months with young, are left untended;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the wild beasts are herded together (in the human habitations);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the oceans boil over with a swell;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the souls are sorted out, (being joined, like with like);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the female (infant), buried alive, is questioned -
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For what crime she was killed;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the scrolls are laid open;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the world on High is unveiled;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the Blazing Fire is kindled to fierce heat;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when the Garden is brought near;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Then) shall each soul know what it has put forward.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So verily I call to witness the planets - that recede,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Go straight, or hide;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Night as it dissipates;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Dawn as it breathes away the darkness;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily this is the word of a most honourable Messenger,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Endued with Power, with rank before the Lord of the Throne,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With authority there, (and) faithful to his trust.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And (O people!) your companion is not one possessed;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And without doubt he saw him in the clear horizon.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Neither doth he withhold grudgingly a knowledge of the Unseen.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor is it the word of an evil spirit accursed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When whither go ye?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily this is no less than a Message to (all) the Worlds:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(With profit) to whoever among you wills to go straight:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But ye shall not will except as Allah wills,- the Cherisher of the Worlds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the Sky is cleft asunder;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the Stars are scattered;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the Oceans are suffered to burst forth;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when the Graves are turned upside down;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Then) shall each soul know what it hath sent forward and (what it hath)
 kept back.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O man! What has seduced thee from thy Lord Most Beneficent?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Him Who created thee.
 Fashioned thee in due proportion, and gave thee a just bias;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In whatever Form He wills, does He put thee together.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay! But ye do reject Right and Judgment!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But verily over you (are appointed angels) to protect you,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Kind and honourable,- Writing down (your deeds):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They know (and understand) all that ye do.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As for the Righteous, they will be in bliss;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Wicked - they will be in the Fire,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Which they will enter on the Day of Judgment,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they will not be able to keep away therefrom.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And what will explain to thee what the Day of Judgment is?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Again, what will explain to thee what the Day of Judgment is?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It will be) the Day when no soul shall have power (to do) aught for another:
 For the command, that Day, will be (wholly) with Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Woe to those that deal in fraud,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who, when they have to receive by measure from men, exact full measure,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But when they have to give by measure or weight to men, give less than due.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they not think that they will be called to account?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On a Mighty Day,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A Day when (all) mankind will stand before the Lord of the Worlds?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay! Surely the record of the wicked is (preserved) in Sijjin.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And what will explain to thee what Sijjin is?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(There is) a Register (fully) inscribed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Woe, that Day, to those that deny-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those that deny the Day of Judgment.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And none can deny it but the Transgressor beyond bounds the Sinner!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When Our Signs are rehearsed to him, he says, "Tales of the ancients!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By no means! but on their hearts is the stain of the (ill) which they do!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily, from (the Light of) their Lord, that Day, will they be veiled.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Further, they will enter the Fire of Hell.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Further, it will be said to them: "This is the (reality) which ye rejected
 as false!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, verily the record of the Righteous is (preserved) in 'Illiyin.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And what will explain to thee what 'Illiyun is?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(There is) a Register (fully) inscribed,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To which bear witness those Nearest (to Allah).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly the Righteous will be in Bliss:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On Thrones (of Dignity) will they command a sight (of all things):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thou wilt recognise in their faces the beaming brightness of Bliss.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Their thirst will be slaked with Pure Wine sealed:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The seal thereof will be Musk: And for this let those aspire, who have aspiratio
ns:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
With it will be (given) a mixture of Tasnim:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A spring, from (the waters) whereof drink those Nearest to Allah.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those in sin used to laugh at those who believed,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And whenever they passed by them, used to wink at each other (in mockery);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when they returned to their own people, they would return jesting;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And whenever they saw them, they would say, "Behold! These are the people
 truly astray!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But they had not been sent as keepers over them!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But on this Day the Believers will laugh at the Unbelievers:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On Thrones (of Dignity) they will command (a sight) (of all things).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Will not the Unbelievers have been paid back for what they did?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the sky is rent asunder,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And hearkens to (the Command of) its Lord, and it must needs (do so);-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when the earth is flattened out,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And casts forth what is within it and becomes (clean) empty,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And hearkens to (the Command of) its Lord,- and it must needs (do so);-
 (then will come Home the full reality).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
O thou man! Verily thou art ever toiling on towards thy Lord- painfully
 toiling,- but thou shalt meet Him.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then he who is given his Record in his right hand,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Soon will his account be taken by an easy reckoning,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And he will turn to his people, rejoicing!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But he who is given his Record behind his back,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Soon will he cry for perdition,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And he will enter a Blazing Fire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly, did he go about among his people, rejoicing!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly, did he think that he would not have to return (to Us)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, nay! for his Lord was (ever) watchful of him!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So I do call to witness the ruddy glow of Sunset;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Night and its Homing;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Moon in her fullness:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ye shall surely travel from stage to stage.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What then is the matter with them, that they believe not?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And when the Qur'an is read to them, they fall not prostrate,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But on the contrary the Unbelievers reject (it).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But Allah has full knowledge of what they secrete (in their breasts)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So announce to them a Penalty Grievous,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Except to those who believe and work righteous deeds: For them is a Reward
 that will never fail.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the sky, (displaying) the Zodiacal Signs;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the promised Day (of Judgment);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By one that witnesses, and the subject of the witness;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Woe to the makers of the pit (of fire),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Fire supplied (abundantly) with fuel:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold! they sat over against the (fire),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they witnessed (all) that they were doing against the Believers.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they ill-treated them for no other reason than that they believed in
 Allah, Exalted in Power, Worthy of all Praise!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Him to Whom belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth! And Allah
 is Witness to all things.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who persecute (or draw into temptation) the Believers, men and women,
 and do not turn in repentance, will have the Penalty of Hell: They will
 have the Penalty of the Burning Fire.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For those who believe and do righteous deeds, will be Gardens; beneath which
 rivers flow: That is the great Salvation, (the fulfilment of all desires),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly strong is the Grip (and Power) of thy Lord.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is He Who creates from the very beginning, and He can restore (life).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He is the Oft-Forgiving, Full of Loving-Kindness,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Lord of the Throne of Glory,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Doer (without let) of all that He intends.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Has the story reached thee, of the forces-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Of Pharaoh and the Thamud?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And yet the Unbelievers (persist) in rejecting (the Truth)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But Allah doth encompass them from behind!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, this is a Glorious Qur'an,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Inscribed) in a Tablet Preserved!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Sky and the Night-Visitant (therein);-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And what will explain to thee what the Night-Visitant is?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It is) the Star of piercing brightness;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There is no soul but has a protector over it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now let man but think from what he is created!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He is created from a drop emitted-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Proceeding from between the backbone and the ribs:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Surely (Allah) is able to bring him back (to life)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Day that (all) things secret will be tested,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Man) will have no power, and no helper.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Firmament which returns (in its round),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And by the Earth which opens out (for the gushing of springs or the sprouting
 of vegetation),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold this is the Word that distinguishes (Good from Evil):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It is not a thing for amusement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As for them, they are but plotting a scheme,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And I am planning a scheme.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore grant a delay to the Unbelievers: Give respite to them gently
 (for awhile).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Glorify the name of thy Guardian-Lord Most High,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who hath created, and further, given order and proportion;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who hath ordained laws.
 And granted guidance;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Who bringeth out the (green and luscious) pasture,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And then doth make it (but) swarthy stubble.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By degrees shall We teach thee to declare (the Message), so thou shalt not
 forget,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Except as Allah wills: For He knoweth what is manifest and what is hidden.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And We will make it easy for thee (to follow) the simple (Path).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore give admonition in case the admonition profits (the hearer).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The admonition will be received by those who fear (Allah):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But it will be avoided by those most unfortunate ones,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who will enter the Great Fire,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In which they will then neither die nor live.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those will prosper who purify themselves,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And glorify the name of their Guardian-Lord, and (lift their hearts) in
 prayer.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay (behold), ye prefer the life of this world;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But the Hereafter is better and more enduring.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And this is in the Books of the earliest (Revelation),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Books of Abraham and Moses.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Has the story reached thee of the overwhelming (Event)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Some faces, that Day, will be humiliated,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Labouring (hard), weary,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The while they enter the Blazing Fire,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The while they are given, to drink, of a boiling hot spring,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No food will there be for them but a bitter Dhari'
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Which will neither nourish nor satisfy hunger.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(Other) faces that Day will be joyful,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Pleased with their striving,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In a Garden on high,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Where they shall hear no (word) of vanity:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therein will be a bubbling spring:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therein will be Thrones (of dignity), raised on high,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Goblets placed (ready),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And cushions set in rows,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And rich carpets (all) spread out.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Do they not look at the Camels, how they are made?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And at the Sky, how it is raised high?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And at the Mountains, how they are fixed firm?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And at the Earth, how it is spread out?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore do thou give admonition, for thou art one to admonish.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thou art not one to manage (men's) affairs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But if any turn away and reject Allah,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah will punish him with a mighty Punishment,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For to Us will be their return;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then it will be for Us to call them to account.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the break of Day
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Nights twice five;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the even and odd (contrasted);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And by the Night when it passeth away;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is there (not) in these an adjuration (or evidence) for those who understand?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou not how thy Lord dealt with the 'Ad (people),-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Of the (city of) Iram, with lofty pillars,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The like of which were not produced in (all) the land?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And with the Thamud (people), who cut out (huge) rocks in the valley?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And with Pharaoh, lord of stakes?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(All) these transgressed beyond bounds in the lands,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And heaped therein mischief (on mischief).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore did thy Lord pour on them a scourge of diverse chastisements:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For thy Lord is (as a Guardian) on a watch-tower.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Now, as for man, when his Lord trieth him, giving him honour and gifts,
 then saith he, (puffed up), "My Lord hath honoured me."
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But when He trieth him, restricting his subsistence for him, then saith
 he (in despair), "My Lord hath humiliated me!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, nay! but ye honour not the orphans!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor do ye encourage one another to feed the poor!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And ye devour inheritance - all with greed,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And ye love wealth with inordinate love!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay! When the earth is pounded to powder,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And thy Lord cometh, and His angels, rank upon rank,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And Hell, that Day, is brought (face to face),- on that Day will man remember,
 but how will that remembrance profit him?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He will say: "Ah! Would that I had sent forth (good deeds) for (this) my
 (Future) Life!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For, that Day, His Chastisement will be such as none (else) can inflict,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And His bonds will be such as none (other) can bind.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(To the righteous soul will be said:) "O (thou) soul, in (complete) rest
 and satisfaction!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Come back thou to thy Lord,- well pleased (thyself), and well-pleasing
 unto Him!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Enter thou, then, among My devotees!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Yea, enter thou My Heaven!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
I do call to witness this City;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And thou art a freeman of this City;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And (the mystic ties of) parent and child;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily We have created man into toil and struggle.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thinketh he, that none hath power over him?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He may say (boastfully); Wealth have I squandered in abundance!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thinketh he that none beholdeth him?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Have We not made for him a pair of eyes?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And a tongue, and a pair of lips?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And shown him the two highways?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But he hath made no haste on the path that is steep.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And what will explain to thee the path that is steep?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It is:) freeing the bondman;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or the giving of food in a day of privation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To the orphan with claims of relationship,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or to the indigent (down) in the dust.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then will he be of those who believe, and enjoin patience, (constancy, and
 self-restraint), and enjoin deeds of kindness and compassion.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Such are the Companions of the Right Hand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those who reject Our Signs, they are the (unhappy) Companions of the
 Left Hand.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On them will be Fire vaulted over (all round).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Sun and his (glorious) splendour;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Moon as she follows him;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Day as it shows up (the Sun's) glory;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Night as it conceals it;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Firmament and its (wonderful) structure;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Earth and its (wide) expanse:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Soul, and the proportion and order given to it;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And its enlightenment as to its wrong and its right;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly he succeeds that purifies it,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And he fails that corrupts it!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Thamud (people) rejected (their prophet) through their inordinate wrong-doin
g,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Behold, the most wicked man among them was deputed (for impiety).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But the Messenger of Allah said to them: "It is a She-camel of Allah! And
 (bar her not from) having her drink!"
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then they rejected him (as a false prophet), and they hamstrung her.
 So their Lord, on account of their crime, obliterated their traces and
 made them equal (in destruction, high and low)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And for Him is no fear of its consequences.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Night as it conceals (the light);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Day as it appears in glory;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By (the mystery of) the creation of male and female;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily, (the ends) ye strive for are diverse.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So he who gives (in charity) and fears (Allah),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And (in all sincerity) testifies to the best,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We will indeed make smooth for him the path to Bliss.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But he who is a greedy miser and thinks himself self-sufficient,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And gives the lie to the best,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We will indeed make smooth for him the path to Misery;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor will his wealth profit him when he falls headlong (into the Pit).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily We take upon Ourselves to guide,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And verily unto Us (belong) the End and the Beginning.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore do I warn you of a Fire blazing fiercely;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
None shall reach it but those most unfortunate ones
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who give the lie to Truth and turn their backs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But those most devoted to Allah shall be removed far from it,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who spend their wealth for increase in self-purification,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And have in their minds no favour from anyone for which a reward is expected
 in return,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But only the desire to seek for the Countenance of their Lord Most High;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And soon will they attain (complete) satisfaction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Glorious Morning Light,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And by the Night when it is still,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thy Guardian-Lord hath not forsaken thee, nor is He displeased.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And verily the Hereafter will be better for thee than the present.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And soon will thy Guardian-Lord give thee (that wherewith) thou shalt be
 well-pleased.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Did He not find thee an orphan and give thee shelter (and care)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He found thee wandering, and He gave thee guidance.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He found thee in need, and made thee independent.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore, treat not the orphan with harshness,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor repulse the petitioner (unheard);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But the bounty of the Lord - rehearse and proclaim!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Have We not expanded thee thy breast?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And removed from thee thy burden
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The which did gall thy back?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And raised high the esteem (in which) thou (art held)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So, verily, with every difficulty, there is relief:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily, with every difficulty there is relief.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore, when thou art free (from thine immediate task), still labour
 hard,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And to thy Lord turn (all) thy attention.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the Fig and the Olive,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the Mount of Sinai,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And this City of security,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have indeed created man in the best of moulds,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then do We abase him (to be) the lowest of the low,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Except such as believe and do righteous deeds: For they shall have a reward
 unfailing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then what can, after this, contradict thee, as to the judgment (to come)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Is not Allah the wisest of judges?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Proclaim! (or read!) in the name of thy Lord and Cherisher, Who created-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Created man, out of a (mere) clot of congealed blood:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Proclaim! And thy Lord is Most Bountiful,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He Who taught (the use of) the pen,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Taught man that which he knew not.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, but man doth transgress all bounds,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In that he looketh upon himself as self-sufficient.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily, to thy Lord is the return (of all).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou one who forbids-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A votary when he (turns) to pray?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou if he is on (the road of) Guidance?-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Or enjoins Righteousness?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou if he denies (Truth) and turns away?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Knoweth he not that Allah doth see?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let him beware! If he desist not, We will drag him by the forelock,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A lying, sinful forelock!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, let him call (for help) to his council (of comrades):
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We will call on the angels of punishment (to deal with him)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, heed him not: But bow down in adoration, and bring thyself the closer
 (to Allah)!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We have indeed revealed this (Message) in the Night of Power:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And what will explain to thee what the night of power is?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Night of Power is better than a thousand months.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therein come down the angels and the Spirit by Allah's permission, on every
 errand:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Peace!...
 This until the rise of morn!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who reject (Truth), among the People of the Book and among the Polytheists
, were not going to depart (from their ways) until there should come to
 them Clear Evidence,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
An messenger from Allah, rehearsing scriptures kept pure and holy:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Wherein are laws (or decrees) right and straight.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor did the People of the Book make schisms, until after there came to them
 Clear Evidence.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And they have been commanded no more than this: To worship Allah, offering
 Him sincere devotion, being true (in faith); to establish regular prayer;
 and to practise regular charity; and that is the Religion Right and Straight.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who reject (Truth), among the People of the Book and among the Polytheists
, will be in Hell-Fire, to dwell therein (for aye).
 They are the worst of creatures.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who have faith and do righteous deeds,- they are the best of creatures.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Their reward is with Allah: Gardens of Eternity, beneath which rivers flow;
 they will dwell therein for ever; Allah well pleased with them, and they
 with Him: all this for such as fear their Lord and Cherisher.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When the earth is shaken to her (utmost) convulsion,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the earth throws up her burdens (from within),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And man cries (distressed): 'What is the matter with her?'-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On that Day will she declare her tidings:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For that thy Lord will have given her inspiration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
On that Day will men proceed in companies sorted out, to be shown the deeds
 that they (had done).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then shall anyone who has done an atom's weight of good, see it!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And anyone who has done an atom's weight of evil, shall see it.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By the (Steeds) that run, with panting (breath),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And strike sparks of fire,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And push home the charge in the morning,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And raise the dust in clouds the while,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And penetrate forthwith into the midst (of the foe) en masse;-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Truly man is, to his Lord, ungrateful;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And to that (fact) he bears witness (by his deeds);
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And violent is he in his love of wealth.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Does he not know,- when that which is in the graves is scattered abroad
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And that which is (locked up) in (human) breasts is made manifest-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
That their Lord had been Well-acquainted with them, (even to) that Day?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The (Day) of Noise and Clamour:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
What is the (Day) of Noise and Clamour?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And what will explain to thee what the (Day) of Noise and Clamour is?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It is) a Day whereon men will be like moths scattered about,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And the mountains will be like carded wool.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, he whose balance (of good deeds) will be (found) heavy,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Will be in a life of good pleasure and satisfaction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But he whose balance (of good deeds) will be (found) light,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Will have his home in a (bottomless) Pit.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And what will explain to thee what this is?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It is) a Fire Blazing fiercely!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The mutual rivalry for piling up (the good things of this world) diverts
 you (from the more serious things),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Until ye visit the graves.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But nay, ye soon shall know (the reality).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Again, ye soon shall know!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nay, were ye to know with certainty of mind, (ye would beware!)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ye shall certainly see Hell-Fire!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Again, ye shall see it with certainty of sight!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then, shall ye be questioned that Day about the joy (ye indulged in!).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By (the Token of) Time (through the ages),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Verily Man is in loss,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Except such as have Faith, and do righteous deeds, and (join together) in
 the mutual teaching of Truth, and of Patience and Constancy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Woe to every (kind of) scandal-monger and-backbiter,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who pileth up wealth and layeth it by,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thinking that his wealth would make him last for ever!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By no means! He will be sure to be thrown into That which Breaks to Pieces,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And what will explain to thee That which Breaks to Pieces?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(It is) the Fire of (the Wrath of) Allah kindled (to a blaze),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The which doth mount (Right) to the Hearts:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
It shall be made into a vault over them,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In columns outstretched.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou not how thy Lord dealt with the Companions of the Elephant?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Did He not make their treacherous plan go astray?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And He sent against them Flights of Birds,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Striking them with stones of baked clay.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then did He make them like an empty field of stalks and straw, (of which
 the corn) has been eaten up.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For the covenants (of security and safeguard enjoyed) by the Quraish,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Their covenants (covering) journeys by winter and summer,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Let them adore the Lord of this House,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who provides them with food against hunger, and with security against fear
 (of danger).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Seest thou one who denies the Judgment (to come)?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then such is the (man) who repulses the orphan (with harshness),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And encourages not the feeding of the indigent.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
So woe to the worshippers
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Who are neglectful of their prayers,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Those who (want but) to be seen (of men),
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
But refuse (to supply) (even) neighbourly needs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To thee have We granted the Fount (of Abundance).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Therefore to thy Lord turn in Prayer and Sacrifice.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For he who hateth thee, he will be cut off (from Future Hope).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: O ye that reject Faith!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
I worship not that which ye worship,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor will ye worship that which I worship.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And I will not worship that which ye have been wont to worship,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Nor will ye worship that which I worship.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To you be your Way, and to me mine.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
When comes the Help of Allah, and Victory,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And thou dost see the people enter Allah's Religion in crowds,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Celebrate the praises of thy Lord, and pray for His Forgiveness: For He
 is Oft-Returning (in Grace and Mercy).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Perish the hands of the Father of Flame! Perish he!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
No profit to him from all his wealth, and all his gains!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Burnt soon will he be in a Fire of Blazing Flame!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
His wife shall carry the (crackling) wood - As fuel!-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A twisted rope of palm-leaf fibre round her (own) neck!
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: He is Allah, the One and Only;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Allah, the Eternal, Absolute;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
He begetteth not, nor is He begotten;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And there is none like unto Him.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: I seek refuge with the Lord of the Dawn
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From the mischief of created things;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From the mischief of Darkness as it overspreads;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From the mischief of those who practise secret arts;
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And from the mischief of the envious one as he practises envy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Say: I seek refuge with the Lord and Cherisher of Mankind,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The King (or Ruler) of Mankind,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The god (or judge) of Mankind,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
From the mischief of the Whisperer (of Evil), who withdraws (after his whisper),
-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
(The same) who whispers into the hearts of Mankind,-
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Among Jinns and among men.
\end_layout

